INSERT INTO `entradas` VALUES (154,'linux','en','/a/IT/2010/1026/801.html','JAVA platform is moving toward closure','2010-10-26','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">As a member of the Apache Software Foundation, I tend to support the position of open source software license agreements more freely, such as Apache License (v2.0), BSD, or MIT license agreement. I firmly believe that businesses should be encouraged to use open source software, so that they can use open source software to do anything they want, as much as possible in the current legal framework of the relaxation of restrictions. Liberal free software license agreement allows the software development community to do better. Free and open source software development to encourage genuine, attentive, and the strength of the volunteer activities of participants as &quot;open heart&quot; campaign, as the software companies can sell services and &quot;enterprise-class software functionality,&quot; and do not change into a single individual to master all the important rights of software.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">I have to honest - I\'m not very keen on the Java language - I prefer to use Python, Javascript, C, C + +, PHP and even write a program, but I found that Java is everywhere, I fell. Java and the JVM has now become my team developed Cloudkick in the core of many components, but no replacement.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Today IBM announced the need to shift their focus to shift to develop based on OpenJDK. This is the Oracle infringement against Google\'s Android, after another major event. Oracle is a big company specializes in playing the political company, specializes in the extraction of value - I am sure he will extract from the Sun of the shell in the last dime out of date.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">When the Sun, is now Oracle, the OpenJDK when placed under the GPL license, TCK license agreement problem has been hanging more than 5 years. Some blog on this issue in-depth introduction to [1] [2] [3], I suggest everyone TCK, Apache and Sun should be more between the stories to find out - but this is not my concern here.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">I think he is an advocate of open source software, though with some people, such as Richard Stallman - GNU\'s founder, the approach is different. Richard\'s point of view on many issues with me are not very consistent, but one thing is consistent, Java world, the phenomenon of more and more chaotic that I began license agreement for software platforms and beliefs to change.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">6 years ago, Richard made a &quot;free but with a yoke - Java trap.&quot; At that time I do not agree that moral arguments about software freedom, but now I believe, Java platform is a trap.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">In his article, Richard talked about &quot;free software world,&quot; and a lot of other GNU projects, one of which I find very important: If your application relies on a platform, you will be the platform of the license agreement and the development process constraints.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Any software, any language will encounter this problem. For example, if a free run only on Microsoft\'s Windows operating system that still need to pay for the free world. However, in GUN / Linux software running as dependent on other non-free software, it is equally meaningless. In the past, Motif (before the LessTif) and Qt (the developers to its free before) the major problems are arising in this regard. Most 3D graphics are dependent on non-free driver, also have this problem. But now, the biggest problem has come from Java, because the development of free software Java people are great feeling. The attractiveness of the language deceived them, they ignore the issue of independence, fall into the Java trap.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">If you develop software on Java and the JVM, you trapped in a company by - Oracle control of a single platform. Oracle to maintain control of the platform and refused to remove the TCK in the terms of use, effectively blocked the Apache Harmony project has not officially released. The lawsuit against Google over the obsession with the Oracle on the platform control.</span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(155,'linux','en','/a/IT/2010/1026/800.html','Linux 2.6.36 kernel release, give the user','2010-10-26','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">After 80 days after the development, Linus Torvalds released the Linux 2.6.36 version. It has a name &quot;fanged carnivorous bat&quot;; from the name on his way home from Torvalds get inspiration. New Linux kernel better than the previous version of it big - this is a rare thing, because in the past few years, the main development branch in each new version of the kernel source distribution has grown to hundreds of thousands of lines.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><br /> Kernels do not grow in size, because the developer carefully streamlined the default configuration file. However, other patch brings a wealth of new source code, so 2.6.36 can provide a large number of significant new features - for example, the controversial expansion of AppArmor security, a new external memory (OOM) end of the process device, the kernel thread improved, the basic Xen Dom0 support, and many file systems and related optimization, virtual file system. Kernel hackers have also repaired a virtual machine system of one of them can cause some systems to write to the file storage medium slow slow unbearable bug. Other changes are expected by improving the response time of the system seems faster. As before, this new version also includes many new and improved drive - for example, for the Nouveau driver NVIDIA graphics chips now support the use of the recently out of the GeForce graphics cards on the Fermi chip. Kernel hackers as well to improve on the infrared remote control and receiver support.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><br /> The following provides a 2.6.36 kernel records brought more and more an overview of new features. This change will be issued with the Linux 2.6.36 kernel or a subsequent release by the end of all Linux users, and allow end users to effectively feel the improvement. Finally, the kernel records also a glimpse into the 2.6.37 kernel version that will be some new directions.</span></span> </p><p> <strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">The kernel update has the following highlights:</span></span></strong> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Tilera processor architecture support. <br /> New file notification interface to fanotify. <br /> Intel graphics cards to achieve the integration of KMS and the KDB. <br /> Parallel management of the queue. <br /> Intel i3 / 5 platform, built-in smart card and the CPU power management. <br /> CIFS file system, the local cache. <br /> Virtual memory hierarchy to improve and enhance the desktop operating speed of response. <br /> To improve the virtual memory overflow terminator algorithms. <br /> AppArmor security model integrated (note: SELinux file-based tagging different, AppArmor is based on the path.)</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Download: <a href=\"http://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v2.6/linux-2.6.36.tar.bz2\">http://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v2.6/linux-2.6.36.tar.bz2</a></span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(156,'linux','en','/a/IT/2010/1017/799.html','Unix four decades, Who!','2010-10-17','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">IT sector as one of the few remaining myths, UNIX history of the development history of the development as a nation, full of ups and downs and struggle. It turned out to 70-80 years to the 20th century, almost all of the most significant invention of the computer, the great business stories, and other commercial open source movement closely linked to the war, witnessed a period of IT industry and a legend. <br /><br /> In 1969, Ken Thompson of Bell Labs to his beloved game to develop a new operating environment, and Dennis Ritchie to design a set of operating system called UNICS (later homonym taken as &quot;UNIX&quot;). R &amp; D results in this casual, but the computer field has opened up dramatically in the new world. <br /><br /> In the course of development of UNIX in the past forty years, never stopped crowded situation. Which last for decades between the two giants of war, as the industry made an indelible contribution. Today, customers are going to review IT is such a history has been settled, from the brilliant to the bottom, from the equal strength to the great disparities between the success or failure in that study. <br /><br /> Two giants, two peak showdown <br /><br /> If the IT industry in 2009 to make a ranking event occurs, then the &quot;big S&quot; the company was acquired events, will be able to squeeze into the top three. &quot;Big S&quot; which was once only in Silicon Valley with the &quot;Big I&quot; standing shoulder to shoulder of giants, and now the setting sun, had to make people regret the ever-changing shopping contest. What kind of events completely changed the &quot;Big S&quot; development path? What kind of competition is completely defeated &quot;Big S&quot; line of defense? <br /><br /> The first battle - UNIX separatist war <br /><br /> Early 80s, the face of fast-growing IT market in the computer information industry vendors, in pursuit of product differentiation and added value, have improved UNIX, derived from a variety of commercial UNIX versions, fully started the UNIX market battle . <br /><br /> In 1982, the station started the &quot;Big S&quot; ascended the stage of history. Derived from the UNIX operating system version of the introduction to the Java programming language and J2EE (Java2EnerpriseEdition) application platform launched, &quot;Big S&quot; greatly contributed to the development of business applications. Improved through continuous updates, the company\'s Solaris operating system has made considerable progress can be broad support for UNIX-based business applications. Meanwhile, the firm\'s market share, R &amp; D investment in time, well-trained staff, excellent business advice, so that the &quot;Big S&quot; made a brilliant market performance, becoming the most dynamic UNIX commercial manufacturers. However, as the most promising one of the commercial versions of UNIX, Solaris itself brought poor standard software, the optional and very expensive package, which affect the company\'s future development as a major drawback. <br /><br /> January 1986, &quot;Big I&quot; the birth of the company\'s AIX operating system. Since then, it take up a UNIX server platform to create the task, has become a &quot;Big I&quot; open systems and standards for companies to enter the world of the catalyst. With the continuing escalation of AIX version, which gradually version of Java2 support, and provide improved tools for load management applications, in business and government sectors to show their talents. Meanwhile, AIX performance in terms of security but also reputation, AIX4.3 became the first TCSECC2 the U.S. National Security Agency and the German Information Technology Security Certification Authority E3F-C2-certified 64-bit UNIX systems, the field in the UNIX market performance extraordinary. And &quot;Big S&quot; than the company\'s Solaris, AIX has a large database and development tools, the user can choose in addition to the existing application software can also be developed according to their needs, which is the &quot;big I&quot; company is a major lead, but also to promote sustainable and stable development of its future an important factor. <br /><br /> Especially noteworthy is the highlight AIX powerful is a landmark event. May 11, 1997, 4:50, world chess champion Garry Kasparov in with one called &quot;Deep Blue&quot; supercomputer through six innings against, the final hand over to concede defeat. The claims of the most intelligent person, Bureau of 2.5 pairs of 2.5 in the first five cases tie, deciding game in the sixth disc only 19 steps away to defeat at the hands of blue. This station is running the computer Deep Blue was the best commercial UNIX operating system - &quot;Big I&quot; of the AIX. <br /><br /> Battle in the UNIX market, the &quot;Big S&quot; a rapid response to make it to seize the opportunities, even in the &quot;Big I&quot; catch up time, still can not shake the &quot;Big S&quot; a brilliant performance, both through the eventual realization of a separatist war in the market to keep pace.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">The second confrontation - Processor Dispute <br /><br /> However, in the processors, the face of &quot;Big I&quot; strong technical innovation, &quot;Big S&quot; did not effectively countered the decline of the future foreshadowed. Whether to firmly grasp the leading edge of technological innovation, and has sufficient capital support, the business of winning opponents. <br /><br /> 80 20th century, is RISC (reduced instruction set computer) processor era. In 1984, the &quot;Big S&quot; of the SPARC architecture proposed; 1987, the first SPARC processor come out and quickly capture the market, to help the &quot;big S&quot; exceeded 10 billion revenue mark; in 1995, 64 UltraSPARCI the company microprocessor technology to achieve a qualitative leap; 1999, was a great success of the UltraSPARC-III, a &quot;Big S&quot; a milestone in the history of the microprocessor; 2005, 8-core 32-thread UltraSPARC-T1 launched; 2008 -2009, the 16-core &quot;Rock&quot; Ship Even Sank, this after 5 years, invested billions of dollars of products in the development process has some serious performance issues. Continuous deficit for the &quot;big S&quot; inability to continue to afford the high development costs, the outcome of the acquisition, but also to the future of this product has become more complicated and confusing. <br /><br /> In 1980, the &quot;Big I&quot; invented a prototype based on RISC architecture, microprocessor architecture to create a new heaven and earth; 1990, the &quot;Big I&quot; launched a RISC-based systems POWER1, officially opened the Power family genealogy brilliant prelude , since each generation of Power processors have created amazing success, has been at the pinnacle of processors. In 1997, based on the POWER2 architecture &quot;Deep Blue&quot; computer made the victory of man-machine war, is considered a milestone in the history of computer development; 1998, POWER3 processor and the subsequent update, the speed of the processor frequency shine ; 2001, the &quot;Big I&quot; am the history of mankind\'s first dual-core processor POWER4; 2007Ã¥Â¹Â´, POWER6 processor performance and speed and no one can, technically ahead by 2-3 in a processor market Pioneer; 2010, POWER78 core processors debut as a beautiful dawn, in the number of cores, chip design, operation speed, performance and other aspects of the work demonstrated an unrivaled advantage. <br /><br /> And &quot;Big S&quot; than the company\'s SPARC processor, &quot;Big I&quot; the company\'s POWER processors have no king to shake the status of the technology. With the industry\'s most robust product development roadmap, continuous research and development, advancing with a powerful innovation, &quot;Big I&quot; continue to inject fresh blood into the server market, to fully protect your investment, overall achievements in technology, performance and market leadership position. Processors, the war, the decisive opened the distance between the two giants, the &quot;Big S&quot; from glory into the bottom. <br /><br /> Fallen star, is lost to technology or capital loss? <br /><br /> SPARC twenty-five years of ups and downs, laid the &quot;Big S&quot; in the high-end microprocessor market leader, however, focusing as much on high-end server hardware and software development of the &quot;behind closed doors&quot; strategy, as well as hardware products are daily necessities of the trend, but as always, the standard of sales and production based on traditional general-purpose servers, the &quot;Big S&quot; has separated itself from the trend of industrial development, missed a good opportunity for development. Meanwhile, the high R &amp; D investment and market performance unsatisfactory, but also the &quot;big S&quot; the two most troublesome issues. <br /><br /> Recalling the most glorious era, in September 2000, &quot;Big S&quot; in the stock price close to 260 dollars, but the advanced information technology company in a very long period of time are not aware of the need with the times, when the elephants learn to dance &quot;Big I&quot; has an annual turnover of billions of dollars into the threshold, the &quot;Big S&quot; but with billions of dollars in market value of the club further away. In the financial crisis, business difficulties, large fund companies to sell shares under the influence of multiple factors such as, &quot;Big S&quot; performance gradually decline and eventually become a takeover target. Compete with the capital markets, technology sometimes have to yield to capital, because technological innovation can not do without the support of the capital. <br /><br /> Founded in 1982, was acquired in 2009, with the former glory, &quot;Big S&quot; slowly fade out of sight. In the future, &quot;Big S&quot; in the hardware business will go from here? Face the loss of personnel and their customers, &quot;Big S&quot; turn Zuoheganxiang? Regardless of whether the problem is solvable, it is always worth the contribution of the industry people to admire. We will remember, once a star of the fall of the achievements of a legendary Silicon Valley ... ...</span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(157,'linux','en','/a/IT/2010/1015/798.html','2010 China Linux kernel developers (CLK)','2010-10-15','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Linux Kernel Developers Conference in China (China Linux Kernel Developer Conference referred to CLK), is the highest-level Linux kernel technology field event. General Assembly to &quot;freedom, collaboration, and create&quot; for the idea, and the popularization of open source technology for the mission to encourage the development of China\'s Linux kernel technology enthusiasts continue to climb the peak, in the exchange and discussion of shared resources, and work progress.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">In the CLK conference organizers and the wider community the joint efforts of developers, the Assembly has been more and more attention and participation in the development of the wider community to provide a good platform. <br /><br /> For more information please visit: http://www.aka-kernel.org <br /><br /> Meeting time: 2010 10Ã¦ÂœÂˆ17Ã¦Â—Â¥(Ã¥Â‘Â¨Ã¦Â—Â¥) 9:00 Venue: Shanghai Minhang campus of Shanghai Jiaotong University Software College Auditorium Registration: Online registration official website of the General Assembly <br /><br /> Meeting seven technical topics: <br /><br /> 1 Opening Remarks Dr. Yang Cheng <br /> Yang Cheng - Intel\'s chief development officer, Asia Pacific R &amp; D Co., Ltd. <br /><br /> 2 Debugging Linux Kernel by Ftrace <br /><br /><br /> AceLan Gao - Ubuntu Kernel Development Engineer <br /><br /> 3 Receive packet steering <br /><br /> Wei Yongjun - Fujitsu Kernel Development Engineer <br /><br /> 4, many restrictions for dirty memory <br /> Wu Fengguang - Intel Open Source Technology Center, Senior Engineer <br /><br /> 5 Linux kernel changes and the measures <br /> Chen Lijun - Professor, Xi\'an Institute of Posts and Telecommunications <br /><br /> 6 Linux RAS (Reliability, Availability, Serviceability) <br /><br /> Huang Ying - Intel Open Source Technology Center, Senior Engineer <br /><br /> 7 Topic Visual comparison of linux and other Unix - like systems <br /><br /> Mark SMITH - HP\'s Linux leader in China <br /><br /> 8 Networking and Multicore / NUMA - The Last Mile <br /><br /> Herbert Xu - RedHat senior experts <br /><br /><br /> Linux Kernel Developers Conference in China\'s mission is: to promote open source technology, strong support for the construction of the open source community and development of Linux kernel developers to promote domestic to international interest and participation in open source projects. The conference is expected for the open source community to provide technical support for more powerful platform, brought together more open-source Linux kernel elites contribute to the cause, and will actively integrate with the international open source community, participation, and organize more international open source project. <br /><br /> 2010 Linux Kernel Developers Conference in China look forward to your interest and participation, let us gather in the October 17, 2010, together for open-source contribution to the cause more power!</span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(158,'linux','en','/a/IT/2010/1015/797.html','Linux Foundation Survey: Linux made the next 5 years','2010-10-15','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">The survey also revealed some interesting information, review the following points down:</span></span> </p><ol><li> <span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Migrate from Windows to <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\">Linux</a></u> users will be higher than migrating from Unix to <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\">Linux</a></u> users, but 66% of users surveyed said they are using the latest Linux deployment (&quot;greenfield&quot;). Greenfield market share in this monopoly is a good future indicator Linux platform.</span></span> </li><li> <span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Application surprisingly low clouds in the next year only 26% of users plan to migrate their applications and servers to the clouds. In fact, this is not surprising, because once the move to the cloud, Linux will dominate the server market, as 70.3% of users will choose Linux as their private cloud platform</span></span> </li><li> <span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">86.5% of respondents feel that Linux needs to continue improvement.</span></span> </li><li> <span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Management\'s views have changed for Linux, 60% said their CIO report that Linux is compared to three years ago, more strategic significance of the enterprise.</span></span> </li><li> <span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Linux IT professionals in the growing importance in enterprises, with 38.3% of respondents said the lack of professional platform for Linux-related personnel to solve the problem.</span></span> </li></ol><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"> </span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(159,'linux','en','/a/mz/2010/1026/802.html','Silly apache error (. Htaccess pcfg','2010-10-26','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">apache error appear a lot, but this error really been neglected, and today a web server has access to 403 exceptions, see the configuration file no problem, and in the error.log file, similar to so few lines are given tips:</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">[Tue Oct 26 12:42:58 2010] [crit] [client 8.8.8.8] (13) Permission denied: / cicro / .htaccess pcfg_openfile: unable to check htaccess file, ensure it is readable <br /> [Tue Oct 26 12:42:59 2010] [crit] [client 8.8.8.8] (13) Permission denied: / cicro / .htaccess pcfg_openfile: unable to check htaccess file, ensure it is readable <br /> [Tue Oct 26 12:42:59 2010] [crit] [client 8.8.8.8] (13) Permission denied: / cicro / .htaccess pcfg_openfile: unable to check htaccess file, ensure it is readable <br /> [Tue Oct 26 12:42:59 2010] [crit] [client 8.8.8.8] (13) Permission denied: / cicro / .htaccess pcfg_openfile: unable to check htaccess file, ensure it is readable <br /> [Tue Oct 26 12:42:59 2010] [crit] [client 8.8.8.8] (13) Permission denied: / cicro / .htaccess pcfg_openfile: unable to check htaccess file, ensure it is readable <br /> [Tue Oct 26 12:43:28 2010] [crit] [client 8.8.8.8] (13) Permission denied: / cicro / .htaccess pcfg_openfile: unable to check htaccess file, ensure it is readable</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">At first thought / cicro / .htaccess file permissions due and found no such fundamental documents, then create a / cicro / .htaccess file, the error still continues, after analysis, not a lack of this file causes the error because there is no such documents will not affect the web visit.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">After careful analysis, we found the root of the problem, if log prompt is another directory. Htaccess is not read, generally because of the parent directory of the user group privileges or owner error. The correct directory permissions should be 755, but not apache\'s root directory permissions, but the home directory of files stored procedures, thus positioning the problem to the / cicro this directory, see cicro directory permissions, that essence of the problem!</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">drw-rw-rw 9 root root 4096 10-26 13:03 cicro</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">This authority is really interesting, misuse or others do not know the command in practice, changed back to 755 should be enough.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">chmod-R 755 / cicro</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">In fact, to create the directory root under linux, the default permissions are 755, you may ignore this, and thinking about other aspects of off the subject. On this record, for future reference to use!</span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(160,'linux','en','/a/mz/2010/0917/720.html','RHEL5 does not support modification issue Oracle10g','2010-09-17','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Oracle10.2 itself does not support RHEL5, so the installation needs some modification, otherwise the installation window does not start properly, can be achieved in two ways.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">A modified system file / etc / redhat-release, or other Oracle10.2 support to RHEL4 version. <br /> 2 Modify Oracle configuration file, so that he can support RHEL5.5</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Extract 10201_database_linux32.zip file, database is Oracle\'s installation files into the install directory, modify oraparam.ini file, find the [Certified Versions], modified to look like the following: <br /> [Certified Versions] <br /> Linux = redhat-3, SuSE-9, redhat-4, redhat-5, UnitedLinux-1.0, asianux-1, asianux-2 <br /> [Linux-redhat-5.0-optional] <br /> TEMP_SPACE = 80 <br /> SWAP_SPACE = 150 <br /> MIN_DISPLAY_COLORS = 256 <br /> This allows Oracle to allow RHEL5.5 the. <br /></span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(161,'linux','en','/a/IT/2010/0917/719.html','The value of open source where the value of open source','2010-09-17','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">For some time, inside the circle of developers, many of Apple, and iPhone OS platforms (including the iPhone, iPod touch, iPad) voice of criticism, the main criticism of this platform is not open. Some critics are very sincere and hit crucial point, and some entirely groundless, incorrectly relay an erroneous.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">First, the opening is not a simple concept.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Before the advent of smart phones, mobile phone operating system manufacturers are often private, above the built-in software is often the only manufacturer to develop the above procedures, but most machines do not support installing new software. This is the real closed.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">With smart phones, though a large number of platforms and languages we can use, but did not actually form a robust application development market.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">J2ME applications to the mobile phone market had illusions of prosperity. But in fact, on the one hand, in order to ensure compatibility, J2ME give up a lot of features, performance and application scenarios are greatly limited, difficult to develop and sell the user a powerful and easy to use program.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">In another aspect, it is no perfect interface and operational standards, support of various kinds of mobile phones, the fact of the compatibility and completely can not be guaranteed, few programs can really be the perfect support for a variety of mobile phones particular game type applications, really be compatible with a variety of mobile phone rare.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Nokia S40 and S60 adhere to the two fronts, on the standardization and product diversity to achieve a relatively good balance. Once considered the savior of mobile applications market, however, the past 10 years, Nokia\'s mobile phones although the appearance of each passing day, but the software and operating system improvements inadequate. And the difficulty of system development has been too high Symbian, Nokia Symbian platform and no momentum in the best of times AppStore launch such a business model similar to it. Therefore, since the advent of iPhone, a lot of developers interested in mobile developers, Nokia and the Symbian platform started to give up.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Now, no matter the platform for mobile application from the quantity, quality, and the developer\'s revenue, we can say that Apple iPhone is the mobile application market really began to boom.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Of course no doubt that Apple is indeed very close in some ways. But I do not think it is bad children.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Picture of the future of the software industry should not only open source software, only commercial software, or software only under the AppStore. Three different modes, each other to form a very good supplement.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">In the iPhone / iPod touch, and specific areas such iPad, AppStore model is incredibly powerful. Apple earnings to see you will know how much this opens up a third-party software market. The concept of smart phones appeared almost 10 years, has never been a platform, bringing together so many third-party developers, so many excellent free and paid applications. Previously, third-party developers are making money of course, but the scale and form together in such a platform is unprecedented.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Assuming iPhone OS platform, all the same, just remove the AppStore, we will find that many are now third-party developers to get rich, they just only in the dreams of fortune. Therefore, a certain degree of closure is not necessarily a root of all evil.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">It is because when the issue in the application of the strict need Apple Developer Certificate signed by the greatest extent in the prevention of piracy, making sales of a variety of payment applications have been guaranteed. It is also because of criticism by many people can even say that is too strict quality audits to ensure only the procedures within the AppStore has a certain quality level, which would allow consumers to enjoy in the AppStore in to look and buy more procedures.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">What\'s more, Apple\'s next picture, the only piece of gorgeous, not all. Open source / commercial / AppStore three modes, I think that their own strength in the future, will have their place.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">I have repeatedly stressed that, like open people, the mentality is more to open. Some people do not want to allow the open source world, do not want to open, this is an open mind. You love CopyLeft, you could have your code open sourced. But CopyLeft not include forcing others to the spirit of open source (subject to licensing restrictions would result in a different matter.)</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">I also agree with the spirit of open source, open source projects themselves, are being maintained, but do these open source projects, and I made such a relatively closed iPhone platform for the above items, did not create any conflict.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">I would like to see in the next open source / commercial / AppStore three models, fancy, are booming. In fact, the rise of open source, and not kill the business, but expanded our vision of the entire software industry and territory. App Store also has a similar role, I look forward to it gives me more to come.</span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(162,'linux','en','/a/IT/2010/0917/718.html','Large adjustments or will abandon Novell SUSE Linux, V','2010-09-17','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">According to The Wall Street Journal reported that several sources said, Novell is working with VMware, including at least two potential buyers, including negotiations to sell its business. <br /> The source said, VMware wants to acquire Novell\'s SUSE <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\"><span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=Linux\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">Linux</span></a></u> operating <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%CF%B5%CD%B3\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">system</span> business, the acquisition of <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%C8%ED%BC%FE\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">software</span> company Attachmate may include NetWare <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%CD%F8%C2%E7\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">network</span> operating systems, including Novell SUSE Linux part of the assets other than or in addition to other assets. <br /><br /> It is reported that, although there are differences between the two sides in the price, but Novell is likely to Linux business to VMware. Analysts pointed out, Linux business will strengthen VMware\'s position in the cloud. The source said that if that price is too low, Novell might not be the remaining assets to Attachmate. <br /><br /> The first 9 months of this fiscal, Novell revenue of $ 605,000,000, profits of $ 56,000,000. Novell 2.1 billion market value, has over 10 million in cash and short-term investments. <br /><br /> Novell is still in discussions with potential buyers deal terms and structure. One reason for <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%BD%F8%B3%CC\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">the</span> slow pace of negotiations is how to split the Novell\'s sales staff and intellectual property. The source said, which makes the negotiations need to continue for several <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%CA%B1%BC%E4\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">weeks.</span> They warned that negotiations could end &quot;fruitless.&quot;</span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(163,'linux',