ll\">8 years experience in Linux system administration and maintenance of more than 5 years experience with oracle database</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Served with a large foreign telecommunications equipment suppliers, is responsible for China Mobile and oracle database backend unix system normal operation, currently working in the domestic well-known e-government enterprise, planning and design and maintain the country\'s 10 provincial-level e-government system a few.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><br /> <font color=\"#256eb1\"><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/2010/0507/98.html\" target=\"_blank\">Individual monograph published in 2010 &quot;Linux the essence of enterprise applications,&quot;</a></font> <br /> <a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/2010/0421/10.html\" target=\"_blank\"><font color=\"#256eb1\">Individual monograph published in 2009 &quot;step by step Linux&quot;</font></a> <br /> 2007 Technical Excellence Award winner IXPUB IT168 Linux Forum Moderator plate</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">You can contact the webmaster as follows:</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">MSN: <a href=\"mailto:gaojf_888@hotmail.com\"><font color=\"#256eb1\">gaojf_888@hotmail.com</font></a></span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">QQ: 397824870</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Email: dba.gao @ gmail.com</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Can also site a message, I will reply to you within the first time!</span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(164,'linux','en','/a/os/aix/2010/0819/498.html','AIX5.1L install bash','2010-08-19','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <font size=\"4\"><b>A: binary installation</b></font> </p><div></div><div> <b>Need to download the software:</b> </div><div> 1: gettext </div><div> Download: http://bio.gsi.de/DOCS/AIX/aixpdslib.seas.ucla.edu/packages/gettext.html </div><div> gettext GNU internationalization library </div><div> gettext.0.14.5.tar.Z </div><div> 2: bash </div><div> Download: http://bio.gsi.de/DOCS/AIX/aixpdslib.seas.ucla.edu/categories/shells.html </div><div> bash.3.1.tar.Z </div><div> <b>Installation:</b> </div><div> Placed the downloaded file to the root partition </div><div> Zcat gettext.0.14.5.tar.Z | tar vxf - </div><div> Zcat bash.3.1.tar.Z | tar vxf - </div><div> This file will be automatically installed to / usr / local following. </div><div></div><div> <b>Some remarks:</b> </div><div> If you do not install gettext.0.14.5.tar.Z then run bash in the following error occurs when: </div><div> exec (): 0509-036 Cannot load program-bash because of the following errors: <br /> 0509-150 Dependent module / usr / local / lib / libintl.a (libintl.so.3) could not be loaded. <br /> 0509-022 Cannot load module / usr / local / lib / libintl.a (libintl.so.3). <br /> 0509-026 System error: A file or directory in the path name does not exist. </div><div></div><div> <b>Reason:</b> </div><div> Although the libintl library in / usr / lib under, but they can not use the binary package libintl library system comes with a need for these binary library initialization environment, that is to install GNU internationalization library, that is, to install gettext.0.14 .5. tar.Z, gettext package contains the libintl library libintl.a. </div><div></div><div> <font size=\"4\"><b>2: Source Installation</b></font> </div><div> Download the appropriate source from the http://bio.gsi.de/DOCS/AIX/aixpdslib.seas.ucla.edu/categories/shells.html also from http://bio.gsi.de/DOCS/AIX/aixpdslib .seas.ucla.edu / categories / development.html Download bison package, that is, yacc, because the bash at compile time to use the yacc. </div><div></div><div> It should be noted that the bison is also dependent on the GNU internationalization library, bison is installed, you must have installed the GNU internationalization library gettext package. </div><div></div><div> <b>Installation:</b> </div><div> Zcat bash.3.1.tar.Z | tar vxf - </div><div> Cd bash.3.1 </div><div> . / Configure </div><div> Make </div><div> Make install </div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(165,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0817/486.html','Original Series Linux system performance analysis tool','2010-08-17','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/\">System</a></u> performance analysis tools</span></span></strong> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">The above section describes several aspects of the performance of linux and how to solve these problems, but how can the system found to be an aspect or several aspects of a problem does arise, which need to use a few linux system performance analysis tools commonly used, the following specific about these popular performance analysis tools. <br /> <strong>1. vmstat command</strong> <br /> vmstat is a Virtual Meomory Statistics (virtual memory statistics) stands, a lot of linux distributions have this command tool installed by default, use the operating system vmstat command to the memory information, process status, CPU monitoring activities, the inadequacies can not be depth analysis of a process. <br /> vmstat uses the following syntax: <br /> vmstat [-V] [-n] [delay [count]] <br /> The meaning of the various options and parameters are as follows: <br /> l-V: print the publication of this information is optional. <br /> l-n: that the periodic loop output, the output of the header information only once. <br /> l delay: that the time interval between the two outputs. <br /> l count: that in accordance with the &quot;delay&quot; time interval specified number of statistics. The default is 1. <br /> For example: <br /> vmstat 3 <br /> Updated once every 3 seconds, said output information, cycle output, press ctrl + c to stop output. <br /> vmstat 3 5 <br /> Updated once every 3 seconds, said output information, statistics, stop after 5 times the output. <br /> <strong>2. iostat command <br /></strong> iostat is the I / O statistics (input / output statistics) stands, the main function is the system disk I / O operations to be monitored. The output shows the disk read and write the main statistical information, but also gives the CPU usage. As with vmstat, iostat can not be in-depth analysis of a process, only the overall system were analyzed. <br /> iostat generally not with the system installed, to use the iostat tool, you need to install a Sysstat system toolkit, Sysstat is an open source software, the official address is <a href=\"http://pagesperso-orange.fr/sebastien.godard\">http://pagesperso-orange.fr/sebastien.godard</a> <br /> Can select the source code package or rpm packages install, here is not about the installation process, the installation is complete, the system will be more three command: iostat, sar and mpstat. You can then run directly in the system iostat command. <br /> iostat syntax is as follows: <br /> iostat [-c |-d] [-k] [-t] [-x [device]] [interval [count]] <br /> The meaning of the various options and parameters are as follows: <br /> -C: show CPU usage. <br /> -D: shows disk usage. <br /> -K: the k bytes per second, units of display data. <br /> -T: print statistics begin time. <br /> -X device: Specify the name of the disk device to statistics, the default for all disk devices. <br /> interval: specifies the time interval between the two statistics; <br /> count: in accordance with the &quot;interval&quot; interval specified number of statistics. <br /> <strong>3. sar command</strong> <br /> sar command is very powerful, is an important tool for analysis of system performance, through the sar command, you can fully access the system CPU, the run queue, disk I / O, paging (swap), memory, CPU interrupts, network performance data. <br /> sar uses the format: <br /> sar [options] [g1] [-o filename] [interval [count]] <br /> The meaning of the various options and parameters are as follows: <br /> l options for the command-line options, sar command options are many, listing only commonly used options below: <br /> ÃƒÂ˜-A: Display System devices all the resources (CPU, memory, disk) operating conditions. <br /> ÃƒÂ˜-u: display system at the sampling time for all CPU load status. <br /> ÃƒÂ˜-P: Display the current system CPU usage is specified. <br /> ÃƒÂ˜-d: Show all hard disk drives in the system sampling time conditions of use. <br /> ÃƒÂ˜-r: Displays the system memory at the sampling time of usage. <br /> ÃƒÂ˜-b: display buffer in the use of sampling time. <br /> ÃƒÂ˜-v: show process, file, I state the nodes and the lock table. <br /> ÃƒÂ˜-n: display the network running. Parameters can be followed with the DEV, EDEV, SOCK, and FULL. DEV display network interface information, EDEV shows network error statistics, SOCK display socket information, FULL three all of the information displayed. They can be used separately or together. <br /> ÃƒÂ˜-q: shows the size of the run queue, the average time it loads the same system. <br /> ÃƒÂ˜-R: Display process activities within the sampling time. <br /> ÃƒÂ˜-y: the display terminal device activities within the sampling time. <br /> ÃƒÂ˜-w: display system exchange activities in the state of the sampling period. <br /> l-o filename: the results of said commands in binary format will be stored in the file, filename is the file name. <br /> l interval: the sampling interval, must be some parameters. <br /> l count: that the sampling frequency, is an optional parameter, the default value is 1. <br /> For example: <br /> To view the system\'s overall CPU load conditions, once every 3 seconds and Statistics, statistics 5 times, you can use the following combinations: <br /> sar-u 3 5 <br /> System CPU count is 0, and if you want to view the operation of the second-CPU load, use the following combinations: <br /> sar-P 1 3 5 <br /> To view the system disk read and write performance, use the following combinations: <br /> sar-d 3 5 <br /> Similarly, view the system memory usage, network operation status, you can use the following commands respectively: <br /> sar-r 5 2 <br /> sar-n DEV 5 3</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><br /> <strong>15.2.3 System Performance Standards</strong></span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><br /> The main purpose of tuning the system to effectively use various resources, most of it between the application and system performance integration, the application of efficient and stable operation. However, measuring the system resource utilization is not a strict quality standard definition, for different systems and applications do not have a unified view, therefore, here is an experience of the standard value, Table 15.1 shows the determination of system resources the utilization of general guidelines: <br /></span></span> </p><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Table 15.1 shows the system resource utilization to determine the general guidelines:</span></span> </div><div align=\"center\"> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Table 15.1</span></span> </div><div align=\"center\"><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td rowspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\"><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã‚Â </span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Factors affecting performance</span></span> </div></td><td colspan=\"3\" valign=\"top\"><div align=\"center\"> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Criteria</span></span> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\"><div align=\"center\"> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Good</span></span> </div></td><td valign=\"top\"><div align=\"center\"> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Bad</span></span> </div></td><td valign=\"top\"><div align=\"center\"> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Bad</span></span> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\"><div align=\"center\"> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">CPU</span></span> </div></td><td valign=\"top\"><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">user% + sys% &lt;70% &lt;</span></span>'),(166,'linux','en','/a/IT/2010/0812/439.html','Linux or Windows server system, we','2010-08-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p class=\"newtext\"> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">What do you think of a better server operating system is Microsoft\'s Windows or open-source Linux? On this issue gave rise to numerous debates, but a long time Windows and Linux, used by IT consultants say, to say which server operating system best work to hard to answer, because in the choice of server operating system, we need to combine cost, performance, security and applications considered.</span></span> </p><p class=\"newtext\"> <strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Select the reason Linux operating system</span></span></strong> </p><p class=\"newtext\"> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">SystemExperts chief adviser Phil Cox said: &quot;The use of Linux, the operating system can not spend money, but if you choose Windows, will need to pay licensing fees to Microsoft, so from a cost considerations, Linux is the best choice, and in any physical hardware platform, Linux is always showing the performance of about 25% faster. &quot;</span></span> </p><p class=\"newtext\"> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Linux is also more flexible to use, free, and even the kernel can make changes to, a lot of customization settings in Windows, is not experience, so there are too many people praising Linux, but something always has two sides, Cox pointed out, is Because Linux is flexible, making maintenance more difficult, leading to many business users prohibitive.</span></span> </p><p class=\"newtext\"> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">For example, Linux kernel can be modified and highly customized, so the IT staff have higher skill requirements, the other, Linux versions of many application compatibility issues often all kinds of weird.</span></span> </p><p class=\"newtext\"> <strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Select the reason Windows operating system</span></span></strong> </p><p class=\"newtext\"> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Windows attraction is stable, although less flexible, but in the integration of applications, Windows is often the most simple. And Microsoft executives said: The future of server operating system will have great movement.</span></span> </p><p class=\"newtext\"> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">In addition, Windows itself comes with a good access control mechanisms need to install any plug-ins or patches can achieve effective access control.</span></span> </p><p class=\"newtext\"> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Either Windows or Linux, system patch exists, but to the Windows patching is much easier, and all patches are from Microsoft. Patch mechanism under which Linux is more complicated, a software development organization released a patch for a single software, Linux distribution vendors have released a collection of patches, while Linux is a patch under the high-risk thing. Although Linux, patching some difficulties, but in the powerful open source software in several very strong patch management tools. In short, the patch to the Linux system is a very complicated matter, not a bit daring and is not easily grasp the patches, and in Windows, even if it was new to the line started going to sit back and relax in to the system can also install the patch.</span></span> </p><p class=\"newtext\"> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Cox said: &quot;Linux community does not TechNet, Linux users must seek the help of the community, and as such, Linux community will be so prosperous.&quot;</span></span> </p><p class=\"newtext\"> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Perhaps it is for these reasons that has caused everyone to say that Linux is good, yet you dare not, otherwise why continue to occupy most of the Windows enterprise server? Some vertical industries, but now began to favor Linux, and Linux as the financial industry has become the largest user.</span></span> </p><p class=\"newtext\"> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Cox said that Linux and open source software applications in the enterprise extranet is still very common, and the other, Linux is loved in the field of industrial technology, we have many products and services can see the shadow of Linux, such as Amazon\'s EC2 cloud computing data center is built on top of Xen\'s Linux server.</span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(167,'linux','en','/a/db/mysql/2010/0810/431.html','mysql how to write the table name is case sensitive','2010-08-10','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Under linux <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/db/mysql/\">mysql</a></u> database table name by default is case-sensitive, to ignore the table names case, add a configuration to: <br /></p><p> vi / etc / my.cnf <br /> In the [mysqld] to increase column: <br /> lower_case_table_names = 0 </p><p> Can ignore case, if you set </p><p> lower_case_table_names = 1 Ã¥ÂˆÂ™ case sensitive. </p><p> The default mysql is case sensitive. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(168,'linux','en','/a/db/oracle/2010/0806/418.html','How to determine the connection mode is the oracle database','2010-08-06','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> This problem not only with the parameters shared_servers, dispatchers, but also with the server, the client\'s TNSname.ora documents are related. </p><p> In the DB server side shared_servers parameter controls whether to accept share server connection, but, client can be set by TNSname.ora mandatory DEDICATED <br /> As follows, 4 kinds of situations: <br /> DB shared_servers = 0, TNSname.ora server = shared, or not set ==&gt; DEDICATED connection <br /> DB shared_servers = 0, TNSname.ora server = DEDICATED ==&gt; DEDICATED connection <br /> DB shared_servers&gt; 0, TNSname.ora server = DEDICATED ==&gt; DEDICATED connection <br /> DB shared_servers&gt; 0, TNSname.ora server = shared, or not set ==&gt; Shared Connection </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(169,'linux','en','/a/os/aix/2010/0806/417.html','AIX common command summary (from IBM)','2010-08-06','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> In the use and System p Ã¢Â„Â¢ AIX Ã‚Â® server is experiencing problems, you want to be able to find their own answer? Do you want do not always turn to professional support staff, so save some time? Well, this article will discuss some of these questions can be answered AIX commands, and tells you how to look for other answers. <br /> Introduction </p><p> As you know, AIX Ã‚Â® has a myriad of commands that allow you to perform a large number of tasks. Depending on the tasks you need, you may use only to a subset of these commands. These sub-sets with different users and different needs vary. However, there are some you usually want to use the core command. You need these commands to answer your own questions, or ask for the support staff to provide answers. </p><p> In this article, I will discuss some of these core commands. The purpose can be used to provide you with a convenient reference list. Although the behavior of these commands on all AIX versions should be the same, but only under the AIX 5.3 are tested. </p><p> Note: <br /> Bootinfo discussed in the following paragraphs is not user-level commands, and AIX 4.2 or later is not supported. <br /></p><p> Command ------------------------------------------------- ---------------- </p><p> <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Kernel command</span></strong> </p><p> How do I know running a 32 bit kernel or a 64-bit kernel? </p><p> Enabled to display the kernel is 32 bit or 64-bit, enter the following command: </p><p> bootinfo-K </p><p><br /> How do I know running a single processor or multiple processor cores? </p><p> / Unix is a pointer to the kernel of the symbolic link is activated. To find out what kernel mode is running, enter ls-l / unix and view the / unix link to any file. Here is ls-l / unix command and its corresponding three possible output of the kernel: </p><p> / Unix -&gt; / usr / lib / boot / unix_up # 32 bit uniprocessor kernel <br /> / Unix -&gt; / usr / lib / boot / unix_mp # 32 bit multiprocessor kernel <br /> / Unix -&gt; / usr/lib/boot/unix_64 # 64 bit multiprocessor kernel <br /></p><p> Note: <br /> AIX 5L Version 5.3 does not support single-processor core. </p><p> How to change from one kernel mode to another kernel mode? </p><p> During the installation process will enable a default for the AIX version and the operation of the hardware kernel. Let us use the method in the previous question and assume 32-bit kernel is enabled. We also assume that you want 64-bit kernel mode. This can be done in order to achieve the following command: </p><p> ln-sf / usr/lib/boot/unix_64 / unix <br /> ln-sf / usr/lib/boot/unix_64 / usr / lib / boot / unix </p><p> bosboot-ad / dev / hdiskxx <br /> shutdown-r <br /><br /> / Dev / hdiskxx directory is to start the logical volume / dev/hd5 location. To find out hdiskxx in which xx, run the following command: </p><p> lslv-m hd5 <br /><br /> Note: <br /> In AIX 5.2, the default installation of a 32-bit kernel. In AIX 5.3, the default 64-bit hardware will be installed on 64-bit kernel, 32-bit hardware to install 32-bit kernel. </p><p> Hardware </p><p> How do I know if my computer can run AIX 5L Version 5.3? </p><p> AIX 5L Version 5.3 can be supported in all current common hardware reference platform-based (Common Hardware Reference Platform, CHRP) of the POWER hardware. </p><p> How do I know my computer is based on CHRP? </p><p> Run the prtconf command. If CHRP computer, the string chrp will appear in the Model Architecture line. </p><p> How do I know my System p machine (hardware) is a 32-bit or 64-bit? </p><p> To display hardware 32-bit or 64-bit, enter the following command: </p><p> bootinfo-y </p><p><br /> The actual number of my computer memory? </p><p> To display the KB as the unit of real memory, enter the following commands: </p><p> bootinfo-r </p><p></p><p> lsattr-El sys0-a realmem </p><p><br /> My computer can run 64-bit kernel? </p><p> Need 64-bit hardware to run 64-bit kernel. </p><p> My property value devices in the system What is it? </p><p> To list the current tape device rmt0 attribute value, enter the following command: </p><p> lsattr-l rmt0-E </p><p><br /> To list the default tape device rmt0 attribute value, enter the following command: </p><p> lsattr-l rmt0-D </p><p><br /> Tty0 TTY device to list the possible registry attribute value, enter the following command: </p><p> lsattr-l tty0-a login-R </p><p><br /> To display system level attributes, enter the following command: </p><p> lsattr-E-l sys0 </p><p><br /> My system has the number of processors? </p><p> To display the number of processors on your system, enter the following command: </p><p> lscfg | grep proc </p><p><br /> The number on my system hard disk, hard disk which is currently being used? </p><p> To display the number on the system disk, enter the following command: </p><p> lspv </p><p><br /> How to list information about a specific physical volume? </p><p> For example, to learn more information about hdisk1, run the following command: </p><p> lspv hdisk1 <br /></p><p></p><p> Details of how to get the system configuration? </p><p> Enter the following command: </p><p> lscfg </p><p><br /> The following options can provide specific information: </p><p> -P Display the platform-specific device information. This flag applies to AIX 4.2.1 or later. <br /> -V Display VPD object class in a custom key products found in the database (Vital Product Database, VPD). </p><p><br /> For example, to display information about the tape drive rmt0 more information, enter the following command: </p><p> lscfg-vl rmt0 </p><p><br /> By running the prtconf command can also get very similar information. </p><p> How to determine the chip type, system name, node name, type, etc.? </p><p> uname command provides detailed information about the system. </p><p> uname-p display system chip types. For example, PowerPC. <br /> uname-r displays the operating system version number. <br /> uname-s display system name.Ã¤Â¾Â‹Ã¥Â¦Â‚, AIX. <br /> uname-n displays the node name. <br /> uname-a display system name, node name, version, machine ID. <br /> uname-M display system model name. For example, IBM, 9114-275. <br /> uname-v display version of the operating system. <br /> uname-m shows the hardware of the computer operating system ID number. <br /> uname-u display system ID number. </p><p><br /> AIX </p><p> My system is running any version of AIX major, minor version and maintenance level? </p><p> Enter the following commands: </p><p> oslevel-r </p><p></p><p> lslpp-h bos.rte </p><p><br /> How to determine a specific set of AIX-level file update which is missing? </p><p> For example, to determine which files are missing set of 5300-04 update, run the following command: </p><p> oslevel-rl 5300-04 </p><p><br /> Installed on my system, what SP (Service Pack)? </p><p> To understand what is currently installed on the system SP, can run oslevel-s command. TL4 and SP2 installed for the AIX 5L Version 5.3 system, the sample output as follows: </p><p> oslevel-s <br /> 5300-04-02 <br /></p><p><br /> My system is installed CSP (Concluding Service Pack)? </p><p> To determine whether the system is currently installed on a CSP, you can run oslevel-s command. TL3, and CSP for the installation of AIX 5L Version 5.3 system, the sample output as follows: </p><p> oslevel-s <br /> 5300-03-CSP <br /></p><p><br /> How to create a file system? </p><p> The following command will create a volume group testvg size of 10MB, installation of point / fs1 the jfs file system: </p><p> crfs-v jfs-g testvg-a size = 10M-m / fs1 <br /></p><p><br /> The following command will create a volume group testvg size of 10MB, installation of point / fs2 and have read-only file system permissions jfs2: </p><p> crfs-v jfs2-g testvg-a size = 10M-p ro-m / fs2 <br /></p><p><br /> How do I change the size of the file system? </p><p> To the / usr file system to increase the size of one million 512 byte blocks, enter the following command: </p><p> chfs-a size = +1000000 / usr </p><p><br /> Note: <br /> In AIX 5.3 in, JFS2 file system size also shrinking. </p><p> How to install CD? </p><p> Enter the following command: </p><p> mount-V cdrfs-o ro / dev/cd0 / cdrom </p><p><br /> How to install the file system? </p><p> The following command will / test directory to install the file system / dev/fslv02: </p><p> mount / dev/fslv02 / test <br /></p><p><br /> How to install all the default file system (/ etc / filesystems file have mount = true attribute tag all the standard file system)? </p><p> The following command will install all of these text'),(170,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0803/394.html','Linux system management and maintenance-wget command','2010-08-03','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <b><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">wget command</span></span></b> </p><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Function: to download a software from the network, this command can be connected to the Internet for linux system function is very large, can be downloaded directly from the network the software they need.</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Using the format: wget [URL to download the software]</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">For example:</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Download a linux 2.6.26 kernel version, you can use the following command:</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">[Root @ localhost ~] # wget \\</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">&gt;</font> Http://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v2.6/patch-2.6.26.bz2</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">- 09:35:32 - http://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v2.6/patch-2.6.26.bz2</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">=&gt; `Patch-2.6.26.bz2 \'</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Resolving www.kernel.org ... 204.152.191.5, 204.152.191.37</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Connecting to www.kernel.org|204.152.191.5|:80 ... connected.</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">HTTP request sent, awaiting response ... 200 OK</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Length: 7,691,397 (7.3M) [application/x-bzip2]</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">7% [=====&gt;] 580,338 27.85K / s ETA 03:42</span></span> </div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(171,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0803/393.html','Linux system management and maintenance-telnet command','2010-08-03','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <b><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">telnet command</span></span></b> </p><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Function Description: The telnet protocol communications with the remote host or remote host to obtain the information corresponding to the port. Telnet under windows complete with the same function.</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Using the format: telnet host name or ip address port</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">For example:</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">1. Log in via telnet protocol to open a telnet service on a remote host, use the following command:</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">[Root @ localhost ~] # telnet 192.168.60.123 23</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Trying 192.168.60.123 ...</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Connected to 192.168.60.123 (192.168.60.123).</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Escape character is\'^]\'.</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">HP-UX host4 B.11.11 U 9000/800 (ta)</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">login: root</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Password:</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"># When we enter a user name and password after the log on to the &quot;192.168.60.123&quot; server, where we directly use the &quot;telnet 192.168.60.123&quot; is possible, because the telnet default search is &quot;23&quot; port.</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">[Root @ localhost ~] # telnet 192.168.60.123 25</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Trying 192.168.60.123 ...</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">telnet: connect to address 192.168.60.123: Connection refused</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"># If this problem occurs, the corresponding service that the port is not open, or the port is blocked, no access.</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">2. View a table of 22 and 80 linux system ports are open and what services were opened, use the following command:</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">[Root @ localhost ~] # telnet 192.168.60.88 22</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Trying 192.168.60.21 ...</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Connected to 192.168.60.21 (192.168.60.21).</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Escape character is\'^]\'.</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">SSH-1.99-OpenSSH_3.9p1</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Protocol mismatch.</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Connection closed by foreign host.</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"># It can be seen in &quot;192.168.60.88&quot; port 22 ssh service running, the corresponding ssh version is OpenSSH_3.9p1.</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">[Root @ localhost ~] # telnet www.ixdba.net 80</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Trying 221.130.192.57 ...</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Connected to www.ixdba.net (221.130.192.57).</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Escape character is\'^]\'.</span></span> </div><div> <b><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">get</span></span></b> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">&lt;! DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;- / / IETF / / DTD HTML 2.0 / / EN&quot;&gt;</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">&lt;html&gt; &lt;head&gt;</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">&lt;title&gt; 501 Method Not Implemented &lt;/ title&gt;</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">&lt;/ Head&gt; &lt;body&gt;</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">&lt;h1&gt; Method Not Implemented &lt;/ h1&gt;</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">&lt;p&gt; get to / index.html not supported.</span></span>'),(172,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0803/392.html','Linux system management and maintenance-traceroute','2010-08-03','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(173,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0711/315.html','How to choose your own linux distribution','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> About <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\">linux</a></u> distributions, too much, probably no one can give an accurate number, but one thing is for sure, <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\">Linux</a></u> is becoming increasingly popular, in the face of so many Linux distributions, going from Go to linux system to other systems may be confusing for beginners, even the faithful Linux users do not have time and energy to try one by one, so the beginners in learning linux, you need to have a clear direction, choose a suitable system is essential to start learning linux! Here we introduce classification. </p><div style=\"text-align: center\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"148\" onclick=\"window.open(\'/uploads/allimg/100711/1_100711185103_1.jpg\')\" src=\"http://www.ixdba.net/uploads/allimg/100711/1_100711185103_1.jpg\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" width=\"209\" /></div><p> 1.1.1 Beginners series of preferred-redhat linux in the series before learning redhat, redhat linux must first understand the following relationships between the various releases. <br /></p><p> 1. Red Hat Linux <br /> Redhat Red Hat Linux is the first release of the personal version of linux, the 1.0 version on November 3, 1994 issue. Although its history is less than other linux releases a long, but compared to a lot of Linux distributions, Red Hat\'s long history and much more. Since Red Hat 9. 0 after release, RedHat is no longer developing the company\'s Linux desktop distributions, Red Hat Linux to stop the development, and will be fully concentrate on the development of the server version, which is Red Hat Enterprise Linux version. April 30, 2004, Red Hat the company official to stop Red Hat 9. 0 version of the support, marking the official end of the Red Hat Linux. The original Red Hat Linux desktop distributions are Fedora open source community and from the plan to merge into Fedora Core release. <br /> Red Hat is currently divided into two series: the Red Hat provides technical support and updated charging Red Hat Enterprise Linux, as well as community development free from the Fedora Core. <br /></p><p> 2. Fedora Core <br /> Fedora Core (abbreviated as FC) is targeting Red Hat\'s experimental site for the new technology, many new technologies will be tested in the FC, if stable, then Red Hat will consider joining the Red Hat Enterprise Linux. <br /> Fedora Core 1 was released in late 2003, and FC is the positioning of desktop users. FC provides the latest package, while its version of the update cycle is very short, only 6 months. Since version update frequently, performance and stability can not be guaranteed, therefore, generally not recommended on the server Fedora Core. <br /> In fact, so to that, Fedora is Red Hat released Red Hat Enterprise linux version of an experiment, take the user to do the test for Red Hat Enterprise Edition released as a foundation. <br /></p><p> 3. Red Hat Enterprise Linux <br /> Red Hat Enterprise Linux (abbreviated to RHEL, Red Hat Enterprise Edition.) Red Hat is now the main job of the server version of linux development, in the version of emphasis on the performance and stability as well as hardware support. Enterprise Edition operating system, because the development cycle is longer, pay attention to performance, stability, and server software support, version updates are relatively slow. <br /> RedHat Enterprise Linux version is divided into 4 Advanced Server (AS), ES Workstation (WS), Desktop, their difference is not large, only a function of the difference. <br /></p><p> 4. Centos <br /> CentOS full name of the &quot;Community Enterprise Operating System&quot; (Community Enterprise Operating System) <br /> CentOS background: <br /> Redhat released Redhat 9. 0, no longer develop redhat 10,11 ... ..., a comprehensive shift Redhat enterprise linux (abbreviated as rhel) development, and different from the past, the new redhat Enterprise Edition requires users to first purchase lisence, redhat same time commitment to ensure the stability, security. rhel binary code is no longer available for download, but as part of redhat service, but the source code remains open. In this case, there has been centos, whitebox, dao, and so a number of open source in the enterprise version, which centos most active. <br /></p><p> Here is how to make about centos generated: </p><p><br /> Redhat CentOS community to the site download all the source code, recompile. As AS / ES / WS is a commercial product, therefore, must be all the Redhat\'s Logo CentOS and logo into their own identity. Such as the AS4. 0 SRPM original source compiled and put on Centos community logo, so that became the CentOS 4. 0. Redhat Enterprise Linux AS4 Update1 the source compiled to become a CentOS4. 1. AS4 Update2 source code compiled to become a CentOS4. 2 and so on. CentOS is produced. <br /> Therefore, it can be said of CentOS is Redhat AS / ES / WS free version can be obtained using the centos redhat enterprise linux with the same features and performance. Centos while also providing free long-term upgrade and update services. Thus, in many versions of RHEL clone, CentOS is a very outstanding very good. <br /> Although it is a RHEL clone centos, but not exactly the same, said cloning is a 100% interchangeability. In fact, different for centos, RHEL on CentOS software can not guarantee 100% above normal. <br /> To understand the difference between Redhat version series, after all. In fact, we found Why Redhat linux as a beginner to learn the reason. <br /> First of all: in the country, and even the world\'s Linux users are most familiar with, the most heard details of the distribution can be sure it is a Red Hat. Red Hat is the linux community as the &quot;boss&quot;, the U.S. company Red Hat released Red Hat linux is a commercial operation of the most successful Linux distributions, so Red Hat linux issued by a trusted company, Red Hat linux functionality and performance There is no doubt. <br /> Second: Red hat now has a huge network of user groups, network resources, the basic 90% of linux are based on Redhat linux, if you encounter any problems in the learning process, whatever the search network, there are thousands of answers to display in front of you. <br /> III: Red Hat linux version of complementary series, complement each other: If your first contact with linux, it is recommended that you install Fedora Core, Fedora Core installation is simple, good hardware support, the interface is also very beautiful, but also can experience the Redhat linux the latest features; if you have some knowledge of linux, need further study, I suggest you use the CENTOS system; if you are doing linux enterprise applications, we recommend you use RHEL version. <br /> Last: redhat wide range of applications, with typical and representative, many systems (such as red redflag, winning linux, oracle release of Enterprise Linux) are based on Red Hat linux as the base, and therefore can be said to learn the Red Hat linux, will be able to comprehend by analogy, other similar linux system can quickly mastered; around now in general are also learning to linux redhat linux based, so to facilitate communication, learning problems, more easily solved. Redhat linux while installing and using the most simple, therefore, is basically not in the &quot;loading system&quot; to waste too much time. <br /></p><p> 1.1.2 Enterprise Application preferred-suse linux <br /> The pursuit of enterprise-class applications is reliability and stability, which requires the application of building enterprise-class platform with high reliability and high stability. Enterprise linux distributions is to solve this problem. <br /> SUSE Linux is Germany\'s most famous release, around the world also enjoys a high reputation. November 4, 2003, Novell announced the company will acquire SuSE. January 2004 completion of the acquisition process, Novell SuSE also will be officially named SuSE Linux. Novell\'s acquisition of suse, speed up the development of the suse linux, suse linux server, both in the desktop market or markets are more specialized, according to incomplete statistics, suse linux linux market share in Europe is now nearly 80% of the share, most of the critical applications is built under suse linux. Suse shorter due to China, while with suse marketing model in China, the domestic short-term can not be accepted, so now suse market share in China is not great, but this does not affect the suse linux high reliability and stability the fact that, with the development of suse, suse linux in China believe that the application will be more and more. <br /></p><p> 1.1.3 Preferred-Ubuntu Linux Game <br /> Speaking of linux desktop market, Ubuntu Linux account for almost half of the desktop linux, Ubuntu Linux main linux desktop, the most beautiful interface, simple yet gorgeous, if you want entertainment under linux, Ubuntu Linux is definitely the first choice. <br /> Ubuntu is very user-friendly installation, simply follow the instructions step by step, the installation is as easy as with Windows! And, Ubuntu is best known for the most comprehensive hardware support for Linux distributions, and many other distributions can not be used or not used in the default configuration of hardware, in Ubuntu, can be easy to get. So you can install windows as easily as the installation of Ubuntu. Enjoy the fun of Ubuntu linux. </p><p><br /> 1.1.4 linux as a server is the trend </p><p><br /> In the above section introduces some of the most common linux distributions, in fact, there are many linux distributions much more common there is Debian GNU / Linux, Mandriva, Gentoo, Slackware, Knoppix, MEPIS, Xandros, domestic red flag redflag, winning linux, etc., and is not introduced one by one, in fact, look at the various linux distributions, linux release is nothing more than moving from two aspects, one is the server market, but the desktop market. <br /> As the representative of the Ubuntu Linux distribution linux desktop market is taking the route, although they bring a lot of surprises to the user, update soon, but because of the desktop market has such a strong opponent windows, linux desktop'),(174,'linux','en','/a/web/nginx/2010/0630/261.html','apache alias in the realization of the nginx','2010-06-30','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> In my environment, set documentRoot directory: <br /> root / data0/htdocs/NetBeansProjects/_example/passport; <br /> Php file set forwarded to fastcgi: <br /> location ~ .* \\. (php | php5)? $ <br /> { <br /> # Fastcgi_pass unix: / tmp / php-cgi.sock; <br /> fastcgi_pass 127.0.0.1:9000; <br /> fastcgi_index index.php; <br /> include fcgi.conf; <br /> } <br /> Now the requirement is to achieve the secondary directory to forward, which is a very easy apache, alias can be a secondary directory: </p><p><br /> alias / lowgame / &quot;/ data0/htdocs/NetBeansProjects/_example/lowgame /&quot; <br /> In the corresponding nginx is written: <br /> location / lowgame / { <br /> alias / data0/htdocs/NetBeansProjects/_example/lowgame /; <br /> index index.html index.htm index.php; <br /> } <br /> Thus, access to localhost / lowgame / ddd.jpg and other non-php file which is equivalent to access / data0/htdocs/NetBeansProjects/_example/lowgame/ddd.jpg, which has not a problem. Now many people will face a problem: we take for granted the wish / lowgame / *. php files are submitted to the fastcgi analysis, the results are not so that when I visited localhost / lowgame / ddd.php time, fastcgi returns an error: <br /> No input file specified. <br /> ddd.php true existence, permissions, and no problem, apparently can not find the file fastcgi, nginx actually submitted this path / data0/htdocs/NetBeansProjects/_example/passport/lowgame/ddd.php, of course, can not find it. Try to add the following code: <br /> location ~ / lowgame /(.*/)?.* \\. (php | php5)? $ <br /> { <br /> # Fastcgi_pass unix: / tmp / php-cgi.sock; <br /> fastcgi_pass 127.0.0.1:9000; <br /> fastcgi_index index.php; <br /> include fcgi.conf; <br /> } <br /> But will be matched to the above location ~ .* \\. (Php | php5)? $, The Internet search a lot, no one used the. Then think of apache virtual host configuration has a strategy is a particular second level domain EDITORIAL, if no match to the last, and finally set up a common match. nginx is not also have this feature? The location ~ / lowgame /(.*/)?.* \\. (Php | php5)? $ Code into the location ~ .* \\. (Php | php5)? $ Code in front, finally done! </p><p> Here is my nginx configuration file: <br /> user www www; </p><p> worker_processes 2; </p><p> error_log / data0/logs/nginx_error.log crit; </p><p> pid / usr / local / webserver / nginx / nginx.pid; </p><p> # Specifies the value for maximum file descriptors that can be opened by this process. <br /> worker_rlimit_nofile 65535; </p><p> events <br /> { <br /> use epoll; <br /> worker_connections 65535; <br /> } </p><p> http <br /> { <br /> include mime.types; <br /> default_type application / octet-stream; </p><p> # Charset gb2312; </p><p> server_names_hash_bucket_size 128; <br /> client_header_buffer_size 32k; <br /> large_client_header_buffers 4 32k; <br /> client_max_body_size 8m; </p><p> sendfile on; <br /> tcp_nopush on; </p><p> keepalive_timeout 60; </p><p> tcp_nodelay on; </p><p> fastcgi_connect_timeout 300; <br /> fastcgi_send_timeout 300; <br /> fastcgi_read_timeout 300; <br /> fastcgi_buffer_size 64k; <br /> fastcgi_buffers 4 64k; <br /> fastcgi_busy_buffers_size 128k; <br /> fastcgi_temp_file_write_size 128k; </p><p> gzip on; <br /> gzip_min_length 1k; <br /> gzip_buffers 4 16k; <br /> gzip_http_version 1.0; <br /> gzip_comp_level 2; <br /> gzip_types text / plain application / x-javascript text / css application / xml; <br /> gzip_vary on; </p><p> # Limit_zone crawler $ binary_remote_addr 10m; </p><p> server <br /> { <br /> listen 80; <br /> server_name localhost; <br /> index index.html index.htm index.php; <br /> root / data0/htdocs; </p><p> # Limit_conn crawler 20; </p><p> location ~ .* \\. (php | php5)? $ <br /> { <br /> # Fastcgi_pass unix: / tmp / php-cgi.sock; <br /> fastcgi_pass 127.0.0.1:9000; <br /> fastcgi_index index.php; <br /> include fcgi.conf; <br /> } </p><p> log_format access \'$ remote_addr - $ remote_user [$ time_local] &quot;$ request&quot;\' <br /> \'$ Status $ body_bytes_sent &quot;$ http_referer&quot;\' <br /> \'&quot;$ Http_user_agent&quot; $ http_x_forwarded_for\'; <br /> access_log / data0/logs/access.log access; </p><p> location / status { <br /> stub_status on; <br /> access_log off; <br /> # Auth_basic &quot;NginxStatus&quot;; <br /> # Auth_basic_user_file conf / htpasswd; <br /> } <br /> } </p><p> server <br /> { <br /> listen 80; <br /> server_name localpassport.nb; <br /> index index.html index.htm index.php; <br /> root / data0/htdocs/NetBeansProjects/_example/passport; <br /> access_log / data0/logs/access.log access; </p><p> # Limit_conn crawler 20; </p><p> # Comment out the following seemingly will automatically add slashes <br /> # Optimize_server_names off; This method is not recommended <br /> server_name_in_redirect off; # # These two lines and the following three lines is to enable the automatic subdirectory / <br /> if (-d $ request_filename) { <br /> # Rewrite ^/(.*)([^/])$ <a href=\"http://$host/$1$2/\">http:// $ Host / $ 1 $ 2 /</a> Permanent; <br /> } </p><p> location ~ ^ / (lowgame | lowproxy | lowadmin | passportadmin )/(.* \\. php) $ <br /> { <br /> alias / data0/htdocs/NetBeansProjects/_example / $ 1 / $ 2; <br /> fastcgi_pass 127.0.0.1:9000; <br /> fastcgi_index index.php; <br /> include fcgi.conf; <br /> } </p><p> location ~ .* \\. (php | php5)? $ { <br /> # Fastcgi_pass unix: / tmp / php-cgi.sock; <br /> fastcgi_pass 127.0.0.1:9000; <br /> fastcgi_index index.php; <br /> include fcgi.conf; <br /> } </p><p> location / lowgame / { <br /> alias / data0/htdocs/NetBeansProjects/_example/lowgame /; <br /> } </p><p> location / lowproxy / { <br /> alias / data0/htdocs/NetBeansProjects/_example/lowproxy /; <br /> } </p><p> location / lowadmin / { <br /> alias / data0/htdocs/NetBeansProjects/_example/lowadmin /; <br /> } </p><p> location / passportadm'),(175,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0623/251.html','Full installation and configuration nagios3.2.0 combat attack','2010-06-23','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> First, install the support package </p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Yum-y install gcc gcc-c + + gd gd-devel php httpd openssl-devel <br /> # Yum-y install gcc gcc-c + + gd gd-devel php httpd openssl-devel <br /></p><p> Second, install nagios </p><p> Create User </p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Useradd nagios # passwd nagios <br /> # Useradd nagios # passwd nagios <br /></p><p> Create Group </p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Groupadd nagcmd # usermod-G nagcmd nagios # usermod-G nagcmd apache <br /> # Groupadd nagcmd # usermod-G nagcmd nagios # usermod-G nagcmd apache <br /></p><p> Installation </p><p> Bash code <br /> # Tar xzf nagios-3.2.0.tar.gz <br /> # Cd nagios-3.2.0 <br /> #. / Configure - with-command-group = nagcmd - prefix = / usr / local / nagios <br /> # Make all <br /> # Make install # make install to install the main program to use, CGI and HTML files <br /> # Make install-init # make install-init to use in / etc / rc.d / init.d install the startup script # make install-config # make install-cofig used to install the sample configuration file, the installation path is / usr / local / nagios / etc. <br /> # Make install-commandmode # make install-commandmode used to configure the directory permissions <br /> # Tar xzf nagios-3.2.0.tar.gz <br /> # Cd nagios-3.2.0 <br /> #. / Configure - with-command-group = nagcmd - prefix = / usr / local / nagios <br /> # Make all <br /> # Make install # make install to install the main program to use, CGI and HTML files <br /> # Make install-init # make install-init to use in / etc / rc.d / init.d install the startup script # make install-config # make install-cofig used to install the sample configuration file, the installation path is / usr / local / nagios / etc. <br /> # Make install-commandmode # make install-commandmode used to configure the directory permissions </p><p> nagios directory features a brief description: <br /> execution directory bin Nagios, nagios file is the main program <br /> etc Nagios configuration file location <br /> sbin Nagios Cgi file directory, execute external command is the directory where the required documents <br /> Share Nagios web directory where the file <br /> var Nagios log file, spid and other file\'s directory <br /> var / archives log archive directory <br /> var / rw external command file used to store </p><p> Configuring apache </p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Vi / etc / httpd / conf / httpd.conf # add the end of the <br /> # Vi / etc / httpd / conf / httpd.conf # add the end of the </p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p> Bash code <br /> ScriptAlias / nagios / cgi-bin &quot;/ usr / local / nagios / sbin&quot; <br /><br /> &lt;Directory &quot;/usr/local/nagios/sbin&quot;&gt; <br /> # SSLRequireSSL <br /> Options ExecCGI <br /> AllowOverride None <br /> Order allow, deny <br /> Allow from all <br /> # Order deny, allow <br /> # Deny from all <br /> # Allow from 127.0.0.1 <br /> AuthName &quot;Nagios Access&quot; <br /> AuthType Basic <br /> AuthUserFile / usr / local / nagios / etc / htpasswd.users <br /> Require valid-user <br /> &lt;/ Directory&gt; <br /><br /> Alias / nagios &quot;/ usr / local / nagios / share&quot; <br /><br /> &lt;Directory &quot;/usr/local/nagios/share&quot;&gt; <br /> # SSLRequireSSL <br /> Options None <br /> AllowOverride None <br /> Order allow, deny <br /> Allow from all <br /> # Order deny, allow <br /> # Deny from all <br /> # Allow from 127.0.0.1 <br /> AuthName &quot;Nagios Access&quot; <br /> AuthType Basic <br /> AuthUserFile / usr / local / nagios / etc / htpasswd.users <br /> Require valid-user <br /> &lt;/ Directory&gt; <br /> ScriptAlias / nagios / cgi-bin &quot;/ usr / local / nagios / sbin&quot; <br /><br /> &lt;Directory &quot;/usr/local/nagios/sbin&quot;&gt; <br /> # SSLRequireSSL <br /> Options ExecCGI <br /> AllowOverride None <br /> Order allow, deny <br /> Allow from all <br /> # Order deny, allow <br /> # Deny from all <br /> # Allow from 127.0.0.1 <br /> AuthName &quot;Nagios Access&quot; <br /> AuthType Basic <br /> AuthUserFile / usr / local / nagios / etc / htpasswd.users <br /> Require valid-user <br /> &lt;/ Directory&gt; <br /><br /> Alias / nagios &quot;/ usr / local / nagios / share&quot; <br /><br /> &lt;Directory &quot;/usr/local/nagios/share&quot;&gt; <br /> # SSLRequireSSL <br /> Options None <br /> AllowOverride None <br /> Order allow, deny <br /> Allow from all <br /> # Order deny, allow <br /> # Deny from all <br /> # Allow from 127.0.0.1 <br /> AuthName &quot;Nagios Access&quot; <br /> AuthType Basic <br /> AuthUserFile / usr / local / nagios / etc / htpasswd.users <br /> Require valid-user <br /> &lt;/ Directory&gt; <br /></p><p> Create a verification file apache directory </p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Htpasswd-c / usr / local / nagios / etc / htpasswd.users nagiosadmin <br /> New password: (Enter password) <br /> Re-type new password: (enter a password) <br /> Adding password for user nagiosadmin <br /><br /> # Service httpd restart <br /> # Htpasswd-c / usr / local / nagios / etc / htpasswd.users nagiosadmin <br /> New password: (Enter password) <br />'),(176,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0623/250.html','sendmail problem of slow start','2010-06-23','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> This is nothing new, the problem is the host name resolution, but see your / etc / hosts, still do not see why there will be problems parsing: <br /> 127.0.0.1 localhost localhost.localdomain <br /> 192.168.12.246 ixdba.net </p><p> Explain here, my host name is ixdba.net </p><p> In my / etc / mail / sendmail.cf in <br /> O DaemonPortOptions = Port = smtp, Addr = 127.0.0.1, Name = MTA </p><p> This address is 127.0.0.1, should be concerned with this, to read: <br /> 127.0.0.1 localhost localhost.localdomain <br /> 127.0.0.1 ixdba.net <br /> Still not work, it appears that the new line did not play a role in the following, try the following </p><p> 127.0.0.1 localhost localhost.localdomain ixdba.net </p><p> Try again, Oh, start the flash, the problem should be solved, in fact, read sendmail start / etc / hosts of the first line. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(177,'linux','en','/a/db/mysql/2010/0521/108.html','Growth of the primary key automatically in Mysql, SqlServer','2010-05-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> 1, the automatic growth of the primary key identifier type is defined as </p><p> <font color=\"#333399\">In mysql, if the table is set to <font color=\"#ff0000\">auto_increment</font> primary key type, the database will automatically assign the primary key.</font> For example: </p><p> create table customers (id int auto_increment primary key not null, name varchar (15)); </p><p> insert into customers (name) values (&quot;name1 &quot;),(&quot; name2&quot;); </p><p> select id from customers; </p><p> Sql statement to be created over the customers table, then insert two records in the inserted field, just set the value name. Finally, the field id lookup table, the query results: </p><p> id </p><p> 1 </p><p> 2 </p><p> Thus, once the type of id is set to auto_increment, mysql database by increments automatically assign the primary key. </p><p> <font color=\"#333399\">In the MS SQLServer, if the table\'s primary key is set to <font color=\"#ff0000\">identity</font> the type, the database will automatically assign the primary key.</font> For example: </p><p> create table customers (id int identity (1,1) primary key not null, name varchar (15)); </p><p> insert into customers (name) values (&quot;name1 &quot;),(&quot; name2&quot;); </p><p> select id from customers; </p><p> Mysql query results and the same. Thus, if the id is set to identity the type, MS SQLServer database automatically by increments as the primary key assignment. identity contains two parameters, the first argument that the initial value, said second parameter increments. </p><p> 2, obtained from the automatic growth of the sequence identifier </p><p> <font color=\"#333399\">In Oracle, for the primary key of each table to create a separate sequence, and then get automatic increases in the sequence identifier, assign it to the primary key.</font> For example, what statement creates a named customer_id_seq sequence, the sequence of the starting value is 1, in increments of 2. </p><p> create sequence customer_id_seq increment by 2 start with 1 </p><p> Once you have defined customer_id_seq sequence, you can access the sequence curval and nextval properties. </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\">curval: Returns the current value of sequence</font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\">nextval: first increase the value of the sequence, and then return the sequence value</font> </p><p> The following sql statement, first create the customers table, then insert two records in the insertion set the value of id and name fields, in which the value of the id field from the customer_id_seq sequence. Last queries customers table id field. </p><p> create table customers (id int primary key not null, name varchar (15)); </p><p> insert into customers values (customer_id_seq.curval, &quot;name1&quot;), (customer_id_seq.nextval, &quot;name2&quot;); </p><p> select id from customers; </p><p> If the above statement is executed in oracle, query results are: </p><p> id </p><p> 1 </p><p> 3 </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(178,'linux','en','/a/IT/2010/0924/788.html','Linus Torvalds says Linux kernel design is only designed for the fun of Linus Torvalds says Linux kernel','2010-09-24','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Linus Trovalds rarely appeared at the meeting, standing in front of the crowd is very little speech for him. However, he made an exception in Brazil in August, attended the <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\">Linux</a></u> Con General Assembly, at which he and Andrew Morton has joined the <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\">Linux</a></u> Foundation Jim Zemlin President of Q &amp; A session chaired. The conversation related to the kernel development process and development history, and many other topics.</span></span> </p><div style=\"text-align: center\"> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"314\" onclick=\"window.open(\'/uploads/allimg/100924/1_100924132211_1.png\')\" src=\"http://www.ixdba.net/uploads/allimg/100924/1_100924132211_1.png\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" width=\"484\" /></span></span> </div><p> <strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Question 1: Is it conceivable that such a large Linux development?</span></span></strong> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Jim opening to ask: do not know if Andrew had not thought about Linus and Linux developed to become so big? Linus\'s answer is no; He said he wrote the original Linux only as a short-term projects, and ready to use better the to be replaced. GNU project because it was also very good and BSD camp, he believes there will be other people to make more powerful and more professional to the core. At the same time, when he was just a little Linux as their love only. Zheshi witty Andrew added: &quot;However, final proof, no one do than Linux better. I, as one kernel newbie (modest argument, in fact in the field Andrew least 10 years), though not be term vision, but I personally think that Linux is indeed very alarming development. &quot;</span></span> </p><p> <strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Question 2: How do you cope with the rapid development of the kernel?</span></span></strong> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Jim then asked, How do you cope with the rapid development of the kernel? Andrew said, as the core of continuous improvement, the number of developers who continue to expand. The development of core responsibilities assigned to each person then, and now I just take the Linux Linus total project only a small part of the work. Quality assurance in the code the dealer has played a big role. Based on this, Andrew said that just now the kernel community to provide technical, but the dealers can get the kernel from the community, and then into actual products.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Linus on the Linux kernel that in general people are not interested in things. For example, he said he always felt that <span class=\"nounderline\">the server</span> market is a boring place, but was successfully applied to shift the Linux <span class=\"nounderline\">servers.</span> This is also one of the main advantages of Linux, Linus pointed out that no company would be interested in all uses of Linux, but their effect is often used for Linux, that he was amazed. He expressed some areas of Linux applications and even he did not expect. This also means that no one needs to use the Linux kernel users of the product while maintaining full responsibility for the negative. In particular, Linus, the real need is to care for myself, to ensure that all of the code fragment into together. After all, the power of a single kernel is limited, can not satisfy all application requirements, it can do is to constantly improve the core, allowed to meet the wider environment.</span></span> </p><p> <strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Question 3: Is it wise to continue to use the single-core? Single core can be applied to multi-task environment? Handle fragmentation, when this particular task is not to temporarily give up multi-core features?</span></span></strong> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">From this interview, Jim asked to split the kernel, as well as Linux continues to use the wisdom of a single core, while the single core is suitable for multi-tasking environment; future to support the development needs of different areas will separate out the different versions of the core issues .</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Linus that the single-core to work well, he is also very annoying to see Linux division. Present problems in many areas there is a commonality in fact, for example, when the field of Linux used in <span class=\"nounderline\">mobile phones,</span> then the system for <span class=\"nounderline\">power</span> management requires more points, but proved to <span class=\"nounderline\">servers, power</span> management is also very important. In general, users in different application areas of concern in fact the same thing, only concerned the timing is different. Only high-end <span class=\"nounderline\">server</span> applications, such as who will be concerned in the symmetric multiprocessing, and now is basically to buy a desktop computer does not support SMP, right, and now SMP is also used in <span class=\"nounderline\">mobile phones</span> in the. This is the single-core approach has the advantage: If the <span class=\"nounderline\">phone</span> user needs SMP support, Linux always waiting for you.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Andrew said that Linux is widely used mainly due to the unique technical properties of the kernel. Linux kernel is now very easy to work together. The current Linux kernel has been the efforts of everyone from the original &quot;small&quot; devices become more and more. Unfortunately, there are still many small embedded systems in the community is still not very good technical support, but the Linux community as a whole is very concerned about this part of the body, embedded in the future we will also give good technical support groups .</span></span> </p><p> <strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Question 4: Where is the kernel development workers, mainly from Brazil to the kernel developers to participate in the development come from?</span></span></strong> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Linus responded that, Linux kernel developers are mainly from North America, Europe and Australia. Because of cultural and language differences, increasing the difficulty of the entire community management. Linus said to run a global project, first of all need to solve the problem of language commonality, Linus is also fun to say: &quot;Unfortunately, instead of using the Finnish community (Linus is Finnish).&quot; Linus said that the world has a lot of good developers, But at the same time difficult to find good developers who are good at English. In order to solve regional and language and cultural differences, Linus said that they usually work is to establish a local community, and then connect these communities as a bridge to other communities and headquarters.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Andrew pointed out that obviously many people in Japan in recent years to participate in kernel development to; he recorded a lot of efforts on the Linux Foundation, the community members. He also found that people use Email for communication between non-native is helpful; because both sides have enough time to understand each other\'s meaning. As to where to start communication, Andrew opinion is to choose an interesting and challenging work begins.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Linus that open source software is programmed to understand the world situation in a good way. Unlike the class open source projects, the project requires an active exchange with the people together to solve the problem. Some companies in need of technical personnel, often in the open source community to find those activists. Therefore, to participate in open source projects, but also to the world a good way to promote their own. Finally, Linus said that it is difficult to find good programmers, they generally get good pay, they often work for open source software. Andrew also agreed with the firm belief that programmers are widely available light. The time at Google, Andrew often issued to him by a number of internal staff qualifications, to hire whom he chooses. He made the first move was to open the git log to see who has done what in the community activities.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Linus said that although the kernel may not be a good starting point to learn the best programmers. However, there are many kernel developers, people often think that the kernel is very mysterious, and even have a fear of psychological approach. The initial development of small projects for those who are a good starting environment.</span></span> </p><p> <strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Question 5: Will never work for Linux?</span></span></strong> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Linus replied, &quot;Never is a very long time,&quot; he initially only to the kernel as a two-month project, but he said they would continue to do the kernel, because now he felt fun. Because there will always be new problems to be solved and new hardware needs</span></span>'),(179,'linux','en','/a/lb/2010/0920/766.html','Original Series Introduction to Linux Cluster Technology Original Series Introduction to Linux Cluster Technology','2010-09-20','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><strong>A <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/lb/\">cluster</a></u> definition</strong> <br /> Cluster is a group work set of services, to provide more stable than a single service, more efficient, more scalable platform, the outside, the cluster is an independent service entity, but in fact, in the cluster Internally, there are two or more entities in the coordination of services, with the completion of a complex task. <br /> Clusters of two or more generally formed from a server, each server is called a cluster node, the cluster nodes can communicate with each other, communicate in two ways, one is based on the RS232 line heart rate monitor, Another is to use a separate card to run the heartbeat, therefore, the cluster service with the state monitoring function between the nodes, but also must have the extension service entities, the flexibility to add and remove a service entity. <br /> In the cluster, the same services can be provided by multiple service entities. Thus, when a node fails, another node in the cluster automatically take over the failed node\'s resources to ensure service lasting, uninterrupted operation. Thus the transfer function of the cluster with automatic fault. <br /> A cluster must have a shared data storage, because the services provided outside the cluster is the same, any one cluster node to run an application, the application of the data are centrally stored in the node shared space, each node of the operating system only running application services, application files stored. <br /> In summary, to build a cluster system requires at least two servers, but also need to have the serial line, cluster software, shared storage devices (such as disk arrays) and so on. <br /> Based <a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\"><u>Linux</u></a> cluster with its very high computing power, scalability, availability and more cost-effective optimization of a variety of applications in the enterprise to stand out. Become a concern for all <a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\"><u>Linux</u></a> applications hot, master knowledge of Linux clusters, low price can be used to make high-performance applications. To enterprises and individuals to save costs. Large domestic Sina, Netease, adopted high-performance linux cluster building web applications, using the famous search engine google linux servers on a million, a large cluster, the cluster of these instances shows the status of the application in linux and important sex. <br /> <strong>2 Characteristics and function of the cluster</strong> <br /> 2.1 High availability and scalability <br /> 1. High availability for some very strong real-time applications, must ensure that the service runs 24 hours a day, and as software, hardware, network, human and other reasons, a single service operating environment difficult to meet this requirement at this time build a cluster system is a good choice to build one of the greatest advantages of the cluster with high availability cluster, the service fails, the cluster system can automatically switch the service from the failed node to another backup node, to provide uninterrupted service, ensure the continued operation of the business. <br /> 2. Scalability with the increasing volume of business, the existing entity can not meet the needs of the cluster service, you can dynamically to the cluster, add one or more service nodes, to meet application needs, and enhance the overall performance of the cluster. This is the scalability of the cluster. <br /> 2.2 load balancing and error recovery <br /> 1. Load balancing cluster system is characterized by the greatest flexibility, and effective sharing of system load, defined by the cluster load sharing their own strategies, allocation of the client\'s access to the following each service node, for example, you can define polling allocation strategy, the average request allocation to each service node, you can also define the minimum load allocation strategy, when a request comes in, determine which service node cluster system are relatively free to distribute this request to this node. <br /> 2. Error recovery when a node in a task not yet complete, for some reason fails, time, and then another service node should be able to accomplish this task, which is the cluster to provide error recovery, through error redirection to ensure that each mission can be effectively completed. <br /> 2.3 IP heartbeat detection and drift <br /> One. Heart rate monitoring in order to achieve load balancing, providing high availability services and the implementation of error recovery, the cluster system provides the heartbeat monitoring, heart rate monitoring is achieved through the heartbeat, the heartbeat of the equipment can do a RS 232 serial line can also be used independently heartbeat to run a piece of card can also be a shared disk arrays, the number of heartbeat cluster nodes should be decreased by 1, note that if the heartbeat through the card to do so, each node has two network cards, of which a private network as the machine is connected directly to each other the appropriate card, to monitor each heartbeat. Also a connection to the outside public network to provide services, while heart rate card and IP card services, as not in a subnet address. Direct impact on the efficiency of the heart rate monitor the duration of failover, the cluster system is maintained through the heart technology and effective communication between nodes inside. <br /> 2. IP address of the cluster shift, in addition to each service node itself the real IP address, IP address there is a drift, drift IP Why is it, because the IP addresses are not fixed, for example, double the two nodes hot standby, the normal state, the drift of IP in the master node, when the primary node fails, the drift IP address automatically switches to the standby node, therefore, in order to ensure uninterrupted service in the cluster system, external provision of services IP must be to the drift IP address, although the IP node itself can also offer services, but when the node failure, the service switched to another node, but the service failed node IP is still IP address, this time, the service with the interrupt.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><strong>Category 3 Cluster <br /></strong> 3.1 High Availability Cluster <br /> 1. The concept of high availability in English stands for High Availability Cluster High Availability Cluster, referred to as HA Cluster, the maximum availability of the means available, from the name of the cluster can be seen, the function of these Clusters is to protect the user\'s application program lasting, uninterrupted service. <br /> When an application fails, or the system hardware, network failure, the application can automatically, quickly switching from one node to another node, thus ensuring the application of sustained, uninterrupted service outside, which is to achieve high-availability clustering functions <br /> 2. Common HA Cluster <br /> We often say that the hot standby, dual-prepared, multi-machine equipment and so on are each other\'s areas of high availability clusters, these clusters typically have two or more nodes. A typical hot standby structure shown in Figure 1:</span></span> </p><div style=\"text-align: center\"> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"182\" onclick=\"window.open(\'/uploads/allimg/100920/1_100920093219_1.png\')\" src=\"http://www.ixdba.net/uploads/allimg/100920/1_100920093219_1.png\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" width=\"384\" /><br /><br /> Figure 1 Structure of Hot Standby</span></span> </div><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Hot Standby mode is the simplest application, that is often said that the active / standby mode, it uses two servers, one as the master server (action), run the application outside service, the other as a standby machine (standby ), installation and application as the main server, but did not start the service, is in the standby state. Between the host and prepare machine technology with each other through the heartbeat monitoring, monitoring of the resources can be network, operating system, and also the service, the user can according to your needs, choose the resources need to be monitored, when monitoring and controlling equipment to host a resource failure, based on pre-configured strategy, first to switch over IP and application services will have to take over over and went on to provide services outside You prepare machines due to switching process time is very end user procedures do feel out issues, but also for the switching, in order to protect the application lasting, uninterrupted service. <br /> Dual Active in hot standby, based on two independent applications to run simultaneously on two machines, Internet-based equipment, which is prepared by two servers both host machine, when any one application fails, another server in a short time can be taken over the application of machine malfunction, in order to protect the service continued, uninterrupted operation. Dual Active advantage is saving equipment resources, the two hot standby application requires at least four servers, and Dual Active only two to complete high-availability server clustering capabilities, but also have Dual Active the shortcomings of its own: in a node failover, another node to run the two applications to the service, there may be the case load is too large. <br /> Preparation of multi-machine interaction is a hot standby of the technology upgrade, through a cluster composed of multiple machines can be set up between multiple machines over a flexible strategy, for example, a server cluster environment composed of 8, 3 runs web applications, 3 applications to run mail, therefore, the remaining one can be as prepared 3 sets of web server machines, 3 sets another mail server as a reserve unit, through such arrangements, adequate and reasonable use of the server resources, but also to ensure the system\'s high availability. <br /> To note are: high-availability cluster can not guarantee the security of application data, it is only lasting solution is to provide uninterrupted service of external, to the software, hardware, networking, human factors failures reduce the impact of the application to the lowest level. <br /> 3. High Availability Cluster high-availability cluster software is generally achieved through the high-availability software, commonly used in high availability under linux software: open source heartbea HA, Redhat provides RHCS, business software ROSE, keepalived and so on. In the following sections we will detail heartbea HA configuration and use. <br /> 3.2 Load Balancing Load balancing system, the English full name Load Balance Cluster, referred to as LB Cluster, the load balancing cluster also has two or more than two servers, divided into front end and back-end node services load scheduling of two parts, the load scheduling partially responsible for the client\'s request in accordance with the policies assigned to different back-end service node, and back-end nodes is the real part of providing application services. <br /> The difference is that with HA Cluster in the load balancing cluster, all the back-end nodes are active, they offer services, work load sharing system. <br /> Load balancing cluster can be applied to a high load across multiple nodes to jointly complete for the busy business, access to a large load applications, but it also has deficiencies: When a node fails, the front-end dispatch system does not that this node can no longer provide services, will continue to dispatch client requests to the failed node up, so that access will fail, in order to solve this problem, the load scheduling system into a node generally monitoring system. <br /> Node is located in front of the load dispatch control system aircraft, responsible for monitoring the following service node, when a node fails, the node monitoring system</span></span>'),(180,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0719/327.html','Red Hat Linux6 Beta 2 new tests to look forward to! Red Hat Linux6 Beta 2 new test, the value','2010-07-19','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p style=\"text-align: left\"> Back in April, following the Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6.0 version of the first test, the first time with CentOS 5. 4 and Fedora 12.0 test comparison. RedHat is published in the July 1 edition of its Enterprise Linux 6 of the second Beta version, modified in this version from a large number of Beta 1, including the installation manager, after adjustment, and add a new package. Enterprise Linux 6 blurred virtual, physical, and the boundaries between cloud computing to adapt to contemporary changes occurring in IT environments. After these changes, the new version of the Linux system performance, how, where and Ubuntu, CentOS, and test the latest version of openSUSE its comparison can gain comparison. <br /><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" onclick=\"if(!this.resized) {return true;} else {window.open(\'/uploads/allimg/100719/0S604H93-0.jpg\');}\" onload=\"if(this.width>screen.width*0.7) {this.resized=true; this.width=screen.width*0.7; this.alt=\'Click here to open new window\\nCTRL+Mouse wheel to zoom in/out\';}\" onmouseover=\"if(this.width>screen.width*0.7) {this.resized=true; this.width=screen.width*0.7; this.style.cursor=\'hand\'; this.alt=\'Click here to open new window\\nCTRL+Mouse wheel to zoom in/out\';}\" onmousewheel=\"return imgzoom(this);\" src=\"/uploads/allimg/100719/0S604H93-0.jpg\" /><br /><br /> View: Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Beta 2 Release Notes <br /> <b>Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Beta</b> <br /> For this RHEL 6.0 Beta 2, was tested in the repair of the Beta 1 pm and Bug and updated the Anaconda installer and many packages. This version uses the 2.6.32-37.el6 kernel, Gnome 2.28.2 Desktop, X. Org Server 1.7.7, Mesa 7.7.1, GCC 4.4.4, the default file system used EXT4. <br /> For comparison of this test Ubuntu, CentOS, OpenSUSE is the latest release versions Ubuntu 10.04, the latest version of CentOS 5.5 and OpenSUSE 11.3 RC2, all those involved in the test are 64-bit Linux distributions. <br /> Depending on the application environment, test tools are Phoronix Test Suite, including Apache, PostMark, LZMA compression, CompileBench, TTSIOD 3D rendering, C-Ray ,7-Zip compression, FFmpeg, John The Ripper, NAS parallel test and Loopback TCP network performance testing, Test System Platform with Intel Core processor i7 920, clocked at 3.60GHz, 8 logical core, the motherboard is SuperComputer the ASRock 58, RAM 3GB, 320GB Seagate ST3320620AS, Nvidia GeForce 9800GTX graphics cards, directly through various benchmark tests to compare the first Second, the performance version of Linux 6. <br /><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" onclick=\"if(!this.resized) {return true;} else {window.open(\'/uploads/allimg/100719/0S6041204-1.jpg\');}\" onload=\"if(this.width>screen.width*0.7) {this.resized=true; this.width=screen.width*0.7; this.alt=\'Click here to open new window\\nCTRL+Mouse wheel to zoom in/out\';}\" onmouseover=\"if(this.width>screen.width*0.7) {this.resized=true; this.width=screen.width*0.7; this.style.cursor=\'hand\'; this.alt=\'Click here to open new window\\nCTRL+Mouse wheel to zoom in/out\';}\" onmousewheel=\"return imgzoom(this);\" src=\"/uploads/allimg/100719/0S6041204-1.jpg\" /><br /> Apache test results <br /><br /> The first is to begin testing by the Apache, the results can be seen from the test data, leading the CentOS 5.5, the transaction per second than the RHEL 6.0 Beta 2 leading nearly 70%. The Ubuntu 10.04 LTS also good performance. In this test RHEL 6.0 Beta 2 a little behind compared to OpenSUSE 11.3 RC2, CentOS leading reason may be that it defaults to using the EXT3 file system on the other three have used EXT4 file system. <br /><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" onclick=\"if(!this.resized) {return true;} else {window.open(\'/uploads/allimg/100719/0S604B26-2.jpg\');}\" onload=\"if(this.width>screen.width*0.7) {this.resized=true; this.width=screen.width*0.7; this.alt=\'Click here to open new window\\nCTRL+Mouse wheel to zoom in/out\';}\" onmouseover=\"if(this.width>screen.width*0.7) {this.resized=true; this.width=screen.width*0.7; this.style.cursor=\'hand\'; this.alt=\'Click here to open new window\\nCTRL+Mouse wheel to zoom in/out\';}\" onmousewheel=\"return imgzoom(this);\" src=\"/uploads/allimg/100719/0S604B26-2.jpg\" /><br /> PostMark disk test results but PostMark disk test, CentOS system because it is using EXT3 file system data is not as EXT4 file system using the operating system. OpenSUSE 11.3 has obvious advantages in the test, RHEL 6.0 Beta 2 Despite the use of EXT4 file system, but the results are not satisfactory. <br /><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" onclick=\"if(!this.resized) {return true;} else {window.open(\'/uploads/allimg/100719/0S60443b-3.jpg\');}\" onload=\"if(this.width>screen.width*0.7) {this.resized=true; this.width=screen.width*0.7; this.alt=\'Click here to open new window\\nCTRL+Mouse wheel to zoom in/out\';}\" onmouseover=\"if(this.width>screen.width*0.7) {this.resized=true; this.width=screen.width*0.7; this.style.cursor=\'hand\'; this.alt=\'Click here to open new window\\nCTRL+Mouse wheel to zoom in/out\';}\" onmousewheel=\"return imgzoom(this);\" src=\"/uploads/allimg/100719/0S60443b-3.jpg\" /><br /> LZMA compression test results even though the three test before the performance is not very good, but the RHEL 6.0 Beta 2 was in the LZMA compression test has advantages, LZMA compression test using a 256MB size file, RHEL 6.0 Beta 2 of the compression speed was faster than OpenSUSE , Ubuntu and CentOS, the compression time of the three systems are roughly equal. <br /><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" onclick=\"if(!this.resized) {return true;} else {window.open(\'/uploads/allimg/100719/0S604EI-4.jpg\');}\" onload=\"if(this.width>screen.width*0.7) {this.resized=true; this.width=screen.width*0.7; this.alt=\'Click here to open new window\\nCTRL+Mouse wheel to zoom in/out\';}\" onmouseover=\"if(this.width>screen.width*0.7) {this.resized=true; this.width=screen.width*0.7; this.style.cursor=\'hand\'; this.alt=\'Click here to open new window\\nCTRL+Mouse wheel to zoom in/out\';}\" onmousewheel=\"return imgzoom(this);\" src=\"/uploads/allimg/100719/0S604EI-4.jpg\" /><br /> Compile Bench test results, but in the test'),(181,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0711/317.html','Beautification of the nine aspects of landscaping from nine aspects Ubuntu Desktop Ubuntu Desktop','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p style=\"text-align: center\"> <span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"148\" onclick=\"window.open(\'/uploads/allimg/100711/1_100711185830_1.jpg\')\" src=\"http://www.ixdba.net/uploads/allimg/100711/1_100711185830_