der=\"0\" height=\"129\" onclick=\"window.open(\'/uploads/allimg/100422/1_100422144825_1.jpg\')\" src=\"http://www.ixdba.net/uploads/allimg/100422/1_100422144825_1.jpg\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" width=\"268\" /></div><p> <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/web/tomcat/\">Tomcat</a></u> 5.5 is an older version, just released 5.5.29 version mainly fixes some serious bug, but also to upgrade a number of Java class libraries, such as commons-pool and so on. </p><p> Although this version there are many functional improvements, but it is recommended that users upgrade to version 6.0, 6.0, 26 has released the first version, and now is very stable and has a good performance. </p><p> Details on the Tomcat 5.5.29 version of the improved content see <a href=\"http://tomcat.apache.org/tomcat-5.5-doc/changelog.html\" target=\"_blank\">ChangeLog</a> . </p><p> <a href=\"http://tomcat.apache.org/download-55.cgi\" target=\"_blank\">Download Tomcat5.5.29</a> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(183,'linux','en','/a/IT/2010/0422/54.html','Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 announced support for Itanium, Red Hat will no longer be declared no longer Enterprise Linux 6','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p></p><div style=\"text-align: center\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"350\" onclick=\"window.open(\'/uploads/allimg/100422/1_100422144350_1.jpg\')\" src=\"http://www.ixdba.net/uploads/allimg/100422/1_100422144350_1.jpg\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" width=\"318\" /><br /></div><p> <strong>Red Hat said in a statement Sunday that its next major release of Linux operating system, version of &quot;Enterprise Linux 6&quot; will give up on Intel Itanium processors.</strong> </p><p> According to market research firm IDC research manager for European systems division, said Chris Ingle, to abandon support for Red Hat Itanium processors have economic interests. Itanium processor-based server sales may not be too much, not enough to invest in Red Hat to prove that it supports Itanium processors for Enterprise Linux operating system is reasonable. On the contrary, it will focus on support for x86 servers. </p><p> Currently, Red Hat\'s &quot;Enterprise Linux 5&quot; support the IBM Power processor-based servers, System z servers and S/390 processor architecture. <br /><br /> Ingle, IDC said, for users, Red Hat to abandon support for Itanium is not much difference, because most vendors have received from the OEM manufacturers technical support. <br /><br /> Red Hat in March 2014 before the still running on the Itanium server &quot;Enterprise Linux 5&quot; for technical support. Red Hat will run on Itanium server &quot;Enterprise Linux 5&quot; to add new features and product life cycle in accordance with its standard policy of support for new hardware. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(184,'linux','en','/a/IT/2010/0422/53.html','Red Hat Enterprise Linux (RHEL) 6 beta today released Red Hat Enterprise Linux (RHEL) 6 beta','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><div style=\"text-align: center\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"180\" onclick=\"window.open(\'/uploads/allimg/100422/1_100422143041_1.png\')\" src=\"http://www.ixdba.net/uploads/allimg/100422/1_100422143041_1_lit.png\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" width=\"555\" /><br /><br /> <span>Red Hat has just released Enterprise Linux RHEL 6.0 in the Beta version, the version of the most noteworthy improvements include:</span> </div><ul><li> <span>Comprehensive power management features</span> </li><li> <span>Performance</span> </li><li> <span>Enhanced Scalability</span> </li><li> <span>The new security features</span> </li><li> <span>Virtualization</span> </li><li> <span>Storage improvements, support the FCoE and iSCSI support network block device</span> </li><li> <span>EXT4 file system support</span> </li><li> <span>Reliability, availability, and applicability</span> </li><li> <span>Enhanced Compilation Tools - GCC 4.4</span> </li><li> <span>Improved desktop, support for multiple virtual desktops</span> </li></ul><p> The following address to download the Beta version: </p><p> <a href=\"http://www.redhat.com/rhel/beta/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.redhat.com/rhel/beta/</a> </p><p> <a href=\"http://ftp.redhat.com/redhat/rhel/beta/6/i386/iso/RHEL6.0-20100414.0-AP-i386-DVD1.iso\">RHEL6.0-AP-i386-DVD1.iso</a> (3,650 MB, <a href=\"http://ftp.redhat.com/redhat/rhel/beta/6/i386/iso/SHA256SUM\">SHA256</a> ) <br /> <a href=\"http://ftp.redhat.com/redhat/rhel/beta/6/x86_64/iso/RHEL6.0-AP-x86_64-DVD1.iso\">RHEL6.0-20,100,414.0-AP-x86_64-DVD1.iso</a> (4,105 MB, <a href=\"http://ftp.redhat.com/redhat/rhel/beta/6/x86_64/iso/SHA256SUM\">SHA256</a> ). </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(185,'linux','en','/a/os/Solris/2010/0422/31.html','inode linux file system linux file system related concepts of the relevant concepts in the inode','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <strong>One. inode size defined</strong> &lt;br /&gt; unit: Byte <br /></p><div style=\"text-align: center\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"314\" onclick=\"window.open(\'/uploads/allimg/100422/1_100422112131_1.gif\')\" src=\"http://www.ixdba.net/uploads/allimg/100422/1_100422112131_1.gif\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" width=\"438\" /><br /></div><p></p><p> inode table is the data area of the index table. </p><p> Inode inode into memory and file <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/\">system</a></u> in the inode, we have said here is the file <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/\">system</a></u> in the inode. </p><p> <strong>1.</strong> Linux FS inode table can be simply divided into two parts with the data area. inode table has many of the inode, inode were recorded for each attribute of a file distributed with this file which datablock on (that is, we say that the pointer.) <br /> inode two functions: the log file attributes and pointers </p><p> <strong>2.</strong> Inode table in the red area that inode size, is 128Byte, in liunx system through the command we can see, the system is so defined. <br /> Inode size is assigned to an inode to record the document properties of the disk block size. </p><pre> <code>dumpe2fs -h /dev/hda6 | grep node <br /> Inode size:128</code>\r\n<code>dumpe2fs -h /dev/hda6 | grep node <br /> Inode size:128</code> </pre><p> <strong>3.</strong> Data ares in the purple zone block size, is our general concept of disk blocks. This area is where we used to store data. </p><p> <strong>4.</strong> There is also a logical concept: FS 2048 byte assigned to each data area, to assign an inode. But one does not necessarily spent on inode 2048 byte, does not mean that files allocation of a minimum of 2048 byte, it simply represents the filesystem in inode table / data area allocated space ratio is 128/2048, which is 1 / 16 . </p><p> <strong>mkfs.ext3-i 2048</strong> of this command-i parameter is what we call the logic of the concept, and its size determines the size of inode count, redhat5 default-i minimum can be set to 1024. </p><p> Many online articles introduced on the inode, the inode size of the definition of a mistake, they put-i parameter or the value of the inode size block size read as many articles so confusing. </p><p> <strong>5.</strong> Inode <strong>mkfs.ext3</strong> command parameters can be changed: </p><pre>\r\n<code>mkfs.ext3 -i 2048 -b 8192 -f 1024 /dev/sdb2</code> </pre><p> <strong>-I 2048</strong> inode for every change creates a 2KB <br /> <strong>-B 8192</strong> to set the size of 8kB block size <br /> <strong>-F 1024</strong> to set the size of fragments 1KB </p><pre>\r\n<code>mkfs.ext3 Ã¢Â€Â“N 2939495Ã‚Â  /dev/sdb2</code> </pre><p> <strong><br /> -N 2939495</strong> change inode count. </p><p> <strong>II. Inode change a partition\'s complete operation parameters:</strong> </p><p> <strong>1.</strong> Uninstall hard disk partition: </p><pre>\r\n<code>[root@localhost ~]# umount /dev/hda7</code> </pre><p> <strong>2.</strong> Inode parameter adjustment </p><pre> <code>[root@localhost ~]# mkfs.ext3 -i 1024 -b 8192 /dev/hda7 <br /> <br /> mke2fs 1.39 (29-May-2006) <br /> Filesystem label= <br /> OS type: Linux <br /> Block size=4096 (log=2) <br /> Fragment size=4096 (log=2) <br /> 2048256 inodes, 512064 blocks <br /> 25603 blocks (5.00%) reserved for the super user <br /> First data block=0 <br /> Maximum filesystem blocks=525250560 <br /> 63 block groups <br /> 8240 blocks per group, 8240 fragments per group <br /> 32512 inodes per group <br /> Superblock backups stored on blocks: <br />Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â 8240, 24720, 41200, 57680, 74160, 206000, 222480, 403760 <br /> <br /> Writing inode tables: done <br /> Creating journal (8192 blocks): done <br /> Writing superblocks and filesystem accounting information: done <br /> <br /> This filesystem will be automatically checked every 30 mounts or <br /> 180 days, whichever comes first.Ã‚Â  Use tune2fs -c or -i to override.</code>\r\n<code>[root@localhost ~]# mkfs.ext3 -i 1024 -b 8192 /dev/hda7 <br /> <br /> mke2fs 1.39 (29-May-2006) <br /> Filesystem label= <br /> OS type: Linux <br /> Block size=4096 (log=2) <br /> Fragment size=4096 (log=2) <br /> 2048256 inodes, 512064 blocks <br /> 25603 blocks (5.00%) reserved for the super user <br /> First data block=0 <br /> Maximum filesystem blocks=525250560 <br /> 63 block groups <br /> 8240 blocks per group, 8240 fragments per group <br /> 32512 inodes per group <br /> Superblock backups stored on blocks: <br />Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â 8240, 24720, 41200, 57680, 74160, 206000, 222480, 403760 <br /> <br /> Writing inode tables: done <br /> Creating journal (8192 blocks): done <br /> Writing superblocks and filesystem accounting information: done <br /> <br /> This filesystem will be automatically checked every 30 mounts or <br /> 180 days, whichever comes first.Ã‚Â  Use tune2fs -c or -i to override.</code> </pre><p> 3. To modify / etc / fstab <br /> Before the amendment </p><pre> <code>[root@localhost ~]# vi /etc/fstab <br /> <br /> LABEL=/Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â /Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  ext3Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  1 1 <br /> LABEL=/boot /bootÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  ext3Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  1 2 <br /> devptsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â /dev/ptsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â devptsÃ‚Â  gid=5,mode=620Ã‚Â  0 0 <br /> tmpfsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  /dev/shmÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â tmpfsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â defaultsÃ‚Â  0 0 <br /> LABEL=/optÃ‚Â  /optÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  ext3Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  1 2 <br /> procÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â /procÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â procÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  0 0 <br /> sysfsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  /sysÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  sysfsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  0 0 <br /> LABEL=/usrÃ‚Â  /usrÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  ext3Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  1 2 <br /> LABEL=/varÃ‚Â  /varÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  ext3Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  1 2 <br /> LABEL=SWAP-hda8Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â swapÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â swapÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  0 0 <br /> ~</code>\r\n<code>[root@localhost ~]# vi /etc/fstab <br /> <br /> LABEL=/Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â /Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  ext3Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  1 1 <br /> LABEL=/boot /bootÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  ext3Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  1 2 <br /> devptsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â /dev/ptsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â devptsÃ‚Â  gid=5,mode=620Ã‚Â  0 0 <br /> tmpfsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  /dev/shmÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â tmpfsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â defaultsÃ‚Â  0 0 <br /> LABEL=/optÃ‚Â  /optÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  ext3Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  1 2 <br /> procÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â /procÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â procÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  0 0 <br /> sysfsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  /sysÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  sysfsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  0 0 <br /> LABEL=/usrÃ‚Â  /usrÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  ext3Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  1 2 <br /> LABEL=/varÃ‚Â  /varÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  ext3Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  1 2 <br /> LABEL=SWAP-hda8Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â swapÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â swapÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  0 0 <br /> ~</code> </pre><p> Modified: </p><pre> <code>[root@localhost ~]# vi /etc/fstab <br /> <br /> LABEL=/Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  /Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â ext3Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  1 1 <br /> LABEL=/boot /boot ext3Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â 1 2 <br /> devptsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â /dev/ptsÃ‚Â  devptsÃ‚Â  gid=5,mode=620Ã‚Â  0 0 <br /> tmpfsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â /dev/shm tmpfsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  0 0 <br /> /dev/hda7 /optÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â ext3Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â 1 2 <br /> procÃ‚Â  /procÃ‚Â  procÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â 0 0 <br /> sysfsÃ‚Â  /sysÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â sysfsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â defaultsÃ‚Â  0 0 <br /> LABEL=/usrÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â /usrÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  ext3Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  1 2 <br /> LABEL=/varÃ‚Â  /varÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â ext3Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  1 2 <br /> LABEL=SWAP-hda8Ã‚Â  swapÃ‚Â  swapÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â defaultsÃ‚Â  0 0</code>\r\n<code>[root@localhost ~]# vi /etc/fstab <br /> <br /> LABEL=/Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  /Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â ext3Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  1 1 <br /> LABEL=/boot /boot ext3Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â 1 2 <br /> devptsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â /dev/ptsÃ‚Â  devptsÃ‚Â  gid=5,mode=620Ã‚Â  0 0 <br /> tmpfsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â /dev/shm tmpfsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  0 0 <br /> /dev/hda7 /optÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â ext3Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â 1 2 <br /> procÃ‚Â  /procÃ‚Â  procÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â 0 0 <br /> sysfsÃ‚Â  /sysÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â sysfsÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â defaultsÃ‚Â  0 0 <br /> LABEL=/usrÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â /usrÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  ext3Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  1 2 <br /> LABEL=/varÃ‚Â  /varÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â ext3Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  defaultsÃ‚Â  1 2 <br /> LABEL=SWAP-hda8Ã‚Â  swapÃ‚Â  swapÃ‚Â  Ã‚Â defaultsÃ‚Â  0 0</code> </pre><p> 4. Mount the partition </p><pre>\r\n<code>mount -a</code> </pre><p> 5. Is complete, the parameter-i minimum is 1024, this value determines the size of inode count size, the correspondence between them is: </p><blockquote><p> i = 2048 Inode count: 1025024 <br /> i = 1024 Inode count: 2048256 </p></blockquote><p> inode size of the value is not changed, it can prove that I defined above inode size. <br /> Let us define more clearly the relationship between these. <br /> Inode size <br /> Block size <br /> Inode conut </p><pre> <code>[root@localhost ~]# dumpe2fs -h /dev/hda7 <br /> dumpe2fs 1.39 (29-May-2006) <br /> Filesystem volume name:Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â &lt;none&gt; <br /> Last mounted on:Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  Ã‚Â  &lt;not available&gt; <br /> Filesyst</code>'),(186,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/1011/795.html','DRDB installation configuration and use (second edition)','2010-10-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><strong>Schematic diagram of a DRBD implementation</strong> <br type=\"_moz\" /></span></span> </p><div style=\"text-align: center;\"> <span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"432\" onclick=\"window.open(\'/uploads/allimg/101011/1_101011092253_1.png\')\" src=\"/uploads/allimg/101011/1_101011092253_1.png\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\" width=\"591\" /><br type=\"_moz\" /></span></span> </div><div style=\"text-align: left;\"> <span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><strong>Installation of two DRDB</strong> <br /> Download the source package from the official website to compile the source or use yum to install, an example here to CentOS installation process, similar to other systems. <br /> [Root @ drbd1 ~] # uname-a <br /> Linux drbd1 2.6.18-194.11.1.el5 # 1 SMP Tue Aug 10 19:09:06 EDT 2010 i686 i686 i386 GNU / Linux <br /> Yum install DRBD service through: <br /> [Root @ drbd1 ~] # yum-y install kmod-drbd83 drbd83 <br /> Check DRBD is installed successfully: <br /> [Root @ drbd1 ~] # lsmod | grep-i drbd <br /> drbd 228528 3 <br /> [Root @ drbd1 ~] # modprobe-l | grep-i drbd <br /> / Lib/modules/2.6.18-194.11.1.el5/weak-updates/drbd83/drbd.ko <br /> After a successful installation / sbin directory below drbdadm, drbdmeta, drbdsetup command, and / etc / init.d / drbd start script. <br /> <strong>Three configurations DRDB</strong> <br /> DRBD is running needs to read / etc / drbd.conf configuration file, the following are the two host node configuration file drbd.conf simple example: <br /> [Root @ drbd1 ~] # cat / etc / drbd.conf <br /> # <br /> # Drbd.conf <br /> # <br /> # Create by jackbillow@gmail.com at 2010-08-12 <br /> global { <br /> # Minor-count 64; <br /> # Dialog-refresh 5; # 5 seconds <br /> # Disable-ip-verification; <br /> usage-count no; <br /> # Whether to participate in DRBD user statistics, default yes <br /> } <br /><br /> common { <br /> syncer {rate 200M;} <br /> # Set the standby node, the maximum rate of network synchronization, in bytes. <br /> } <br /><br /> resource r0 { <br /> # Resource name is r0. <br /> protocol C; <br /> # Use a third drbd synchronization protocol that received written confirmation of the remote host is considered to be written to complete. <br /> handlers { <br /> pri-on-incon-degr &quot;echo o&gt; / proc / sysrq-trigger; halt-f&quot;; <br /> pri-lost-after-sb &quot;echo o&gt; / proc / sysrq-trigger; halt-f&quot;; <br /> local-io-error &quot;echo o&gt; / proc / sysrq-trigger; halt-f&quot;; <br /> fence-peer &quot;/ usr/lib64/heartbeat/drbd-peer-outdater-t 5&quot;; <br /> pri-lost &quot;echo pri-lost. Have a look at the log files. | mail-s \'DRBD Alert\' root&quot;; <br /> split-brain &quot;/ usr / lib / drbd / notify-split-brain.sh root&quot;; <br /> out-of-sync &quot;/ usr / lib / drbd / notify-out-of-sync.sh root&quot;; <br /> } <br /><br /> net { <br /> # Timeout 60; <br /> # Connect-int 10; <br /> # Ping-int 10; <br /> # Max-buffers 2048; <br /> # Max-epoch-size 2048; <br /> cram-hmac-alg &quot;sha1&quot;; <br /> shared-secret &quot;MySQL-HA&quot;; <br /> # DRBD synchronization using authentication and password information. <br /> } <br /><br /> disk { <br /> on-io-error detach; <br /> fencing resource-only; <br /> # Use dpod function (drbd outdate-peer daemon) to ensure that the data does not sync to switch. <br /> } <br /><br /> startup { <br /> wfc-timeout 120; <br /> degr-wfc-timeout 120; <br /> } <br /><br /> device / dev/drbd0; <br /><br /> on dbm157 { <br /> # On each host to begin with a description, followed by hostname (uname-n), {} in the following configuration for this host. <br /> disk / dev/sda2; <br /> # / Dev/drbd0 of disk partition is / dev/sda2. <br /> address 192.168.0.157:7788; <br /> # Set the DRBD listener port for communication with another host. <br /> meta-disk internal; <br /> } <br /> on dbm158 { <br /> disk / dev/sda2; <br /> # / Dev/drbd0 of disk partition is / dev/sda2. <br /> address 192.168.0.158:7788; <br /> # Set the DRBD listener port for communication with another host. <br /> meta-disk internal; # drbd meta data storage methods. <br /> } <br /><br /> } <br /> The above files are copied to the drbd.conf two hosts / etc directory. drbd.conf many configuration parameters, are interested can use the command: man drbd.conf to see more of the parameter. <br /> <strong>Four start DRBD</strong></span></span> </div><div style=\"text-align: left;\"> <span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><br /> 1 implementation of the two nodes before starting the DRBD, you need two hosts hdb1 at partition, create records for the DRBD data blocks of information. Were performed on two hosts: <br /> [Root @ drbd1 ~] # drbdadm create-md r0 or perform drbdadm create-md all <br /> [Root @ drbd2 ~] # drbdadm create-md r0 <br /> 2 to start the service on both nodes <br /> [Root @ drbd1 ~] # / etc / init.d / drbd start <br /> [Root @ drbd2 ~] # / etc / init.d / drbd start <br /> Best to start at the same time <br /> 3 node status at any node view <br /> [Root @ drbd1 ~] # cat / proc / drbd <br /> 1: cs: Connected ro: Secondary / Secondary ds: Inconsistent / Inconsistent C r ---- <br /> ns: 0 nr: 0 dw: 0 dr: 0 al: 0 bm: 0 lo: 0 pe: 0 ua: 0 ap: 0 ep: 1 wo: b oos: 2007644 <br /> Explain the meaning of the output is as follows: <br /> ro said the role of information, when you first start drbd, the two default drbd nodes are in Secondary state <br /> ds is the disk state information, &quot;Inconsistent / Inconsisten&quot;, is &quot;consistent / inconsistent&quot; state, said the two nodes of the disk data in an inconsistent state. <br /> Ns said packets of information sent over the network. <br /> Dw is the disk write information <br /> Dr is the disk read information <br /> 4 Set the master node</span></span>'),(187,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0908/664.html','Using rsync remote disaster recovery data','2010-09-08','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">rsync is a Linux system image backup of the data tool, rsync can backup local system data over the network to any remote host, rsync has the following characteristics:</span></span> </p><ul><li> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Can save the entire directory tree mirroring and file systems</span></span> </li><li> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Can be incremental synchronization data, file transfer, high efficiency, and thus synchronization time is very short.</span></span> </li><li> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Can keep the original file permissions, time and other attributes.</span></span> </li><li> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Encrypted data transmission to ensure data security.</span></span> </li></ul><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Then we introduced an example to use rsync under, here we assume that A, B two Linux systems, A system running the business, B system as A, a remote disaster recovery machine, then the A system is rsync the service side, B system is the rsync client. Need A, B rsync installed on both systems software, so that at A rsync daemon running on the system, while the B system daemon through the system crontab to regularly back up data A system specified. In order to achieve the remote disaster recovery of data. <br /> Our installation environment: <br /> Operating System: Red Hat Enterprise Linux Server release 5 <br /> Kernel version: Linux web 2.6.18-8.el5 <br /> A System IP Address: 192.168.60.253 <br /> B system IP address: 192.168.60.231 <br /> (1) A, B rsync installed on both systems <br /> rysnc home page address is: http://rsync.samba.org/, we are here to download the version for rsync-3.0.4, compile and then install: <br /> [Root @ web ~] # tar zxvf rsync-3.0.4.tar.gz <br /> [Root @ web ~] # cd rsync-3.0.4 <br /> [Root @ web rsync-3.0.4] #. / Configure <br /> [Root @ web rsync-3.0.4] # make <br /> [Root @ web rsync-3.0.4] # make install <br /> This completes the installation of rsync. <br /> (2) A system configured rsync <br /> rsync configuration file is / etc / rsyncd.conf, the rsync installed, the default is not this document, we can manually create a. rsyncd.conf file is composed of one or more modular structure. The document module parameters are global parameters and the composition of the definition of a module from the module name in square brackets in the beginning, until the next module definition. Configuration completed as follows: <br /> uid = nobody <br /> gid = nobody <br /> use chroot = no <br /> max connections = 10 <br /> pid file = / var / run / rsyncd.pid <br /> lock file = / var / run / rsync.lock <br /> log file = / var / log / rsyncd.log</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">[Ixdba] <br /> path = / webdata <br /> comment = ixdba file <br /> ignore errors <br /> read only = true <br /> list = false <br /> uid = root <br /> gid = root <br /> auth users = backup <br /> secrets file = / etc / server.pass <br /> The meaning of each option explained above, are as follows: <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ uid This option specifies the file transfer when the module should have a daemon user ID, default is &quot;nobody&quot;. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ gid This option specifies the module to transfer files when the daemon when the user group should have ID. The default is &quot;nobody&quot;. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ max connections This option specifies the maximum number of concurrent connections the module to protect the server, connection requests exceeds the limit will be temporarily restricted. The default value is 0, which is no limit. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ pid file this option is used to specify the corresponding rsync daemon PID file path. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ lock file this option specifies the lock file support for max connections, the default is / var / run / rsyncd.lock. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ log file This option specifies the rsync log output file path. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ [ixdba] that defines the start of a module, ixdba is the corresponding module name. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ path This option is used to specify files or directories to be backed up, required, where the specified directory is / webdata. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ list this option is set when the client requests the list of modules that can be used, the module is listed. The default value is true, if the need to create hidden modules. Can be set to false. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ auth users can connect this option is used to define the user name of the module, multiple users separated by spaces or commas. Note that here the system users and Linux users do not have any relationship. This user is specified backup. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ secrets file This option specifies that contains &quot;username: password&quot; format, the user name is &quot;auth users&quot; option to define the user, the password can easily specify, as long as the client\'s secrets file correspond to the line. Is defined only in the auth users, the file did work. The default without this document, one can manually create their own. <br /> (3) A system startup execute the following command rsync daemon rsync daemon started: <br /> [Root @ web ~] # / usr / local / bin / rsync - daemon <br /> [Root @ localhost /] # ps-ef | grep rsync <br /> root 20278 1 0 16:29? 00:00:00 / usr / local / bin / rsync - daemon <br /> (4) in the B system configuration rsync <br /> The backup machine without any settings, simply run rsync to synchronize operations, in order to synchronize the process, do not enter a password, you need to create a B system secrets file, the contents of this file system rsyncd.conf file for the A &quot; auth users &quot;option specifies the user\'s password, and the file name and path can be arbitrarily specified, as long as specified in the implementation of rsync to synchronize the time. <br /> The next synchronization operation, see the following instructions: <br /> [Root @ web ~] # / usr / local / bin / rsync-vzrtopg - delete - progress backup@192.168.60.253:: ixdba / ixdba.net - password-file = / etc / server.pass <br /> This instruction in the meaning of each parameter are described below: <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ &quot;- vzrtopg&quot; option v is the &quot;-verbose&quot;, the detailed model output, z said &quot;- compress&quot; the backup file that is compressed during transmission, r said &quot;- recursive&quot;, that is, the recursive processing of subdirectories. t the &quot;- times&quot;, used to keep the file time information, o the &quot;- owner&quot; to keep the file owner information. p is &quot;- perms&quot; is used to keep file permissions, g the &quot;- group&quot; is used to keep the file group information. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ &quot;- delete&quot; option specifies the rsync server as a benchmark for synchronous data mirroring, which is to maintain the rsync server directory and the client directory is fully consistent. A server is also here as a benchmark for synchronization. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ &quot;- progress&quot; option is used to display data mirroring synchronization process. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ &quot;backup@192.168.60.253:: ixdba&quot; said the ixdba server 192.168.60.253 backup module, which is the designated backup module, backup that the use of &quot;backup&quot; to back up the users of the module. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ &quot;/ ixdba.net&quot; is used to specify the backup file on the client machine store path, that is, the backup files stored on the backup machine / ixdba.net directory. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ &quot;- password-file = / etc / server.pass&quot; is used to specify the password stored on the client file location, so that the client synchronization command to interact without having to enter the password, and note that the password file name and location can specify, but must exist on the client file, the file contents only for the backup user\'s password, in this case is the backup password. <br /> In fact, rsync as a client tool, providing a lot of options and parameters used here only gives us part of the implementation of more detailed information, please &quot;man rsync&quot; view. <br /> If the configuration is not an error, then rsync will automatically</span></span>'),(188,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0908/663.html','Original Series Linux System Backup Strategies','2010-09-08','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><strong>Why should back up a <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\">Linux</a> <a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/\">system</a></u></strong> <br /> An application in Linux system, due to internal environmental impact, the impact of the underlying hardware, external hackers, problems are inevitable, as a system of management, their role is not to ensure that the system never a problem, in fact, is impossible, but in the system failure or crash, to the fastest speed in the shortest time to restore the system\'s operation to ensure data security, will Guzhang losses to a minimum. <br /> This requires the system manager on the operating systems and business applications have a reasonable backup and recovery strategy, backup strategy can guarantee a perfect zero business downtime and data recovered completely. Because business is run on operating systems, so the operating system backup and recovery efficiency is directly related to the recovery of the entire business system level. So back up the operating system becomes critical. <br /> <strong>Second, the data need to back up Linux systems</strong> &lt;br /&gt; ghost in the software under windows, you can complete the entire system to another hard drive, ghost is a disk mirroring technology, all data can be mirrored system disk to another hard disk backup When the system problems, the backup mirror disk system in a short time all the data can be fully restored. <br /> Linux, although there are tools like ghost, but because of hardware compatibility, such as the complexity of recovery, ghost and can not be good for Linux image backup, and if the Linux system partition is too large, backup and recovery process will be very long, the ghost is not suitable for backup Linux operating system. <br /> In fact, the overall backup system is not a good strategy, Linux operating system does not need to fully back up, we just need to back up all configuration files to the system, so the backup process is quick, recovery is also fast. <br /> Linux system files to be backed up can be divided into two categories: system-level configuration files and user-level configuration file. <br /> System-level configuration file of some major global configuration of the system information, such as / etc / directory, / home directory, / boot directory, / root directory and so on. These directories on the system operation is critical, and apply the settings for different systems are different, if these files are missing, even though the new operating system installed quickly, but also to reconfigure the system to spend more time long. <br /> User-level configuration file is the user\'s business application and system related configuration files that are essential for business applications to run the system, once lost, the system will be unable to start the business, such as / usr / local the entire directory, / var / www directory, / etc throughout the catalog. <br /> Important documents that must be backed up, then the backup directory which does not require it, such as / dev directory, / proc directory, / mnt directory, / tmp directories, etc. These directories are not backed up, because either of these directories of memory data, or a temporary file, no important data, backing up the principle that we must all back up important data, useless data not backed up. <br /> <strong>Three backup media and methods</strong> &lt;br /&gt; to back up data, we must have the security of data containers stored on the storage media Jiben requirements generally from the access speed storage security, storage capacity of three aspects into account. <br /> Access speed is a basic requirement of the storage medium, data backup is a process of read and write operations is extremely frequent, very high speed access to backup media, backup data can greatly shorten the time, but can also reduce the time to recover data . <br /> Storage security is a mandatory requirement storage medium, such as the unsafe storage devices do not store the media, that many storage devices do a lot of security, optimization, such as doing raid disk array, cache reading and writing. Professional storage vendors are EMC, IBM, SUN, etc., have their own storage devices. <br /> Select the storage medium storage capacity is also an aspect to be considered, too much storage space will cause the waste of storage devices, storage space is too small, resulting in data storage failure, therefore, must be based on the size of backup data, select the appropriate size of storage media. <br /> 1. Commonly used backup media are optical storage media, disk, tape drives, floppy disks, etc., where the focus on what the tape drive to use: <br /> Tape drives under Linux using a variety of ways, tar command is the most frequently used method, tar is mainly used for stand-alone environment, the data is written directly to tape. Tape drive in the Linux device name corresponds to / dev / stX, if the first tape drive, that is, / dev/st0, the basic operation is as follows: <br /> (1) rewind, volume to the starting position of the tape mt-f / dev/st0 rewind <br /> (2) erase the contents of the tape mt-f / dev/st0 erase <br /> Newly purchased tape, opened to use, without the need for erase operations, while the tape when the data filled, the tape can cover the original data and continue to write, so without any erase operation, the erase of the tape has some damage, it is recommended not to perform erase operation. <br /> (3) the band is about to roll to the initial position of the tape from the tape machine and then eject mt-f / dev/st0 offline <br /> (4) are listed by tar directory or file on the tape tar tvf / dev/st0 [need to view the file or directory] <br /> If not followed with any file or directory, is to look at all the data on the tape when the tape does not have any data, to do this would be an error, but does not affect the tape used. <br /> (5) backup data to tape via tar tar cvf / dev/st0 [to be written to the file or directory name] <br /> Backup data to tape in two ways, packing tape and do not write compressed package directly into the tape. Here we do not recommend packing the data directly into the tape method. This will increase the security of data storage. Why does not recommend the package back then, because the tape is a sequential write data, that is, the linear storage, if all the data packaged into a separate file, then when the tape failure of any one place, may lead to unzip the zip file failure not available, and if not Dabao backup data storage, then there are a lot of files on tape, even if the tape somewhere fails, the rest of the files are still available, thus greatly improving the security of data backup. <br /> For example, / data/ixdba1.tar.gz the compressed file is written to tape, and cover the original content, you can do the following: <br /> [Root @ webserver / data] # tar cvf / dev/st0 / data/ixdba1.tar.gz <br /> Through the &quot;tar cvf&quot; to write data to tape, each tape will cover any original data, that is, every time from the beginning of the tape to write the data. Transmission speed of the tape drive more slowly, for not a lot of backup files, backup can be completed in a very short period of time, very suitable for system-level file backup. <br /> (6) through the tar continues to write data to tape tar rvf / dev/st0 [to write the file name] <br /> Because tape is linear storage, data is written in turn, in order to write the new data, does not overwrite the original data that already exists, you can use &quot;tar rvf&quot; parameters in order to write data to tape. <br /> For example, in order to / data/ixdba2.tar.gz and / data/ixdba3.tar.gz backup to tape drive: <br /> [Root @ webserver / data] # tar rvf / dev/st0 / data/ixdba2.tar.gz <br /> [Root @ webserver / data] # tar rvf / dev/st0 / data/ixdba3.tar.gz <br /> (7) through the tar to restore data from tape to disk tar xvf / dev/st0 [to restore the file or directory name] <br /> For example, first there is access to all data on the tape: <br /> [Root @ webserver ~] # tar tvf / dev/st0 <br /> -Rw-r - r - root / root 320 2009-2-20 10:19:02 ixdba1.tar.gz <br /> -Rw-r - r - root / root 320 2009-2-20 10:25:10 ixdba2.tar.gz <br /> -Rw-r - r - root / root 320 2009-2-20 10:45:18 ixdba3.tar.gz <br /> Now if you want to restore the tape on the ixdba2.tar.gz file to disk, you can execute the following command: <br /> [Root @ webserver ~] # tar xvf / dev/st0 ixdba2.tar.gz <br /> ixdba2.tar.gz <br /> This will restore data from tape to the current path. <br /> 2. Data backup data backup common are local backup and remote disaster recovery, according to the requirements of the importance of the extent of the data, choose the right backup. <br /> Local backup is to back up data to local system disk, tape or proprietary storage devices, local backup is a level of data security considerations, mainly for system failure, or hacker attacks, data loss situation. <br /> Remote disaster recovery of data and services is considered a higher security indicators, mainly to back up data to another city or country, mainly for possible natural disasters such as earthquakes, fires, floods, etc., when these natural disasters , the local backup data will be lost, this time to a remote disaster recovery need to restore data. <br /> <strong>Four backup strategy formulation <br /></strong> Common backup strategy with full backup, incremental backup, while incremental backups can also be divided between the cumulative incremental backup and incremental backup, the following briefly under the differences between them. <br /> 1. Full backup full backup is to backup all data, for the Linux operating system, is to all the files under the root partition backup, full backup of the benefits are: all data is backed up, the system can recover any data loss, and recovery efficiency; disadvantage is a longer backup time, backup, a lot of useless data and wasted storage space. <br /> 2. Incremental backup data in a large business applications, the daily full backup of the system is unrealistic, requiring an incremental backup strategy. Incremental backup is only backing up or changing data each day, without backup system does not change the data, so the amount of data backed up is greatly reduced, can shorten the backup time, but incremental backups and disadvantages, that is, data recovery When more complex and requires data with the first full backup and incremental backup data recovery portfolio, and if there are multiple incremental backup files, the recovery process will become very slow. <br /> A good backup strategy is: for small data and small daily increase in the amount of data systems, recommended to choose a full backup, shorter backup and restore is very simple. The huge amount of data a day, also a lot of new data system, we must choose an incremental backup.</span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(189,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0831/598.html','Original Series Linux security policy settings under the method used','2010-08-31','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">1. Prohibited from the system to respond to any internal / external to the ping request by the attacker typically begins with the host or the ping command to test IP is active, if you can ping a host, or through IP, then the attacker that the system is active state, and then attack or damage. If no one can ping through the machine and receive a response, it can greatly enhance server security, linux can be performed under the following set against ping request: <br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # echo &quot;1&quot;&gt; / proc/sys/net/ipv4/icmp_echo_ignore_all <br /> By default, the &quot;icmp_echo_ignore_all&quot; the value &quot;0&quot;, that responding ping operation. <br /> The above command line can be added to / etc / rc.d / rc.local file, so every time the system restarts automatically. <br /> 2. Prohibition of Control-Alt-Delete key combination to reboot the system default settings in linux, press Control-Alt-Delete key, the system will automatically reboot, which is very safe, and therefore prohibited Control-Alt-Delete key combination to restart system, simply modify / etc / inittab file: <br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # vi / etc / inittab <br /> Find this line: ca:: ctrlaltdel: / sbin / shutdown-t3-r now <br /> In before &quot;#&quot; <br /> And: <br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # telinit q</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">3. Shell command to limit the size of recorded history, by default, bash shell in the file $ HOME / .bash_history commands stored in records up to 1000 (based on systems, the default number of records different). System, each user\'s home directory has one file. <br /> Command records the history of so many, certainly is not safe, it is necessary to limit the file size. <br /> You can edit / etc / profile file, modify the options are as follows: <br /> HISTSIZE = 30 <br /> Indicated in the file $ HOME / .bash_history recorded in the recent history of 30 commands. If the &quot;HISTSIZE&quot; is set to 0, then the command history does not record, then it can not use the keyboard arrow keys to find the history command. <br /> 4. Remove unnecessary system default user and group <br /> Linux offers a variety of system accounts, the system installed, if not some of the user or group, we should delete it immediately, because the account the more insecure the system becomes, the more vulnerable. <br /> Delete unnecessary user system with the following command <br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # userdel username <br /> Remove unnecessary system group with the following command: <br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # groupdel groupname <br /> Linux system, you can delete the default user and group: <br /> Delete users, such as adm, lp, sync, shutdown, halt, news, uucp, operator, games, gopher, etc.. <br /> Delete the group, such as adm, lp, news, uucp, games, dip, pppusers, popusers, slipusers and so on. <br /> 5. Off selinux <br /> Security-Enhanced Linux SELinux is a short, is a mandatory access control security system kernel, the current SELinux has been integrated into the mainline Linux 2.6 kernel and most Linux distributions, as SELinux and the existing Linux applications and Linux-compatible kernel module There are still some issues of sexual, it is recommended for beginners to close selinux, until linux has in-depth understanding of, and then not later than on the selinux-depth study! <br /> View selinux is enabled linux system, you can use getenforce command: <br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # getenforce <br /> Disabled <br /> Off selinux, in the redhat release series, you can directly modify the following documents: <br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # vi / etc / sysconfig / selinux <br /> # This file controls the state of SELinux on the system. <br /> # SELINUX = can take one of these three values: <br /> # Enforcing - SELinux security policy is enforced. <br /> # Permissive - SELinux prints warnings instead of enforcing. <br /> # Disabled - SELinux is fully disabled. <br /> SELINUX = enforcing <br /> # SELINUXTYPE = type of policy in use. Possible values are: <br /> # Targeted - Only targeted network daemons are protected. <br /> # Strict - Full SELinux protection. <br /> SELINUXTYPE = targeted <br /> Will SELINUX = enforcing modify SELINUX = disabled, reboot the system will stop after the SElinux. <br /> 6. Tcp_wrappers firewall settings <br /> Tcp_Wrappers is used to analyze the TCP / IP packet of software, similar to IP packet software still iptables, linux by default are installed with this software, as a secure system, Linux itself has two layers of firewall security, IP filtering mechanism through iptables implement the first layer of protection, iptables firewall to monitor the system through intuitive operating conditions, blocks malicious network attacks and protect the normal operation of the entire system, from attack and destruction. About iptables implementation, described in detail in the next chapters. If the passage of the first layer of protection, then the next layer of protection is tcp_wrappers, and the system can be achieved through Tcp_Wrappers some of the services provided in the opening and closing, permitted and prohibited, so as to more effectively ensure the safe operation of the system. <br /> Tcp_Wrappers the use of very simple, just two configuration files: / etc / hosts.allow and / etc / hosts.deny <br /> (1) Check whether the system is installed Tcp_Wrappers <br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # rpm-q tcp_wrappers or <br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # rpm-qa | grep tcp <br /> tcp_wrappers-7.6-37.2 <br /> tcpdump-3.8.2-10.RHEL4 <br /> If there is a similar output of the above, that system has been installed tcp_wrappers module. If not, may not be installed, you can find the installation disk from a linux system, the corresponding RPM package installed. <br /> (2) tcp_wrappers firewall limitations of the system can use a service tcp_wrappers firewall, depending on whether the service applied libwrapped library file, if the application can use the tcp_wrappers a firewall, the system default of some services such as: sshd, portmap, sendmail, xinetd, vsftpd, tcpd so you can use the tcp_wrappers firewall. <br /> (3) tcp_wrappers set of rules <br /> tcp_wrappers achieved through the firewall / etc / hosts.allow and / etc / hosts.deny to complete the two files, first look at the set of formats: <br /> service: host (s) [: action] <br /> Ã¯ÂÂ¬ service: service name on behalf of, such as sshd, vsftpd, sendmail and so on. <br /> Ã¯ÂÂ¬ host (s): host name or IP address, you can have more than one, such as 192.168.60.0, www.ixdba.net <br /> Ã¯ÂÂ¬ action: action, meet the conditions of the action taken. <br /> A few keywords: <br /> Ã¯ÂÂ¬ ALL: all services or all of the IP. <br /> Ã¯ÂÂ¬ ALL EXCEPT: all services or all of the IP to remove specified. <br /> For example: ALL: ALL EXCEPT 192.168.60.132 <br /> In addition to 192.168.60.132 said the machine, any machine or perform all services allowed or denied. <br /> Understand the set syntax, the following can be accessed on the service limit. <br /> For example, a linux server on the Internet to achieve the goal: only allow 222.90.66.4,61.185.224.66 services and domain name softpark.com remote login via SSH to the system, set the following: <br /> First set the computer to allow log on, the configuration / etc / hosts.allow files, settings, very simple, just modify / etc / hosts.allow (If you do not have this file, please create your own) this file. <br /> Just add the following rules / etc / hosts.allow to. <br /> sshd: 222.90.66.4 61.185.224.66 softpark.com <br /> Then set the machine does not allow login, which is configured / etc / hosts.deny file. <br /> Under normal circumstances, linux will first determine the / etc / hosts.allow file, if the remote computer logon to meet the file / etc / hosts.allow set, would not have to use / etc / hosts.deny files, on the contrary, If the file does not meet the rules set hosts.allow then hosts.deny files would be to use, if hosts.deny rules, the hosts were restricted to inaccessible linux server, if does not meet the hosts.deny of setting, the host can access the linux server by default, so that when set up / etc / hosts.allow file access rules, just set the / etc / hosts.deny as a &quot;state of all the computers can not log in&quot; button. <br /> sshd: ALL <br /> Thus, a</span></span>'),(190,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0831/597.html','Original Series Use Linux, Yum','2010-08-31','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">A software upgrade to the software functionality improvements and safety upgrades, with the windows system similar to, linux operating system also needs regular updates to the software upgrade and maintain software are up to date. <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\">Linux</a></u> operating system upgrades can be divided into automatic update and manual update in two ways: automatically upgrade is usually authorized in a linux distribution or free distribution carried out under linux, just enter the upgrade command, the system will automatically upgrade without human intervention. <br /> yum is yellowdog updater modified acronym, yellow dog (yellow dog) is a Linux release version, but Redhat is the technical advantage of this upgrade to their distribution on the formation of the current yum. automatic updates for linux yum is a tool commonly used by yum with the Internet tools you can automatically upgrade the system. For example, authorized a Redhat Linux operating system, or a Centos Linux system, as long as your system can connect to the Internet, type yum update automatically upgrade the system can be realized. System upgrade through yum yum command to download the essence of the specified remote host on the Internet, RPM packages, and then automatically installed, while addressing the dependencies between various software. <br /> Manually upgrade is targeted for a system software upgrade, such as upgrading the system ssh login tools, gcc compile tools. Manually upgrade is actually achieved through the RPM package software update tool, so you may encounter when upgrading software dependencies between the software upgrade is relatively trouble. <br /> The following specific about how to set up in Centos Linux4.4 yum tools to perform system updates. <br /> 1. yum installation and configuration (1) yum yum check whether the installation has been installed: <br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # rpm-qa | grep yum <br /> If there is no any indication that the system not yet installed yum tool, yum centos system CD in the installation package can be found, perform the following command to install: <br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # rpm-ivh yum-*. noarch.rpm <br /> Need to install yum python-elementtree, python-sqlite, urlgrabber, yumconf other support packages, these packages in Centos Linux system installation CD-ROM can be found, if occurred during the installation package yum dependency between, just according to rely on tips to find the corresponding package can be installed until the yum package installed successfully. <br /> The following is an example of the installation environment: <br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # rpm-ivh yum-2.4.3-1.c4.noarch.rpm <br /> warning: yum-2.4.3-1.c4.noarch.rpm: V3 DSA signature: NOKEY, key ID 443e1821 <br /> error: Failed dependencies: <br /> python-elementtree is needed by yum-2.4.3-1.c4.noarch <br /> python-sqlite is needed by yum-2.4.3-1.c4.noarch <br /> urlgrabber is needed by yum-2.4.3-1.c4.noarch <br /> yumconf is needed by yum-2.4.3-1.c4.noarch <br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # rpm-ivh python-elementtree-1.2.6-4.2.1.i386.rpm <br /> warning: python-elementtree-1.2.6-4.2.1.i386.rpm: V3 DSA signature: NOKEY, key ID 443e1821 <br /> Preparing ... ########################################### [100% ] <br /> 1: python-elementtree ########################################### [100 %] <br /> <a href=\"mailto:root@localhost\">root @ localhost</a> ~] # rpm-ivh sqlite-3.3.3-1.2.i386.rpm <br /> warning: sqlite-3.3.3-1.2.i386.rpm: V3 DSA signature: NOKEY, key ID 443e1821 <br /> Preparing ... ########################################### [100% ] <br /> 1: sqlite ########################################### [100%] <br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # rpm-ivh python-sqlite-1.1.7-1.2.i386.rpm <br /> warning: python-sqlite-1.1.7-1.2.i386.rpm: V3 DSA signature: NOKEY, key ID 443e1821 <br /> Preparing ... ########################################### [100% ] <br /> 1: python-sqlite ########################################### [100 %] <br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # rpm-ivh python-urlgrabber-2.9.8-2.noarch.rpm <br /> warning: python-urlgrabber-2.9.8-2.noarch.rpm: V3 DSA signature: NOKEY, key ID 443e1821 <br /> Preparing ... ########################################### [100% ] <br /> 1: python-urlgrabber ########################################### [100 %] <br /> <a href=\"mailto:root@localhost\">root @ localhost</a> ~] # rpm-ivh CentOS-yumconf-4-4.5.noarch.rpm <br /> warning: centos-yumconf-4-4.5.noarch.rpm: V3 DSA signature: NOKEY, key ID 443e1821 <br /> Preparing ... ########################################### [100% ] <br /> 1: centos-yumconf ########################################### [100 %] <br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # rpm-ivh yum-2.4.3-1.c4.noarch.rpm <br /> warning: yum-2.4.3-1.c4.noarch.rpm: V3 DSA signature: NOKEY, key ID 443e1821 <br /> Preparing ... ########################################### [100% ] <br /> 1: yum ########################################### [100%] <br /> (2) yum configuration <br /> yum tool installed, the next job is to carry out the configuration of yum, yum configuration file has the main configuration file / etc / yum.conf, repository configuration directory / etc / yum.repos.d, yum install, the default number of Library configuration may not be used, hence the need for change, the following is / etc / yum.repos.d / CentOS-Base.repo repository of the detailed meaning of the configuration file: <br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # / etc / yum.repos.d / CentOS-Base.repo <br /> [Base] <br /> name = CentOS-4 - Base <br /> # Name is the name of release in the format that &quot;the operating system name and release version&quot;, &quot;base&quot; is that this section is the base package to find information.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">baseurl = http://mirror.centos.org/centos/4/os/ $ basearch / <br /> # Baseurl &quot;said yum upgrade file on the Internet to find the URL address. Which&quot; $ basearch &quot;represents the hardware architecture, such as&quot; i386 &quot;,&quot; x86-64, etc., at the same time, yum in the resource update, will check baseurl / repodata / repomd.xml file. &quot;Repomd.xml&quot; is an index file, its role is to provide an update rpm package file to download information and SHA checksum. &quot;Repomd.xml&quot; includes 3 files, namely &quot;other.xml.gz&quot;, &quot;fileli</span></span>'),(191,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0826/535.html','Original Series elaborate Linux System Optimization - Practice papers','2010-08-26','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">As a linux <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/\">system</a></u> administrator, the most important job is to optimize the <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/\">system</a></u> configuration, the application of the system to the optimal state of operation, but due to hardware problems, software problems, network environment, the complexity and variability, leading to system optimization has become extremely complex problem is how to define which aspects of performance, performance optimization is a major problem, starting from the system in this chapter, to highlight the system software and hardware configurations may cause performance problems properly, and gives the detection system failures and optimize performance of the general methods and processes. <br /> 1 cpu performance evaluation is affected Cpu <a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\"><u>Linux</u></a> performance of one of the main factors, the following describes some see CPU performance of the first order. <br /> 1.1 vmstat command displays the command between the various resources on the system summary information related to the performance, here we mainly use it to look at a CPU load. <br /> Here is the vmstat command output in a system: <br /> [Root @ node1 ~] # vmstat 2 3 <br /> procs ----------- memory ---------- --- swap - ----- io ---- - system - ----- cpu ------ <br /> r b swpd free buff cache si so bi bo in cs us sy id wa st <br /> 0 0,016,224,083,046,703,200 1,321,100,723,019,800 <br /> 0,001,622,408,304,670,320 0,101,010,200,110,000 <br /> 0 0 0 162240 8304 67032 0,011,100,918,019,900 <br /> The output of each of the above explanation is as follows: <br /> Ã¯ÂÂ¬ procs <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ r column indicates the run and wait for the number of cpu time slice of the process, this value system, if the CPU is greater than the number of long-term, indicating insufficient CPU, need to increase the CPU. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ b column indicates the number of processes waiting for resources, such as waiting for I / O, or memory exchange. <br /> Ã¯ÂÂ¬ memory <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ swpd out that switching to the amount of memory swap memory (in units of k). If the value is not 0 swpd, or relatively large, as long as the si, so long as the value 0, in which case the general do not worry, do not affect system performance. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ free column indicates the current amount of free physical memory (in k units) <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ buff out the amount of memory that buffers cache, generally only need to read and write block device buffer. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ cache memory column represents the number of page cached, generally as a file system cached, frequently accessed files are cached, if the cache is large, indicating the number of files cached more in the bi if IO is relatively small at this time, indicating that the file system efficiency is better. <br /> Ã¯ÂÂ¬ swap <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ si column represents the disk into memory, the memory access is the number of swap memory. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ so that the memory is transferred to the disk out, that is, into the memory swap the amount of memory. <br /> Under normal circumstances, si, so the value is 0, if si, so the value of the long-term is not 0, then the system memory. Need to increase the system memory. <br /> Ã¯ÂÂ¬ IO read and write disk status display items Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ Bi column represents the data read from the block device the total amount (that is, read the disk) (per kb). <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ Bo column represents the data written to the total amount of block devices (ie, writing to disk) (per kb) <br /> Here we set the reference value bi + bo 1000, if more than 1000, and wa is large, then the system disk IO problems, should consider increasing the disk read and write performance. <br /> Ã¯ÂÂ¬ system acquisition interval shows the number of interrupts occur Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ in column indicates the interval observed in the number of device interrupts per second. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ cs column indicates the number of context switches per second. <br /> Larger the value of the 2 above, you will see CPU time consumed by the kernel will be more. <br /> Ã¯ÂÂ¬ CPU entry shows the status of CPU usage, this column is our focus. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ us column shows the user process consumes the CPU time percentage. us the value of the relatively high, indicating the user process consumes much cpu time, but if more than 50% long-term, we need to consider the optimization of procedures or algorithms. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ sy column shows the kernel process consumes the CPU time percentage. Sy\'s value is high, that the kernel consumes a lot of CPU resources. <br /> Based on experience, us + sy 80% of the reference value, if us + sy that there may be greater than 80% of the CPU resources. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ id column shows the CPU percentage of time in idle state. <br /> Ã¯ÂƒÂ˜ wa column shows the IO wait CPU percentage of time occupied. wa higher the value, indicating the more serious the IO wait, based on experience, wa the reference value of 20%, if the wa more than 20%, indicating serious to wait for IO, IO caused to wait because a lot of random read and write may be caused by the disk may also is a disk or disk controller bandwidth bottleneck caused by the (mainly block operation). <br /> In summary, in the CPU\'s assessment, is important to note that the term r procs column item value and CPU us, sy, and id column values. <br /> 1.2 sar command to check CPU performance of the second tool is the sar, sar function is very powerful, able to separate every aspect of the system statistics, but using the sar command can increase system overhead, but these costs can be assessed, the system The results will not be greatly affected. <br /> The following is a sar command output of the system CPU statistics: <br /> [Root @ webserver ~] # sar-u 3 5 <br /> Linux 2.6.9-42.ELsmp (webserver) 11/28/2008 _i686_ (8 CPU)</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">11:41:24 AM CPU% user% nice% system% iowait% steal% idle <br /> 11:41:27 AM all 0.88 0.00 0.29 0.00 0.00 98.83 <br /> 11:41:30 AM all 0.13 0.00 0.17 0.21 0.00 99.50 <br /> 11:41:33 AM all 0.04 0.00 0.04 0.00 0.00 99.92 <br /> 11:41:36 AM all 0.29 0.00 0.13 0.00 0.00 99.58 <br /> 11:41:39 AM all 0.38 0.00 0.17 0.04 0.00 99.41 <br /> Average: all 0.34 0.00 0.16 0.05 0.00 99.45 <br /> The output of each of the above explanation is as follows: <br /> Ã¯ÂÂ¬% user column shows the user process consumes the CPU time percentage. <br /> Ã¯ÂÂ¬% nice column shows the normal process of running the percentage of time consumed by the CPU. <br /> Ã¯ÂÂ¬% system column shows the CPU consumption of the system processes the percentage of time. <br /> Ã¯ÂÂ¬% iowait column shows the IO wait CPU percentage of time occupied by the Ã¯ÂÂ¬% steal column shows the relative tension in the memory environment pagein different pages force the steal operation. <br /> Ã¯ÂÂ¬% idle CPU column shows the percentage of time in idle state. <br /> This output is the overall system CPU usage statistics, the output of each are very intuitive, and the last line is a summary row Average is an average of the above statistics. <br /> One thing to note is: the first line contains the sar statistics Statistics consumption itself, so the% user column values will be high point, however, it will not have much impact on the statistical results. <br /> In a multi-CPU system, if the program uses a single thread, there will be such a phenomenon, CPU utilization is not high overall, but the system application is responding slowly, it may be due to procedural reasons for using the single-threaded, single-threaded only using a CPU, causing the CPU occupancy rate of 100%, can not process other requests, while the other CPU is idle, which led to the overall CPU utilization is not high, and the application slow phenomenon. <br /> To address this issue, you can query the system separately for each CPU, each CPU usage statistics: <br /> [Root @ webserver ~] # sar-P 0 3 5 <br /> Linux 2.6.9-42.ELsmp (webserver) 11/29/2008 _i686_ (8 CPU)</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">06:29:33 PM CPU% user% nice% system% iowait% steal% idle <br /> 06:29:36 PM 0 3.00 0.00 0.33 0.00 0.00 96.67 <br /> 06:29:39 PM 0 0.67 0.00 0.33 0.00 0.00 99.00 <br /> 06:29:42 PM 0 0.00 0.00 0.33 0.00 0.00 99.67 <br /> 06:29:45 PM 0 0.67 0.00 0.33 0.00 0.00 99.00 <br /> 06:29:48 PM 0 1.00 0.00 0.33 0.33 0.00</span></span>'),(192,'linux','en','/a/db/oracle/2010/1012/796.html','Experience Oracle10gR2 ORA-3136 error and solution','2010-10-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Recently discovered this problem, reproduced eygle article, once again recorded! </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Recently a new database on the line Oracle10gR2 warning log file (alert.log) persists following <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/mz/\">error</a></u> : <br /> Tue Jul 18 23:09:22 2006 <br /> WARNING: inbound connection timed out (ORA-3136) <br /> Tue Jul 18 23:09:23 2006 <br /> WARNING: inbound connection timed out (ORA-3136) <br /> Tue Jul 18 23:09:25 2006 <br /> WARNING: inbound connection timed out (ORA-3136) <br /> Tue Jul 18 23:09:30 2006 <br /> WARNING: inbound connection timed out (ORA-3136) <br /> Tue Jul 18 23:12:15 2006 <br /> WARNING: inbound connection timed out (ORA-3136) <br /><br /> At the same time sqlnet.log the following error logged: <br /><br /> Fatal NI connect error 12170. <br /><br /> VERSION INFORMATION: <br /> TNS for Linux: Version 10.2.0.2.0 - Production <br /> Oracle Bequeath NT Protocol Adapter for Linux: Version 10.2.0.2.0 - Production <br /> TCP / IP NT Protocol Adapter for Linux: Version 10.2.0.2.0 - Production <br /> Time: 19-JUL-2006 11:25:26 <br /> Tracing not turned on. <br /> Tns error struct: <br /> ns main err code: 12535 <br /> TNS-12535: TNS: operation timed out <br /> ns secondary err code: 12606 <br /> nt main err code: 0 <br /> nt secondary err code: 0 <br /> nt OS err code: 0 <br /> Client address: (ADDRESS = (PROTOCOL = tcp) (HOST = 192.168.1.123) (PORT = 58147)) <br /><br /> This is related to network connection and an error, Metalink is given the following solution: <br /><br /> 1.set INBOUND_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_ &lt;listenername&gt; = 0 in listener.ora <br /> 2. Set SQLNET.INBOUND_CONNECT_TIMEOUT = 0 in sqlnet.ora of server. <br /> 3. Stop and start both listener and database. <br /> 4. Now try to connect to DB and observe the behaviour <br /><br /> Here restart the database and the Listener I think it is not necessary, and we look Listner should reload it. <br /><br /> [Oracle @ order admin] $ lsnrctl <br /><br /> LSNRCTL for Linux: Version 10.2.0.2.0 - Production on 19-JUL-2006 15:26:33 <br /><br /> Copyright (c) 1991, 2005, Oracle. All rights reserved. <br /><br /> Welcome to LSNRCTL, type &quot;help&quot; for information. <br /><br /> LSNRCTL&gt; reload <br /> Connecting to (DESCRIPTION = (ADDRESS = (PROTOCOL = TCP) (HOST = 172.16.9.11) (PORT = 1521))) <br /> The command completed successfully <br /> LSNRCTL&gt; services <br /> Connecting to (DESCRIPTION = (ADDRESS = (PROTOCOL = TCP) (HOST = 172.16.9.11) (PORT = 1521))) <br /> Services Summary ... <br /> Service &quot;order&quot; has 2 instance (s). <br /> Instance &quot;order&quot;, status UNKNOWN, has 1 handler (s) for this service ... <br /> Handler (s): <br /> &quot;DEDICATED&quot; established: 0 refused: 0 <br /> LOCAL SERVER <br /> Instance &quot;order&quot;, status READY, has 1 handler (s) for this service ... <br /> Handler (s): <br /> &quot;DEDICATED&quot; established: 0 refused: 0 state: ready <br /> LOCAL SERVER <br /> The command completed successfully <br /><br /> LSNRCTL&gt; show inbound_connect_timeout <br /> Connecting to (DESCRIPTION = (ADDRESS = (PROTOCOL = TCP) (HOST = 172.16.9.11) (PORT = 1521))) <br /> LISTENER parameter &quot;inbound_connect_timeout&quot; set to 0 <br /> The command completed successfully <br /> LSNRCTL&gt; exit <br /><br /> Changes, observed a period of time, the current normal. <br /><br /> About SQLNET.INBOUND_CONNECT_TIMEOUT parameters, Oracle proposed to modify the parameters in order to avoid denial-of-service attacks.</span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(193,'linux','en','/a/db/oracle/2010/0806/416.html','AIX maxuproc parameters to modify to solve TNS-00519 error','2010-08-06','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">An AIX system, memory, 16G, install the oracle database, just apply on-line to find the problem.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">1. Question the phenomenon of clients can not connect to the database, listener is running normally, but after restart the listener reported the following <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/mz/\">error</a></u> : <br /> TNS-12549: TNS: operating system resource quota exceeded <br /> TNS-12560: TNS: protocol adapter error <br /> TNS-00519: Operating system resource quota exceeded <br /> IBM / AIX RISC System/6000 Error: 11: Resource temporarily unavailable</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">jianting not start, observe the background session to connect to the database are not many.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">2. Deal with the problem since the tips of resources beyond the amount of ideas, and nothing less than the pressures and constraints related to the new system is deployed, the equipment performance OK, not the overall control down pressure. <br /> Therefore, from another angle, since the new system to do, and whether certain &quot;limit&quot; parameter is not relevant to adjust?</span></span> </p><p></p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Since it is a new deployment environment, simply stop and look at the parameters need to be modified, AIX, maxuproc parameters gradually emerged. This maxuproc parameter can be interpreted as &quot;max user processes&quot;, to limit each user a maximum number of processes available (similar to Oracle\'s processes limit the number of parameters on the session.) The parameter default value is 128, that something that enough? !</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">3. Solve the fault since the discovery of the problem, it will be more successful the treatment. <br /> 1) Check the current value of the parameter maxuproc <br /> # Lsattr-E-l sys0 | grep maxuproc <br /> 2) using the command chdev parameters will be adjusted as large as 1024 maxuproc <br /> # Chdev-l sys0-a maxuproc = 1024</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Parameters can be dynamically modified, that change will come into force.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Get the fault has been eliminated, call it a day.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">chdev command using the method of reference connection <br /> http://www.kuqin.com/aixcmds/aixcmds1/chdev.htm</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">4. Summary Fortunately, finding problems early, if only to find the problem on the line, the price will be heavy. <br /> Plans and programs is important, such issues need to accumulate and to always remember it. <br /></span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(194,'linux','en','/a/db/mysql/2010/0707/282.html','mysql related error and the corresponding solution summary','2010-07-07','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span class=\"code-comment\">Problem symptoms and error message:</span> </p><p> <font color=\"#000000\"><span class=\"code\">Database connection failed! Please check the database server, user name, password is correct</span> <br /><br /> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions:</span> If the installation is mysql4.1 above, and just installed the password algorithm change will occur without this problem, the solution detailed in this article <br /> Client does not sport authentication protocol requested by server section <br /> <span style=\"font-size: 12px\">But if the problem is in the virtual hosting business devices appears, it must be really wrong your database server, user name, password</span></font> </p><p class=\"code-comment\"> Problem symptoms and error message: </p><p class=\"code\"> Client does not sport authentication protocol requested byserver </p><p><br /> Above all users to install Mysql4.1 see this !!!!!!!!! <b><br /></b> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions:</span> <br /> Mysql 4.1 and above to use the new cryptographic algorithms, and php does not support the new algorithm, so the new user, need to use the following solution to log in Mysql php can not connect the problem <span style=\"font-size: 12px\">(which some_user, some_host, newpwd are your database user name, host, password) <br /><br /> The first solution: <br /> mysql&gt; SET PASSWORD FOR <br /> -&gt; \'Some_user\' @ \'some_host\' = OLD_PASSWORD (\'newpwd\'); <br /><br /> For example, the database user is admin, host localhost, the password is 123456 <br /><br /> Enter the command at this time should be: <br /> mysql&gt; SET PASSWORD FOR admin @ localhost = OLD_PASSWORD (\'123456 \'); <br /> [Thanks henrykim do this example] <br /><br /> The second solution: <br /> mysql&gt; DATE mysql.user SET password = OLD_PASSWORD (\'newpwd\') <br /> -&gt; WHERE Host = \'some_host\' AND User = \'some_user\'; <br /> mysql&gt; FLUSH pRIVILEGES; <br /><br /><br /> The third solution (not recommended) <br /> With the - old-passwords option is enabled mysqld, then use the above method to change the original user <br /><br /> From Mysql official website: <font color=\"#333399\" face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><a href=\"http://dev.mysql.com/doc/mysql/en/old-client.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://dev.mysql.com/doc/mysql/en/old-client.html</a></font></span> <br /></p><div class=\"Mjb598\"></div><p></p><p class=\"code-comment\"> Problem symptoms and error message: </p><p class=\"Mjb598\"></p><p></p><p class=\"code\"> Warning: mysql_fetch_array (): supplied argument is not a valid MySQL result resource in / home / lonmo.com / install.php on line 405 </p><p> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions:</span> mysql and php version mysql version of the library to use that much difference. If not look into the same </p><div class=\"Mjb598\"></div><p></p><p class=\"code-comment\"> Problem symptoms and error message: </p><p class=\"code\"> Warning: mysql_connect (): Too many connections in C: \\ web \\ www.lonmo.com \\ include \\ lib \\ kDB \\ lib \\ mysql.php on line 11 kDB Error: Connecting to MySQL failed, please contact to your administrator </p><p class=\"Mjb598\"></p><p></p><p> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions:</span> server reached the maximum number of mysql connections. Just occasionally, look up the log to see if there is a lot of search engine spiders access to the records of spiders crawling sometimes this is like. <br /> Best to check your configuration file my.cnf file mysql max_connections value, if set to a large number of small to </p><p> <span class=\"code-comment\">Problem symptoms and error message:</span> </p><p> <font color=\"#000000\"><span class=\"code\">To the final step to establish an administrator always says &quot;the administrator to create failed&quot;</span> <br /><br /> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions: It</span> may be a database permissions problem, such as user name or password error</font> </p><p> <span class=\"code-comment\">Problem symptoms and error message:</span> </p><p class=\"code\"> Warning: mysql_connect (): Access denied for user: \'root @ localhost\' (Using password: NO) in C: \\ usr \\ local \\ www \\ data \\ install.php on line 383 </p><p><br /> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions:</span> current user (root) do not have permission to connect to the mysql database. May be connected user name, password is not correct, here is the prompt for the root account you do not specify the connection password </p><p> <span class=\"code-comment\">Problem symptoms and error message:</span> When prompted to create a database </p><p class=\"Mjb598\"></p><p></p><p class=\"code\"> Warning: mysql_connect (): Access denied for user: \'cmsware @ localhost\' (Using password: YES) in C: \\ usr \\ local \\ www \\ data \\ install.php on line 383 </p><p><br /> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions:</span> current user (cmsware) do not have permission to connect to the mysql database. May be connected user name, password is not correct, here is your permission to lack of prompt or password. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(195,'linux','en','/a/db/oracle/2010/0604/172.html','PL / SQL School Notes (1)','2010-06-04','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> PL / SQL block can only be directly embedded SELECT, DML (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE), and transaction control statements (COMMIT, ROLLBACK, SAVEPOINT), but not directly embedded DDL statements (CREATE, ALTER, DROP) and DCL statements (GRANT, REVOKE) </p><p> 1. Retrieve a single row of data <br /> 1.1 accept data using the scalar variable v_ename emp.ename% type; <br /> v_sal emp.sal% type; <br /> select ename, sal into v_ename, v_sal from emp where empno = &amp;no; </p><p> 1.2 accept data using the record variable type emp_record_type is record ( <br /> ename emp.ename% type, sal emp.sal% type); <br /> emp_record emp_record_type; <br /> select ename, sal into emp_record from emp where empno = &amp;no; </p><p> 1.3 embedded SELECT statement Note: <br /> When using the SELECT INTO statement, we must return to a data, and can only return one data <br /> no_date_found: <br /> select into returns no data too_many_rows: <br /> select into multiple data returned <br /> where clause to use NOTE: <br /> Variable name used in the same column name can not otherwise trigger TOO_MANY_ROWS exception. <br /></p><p> 2. Manipulate data using the VALUES clause 2.1 insert data v_deptno dept.deptno% type; <br /> v_dname dept.dname% type; <br /> v_deptno: = no; <br /> v_dname: = \'&amp; name\'; <br /> insert into dept (deptno, dname) values (v_deptno, v_dname); </p><p> 2.2 Inserting Data using subqueries v_deptno emp.deptno% type: = &amp;no; <br /> insert into employee select * from emp where deptno = v_deptno; <br /><br /> Update 2.3 updates the data column values using the expression v_deptno dept.deptno% type: = no; <br /> v_loc dept.loc% type: = \'&amp; loc\'; <br /> update dept set loc = v_loc where deptno = v_deptno; </p><p> 2.4 update using subquery column value v_ename emp.ename% type: = \'&amp; name\'; <br /> update emp set (sal, comm) = (select sal, comm from emp where ename = v_ename) where job = (select job from emp where ename = v_ename) </p><p> 2.5 delete data delete data using variables v_deptno dept.deptno% type: = &amp;no; <br /> delete from dept where deptno = v_deptno; <br /><br /> 2.6 delete data using subqueries v_ename emp.ename% type: = \'&amp; name\'; <br /> delete from emp where deptno = (select deptno from emp where ename = v_ename); </p><p><br /> 3.SQL cursor cursor is a pointer pointing to the context area, including the implicit cursor (SQL cursor) and two types of explicit cursor SQL cursor used to process SELECT INTO, INSERT, UPDATE, and DELETE statements. <br /> Explicit cursor to handle multiple lines of SQL cursor SELECT statement includes: SQL% FOUND, SQL% NOTFOUND, SQL% ROWCOUNT, SQL% ISOPEN other four properties <br /> 3.1 SQL% ISOPEN: execution, will implicitly open and close the cursor. So the value of the property is always FALSE <br /><br /> 3.2 SQL% FOUND: used to determine the successful implementation of SQL statements. When SQL have a role in rows, for TRUE, FALSE otherwise <br /> v_deptno emp.deptno% type: = &amp;no; <br /> update emp set sal = sal * 1.1 where deptno = v_deptno; <br /> if sql% found then dbms_output.put_line (\'the implementation of successful\'); else dbms_output.putline (\'failed\'); endif <br /><br /> 3.3 sql% notfound: SQL statement is executed to determine the success of a role when the SQL rows to false, otherwise true <br /><br /> 3.4 sql% rowcount: returns the SQL statement, the total effect of the number of rows v_deptno emp.deptno% type: = &amp;no; <br /> update emp set sal = sal * 1.1 where deptno = v_deptno; <br /> dbms_output.put_line (\'modify\' | | sql% rowcount | | \'rows\'); </p><p><br /> 4. Transaction control statements, including transaction control statements COMMIT, ROLLBACK, and SAVEPOINT three kinds of statements <br /> v_sal emp.sal% type: = &amp;salary; <br /> v_ename emp.ename% type: = \'&amp; name\'; <br /> update emp set sal = v_sal where ename = v_ename; <br /> commit; <br /> exception <br /> when others then <br /> rollback; </p><p> insert into temp values (1); <br /> savepoint a1; <br /> insert into temp values (2); <br /> savepoint a2; <br /> insert into temp values (3); <br /> savepoint a3; <br /> rollback to a2; <br /> commit; </p><p><br /> 5. Control structures conditional branch statement <br /> 5.1 Simple conditional v_sal number (6,2); <br /> select sal into v_sal from emp where lower (ename) = lowe (\'&amp; &amp; name\'); <br /> if v_sal &lt;2000 then update emp set sal = v_sal +200 where lower (ename) = lower (\'&amp; name\') <br /> end if </p><p> 5.2 The double conditional branch v_comm number (6,2); <br /> select comm into v_comm from emp where empno = &amp; &amp;no; <br /> if v_comm &lt;&gt; 0 then update emp set comm = v_comm +100 where empno = &amp;no; <br /> else update emp set comm = 200 where empno = &amp;no; <br /> end if </p><p> 5.3 Multiple conditional branch v_job varchar2 (10); <br /> v_sal number (6,2); <br /> select job, sal into v_job, v_sal from emp where empno = &amp; &amp;no; <br /> if v_job = \'president\' then update emp set sal = v_sal +1000 where empno = &amp;no; <br /> elseif v_job = \'manager\' then update emp set sal = v_sal +500 where empno = &amp;no; <br /> else update emp set sal = v_sal +200 where empno = &amp;no; <br /> end if; </p><p><br /> 5.4 CASE statement: <br /> CASE statement in a single selector for comparing equivalent declare <br /> v_deptno emp deptno% type; <br /> begin <br /> v_deptno: = &amp;no; <br /> case v_deptno <br /> when 10 then update emp set comm = 100 where deptno = v_deptno; <br /> when 20 then update emp set comm = 80 where deptno = v_deptno; <br /> when 30 then update emp set comm = 50 where deptno = v_deptno; <br /> else <br /> dbms_output.put_line (&quot;does not exist \'); <br /> end case; &lt;'),(196,'linux','en','/a/db/mysql/2010/0520/105.html','Mysql Optimization Experience','2010-05-20','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(197,'linux','en','/a/db/oracle/2010/0521/112.html','Increasing sequence generated from Oracle - and stored procedures','2010-05-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Since the oracle is not added, this configuration, you must manually write a method or sequence or with a trigger </p><p> Or a sequence of easy to use (personal habits) </p><div class=\"dp-highlighter\"><ol class=\"dp-j\"><li> <span>create sequence salary_seq</span> </li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>increment by</span> <font color=\"#c00000\"><span class=\"number\">1</span></font> <span>--- plus a few each</span> </li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>start with</span> <font color=\"#c00000\"><span class=\"number\">1</span></font> <span>- start counting from</span> <font color=\"#c00000\"><span class=\"number\">1</span></font> </li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>nonmaxvalue - do not set the maximum</span> </li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>nocycle - has been incremental, not cycle</span> </li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>cache</span> <font color=\"#c00000\"><span class=\"number\">10</span></font> <span>- a buffer</span> </li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>eg create sequence salary_seq</span> </li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>minvalue</span> <font color=\"#c00000\"><span class=\"number\">100</span></font> <span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>maxvalue</span> <font color=\"#c00000\"><span class=\"number\">9999999999</span></font> <span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>start with</span> <font color=\"#c00000\"><span class=\"number\">560</span></font> <span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>increment by</span> <font color=\"#c00000\"><span class=\"number\">1</span></font> <span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>cache <font color=\"#c00000\"><span class=\"number\">20;</span></font></span> </li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>using: insert into tableName value <font color=\"#0000ff\"><span class=\"string\">(salary_seq.nextval,\'\',\'\');</span></font></span> </li></ol></div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(198,'linux','en','/a/web/tomcat/2010/0520/107.html','Experience jvm memory tuning','2010-05-20','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/web/tomcat/\">JVM</a></u> tuning is a very simple and very complex topic, since such problems often encountered in this summary. </p><p> Start to resolve bug started, when the Java application program memory can be allocated out of the VM, when pure, VM might be the first GC, GC finished if not enough, or the application may have a direct super enough to VM, it will throw out of memory exception. From the VM specification, we can get, about several exceptions. </p><p> <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">java.lang.StackOverflowError: (rare) <br /> java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: heap space (more common) <br /> java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: PermGen space (often)</span></strong> </p><p> <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: GC overhead limit exceeded (an action occurs when using a lot of memory)</span></strong> </p><p> The following are explained, from the beginning of the most common: </p><p> <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: PermGen space</span></strong> this anomaly more common, is that JVM memory area in the Perm abnormal overflow, the JVM in the default case, Perm default is 64M, and many programs need a lot of Perm region memory, especially with to other frameworks like Spring, because of need to use dynamically generated classes, and these classes can not be GC automatically released, thus resulting in OutOfMemoryError: PermGen space exception. Solution is simple, increase the JVM\'s-XX: MaxPermSize startup parameters, we can solve this problem, such as through the use of the default variable is usually 64M [5.0 and newer: 64 bit VMs are scaled 30% larger; 1.4 amd64: 96m ; 1.3.1-client: 32m.], changed to 128M on it,-XX: MaxPermSize = 128m. If you have a 128m (Eclipse has a 128m a) to change the 256m. I usually on the server for security reasons, change the 256m. </p><p> <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: heap space</span></strong> or other OutOfMemoryError, this exception is actually with the above exception is an exception, but the solutions are different, so separate write. Above, that exception is because the JVM\'s perm area caused less distinction between memory (JVM\'s memory is divided into young, old, perm three). And this exception is because the JVM heap memory or less total points. The solution is to change-Xms-Xmx startup parameter, usually 1-fold increase. xms is to manage the minimum amount of memory at startup, xmx tube JVM is the largest amount of memory. <br /> Note: OutOfMemoryError may have a variety of reasons, according to JVM Specification, may be about several situations, I briefly listed. stack: stack partition can not be dynamically expanded, or not enough to generate a new thread. Heap: need more memory, but can not get. Method Area: If you can not satisfy the distribution requirements. runtime constant pool (from the Method Area allocate memory) enough to create a class or interface. native method stacks can not be dynamically expanded, or create new native thread. </p><p></p><p> <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: GC overhead limit exceeded,</span></strong> this is the type of error JDK6 Xintian. Occurs in the GC takes a lot of time when the release occurred in a small space, is a protective mechanism. JSP guide I encountered when a large Excel. The final solution is to disable the function, use the --XX:-UseGCOverheadLimit </p><p> Finally talk about <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">java.lang.StackOverflowError,</span></strong> honestly I have not met the exception too, but the JVM Specification to mention, norms, said there are about several situations may throw the exception, one is allowed Stacks in the threads over time the other is when the native method requires more memory, and more than native method when the memory allows. According to SUN\'s documentation, improve-XX: ThreadStackSize = 512 value. </p><p> JVM memory tuning in general, group purpose is to use memory as small as possible, and make the program run properly, do not throw the net overflow bug. But should be fine minimum memory, maximum memory of the ratio of GC time to avoid wasting too much time, especially to avoid FULL GC. </p><p></p><p> Added: Since JDK1.4 added nio, nio the buffer memory is allocated and rather special (read and write streams can be shared memory). If you have a large number of data exchange, may also lead to java.lang.OutOfMemoryError. The corresponding JDK added a special parameter:-XX: MaxDirectMemorySize default is 64M, you can change something as big 128M. </p><p> -XX: MaxDirectMemorySize = &lt;size&gt; <br /> Specifies the maximum amount of memory in bytes that the Java Ã¢Â„Â¢ NIO library can allocate for direct memory buffers. The default is 64 megabytes, which corresponds to <br /> -XX: MaxDirectMemorySize = 64m. The use of direct memory buffers can minimize the copying cost when doing I / O operations. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(199,'linux','en','/a/web/tomcat/2010/0426/81.html','java.lang.OutOfMemoryError error summary','2010-04-26','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><div><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><strong>1, Permanent Generation space problem</strong> <br /><br /> PermGen space stands for Permanent Generation space, refers to the memory of the permanent preservation areas OutOfMemoryError: PermGen space benefits from a surface is the memory, the solution must also be increased memory. Why talk about the benefits out of memory: This section is used to store information on Class and Meta, Class is Load in the PermGen space when they were placed in regional, and store it in different areas Instance of the Heap, GC (Garbage Collection) does not PermGen space running the main program to clean up on, so if your lot CLASS LOAD APP would then, it is possible PermGen space <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/mz/\">error</a></u> . This <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/mz/\">error</a></u> is common, JSP web server to pre compile time. <br /><br /> Correction:-Xms256m-Xmx256m-XX: MaxNewSize = 256m-XX: MaxPermSize = 256m <br /><br /> <strong>2, tomcat redeploy when outofmemory in</strong> <br /><br /> When the tomcat redeploy outofmemory in error. <br /><br /> Can have the following reasons: <br /><br /> 1, the use of the proxool, because it contains an internal proxool old version of cglib. <br /><br /> 2, log4j, not the best, only common-logging <br /><br /> 3, the old version of cglib, quick update to the latest version. <br /><br /> 4, updated to the latest hibernate3.2 <br /><br /> <strong>3, for example,</strong> <br /><br /> Here to tomcat environment for example, other WEB server such as jboss, weblogic, etc. is the same reason.</font> </p><p><br /> A, java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: PermGen space <br /> PermGen space stands for Permanent Generation space, refers to the memory of the permanent preservation areas, <br /> This memory is stored mainly by JVM Class and Meta information, Class Loader when being PermGen space will be placed in <br /> It and store the class instance (Instance) of the Heap regional differences, GC (Garbage Collection) is not in the main program running on <br /> To clean up the PermGen space, so if your application has a lot of CLASS, then, it is possible PermGen space error <br /> This error is common, JSP web server to pre compile time. If your WEB APP, who uses a lot of third-party jar, its size exceeds the size of the default jvm (4M) that will generate this error messages. <br /> Workaround: manually set the MaxPermSize size <br /><br /> Modify the TOMCAT_HOME / bin / catalina.sh <br /> In the echo &quot;Using CATALINA_BASE: $ CATALINA_BASE; above by adding the following line: <br /> <strong>JAVA_OPTS = &quot;-server-XX: PermSize = 64M-XX: MaxPermSize = 128m</strong> <br /> Recommendation: use the same third-party jar files relocated to the tomcat / shared / lib directory, so you can take to reduce duplication of memory jar documentation purposes. <br /><br /> Second, java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space <br /></p><p> Heap size settings <br /> JVM heap setting is the java program is running JVM memory space can be used to deploy the settings. JVM at startup automatically set Heap size value <br /> The initial space (ie-Xms) is the physical memory of 1 / 64, the maximum space (-Xmx) is the physical memory of 1 / 4. JVM can be used to provide the-Xmn-Xms-Xmx and other options can be set. Heap size is the size of the Young Generation and Tenured Generaion sum. <br /> Tip: In the JVM, if 98% of the time is available for the GC Heap size and less than 2% of the time to throw this exception information. <br /> Tip: Heap Size should not exceed the maximum 80% of physical memory available, the general to-Xms and-Xmx option to set to the same, while the-Xmn 1 / 4 of the-Xmx value. <br /> Workaround: manually set the Heap size <br /> Modify the TOMCAT_HOME / bin / catalina.sh <br /> In the &quot;echo&quot; Using CATALINA_BASE: $ CATALINA_BASE &quot;&quot; above, add the following line: <br /> JAVA_OPTS = &quot;-server-Xms800m-Xmx800m-XX: MaxNewSize = 256m&quot; <br /><br /> Third, the examples given below 1G memory environment java jvm parameter settings for reference: <br /><br /> JAVA_OPTS = &quot;-server-Xms800m-Xmx800m-XX: PermSize = 64M-XX: MaxNewSize = 256m-XX: MaxPermSize = 128m-Djava.awt.headless = true&quot; </p></div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(200,'linux','en','/a/web/2010/0423/66.html','Linux, apache 2.2.6 + php5.2.5 + mysql5.0.46 + Zend installation Raiders','2010-04-23','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<html> <font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">RPM</span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\">packages and source packages storage location</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">/ usr / local / src <br /></span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\">Source package compile install location</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">(prefix) / usr / local / xxx <br /></span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\">Storage location, and maintenance procedures for the script</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">/ usr / local / sbin <br /> MySQL</span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\">database location</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">/ var / lib / mysql <br /> Apache</span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\">web root directory</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">/ usr/loca/apache2/htdocsl <br /> Apache</span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\">virtual host log root</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; m