venscaling.com/mysq...-5.0.46.tar.gz</a></span></font> <br /> # Tar xzvf mysql-5.0.46.tar.gz <br /> # Cd mysql-5.0.46 <br /><br /> Mysql</span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\">client to modify the maximum number of connections</span> <span style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"> </span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\">Only the default</span>'),(201,'linux','en','/a/web/2010/0423/64.html','An bjpeg-6b png error error solution','2010-04-23','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">The default security bjpeg-6b</span></strong> <br /><br /> shell&gt; wget <a href=\"ftp://ftp.uu.net/graphics/jpeg/jpegsrc.v6b.tar.gz\">ftp://ftp.uu.net/graphics/jpeg/jpegsrc.v6b.tar.gz</a> <br /><br /> tar zxvf jpegsrc.v6b.tar.gz <br /> cd jpeg-6b <br /> . / Configure - prefix = / usr/local/jpeg6-enable-shared-enable-static <br /> make <br /> make install <br /></p><p> <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Specify the installation directory install jpeg-6b</span></strong> </p><p><br /> If you choose the default installation, you may very well, but to specify a path, first create the following folder, or will be error: <br /><br /> <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/mz/\">Error</a></u> prompted :...... / usr / bin / install-c-m 644 jconfig.h / usr/local/jpeg6/include/jconfig.h <br /><br /> / Usr / bin / install: can not create a general file \'/ usr/local/jpeg6/include/jconfig.h\': No such file or directory <br /><br /> make: *** [install-headers] Error 1 <br /></p><p> Create the following folders need to <br /> # Mkdir / usr/local/jpeg6 <br /> # Mkdir / usr/local/jpeg6/include <br /> # Mkdir / usr/local/jpeg6/lib </p><p> # Mkdir / usr/local/jpeg6/bin <br /> # Mkdir / usr/local/jpeg6/man <br /> # Mkdir / usr/local/jpeg6/man/man1 </p><p> # Make install-lib <br /> # Make install <br /><br /> Then compile setting: <br /><br /> . / Configure - enable-shared - enable-static <br /><br /> Followed by make, start to go wrong: <br /><br /> . / Libtool - mode = compile gcc-O2-I.-C. / Jcapimin.c <br /><br /> make:. / libtool: command not found <br /><br /> make: *** [jcapimin.lo] Error 127 <br /><br /> <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">First, see if there is not installed libtool and libtool-ltdl-devel <br /><br /> rpm-qa | grep libtool <br /><br /> Jpeg-6b then enter the source directory, and then perform the following steps, remember! <br /> cp / usr / share / libtool / config.sub. <br /> cp / usr / share / libtool / config.guess.</span> <br /></strong> <br /> Libtool which is to bring the two configuration files jpeg-6b overwrite the corresponding file directory <br /><br /> make clean and then re-configure <br /><br /> When the first does not have permission to establish the corresponding folder, make install on the line again <br /><br /> <strong>Installing GD</strong> <br /><br /> Error <br /><br /> make [2]: *** [gd_png.lo] Error 1 <br /><br /> make [2]: Leaving directory `/ usr/local/file/gd-2.0.26gif \' <br /><br /> make [1]: *** [all-recursive] Error 1 <br /><br /> make [1]: Leaving directory `/ usr/local/file/gd-2.0.26gif \' <br /><br /> make: *** [all] Error 2 <br /><br /> (Such as where there is an error, please vi gd_png.c, find the &quot;png.h&quot; changed to &quot;/ usr/local/libpng2/include/png.h&quot;) </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(202,'linux','en','/a/web/apache/2010/0423/62.html','Linux + apache + php + mysql installation and configuration guide','2010-04-23','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> I: Preparation Package, storage / home / xiutuo / software / directory. </p><p> Main package </p><p> 1. Httpd-2.2.6.tar.gz </p><p> 2. Mysql-5.0.45-linux-i686-glibc23.tar.gz (this version is already compiled compressed, slightly after decompression configured to use) </p><p> 3. Php-5.2.5.tar.gz </p><p> Packages needed to install php (where libxml2 is installed php5 required.) </p><p> 1. Libxml2-(Version). Tar.gz ---&gt; <a href=\"http://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/sources/libxm2\">http://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/sources/libxm2</a> </p><p> 2. Libxslt-(Version). Tar.gz ---&gt; <a href=\"http://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/sources/libxslt\">http://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/sources/libxslt</a> </p><p> 3. Curl-(Version). Tar.gz ---&gt; <a href=\"http://curl.haxx.se/download\">http://curl.haxx.se/download</a> </p><p> GD library requires package (some say PHP source code package comes GD2.0.28 and zlib, as long as the three support packages to install GD: jpg, png and freetype, but we still download) </p><p> 1. Gd-(Version). Tar.gz ---&gt; <a href=\"http://www.libgd.org/Main_Page\">http://www.libgd.org/Main_Page</a> or <a href=\"http://www.libgd.org/releases/\">http://www.libgd.org/releases/</a> </p><p> 2. Freetype-(Version). Tar.gz ---&gt; <a href=\"http://sourceforge.net/projects/freetype\">http://sourceforge.net/projects/freetype</a> </p><p> 3. Jpegsrc.v6b.tar.gz ---&gt; <a href=\"http://ijg.org/files/jpegsrc.v6b.tar.gz\">http://ijg.org/files/jpegsrc.v6b.tar.gz</a> </p><p> 4. Libpng-(Version). Tar.gz ---&gt; <a href=\"http://www.libpng.org/pub/png/libpng.html\">http://www.libpng.org/pub/png/libpng.html</a> </p><p> 5. Zlib-1.2.3.tar.gz ---&gt; <a href=\"http://www.zlib.net\">http://www.zlib.net</a> </p><p> All of the above packages to download to: / root / Software / directory. </p><p> Second: Install mysql </p><p> # Tar-zvxf mysql-5.0.45-linux-i686-glibc23.tar.gz </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr / local / mysql </p><p> # Cp-r mysql-5.0.45 / usr / local / mysql </p><p> # Cp / usr / local / mysql / support-files / mysql.server / etc / rc.d / init.d / mysql / / mysql boot </p><p> # Cp / usr / local / mysql / support-files / my-medium.cnf / etc / my.cnf </p><p> Add mysql user and group </p><p> # Groupadd mysql </p><p> # Useradd-g mysql mysql </p><p> Modify the mysql directory permissions </p><p> # Chown-R root / usr / local / mysql </p><p> # Chgrp-R mysql / usr / local / mysql </p><p> # Chown-R mysql / usr / local / mysql / data </p><p> Mysql system database generated </p><p> # / Usr / local / mysql / scripts / mysql_install_db - user = mysql &amp; / / start the mysql service </p><p> # / Usr / local / mysql / bin / mysqld_safe - user = mysql &amp; </p><p> If there Starting mysqld daemon with databases from / usr / local / mysql / data representative of normal start mysql service. </p><p> Press Ctrl + C out of the root mysql password change </p><p> # / Usr / local / mysql / bin / mysqladmin-u root-p password &quot;123456&quot; </p><p> Third: Install GD library (for PHP support GIF, PNG, JPEG) </p><p> <strong>a. Create a directory to install jpeg6:</strong> </p><p> If you choose the default installation, you may very well specify the path, please create the following folder, if you do not create the folder, it will error </p><p> Error :...... / usr / bin / install-c-m 644 jconfig.h / usr/local/jpeg6/include/jconfig.h / usr / bin / install: can not create a general file \'/ usr / local/jpeg6/include/jconfig.h \': No such file or directory and then began to compile <br /> jpeg-6b./configure - enable-shared - enable-static <br /> make may be wrong <br /> . / Libtool - mode = compile gcc-O2-I.-C. / Jcapimin.cmake:. / Libtool: command not found <br /> make: *** [jcapimin.lo] Error 127 <br /> First, see if there is not installed libtool and libtool-ltdl-devel <br /> rpm-qa | grep libtool <br /> Jpeg-6b then enter the source directory, and then perform the following steps, remember! <br /> cp / usr / share / libtool / config.sub. <br /> cp / usr / share / libtool / config.guess. <br /> Libtool which is to bring the two configuration files jpeg-6b overwrite the corresponding file directory make clean <br /> Not have permission to re-configure the time to first establish the corresponding folder, make install on the line again </p><p> Installation is as follows: </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr/local/jpeg6 </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr/local/jpeg6/bin </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr/local/jpeg6/lib </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr/local/jpeg6/include </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr/local/jpeg6/man </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr/local/jpeg6/man1 </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr/local/jpeg6/man/man1 </p><p> # Cd / root / Software / </p><p> # Tar-zvxf jpegsrc.v6b.tar.gz </p><p> # Cd jpeg6 </p><p> <strong>#. / Configure - prefix = / usr/local/jpeg6 / - enable-shared - enable-static</strong> </p><p> # Make </p><p> # Make install </p><p> <strong>b.libpng package (support for PNG)</strong> </p><p> # Cd / root / Software / </p><p> # Tar-zvxf libpng-(version). Tar.gz </p><p> # Cd libpng-(version) </p><p> #. / Configure - prefix = / usr / local / libpng </p><p> # Make </p><p> #&gt; Make install </p><p> <strong>c. Install freetype</strong> </p><p> # Cd / root / Software / </p><p> # Tar-zvxf freetype-(version). Tar.gz </p><p> # Cd freetype-(version) </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr / local / freetype </p><p> #. / Configure - prefix = / usr / local / freetype </p><p> # Make </p><p> # Make install </p><p></p><p> <strong>d. Install zlib</strong> </p><p> # Cd / root / Software / </p><p> # Tar-zxvf zlib-1.2.3.tar.gz </p><p> # Cd zlib.1.2.3 </p><p> # Mkdir / usr / local / zlib </p><p> #. / Configure - prefix = / usr / local / zlib </p><p> # Make </p><p> # Make install </p><p></p><p> <strong>e. Install GD Library</strong> </p><p> # Cd / root / Software / </p><p> # Tar-zvxf gd-(version). Tar.gz </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr/local/gd2 </p><p> # Cd gd-(version) </p><p> #. / Configure - prefix = / usr/local/gd2 - with-jpeg = / usr/local/jpeg6 - with-zlib-dir = / usr / lo'),(203,'linux','en','/a/web/apache/2010/0422/51.html','Apache Prefork and Worker Performance comparison of test patterns','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Select prefork or worker can be compiled using the-with-mpm = MPM parameters specified, the default is prefork, prefork child process derived by way of pre with a separate child process to handle the different requests, processes independent of each other. Compile and make install in make install, use httpd-l to determine the current use of the MPM is prefork.c. View httpd-mpm.conf configuration file, which contains the following default configuration section: <br /> &lt;IfModule Prefork.c&gt; <br /> StartServers 5 <br /> MinSpareServers 5 <br /> MaxSpareServers 10 <br /> MaxClients 150 <br /> MaxRequestsPerChild 0 <br /> &lt;/ IfModule&gt; <br /> prefork <br /> Control of the process in the initial establishment of &quot;StartServers&quot; sub-process, in order to meet the needs of MinSpareServers set to create a process, wait a second, to create two, wait a second, to create four ... ... so created by the exponential increase number of processes, up to 32 per second, until the value set to meet MinSpareServers up. This model comes in the request can not re-spawn a new process, which reduces the system overhead in order to increase performance. MaxSpareServers set the maximum number of idle processes, and if this value is greater than the number of idle process, Apache will automatically kill off some redundant process. Do not set this value too large, but if MinSpareServers smaller than the value set, Apache will automatically adjust it to MinSpareServers +1. <br /> If the site loads more, consider the same time increase MinSpareServers and MaxSpareServers. MaxRequestsPerChild set is that each child process to handle the requests. Each child in dealing with the &quot;MaxRequestsPerChild&quot; requests will be automatically destroyed. 0 means unlimited, and that the child will never be destroyed. Although the default is set to 0, so that each child process can handle more requests, but set to a nonzero value if there are two important advantages: 1, prevents accidental memory leaks. 2, in the server load down at the right time will automatically reduce the number of child processes. Therefore, according to the load on the server to adjust this value. MaxClients is the most important of these instructions, a set that Apache can handle the request, the greatest impact is the performance parameters of Apache. The default value of 150 is not enough, if the total number of requests has reached this value (via ps-ef | grep http | wc-l to confirm), then subsequent requests will queue until the completion of a request has been processed . This is a lot of system resources while remaining the main reason for HTTP access is very slow. Although theoretically the higher the value, the more requests can be handled, but the restrictions can not be greater than the default Apache 256. ServerLimit recompile Apache directive can not increase the MaxClients. <br /> &lt;IfModule Prefork.c&gt; <br /> ServerLimit 10000 <br /> StartServers 5 <br /> MinSpareServers 5 <br /> MaxSpareServers 10 <br /> MaxClients 10000 <br /> MaxRequestsPerChild 0 <br /> &lt;/ IfModule&gt; </p><p> Worker </p><p> Relative to the prefork, worker support for the new multi-threaded and multi-process mixture model MPM. The use of threads to handle, so it can handle the request of the relative mass, and the system resources is less than the cost of process-based server. However, worker also uses a number of processes, each process has generated more than one thread to get the stability of the server-based process. In the configure-with-mpm = worker after the make build, make install to install. Generated in the default httpd-mpm.conf has the following default configuration section: </p><p> &lt;IfModule Worker.c&gt; <br /> StartServers 2 <br /> MaxClients 150 <br /> MinSpareThreads 25 <br /> MaxSpareThreads 75 <br /> ThreadsPerChild 25 <br /> MaxRequestsPerChild 0 <br /> &lt;/ IfModule&gt; </p><p> Worker process generated by the master control &quot;StartServers&quot; sub-processes, each child process ThreadsPerChild contains a fixed number of threads, each thread independently handle the request. Similarly, in order to not generate thread again when a request comes, MinSpareThreads and MaxSpareThreads set the minimum and maximum number of idle threads; while at the same time MaxClients set the maximum number of incoming clients. If the existing number of threads in the child process can not meet the load, the control process will derive a new child process. MinSpareThreads and MaxSpareThreads maximum default values are 75 and 250. These two parameters did not affect the performance of Apache can be adjusted accordingly in accordance with the actual situation. <br /> ThreadsPerChild worker MPM is most closely associated with the performance of the instruction. The default value is the maximum ThreadsPerChild 64, if the load the larger, 64 is not enough. Explicitly use this time to ThreadLimit directive that the maximum default value is 20000. Worker mode, the total number of requests can be processed simultaneously by ThreadsPerChild value multiplied by the total number of child processes of decision, should be greater than equal to MaxClients. If the load is large, the number of existing child process can not meet, the control process will derive a new child process. The largest number of child processes by default is 16, increase the need to explicitly declare when ServerLimit (maximum is 20,000). Note that, if explicitly declared ServerLimit, then it must be multiplied by a value greater than or equal ThreadsPerChild MaxClients, and MaxClients ThreadsPerChild must be an integer multiple, otherwise Apache will automatically adjust to an appropriate value. <br /> &lt;IfModule Worker.c&gt; <br /> ServerLimit 25 <br /> ThreadLimit 200 <br /> StartServers 3 <br /> MaxClients 2000 <br /> MinSpareThreads 50 <br /> MaxSpareThreads 200 <br /> ThreadsPerChild 100 <br /> MaxRequestsPerChild 0 <br /> &lt;/ IfModule&gt; </p><p> The following is a testing tool built using Apache ab to test the situation on the Server (set the requested index page is 6bytes), cpu% occupancy rate for the cpu, mem for the memory usage (M units), RequestsPerSecond per second processing number of requests. </p><p> 1, Prefor way (ServerLimit, StartServer, MinSpareServers, MaxSpareServers, MaxClients, MaxRequestPerChild) </p><p> -n/-c (ab parameter) Cpu% Mem Requestspersecond <br /> (-, 5,5,10,150,0) <br /> 100000/100 28.8 2,858,434 <br /> 100000/200 29.2 3,048,032 <br /> 100000/500 25.3 3,237,348 <br /> 100000/1000 24.4 3,305,886 <br /> (10000,5,5,10,500,0) <br /> 100000/100 28.7 3,718,345 <br /> 100000/200 27.4 3,897,929 <br /> 100000/500 24.9 4,177,229 <br /> 100000/1000 23.4 4,376,676 <br /> (10000,5,5,10,1000,0) <br /> 100000/100 28.8 4,088,517 <br /> 100000/200 27.0 4,228,045 <br /> 100000/500 24.2 4,557,236 <br /> 100000/1000 22.5 4,706,570 <br /> (10000,5,5,10,1500,0) <br /> 100000/100 29.6 3,308,407 <br /> 100000/200 28.1 3,498,014 <br /> 100000/500 26.4 3,807,290 <br /> 100000/1000 24.0 4,006,686 </p><p> 2, Worker mode </p><p> (ServerLimt, Threadlimt, Startservers, MaxClients, MinspareThread, MaxspareThread, ThreadperChild, MaxRequestPerChild) <br /> -n/-c (ab parameter) cpu% mem RequestsperSecond <br /> (50,500,5,10000,50,200,200,0) <br /> 100000/100 18.6 1,886,020 <br /> 100000/200 20.1 1,955,892 <br /> 100000/500 19.8 2,095,708 <br /> 100000/1000 22.2 2,186,081 <br /> (100,500,5,10000,50,200,100,0) <br /> 100000/100 24.5 2,406,919 <br /> 100000/200 23.6 2,476,798 <br /> 100000/500 24.6 2,546,827 <br /> 100000/1000 22.3 2,716,114 <br /> (200,500,5,10000,50,200,50,0) <br /> 100000/100 27.3 3,017,781 <br /> 100000/200 27.4 3,077,789 <br /> 100000/500 26.0 3,207,141 <br /> 100000/1000 21.8 3,446,110 <br /> Relatively speaking, prefork mode speed to slightly higher than the worker, but it requires the cpu and memory resources are also slightly more than woker. </p><p> How to know the current application mode apache </p><p> httpd-l If you have prefork.c prefork way that is, if it is worker.c that work mode. <br /> Reason busy site requires you to conduct your analysis. Generally of logs. And then make judgments based on the actual situation. </p><p> I have done to optimize a friend. He was a machine every night basically scores LOAD. Is very slow. I log out'),(204,'linux','en','/a/web/tomcat/2010/0422/45.html','Prohibited under the Tomcat directory browsing','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 10pt\">tomcat</span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">directory browsing is enabled by default, but usually do not want to have this feature, and to prohibit directory browsing. This feature can be achieved by configuring</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 10pt\">web.xml</span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">file implementation.</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 10pt\"><br /> &lt;servlet&gt; <br /> &lt;servlet-name&gt; default &lt;/ servlet-name&gt; <br /> &lt;servlet-class&gt; <br /> org.apache.catalina.servlets.DefaultServlet <br /> &lt;/ Servlet-class&gt; <br /> &lt;init-param&gt; <br /> &lt;param-name&gt; debug &lt;/ param-name&gt; <br /> &lt;param-value&gt; 0 &lt;/ param-value&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Init-param&gt; <br /> <span style=\"color: red\">&lt;init-param&gt; <br /> &lt;param-name&gt; listings &lt;/ param-name&gt; <br /> &lt;param-value&gt; false &lt;/ param-value&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Init-param&gt; <br /></span> &lt;load-on-startup&gt; 1 &lt;/ load-on-startup&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Servlet&gt; <br /></span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">And the</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 10pt\">listings</span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">property to <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 10pt\">false.</span> But this is a complete directory can not be <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 10pt; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">viewed.</span></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 10pt\"></span></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(205,'linux','en','/a/lb/2010/0711/301.html','Pure software mode hot standby scheme in-depth analysis','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Database dual hot with two typical methods for a standard of comparison, the two servers via a shared storage device (usually a shared disk array or storage area network SAN), and install the software, double, dual hot standby, known as the shared way. Another way is through pure software approach, commonly referred to as pure software or in mirror mode (Mirror). </p><p> For shared mode, the database on a shared storage device. When a server provides services directly in the storage device to read and write. When the system switch, another server also reads the data on the storage device. </p><p> For pure software approach, through the mirroring software, the data can be copied to another server in real time, so that the same data on the existence of a two servers, if one server fails, you can switch to another time servers. </p><p> Pure software approach to a certain extent, reduce costs, but it also has very significant disadvantages: </p><p> 1. Reliability is relatively poor, the two real-time replication of data between servers is a relatively weak link. </p><p> 2. Once a server interruption, even after the resumption for more sophisticated data synchronization recovery. And, this time the system is not protected. </p><p> 3. There is no transaction mechanism, because of its replication is in the file and disk layer, and copy the database transaction will not affect the success of operations, it is a complete change of data is not the case, there is considerable risk in this. </p><p> Therefore, it is recommended unless a last resort, do not choose a software program. </p><p> On the other hand, there is a parallel database solution, it is not in the file or copy the disk layer, but directly in front of the routing database operations distribution, in parallel to complete the database update transaction mechanism, but also can provide the database parallel service. In this way the current application for SQL SERVER very successful, much better than shared memory mode + dual machine software </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(206,'linux','en','/a/lb/2010/0711/300.html','Linux RAC OCFS file system and INODES','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">ITPUB see in such a case, in a set of <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\">Linux</a></u> in the RAC environment, an OCFS volume inode node has been used, but the database still running. <br /> Files can be properly created, the <a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/\"><u>system</u></a> of several conditions as follows:</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">OS: LINUXAS3 U3 <br /> ORACLE: ORACLE9204 RAC</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">The following is the specific show, / U04 produce only two-node storage of archive log</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">[Root @ db1 /] # cat / etc / issue <br /> Red Hat Enterprise Linux AS release 3 (Taroon Update 3)</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">[Root @ db1 /] # rpm-qa | grep ocfs <br /> ocfs-support-1.0.10-1 <br /> ocfs-tools-1.0.10-1 <br /> ocfs-2.4.21-EL-smp-1.0.13-1</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">[Root @ db1 /] # df-h <br /> Filesystem Size Used Avail Use% Mounted on <br /> / Dev/emcpowerd1 50G 44M 50G 1% / u04</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">[Root @ db1 /] # df-i <br /> Filesystem Inodes IUsed IFree IUse% Mounted on <br /> / Dev/emcpowerd1 409580 409231 349 100% / u04</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><br /> Finally, the author found an explanation from Metalink, that OCFS file system and is usually different, inodes are not here to play the role of the file system normally. <br /> This is the characteristics of OCFS, it is normal.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">References that explain the record as follows:</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">@ OCFS does not have the concept of inodes, however, for the vfs layer in the <br /> @ Kernel we need to fill out structures. The number returned by df-i is <br /> @ Based on diskspace free. It\'s the number of clusterblocsk in the filesystem <br /> @ We dont \'preallocate inodes like most filesystems do. Nor do we HAVE to do <br /> @ That. Not a bug, expected behaviour, not required to do what any other <br /> @ Filesystem does. <br /></span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(207,'linux','en','/a/lb/2010/0711/299.html','LifeKeeper High Availability Cluster Software Fault Tolerance','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> SteelEye\'s LifeKeeper the United States is supporting a variety of soft (WindowNT, Windows2000, various Linux, etc.), high-performance fault-tolerant hardware platform, software can support up to 16 servers <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/lb/\">clustered</a></u> . Lifekeeper software from NCR Corporation and the leading U.S. AT &amp; T Bell Labs. For enterprises, banks and government information services, business services, government services to provide high-availability solution. </p><p> LifeKeeper high availability fault-tolerant cluster software is running on NT, Windows 2000, Linux and NCR Unix platforms. Way to support both software-mirrored disk array cabinets and shared approach and real-time replication to support remote disaster backup and recovery system. So that the user\'s servers, operating systems, database systems and critical data and applications to keep 7 days ÃƒÂ— 24 hours of continuous uninterrupted, providing 99.99% availability. Software includes a number of core parts and for different applications ARK. </p><p> The key features of LifeKeeper </p><p><br /> 1. Without any additional investment in hardware, pure software approach to achieve Fault-tolerant, and to the preparation machine without hardware configuration requirements. <br /><br /> 2. Support for Notes, Exchange, SQL Server, Sybase, Informix, Oracle, SAP and other application-level heat recovery system. <br /><br /> 3. Is the world\'s first set of NT-based operating system supports fault-tolerant software and LINUX platforms. Remote disaster recovery. <br /><br /> 4. Support the expansion of shared disk array cabinets and mirrors in two ways, give users the flexibility to choose, but also to adapt to a variety of models, network architecture, software platforms and applications. <br /><br /> 5. LifeKeeper in shared disk array mirrored or extended any way, can achieve two servers running different applications and their mutual hot backup, the dual Active operation mode. <br /><br /> 6. Shared disk array cabinet mode, can support up to 16 nodes, much larger than other similar systems are supported by two nodes. <br /><br /> 7. Maximize the protection of the client application continuity. The user\'s hardware resources (such as network cards), software resources (such as the NT operating system, database management systems, database applications, e-mail systems, etc.) can in under LifeKeeper protection, conservation of resources when these are a technical failure, LifeKeeper implementation of system resources can be switched at any time. So, LifeKeeper truly a user\'s hardware or software failure of the system resources and application-layer switch on the hot line. <br /><br /> 8. LifeKeeper minimal system resources, without increasing network load, and do not disturb any specific application of any operation. <br /><br /> 9. LifeKeeper truly unattended, automatic application of resources to achieve change, and the graphics interface operation, simple and convenient. <br /><br /> 10. Since put into use, has undergone a large number of transactions the actual peak of the test, its implementation is very efficient and reliable operation, the global market share first. <br /></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(208,'linux','en','/a/lb/2010/0711/298.html','LVS ipvsadm command reference guide','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Ipvsadm command of reference, and used according to their own experience, for a simple translation, in the hope ipvsadm will certainly help users. In order to better enable us to understand the commands manual, which the manual a few terms used in the first brief look: <br /> 1, virtual-service-address: is the ip address of the virtual server <br /> 2, real-service-address: refers to the real server ip address <br /> 3, scheduler: Scheduling </p><p><br /> ipvsadm usage and format are as follows: <br /> QUOTE: <br /> ipvsadm-A | E-t | u | f virutal-service-address: port [-s scheduler] [-p <br /> [Timeout]] [-M netmask] <br /> ipvsadm-D-t | u | f virtual-service-address <br /> ipvsadm-C <br /> ipvsadm-R <br /> ipvsadm-S [-n] <br /> ipvsadm-a | e-t | u | f service-address: port-r real-server-address: port <br /> [-G | i | m] [-w weight] <br /> ipvsadm-d-t | u | f service-address-r server-address <br /> ipvsadm-L | l [options] <br /> ipvsadm-Z [-t | u | f service-address] <br /> ipvsadm - set tcp tcpfin udp <br /> ipvsadm - start-daemon state [- mcast-interface interface] <br /> ipvsadm - stop-daemon <br /> ipvsadm-h </p><p> Command options explained: </p><p> There are two command-option format, long and short, has the same meaning. In actual use, the two can be. <br /> -A - add-service virtual server table in the kernel to add a new virtual server records. Is adding a new virtual server. <br /> -E - edit-service edit the kernel virtual server table in a virtual server record. <br /> -D - delete-service Delete the kernel virtual server table in a virtual server record. <br /> -C - clear clear kernel virtual server table all records. <br /> -R - restore restore virtual server rules <br /> -S - save to save the virtual server rules for the-R option readable output format <br /> -A - add-server virtual server table in the kernel to add a record a new record of the real server. That is, in a virtual server, add a new real server <br /> -E - edit-server editing a virtual server records in the record on a particular real server <br /> -D - delete-server virtual server to delete a record in the record on a particular real server <br /> -L |-l - list Display the kernel virtual server table <br /> -Z - zero virtual service table counter is cleared (clear the current number of connections, etc.) <br /> - Set tcp tcpfin udp set the connection timeout value <br /> - Start-daemon start the synchronization daemon. Behind him can be a master or backup, to illustrate the LVS Router is the master or backup. In this function can also be used keepalived the VRRP functionality. </p><p> - Stop-daemon stop synchronization daemon <br /> -H - help Display help information <br /> -T - tcp-service service-address that the virtual server services are tcp <br /> [Vip: port] or [real-server-ip: port] <br /> -U - udp-service service-address that the virtual server service is udp <br /> [Vip: port] or [real-server-ip: port] <br /> -F - fwmark-service fwmark that is marked by the type of service iptables. <br /> -S - scheduler scheduler using the scheduling algorithm, have several options <br /> rr | wrr | lc | wlc | lblc | lblcr | dh | sh | sed | nq, <br /> The default scheduling algorithm is: </p><p> wlc. <br /> -P - persistent [timeout] persistent services. This option means that many times from the same client request will be handled the same real server. The default timeout is 300 seconds. <br /> -M - netmask netmask persistent granularity mask </p><p> -R - real-server server-address the real server [Real-Server: port] <br /> -G - gatewaying specify the operating mode for the LVS direct routing mode (default mode is LVS) <br /> -I - ipip LVS working mode specified tunnel mode <br /> -M - masquerading as the designated working mode of LVS NAT mode <br /> -W - weight weight weight real server <br /> - Mcast-interface interface specifies the synchronization interface to multicast <br /> -C - connection shows the current connection, such as LVS: ipvsadm-L-c <br /> - Timeout show timeout tcp tcpfin udp\'s value as: ipvsadm-L - timeout <br /> - Daemon daemon status display synchronization <br /> - Stats show statistics <br /> - Rate display rate information <br /> - Sort of virtual servers and sort out the real server <br /> - Numeric-n output IP address and port number of the form </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(209,'linux','en','/a/lb/2010/0610/200.html','case under linux tomcat cluster configuration','2010-06-10','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Configuration before the application of preparatory work before the cluster in the configuration of the cluster configuration information has a good design, the following is the configuration of our cluster information: <br /> Different machines on the same network segment configured on the cluster, the following is based on two machines to do clustering, <br /> Machine type operating system, hardware configuration notes the role of an ordinary PC Linux as 4 IP: 10.3.15.85 PORT: 9080 Managed Server Pc1 <br /> Common PC Linux as 4 IP: 10.3.15.84 PORT: 9080 Managed Server Pc2 <br /> Common PC Linux as 4 IP: 10.3.15.85 PORT: 80 Balancer Server Pc1 <br /><br /> 1 operating system <br /> RedHat Linux as4 <br /> 2 Required Software <br /> Apache 2.0.54 Download <br /> http://apache.freelamp.com/httpd/httpd-2.0.54.tar.gz <br /> Tomcat5.5.9 Download <br /> http://apache.justdn.org/jakarta/ <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/web/tomcat/\">Tomcat</a></u> -5/v5.5.9/bin/jakarta- <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/web/tomcat/\">Tomcat</a></u> -5.5.9.tar.gz <br /> Mod_jk 1.2.14 Download <br /> http://apache.justdn.org/jakarta/tomcat-connectors/jk/source/jk-1.2.14/jakarta-tomcat-connectors-1.2.14-src.tar.gz <br /> Jdk 1_5_0_04 Download <br /> http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/download.jsp <br /> Note: Download the package file will be required in the / usr / local directory, you can also use jdk1.4 <br /> 3 Installation Steps <br /> Install JDK 3.1 <br /> # Cd / usr / local / <br /> # Chmod 777 jdk-1_5_0_04-linux-i586-rpm.bin <br /> # ./jdk-1.5.0_04-linux-i586-rpm.bin <br /> # Cd / usr / java / <br /> # Ln-s / usr/java/jdk-1_5_0_04 / usr / local / java <br /> # Vi / etc / profile <br /> # Add the following <br /> JAVA_HOME = / usr / local / java / <br /> CLASSPATH = / usr / local / java / lib / dt.jar: / usr / local / java / lib / tools.jar <br /> PATH = / usr / local / java / bin: $ PATH <br /> export PATH JAVA_HOME CLASSPATH <br /><br /> Installing Apache 3.2 <br /> # Cd / usr / local / <br /> # Tar xvfz httpd-2.0.54.tar.gz <br /> # Cd httpd-2.0.54 <br /> #. / Configure-prefix = / usr / local / apache-enable-module = so <br /> # Make <br /> # Make install <br /> # Cd / usr / local / apache / conf <br /> # Vi. / Httpd.conf <br /> Listen 80 will be modified to Listen &lt;Your IP&gt;: 80 <br /> Will be revised ServerName ServerName &lt;HOST-NAME&gt;: 80 <br /> Add in the DirectoryIndex index.jsp <br /> # Cd / usr / local / apache / bin / <br /> #. / Apachectl configtest <br /> If the display indicates a successful installation Syntax ok <br /> #. / Apachectl start <br /> Start the apache service, access to port 80 of the machine to see whether the normal port <br /> #. / Apachectl stop <br /> Close Services Note: prefix defined in the installation path of apache <br /><br /> Install Tomcat 3.3 <br /> # Cd / usr / local / <br /> # Tar xvfz jakarta-tomcat-5.5.9.tar.gz <br /> # Ln-s / usr/local/jakarta-tomcat-5.5.9 / usr / local / tomcat <br /> # Vi / usr / local / tomcat / bin / catalina.sh <br /> JAVA_HOME = / usr / local / java <br /> Start the service, access to the local 8080 port, see the port is normal <br /> # / Usr / local / tomcat / bin / startup.sh / startup.bat <br /> Close Service <br /> # / Usr / local / tomcat / bin / shutdown.sh / shutdown.bat <br /> 3.4 Installation JK <br /> # Cd / usr / local / <br /> # Tar xzvf jakarta-tomcat-connectors-1.2.14-src.tar.gz <br /> # Cd jakarta-tomcat-connectors-1.2.14-src/jk/native <br /> # Chmod 755 buildconf.sh <br /> #. / Buildconf.sh <br /> #. / Configure-with-apxs = / usr / local / apache / bin / apxs <br /> # Make <br /> # Make install <br /> # Cd / usr / local / jakarta-tomcat-connectors-jk1.2.14-src/jk/native/apache-2.0 / <br /> # Cp mod_jk.so / usr / local / apache / modules / <br /><br /> 4 System Integration <br /> 4.1 at the end of the file add the following statements best <br /> # Vi / usr / local / apache / conf / httpd.conf <br /><br /> # Load mod_jk <br /> LoadModule jk_module modules / mod_jk.so <br /> # Configure mod_jk <br /> JkWorkersFile conf / workers.properties <br /> JkLogFile logs / mod_jk.log <br /> JkLogLevel info <br /> JkMount / *. jsp loadbalancer <br /> JkMount / servlet / * loadbalancer <br /> JkMount / application / * loadbalancer <br /><br /> Add workers.properties 4.2 <br /> # Vi / usr / local / apache / conf / workers.properties <br /> As follows: <br /><br /> worker.list = loadbalancer <br /> # Define a \'local_worker\' worker using ajp13 <br /> worker.worker1.port = 8009 <br /> worker.worker1.host = 10.3.15.84 <br /> worker.worker1.type = ajp13 <br /> worker.worker1.lbfactor = 1 <br /> worker.worker1.local_worker = 0 <br /> worker.worker1.cachesize = 1000 <br /> worker.worker1.cache_timeout = 600 <br /> worker.worker1.socket_keepalive = 1 <br /> worker.worker1.socket_timeout = 0 <br /> worker.worker1.reclycle_timeout = 300 <br /> worker.worker1.retries = 3 <br /><br /> # Define another \'local_worker\' worker using ajp13 <br /> worker.worker2.port = 8009 <br /> worker.worker2.host = 10.3.15.85 <br /> worker.worker2.type = ajp13 <br /> worker.worker2.lbfactor = 1 <br /> worker.worker2.local_worker = 1 <br /> worker.worker2.cachesize = 1000 <br /> worker.worker2.cache_timeout = 600 <br /> worker.worker2.socket_keepalive = 1 <br /> worker.worker2.socket_timeout = 0 <br /> worker.worker1.reclycle_timeout = 300 <br /> worker.worker1.retries = 3 <br /><br /> # Define the LB worker <br /> worker.loadbalancer.type = lb <br /> worker.loadbalancer.balanced_workers = worker1, worker2 <br /> worker.loadbalancer.local_worker_only = 1 <br /> worker.loadbalancer.sticky_session = true <br /> worker.loadbalancer.sticky_session_force = true <b'),(210,'linux','en','/a/lb/2010/0520/106.html','Associated load-balancing software architecture description','2010-05-20','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<html> <font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Ve