 Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">)</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \"Verdana\",\"sans-serif\"; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><br /> Ã‚Â· Heartbeat, ( <a href=\"http://www.linux-ha.org/\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #3300ff; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt\">http://www.linux-ha.org</span></a> )</span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \"Verdana\",\"sans-serif\"; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"></span></p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \"Verdana\",\"sans-serif\"; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><b><span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">1,</span> ipchains</b> <br /> ipchains</span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">is famous</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \"Verdana\",\"sans-serif\"; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Firewall</span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">software under <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \"Verdana\",\"sans-serif\"; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Linux,</span></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \"Verdana\",\"sans-serif\"; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">ipchains</span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">in <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \"Verdana\",\"sans-serif\"; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Linux,</span></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \"Verdana\",\"sans-serif\"; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Linux</span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">kernel and out of control data, including packet filtering and camouflage. In</span>'),(211,'linux','en','/a/lb/2010/0422/47.html','About Lvs-depth study of scheduling policies','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Lvs basic questions: </p><p> Usage in ipvsadm, many documents for the persistent argument is that description. <br /> -P-persistent [timeout] <br /> Persistent service. This option means that many times from the same client request will be handled the same real server. The default timeout is 300 seconds. </p><p> &quot;From the same client&quot; how to understand it, is based on the IP client or browser-based client Cookie it should be based on the source address. In fact, there is a parameter [-M netmask], it noted that the matching source address means such as-p 900-M 255.255.255.0 <br /> After the network is the same as the address mask request to use the same template <br /> IXDBA.NET Community Forums so 10.1.9.8 and 10.1.9.9 to access the same two machines vs the same time to use the same template, that is, to the same rs. </p><p> Rr scheduling algorithm is very simple, it only maintains a circular queue of pointers to point rs, if the vs request scheduling, rr rs put within the meaning of the current pointer in this connection request as rs, and then after the pointer. It no matter what the template . </p><p> Even if the set &quot;quiescent = yes&quot;, the scheduler can dispatch the right to request to the normal node, then the session in the original node can not be copied due to the normal node is lost, then there will be requirements of the client to re-login, etc. suggest that at this time can be saved to a separate session fs, mysql, network storage. </p><p> Lvs join algorithm: </p><p> For the configuration of the p, vs, the system create a new connection for example &lt;x:1234,y:80&gt; before scheduling and create a connection template for example &lt;x:0,y:0,z:0&gt;, the connection template p, timeout parameters, such as 900s, and then used the template to create this connection, for example &lt;x:1234,y:80,z:80&gt;, so data are from the connection before. Then there &lt;x:1235,y:443&gt; if a new request, vs will be looking to find a template, if found, do not re-schedule, but according to the template provided to create real connections rs &lt;x: 1235, y : 443, z: 443&gt;, and also reset the timeout of the template that has reset to the 900s. </p><p> 1. Template is actually a connection, but rather special fills, ipvsadm-Lcn should be able to see <br /> 2. The connection timeout parameter is p, if the template is reused, the timeout to be reset. <br /> If the user does not exceed each of the http request timeout, the user requests are sent to the template fixed rs. </p><p> lvs process operation </p><p> Packet -&gt; vs-&gt; find whether there is a connection <br /> 1. Exists under the connection contract <br /> 2. Does not exist, a new connection, then start scheduling </p><p> If vs is a common server, perform the scheduling algorithm to select a rs, and then create the connection, and then sent if vs is the p server (set-p-persistent parameters of DR server), the first to see if there templates available, if any, is based on the template to create a connection, and then contracting. <br /> If no template is available to perform a rs scheduling scheduler and create a template, and then create a connection based on the template, the final contract. </p><p> Finally thanks to CU qtdszws the help of friends, thank you! <br /></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(212,'linux','en','/a/st/2010/0711/307.html','Bottlenecks for the storage array analysis and discussion','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> On the articles we analyzed the inner workings of raid5 and raid10 details, here we mainly analyze the <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/st/\">storage</a></u> array, the bottleneck, because the emergence of bottlenecks, and the raid is a very different way, so we need to analyze the specific differences in raid5 and raid10. <br /> The bottleneck is mainly reflected in the array 2, the throughput and IOPS. </p><p> 1, the throughput of the throughput depends on the array architecture, the size of the Fibre Channel (now the array are generally fiber array, as such SSA SCSI array, we do not discuss), and the number of hard drives. Array architecture varies with each array, they also exist within the bandwidth (similar to the pc the system bus), but under normal circumstances, the internal bandwidth is designed to be adequate, not where the bottleneck. <br /> The impact of fiber channel is relatively large, such as data warehousing environment, data flow requirements of a large, and a 2Gb Fibre card, can support the maximum flow should be 2Gb / 8 (small B) = 250MB / s ( Big B) the actual flow, when the four fiber cards in order to achieve 1GB / s of the actual flow, so the data warehouse environment can be considered for 4Gb Fibre card. <br /> Finally, talk about hard limits, here is the most important bottlenecks in the current surface, when no longer exists, depends on the number of hard drives, and I look at the different hard drives listed below can support the flow of size: <br /> 10 K rpm 15 K rpm ATA <br /> --- --- --- <br /> 10M / s 13M / s 8M / s <br /> So, assuming there is an array of optical fiber 120 15K rpm hard disk, the drive can support the largest flow is 120 * 13 = 1560MB / s, 2Gb Fibre card if it is, you may need six to be able to, and 4Gb Fibre Cards 3-4 is enough. </p><p> 2, IOPS <br /> The main decision depends on the array IOPS algorithm, cache hit rate, and the disk number. Array algorithm for different arrays vary, as we have recently encountered in the hds usp above, probably because ldev (lun) queue or resource constraints exist, and a single ldev the iops would not increase, so, before using this store is necessary to understand some of the storage algorithm rules and restrictions. <br /> cache hit rate depends on the data distribution, cache size the size of the data access rules, and cache algorithms, if the full discussion down here will become very complicated, can one day good discussion. I am here only to emphasize a cache hit rate, if an array, read cache hit rate as high as possible, the general said it could support more IOPS, Why? The following should be discussed with us the hard disk IOPS with relationship. <br /> Hard constraints, each physical hard disk can handle is limited IOPS, such as 10 K rpm 15 K rpm ATA <br /> --- --- --- <br /> 10,015,050 <br /> Similarly, if there is an array of optical fiber 120 15K rpm hard drive, then it can sustain the maximum IOPS of 120 * 150 = 18,000, the limit of the theoretical value for the hardware, if more than this value, the hard disk of the response may become very slow and can not properly provide services. <br /> In addition, we also discussed on the article in raid5 and raid10, read iops no difference, however, the same business writing iops, ultimately rests on the disk iops there is a difference, and we evaluated it is exactly the disk IOPS, limit if it reaches the disk, the performance is certainly not increase the. <br /> We assume that a case, the business iops is 10,000, read cache hit rate is 30%, 60% read iops, write iops 40%, the disk number is 120, then calculate the situation in raid5 and raid10, each a disk iops have. </p><p> IXDBA.NET Technical Community </p><p> raid5: </p><p> Single-block disk iops = (10000 * (1-0.3) * 0.6 + 4 * (10000 * 0.4)) / 120 <br /> = (4200 + 16000) / 120 <br /> = 168 <br /> Here 10000 * (1-0.3) * 0.6 that is read iops, ratio is 0.6, get rid of cache hit, actually, only 4,200 iops <br /> The 4 * (10000 * 0.4) that the written iops, because each write, in raid5, the actual occurrence of the four io, so write iops to 16,000 </p><p> Raid5 in order to consider when writing, it read 2 hits can also occur, so a more accurate calculation is: </p><p> Single-block disk iops = (10000 * (1-0.3) * 0.6 + 2 * (10000 * 0.4) * (1-0.3) + 2 * (10000 * 0.4)) / 120 <br /> = (4200 + 5600 + 8000) / 120 <br /> = 148 <br /> Iops calculated as a single disk 148, the basic disk limit reached </p><p> raid10 </p><p> Single-block disk iops = (10000 * (1-0.3) * 0.6 + 2 * (10000 * 0.4)) / 120 <br /> = (4200 + 8000) / 120 <br /> = 102 <br /> You can see, because raid10 for a write operation, occurs only 2 times io, therefore, the same pressure, the same disk, each disk iops only 102, far below the limit of the disk iops. </p><p> In a practical case, a lot of pressure recovery standby (here mainly to write, and write a small io), using a raid5 solution, found poor performance, by analyzing each disk iops during peak periods , fast 200, resulting in extremely slow response speed giant. Later transformed into raid10, to avoid this performance problem, each disk iops down to 100 or so. <br /></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(213,'linux','en','/a/st/2010/0711/306.html','How to choose your own level raid','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> How to choose the right RAID level? </p><p> There are different RAID configuration or &quot;class&quot;, each level has its own unique advantages. Understand the RAID level to enable you to determine the server reliability, data availability and storage performance of the right combination to meet specific e-business needs. Intel Integrated RAID software supports the most widely used RAID level: 0,1,5, and 10. </p><p> RAID 0 level will be assigned to the data base with more than one disk, there is no redundancy or parity. The main features of the RAID level is extremely high data throughput speeds. Data access to multiple disks make disk access more efficient, which improves read performance data. Any one disk fails the data stored will be lost </p><p> Copy using two hard drives store data, we implemented a RAID1-level (called disk mirroring), in most cases through the software. If a hard disk fails, it will be all the data (and software applications) to save to another hard disk. Although it provides maximum fault tolerance, but requires twice the disk number, so RAID1 level is extremely expensive option. With the declining cost of disk technology, RAID1-level optimization of data availability has become a viable option. </p><p> RAID 5 level will baseband section and the &quot;parity&quot; the combination together, this case, the data distribution in the online group\'s hard drive. Parity RAID controller data to understand the data stored on your hard drive. Suppose that a hard disk fails, the controller can use the parity information to re-create the lost data. RAID5-level data to allow both read and write, which is data-intensive applications that require high performance provided support. You can adjust the size of the baseband section to optimize performance, the Intel Integrated RAID software support this feature. RAID5 reasonable price level provides the best performance and data security, so far it is very popular. </p><p> RAID 10 level (0 +1) is a RAID0 and RAID1-level combination of grade, it will mirror the baseband section, and together the disk. 0 RAID10 level provides a fast performance and data protection features. In this configuration, the data is distributed across several hard disk (which is similar with the 0 level), and the data of each disk are copied to another disk, thereby protecting the data. We recommend that the best performance and data availability requirements of a small network with 10. </p><p> From large databases to e-mail systems and Web servers, they all select the appropriate RAID configuration are required to provide all the e-commerce data protection, server reliability and storage performance.. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(214,'linux','en','/a/st/2010/0711/305.html','Three major comparative analysis of iSCSI Initiator software','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">To implement iSCSI read and write, in addition to the use of specific hardware devices, but also by software methods, the server-side simulation for the iSCSI initiator or target side, the use of existing processor card with ordinary Ethernet iSCSI connectivity resources to achieve .</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">iSCSI or internet SCSI, is the IETF developed a storage transport protocol standard for the SCSI data block image into Ethernet data packets. iSCSI protocol is essentially a SCSI across the IP network to transmit data block approach, read and write requests initiated by the source of equipment called the Initiator (initiator), the requested destination device is known as Target. In this way the network in IP mode on a block-level access to large amounts of data.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">To implement iSCSI read and write, in addition to using specific hardware device, but also through software means, the server-side simulation for the iSCSI initiator or target side, the use of existing processor card with ordinary Ethernet iSCSI connectivity resources to achieve . At present, most of the iSCSI Target simulation software to be paid for mostly commercial software, but there are many free iSCSI initiator software is available for selection.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">IXDBA.NET Technical Community</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">Microsoft iSCSI Initiator</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">Microsoft provides software initiated iSCSI that allows Windows client initiated iSCSI Ethernet card into the device simulation in order to iSCSI target devices on the network access demand launched to build iSCSI online.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">The latest version of Microsoft iSCSI Initiator version 2.04, supports Windows 2000/XP/Server 2003 and other Microsoft operating environment, and the respective support x64, IA64, x86 processor platforms such as the version. Download the installation is complete, the Discovery menu, enter the iSCSI target device or iqn IP address, you can choose the Target menu to establish a connection with the iSCSI device, through the IP network to access iSCSI storage devices, also supports multi-path transmission.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">Linux-iSCSI</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">There are two versions of Linux kernel 2.4/2.6\'s iSCSI Initiator, in use, the system must be ready kernel-source, kernel, gcc, perl, Apache, and other related files. Download and complete the compilation, the first / etc / iscsi.conf iSCSI configuration within the configuration to match the current iSCSI target device using the correct URL, user name and password, next to # / etc / init.d / iscsi start start iSCSI devices, and disk partition fdisk command, and finally with the mkdir and mount command to mount the disk drive.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">Solaris iSCSI Initiator</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">Solaris 10 has built-in iSCSI Initiator software, including SPARC 64, x64 and IA-32 and other processor platforms can support. Sun related to the iSCSI driver integrated iSCSI Device Driver and Utilities updates, the current version has been updated to 5.10.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">Use, first with the svcadm enable svc: / network / iscsi_initiator first startup instruction format iSCSI Initiator, the operation mainly depends on the next iscsiadm command, first to iscsiadm add discovery-address command to set the target device address, and then iscsiadm modify initiator-node changes the connection between the target device settings, and then order using the devfsadm-c iscsi, format, newfs command to create a new disk and other areas, the last area and then mount command to mount it to a disk. <br /></span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(215,'linux','en','/a/st/2010/0711/304.html','Introduction of several common storage backup systems','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Common data backup <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/\">systems</a></u> are Host-Base, LAN-Base Structure-based SAN LAN-Free, Server-Free and other structures. </p><p> Host-Based backup: </p><p> Host-Based is the traditional structure of the data backup tape library this structure directly connected to the server, and only data backup service for servers. In most cases, the backup server comes with most of the tape drive, the backup operation is by manual operation is often conducted in a way. </p><p> Host-Based backup structure has the advantage of fast data transfer, backup and simple management; disadvantage is not conducive to the sharing of backup system is not suitable for large data backup requirements now. </p><p> LAN-Based backup: </p><p> LAN-Based backup data in the system is web-based transmission. Which to configure a server as backup server, which will be responsible for the entire system backup operations. Tape library is connected to a server, data backup backup object in the data over the network to implement a backup tape library. </p><p> LAN-Based backup structure has the advantage of saving investment, tape library sharing, centralized backup management; its disadvantage is that pressure on the network transmission. </p><p> LAN-Free backup: </p><p> LAN-Free and Server-Free backup system is based on SAN ( <a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/st/\"><u>storage</u></a> area network) based on its structure as shown below. SAN-based backup is a completely solve the need to occupy the traditional backup solutions for LAN bandwidth issues. It uses a new architecture, the tape library and disk array of fiber each node as an independent, multi-host shared tape library backup, data flow through the network no longer directly transmitted from the disk array, tape library, network bandwidth is a need (LAN-Free) solutions. </p><p> With the current SAN technology continues to progress, LAN-Free structure is already quite mature, and Server-Free backup structure is not mature enough. </p><p> LAN-Free has the advantage of unified management of data backup, backup speed, network transmission pressure is small, tape library resource sharing; disadvantage is that high investment. </p><p> Using IBM Tivoly Storage Manager software, with IBM LTO tape library, etc., can achieve all of these backups. </p><p></p><p> other <br /> The choice of data backup </p><p> The main ways of the current data backup: LAN backup, LAN Free backup and SAN Server-Free backup of three. LAN backup for all storage types are available, LAN Free backup and SAN Server-Free backup for SAN-based storage only. </p><p> Traditional LAN-based backup requires the backup on each host to install a tape backup on the local system, using LAN backup strategy, when the data is not very big, centralized backup can be used. A central backup server will be installed in the LAN, and then the application server and workstation configured as a backup server to the client. Accept the central backup server running the backup on the client agent\'s request, the data passed to it through the management LAN, connected to a local tape drive resources. This approach provides a centralized, easy to manage backup program, and through the sharing of tape drives in the network resource efficiency. </p><p> LAN-Free backup of the data transmitted through the LAN, when a larger amount of data to backup, backup tight time window, the network prone to clogging. In the SAN environment, can be stored in the network LAN-Free backup, you need to backup the server through the SAN to connect to the tape machine, the LAN-Free backup client software trigger, the read data to back up, back up through the SAN to a shared the tape drive. This independent network LAN traffic can not be transferred, and its CPU resources required to operate way below the LAN, because the fiber channel connection does not require the server\'s TCP / IP stack, and some level of error checking can be within the Fibre Channel hardware to complete. In many solutions require a host to manage the shared storage devices and data used to find and restore the backup database. </p><p> SAN Server-Free Backup LAN Free backup on the need to take back the host CPU resources, if the backup process can be completed within the SAN, and a large number of data streams without flow through the server, you can greatly reduce the backup of the production system. SAN Server-Free backup is one such technology. </p><p> Backup the current mainstream software, such as IBM Tivoli, Veritas, were in support of the three backup programs. Three programs, LAN backup of the smallest amount of data, most of the server resource consumption, the lowest cost; LAN free backup data volume number, smaller footprint on the server, the cost higher; SAN Server-free backup solution to backup in a short time large amounts of data, at least on the server resource consumption, but the highest cost. Small customers can choose according to the actual situation. <br /> other </p><p> Traditional Backup: How helpless wits </p><p> In the traditional backup mode, each host is equipped with a dedicated disk or tape storage systems, host of the data must be backed up to tape in the device or special local disk array. Thus, even if a tape drive (or tape library) is idle, the other host can not use it for backup, the tape resource utilization is low. In addition, different operating system platforms used in backup and recovery procedures are generally not the same, which makes the backup job and overall management of resources becomes more complex. </p><p> Later, to produce a special tape to overcome the low utilization rate of the improvements of the system: the resource by a master tape backup / restore server control, and backup and recovery process is controlled by some management software. Master backup server to receive the other server through LAN or WAN incoming data and the disk or tape into the public system. This centralized storage in ways that greatly improved the efficiency of resource use tape. But it also has a fatal deficiency: network bandwidth will be the backup and recovery process of the potential bottlenecks. </p><p> Is there a more advanced solution, when the backup system to minimize resource consumption, while ensuring the system\'s high availability and flexibility? </p><p> LAN-free backup: The first one mundane children </p><p> One way is to use LAN-free technology. The so-called LAN-free, the data is backed up directly without a local area network, that user can simply tape drive or tape library and other backup device connected to the SAN, each server to be backed up data can be sent directly to the shared backup device do not have to go through local area network links. Because the server to share large data storage devices is carried out through the SAN network, LAN, bear only the communication between the server (rather than data transfer) missions. </p><p> 2 common means of implementation </p><p> LAN-free implementation of a variety of ways. Typically, users need for each server with a Fibre Channel adapter, the adapter is responsible for these servers connected to one or more tape drives (or tape library) connected to SAN. At the same time, with a particular need for the server management software, through which the system able to block format data from the server memory, the SAN tape drive or transferred to the tape library. </p><p> There is also a common implementation of LAN-free approach, in this structure, the main backup server management software can start the other server data backup operations. Block format of the data from the disk array through the SAN to store data transmitted to the temporary memory of the backup server, after transmission through SAN to the tape drive or tape library. </p><p> LAN-free backup inadequate </p><p> &quot;No one is perfect&quot;, LAN-free technology is also less than obvious. First, it is still involved in the server backup data from one storage device to another storage device in the process, to a certain extent, take up valuable CPU processing time and server memory. Another problem is, LAN-free recovery technology, unsatisfactory, it is very dependent on the user\'s application. Many products do not support file-level or directory-level recovery, image-level recovery to become more common. Image-level recovery is to copy the image from the tape back to disk, if you need to quickly restore a single file, the whole operation will become very troublesome. </p><p> In addition, different vendors implement LAN-free mechanism to vary, which causes the backup process will be required for compatibility problems between systems. </p><p> LAN-free implementation of the complex and often require large hardware and software purchasing costs. </p><p> Serverless Backup: icing on the cake The second measure children </p><p> Another way to reduce resource consumption of the system approach is to use no server (Serverless) backup technology. It is an extension of LAN-free, can provide data to the SAN structure in the direct transmission between the two storage devices, usually between disk arrays and tape libraries. One of the main advantages of this approach is the need for caching data in the server, significantly reduces host CPU occupancy, improve the efficiency of the operating system to help companies do more work. </p><p> 2 common means of implementation </p><p> As with LAN-free, non-implementation of the server backups are also several ways. Typically, the backup data through a device called the Data Mover transfers from the disk array to the tape library. The device may be Fibre Channel switches, storage routers, intelligent tape or disk device or a server. Data Mover command is executed to transfer data from one storage device to another device. One way to implement this process is by means of SCSI-3 extended copy command, which enables the server to send commands to the storage device, instructions which transfer data directly to another device, without going through server memory. Received extended copy data mover command, perform the appropriate function. </p><p> Another method is to use the Network Data Management Protocol (NDMP). This agreement is actually for the server, backup and recovery applications and backup devices and other components to act as an interface between the communication. In the implementation process, NDMP to commands from the server to the backup application, with the NDMP-compliant backup software will start the actual work of data transmission and data transmission is not through the server memory. The purpose is to facilitate the NDMP heterogeneous backup and recovery environment process and enhance backup and recovery of different vendors management software and storage hardware compatibility. </p><p> The advantages of server-backup </p><p> No server backup and LAN-free backup has many similar advantages. If no server backup, the source device, the destination device and the SAN devices are the main components of the data channel. Although the server is still involved in the backup process, but greatly reduce the burden, because it is basically similar to the role of traffic police, only for the command, not used for loading and transport, not the primary backup data channel. </p><p> Serverless backup technology to shorten backup and recovery with the time spent advantages. Because the backup process on the dedicated high-speed storage network, and the decision is a storage device throughput speed, rather than the server\'s processing power, so the system performance will be greatly enhanced. In addition, if no-server backup technology, data can be transmitted in the form of data streams to multiple tape libraries or disk arrays. </p><p> As for shortcomings, though greatly reduced the burden on the server, but still need a backup application software (and its host server) to control the backup process. Metadata must be recorded in the database backup software, which still need to take up CPU resources. </p><p> As with LAN-free, non-server backup mentioned above may lead to the same kind of compatibility issues. Moreover, no server backup may be difficult and costly. Finally, if no server backup applications to be more extensive and greater recovery function remains to be improved. </p><p> Balancing the pros and cons and then decided upon </p><p> We discussed earlier under the Fibre Channel environment, LAN-free and serverless backup technology, because some structural integration of IP-based technology, such as iSCSI, especially as future IP storage network storage technology in the possession of strong advantages, LAN- free and serverless backup technology solutions will become more widespread. </p><p> LAN-free and serverless backup is not suitable for all applications. If you have a large data repository to be 7 ÃƒÂ— 24 readily available, no server backup may be a good choice. But must ensure that you have made it clear how long the recovery process, because this will underestimate the face a more serious problem than at the beginning. </p><p> On the other hand, if you have a database of moderate size can tolerate some downtime, then the traditional backup and recovery technology may be your quite good choice. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(216,'linux','en','/a/st/2010/0711/303.html','Troubleshooting and maintenance of disk arrays Notes','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> The following information easily lead to loss of RAID disk array: <br /> 1. The hard disk in order messed up, causing the boot disk array is not up </p><p> 2. Array disks dropped to two or two more, the collapse of the array </p><p> 3. Expansion of the disk array is not yet complete when the go out into the write data, resulting in the collapse of the array </p><p> 4. Dropped a hard drive, put a good plate Rebuild, cause data is not normal </p><p> 5. The physical disk fails, such as: bad circuit board, heads damage, bad disk, bad sectors, etc. </p><p> 6. In the absence of any exceptional circumstances, the array is not normal boot </p><p> 7. A sudden power outage caused by RAID disk array card information loss </p><p> 8. The hard drive in the wrong order, start the system, or change the configuration; </p><p> If you find raid disk array failure. Please take the following action. </p><p> 1, the system power off, the hard drive in order of number </p><p> 2, will report to the disk array disk array vendor or professional data recovery company </p><p> 3, non-professionals do not try to Rebuild, initialization, synchronization, data recovery attempt to action </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(217,'linux','en','/a/st/2010/0711/302.html','How to test disk and array performance','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Following a similar method to test writing ability </p><p><br /> time dd if = / dev / zero of = / oradata / biddb / testind / testfile.dbf bs = 1024000 count = 1000 </p><p><br /> IO can be used during the system (unix): </p><p><br /> iostat-xnp 2 shows the extent Busy </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(218,'linux','en','/a/st/2010/0623/249.html','iSCSI configuration Raiders (ISCSI Target / initiator)','2010-06-23','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> 1.Target side configuration <br /> end of the target with disk disk array or other hosts. Iscsitarget tool disk space by mapping to the network, initiator side can look to find and use the disk. <br /> Note that a target number of target host can be mapped to the network, which can map multiple block devices to the network. <br /> 1) Package <br /> iscsitarget <br /> From <a href=\"http://sourceforge.net/projects/iscsitarget/files/\">http://sourceforge.net/projects/iscsitarget/files/</a> download the latest version. <br /> 2) compile and install is very simple, unpack, compile, install on the can. <br /> tar zxvf iscsitarget-1.4.19.tar.gz <br /> cd iscsitarget-1.4.19 / <br /> make <br /> make install <br /> The package will iscsitarget kernel module needed, user-level tools, services, startup scripts, configuration files, man manuals installed on your system, including: <br /> iscsi_trgt.ko kernel module <br /> ietd iscsitarget daemon <br /> ietadm iscsitarget the user-level management tools <br /> / Etc / init.d / iscsi-target iscsitarget startup script <br /> / Etc / ietd.conf iscsitarget profile <br /> / Etc / initiators.allow control initiator access to the target. <br /> / Etc / initiators.deny control initiator access to the target. <br /> / Etc / iet / targets.allow been controlling access to different target. <br /> 3) Configure / etc / ietd.conf </p><p> Target iqn.2001-04.com.example: storage.disk2.sys1.xyz <br /> Lun 0 Path = / dev/sda1, Type = fileio <br /> Alias lun0 </p><p> General description: <br /> Target iqn.2001-04.com.example: storage.disk2.sys1.xyz ISCSI Target, said the naming of the same name should be unique within a subnet, the standard naming is: <br /> &quot;Target&quot; + target name (the format is as follows: iqn.yyyy-mm. &lt;reversed Domain name&gt; [: identifier]) <br /> &quot;Lun 0 Path = / dev/sda1&quot; said the block device number is 0, mapped the disk is / dev/sda1. <br /> Type this configuration is set to &quot;fileio&quot;, I mainly used to store a disk share. <br /> Of course, you can set against the need to: &quot;file&quot; or &quot;LVM&quot;. <br /> In addition there are many other parameters can be set, the specific reference: <br /> <a href=\"http://manpages.ubuntu.com/manpages/hardy/man5/ietd.conf.5.html\">http://manpages.ubuntu.com/manpages/hardy/man5/ietd.conf.5.html</a> </p><p> 4) Start iscsitarget <br /> / Etc / init.d / iscsi-target start </p><p> 2.inititor side configuration <br /> 1) Package source package is open-iscsi, rpm package after package, the name iscsi-initiator-utils. <br /> 2) installed the following documents at the main <br /> / Etc / iscsi / iscsid.conf <br /> / Etc / rc.d / init.d / iscsi <br /> / Etc / rc.d / init.d / iscsid <br /> / Sbin / iscsi-iname <br /> / Sbin / iscsiadm <br /> / Sbin / iscsid <br /> / Sbin / iscsistart <br /> / Var / lib / iscsi <br /> / Var / lib / iscsi / ifaces <br /> / Var / lib / iscsi / isns <br /> / Var / lib / iscsi / nodes <br /> / Var / lib / iscsi / send_targets <br /> / Var / lib / iscsi / slp <br /> / Var / lib / iscsi / static <br /> / Var / lock / iscsi </p><p> 3) Connect the target <br /> First, to ensure iscsid daemon started, testing whether a series of operations will fail iscsiadm: <br /> / Etc / init.d / iscsid start </p><p> That target: <br /> iscsiadm-m discovery-t sendtargets-p &lt;iSCSI target ip&gt;: &lt;port&gt; <br /> &lt;port&gt; Is 3260 by default, unless you have a special setting. </p><p> Establish a connection with the target: <br /> iscsiadm-m node-T &lt;target-name&gt;-p &lt;ip-address&gt;: &lt;port&gt; - login <br /> Where target-name is found on the step when the acquired target. </p><p> This time through the fdisk-l can see the map over the disk, the disk can be the same as using the local disk to format, partition and other operations. <br /> Experiment through the following command: <br /> fdisk / dev / sdc <br /> mkfs.ext3 / dev/sdc1 <br /> mount / dev/sdc1 / mnt <br /> dd if = / dev / zero of = 100M.img bs = 1M count = 100 </p><p> 3.target and use CHAP authentication between initiator. <br /> CHAP authentication, there are two, one is for the discovery, that if it does not validate the user name and password, they can not initiator side &quot;-m discovery&quot; found in any of the specified host target. <br /> Command will return authentication fails, as follows: <br /> $ Iscsiadm-m discovery-t sendtargets-p 192.168.29.224 <br /> iscsiadm: Login failed to authenticate with target <br /> iscsiadm: discovery login to 192.168.29.224 rejected: initiator error (02/01), non-retryable, giving up </p><p> The other is for the node login, that fruit does not meet the authentication user name and password, can not initiator-side code - login login one on the specified host target. <br /> Command will return authentication fails, as follows: <br /> $ Iscsiadm-m discovery-t sendtargets-p 192.168.29.224 # successfully discover the target on the specified host <br /> 192.168.29.224:3260,1 iqn.2001-04.com.example: storage.disk2.sys1.xyz <br /> $ Iscsiadm-m node-T iqn.2001-04.com.example: storage.disk2.sys1.xyz-p 192.168.29.224 - login # can not be authenticated, the login fails <br /> Logging in to [iface: default, target: iqn.2001-04.com.example: storage.disk2.sys1.xyz, portal: 192.168.29.224,3260] <br /> iscsiadm: Could not login to [iface: default, target: iqn.2001-04.com.example: storage.disk2.sys1.xyz, portal: 192.168.29.224,3260]: <br /> iscsiadm: initiator reported error (15 - already exists) </p><p> 1) In the initiator-side configuration / etc / iscsi / iscsid.conf, add the following options: <br /> # The following three are for the discovery of the. <br /> # Discovery CHAP authentication enabled <br /> discovery.sendtargets.auth.authmethod = CHAP <br /> # Initiator\'s name, it can be other strings, as long as the name of target-side IncomingUse configuration as on the line <br /> discovery.sendtargets.auth.username = iqn.1994-05.com.fedora: ba72af8aaf5 <br /> # Verify the password, and the target side to the same <br /> discovery.sendtargets.auth.password = 1234567890ab </p><p> # Following three is for the login. <br /> Enable CHAP authentication # login <br /> node.session.auth.authmethod = CHAP <br /> # Initiator\'s name, it can be other strings, as long as the name of target-side IncomingUse configuration as on the line <br /> node.session.auth.username = iqn.1994-05.com.fedora: ba72af8aaf5 <br /> # Verify the password, and the target side to the same <br /> node.session.auth.password = 1234567890 </p><p> Then restart the initiator. <br /> / Etc / init.d / iscsid stop <br /> / Etc / init.d / iscsid start </p><p> 2) for the disc in the target side'),(219,'linux','en','/a/st/2010/0422/50.html','Guide to install and use open source drbd','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> I: Overview: </p><p> DRBD is a kernel module and associated scripts and composition, to build high availability clusters. Its implementation is through the network to mirror the entire device. You can see it as a network RAID. Drbd responsible for receiving data, the data written to local disk, and then sent to another host. Another host and then the data stored to your disk. </p><p> Source download <a href=\"http://oss.linbit.com/drbd/0.7/drbd-0.7.19.tar.gz\">http://oss.linbit.com/drbd/0.7/drbd-0.7.19.tar.gz</a> </p><p> Core reference documentation: <a href=\"http://www.drbd.org/drbd-howto.html\">http://www.drbd.org/drbd-howto.html</a> </p><p></p><p> Second: The main implementation </p><p> Suppose there are two machines nannan: 192.168.0.136 need to mirror the hard disk: / dev/hdc3 </p><p> root: 192.168.0.139 need to mirror the hard disk: / dev/hdc2 </p><p> Referred to as the master server is 192.168.0.136 136 </p><p> Referred to as the backup server is 192.168.0.139 139 </p><p> Normal reading and writing of data to achieve in 136, when the 136 down to start after the 139 swap, hot backup data. </p><p> The real needs of the thermal switch was implemented with the HA. </p><p></p><p> Third: Download and install </p><p> Installation Environment: Red Hat Enterprise Linux AS release 4, kernel version :2.6.9-22. EL </p><p> Confirm the existence of the kernel source, can be <a href=\"http://oss.linbit.com/drbd/\">http://oss.linbit.com/drbd/</a> to load. </p><p> Download Source Note: The most current drbd-8.0pre3, configuration files can not be properly configured, there a lot of mistakes, so download the previous stable version. Source unpacked tar </p><p> Run: </p><p> A, make KDIR = / usr / src / linux / * the location of the kernel * / </p><p> / * If you do not change the kernel can run make, the software will go directly to the / lib / module inside to find the system environment, if the new kernel needs to compile the kernel installed </p><p> Otherwise, time will make mistakes and cut off * / </p><p> B, make install </p><p> After installing the main build command: drbdsetup, drbdadmin </p><p> And configuration files: / etc / drbd.conf, startup file, / etc / init.d / drbd </p><p> Module file: drbd.ko (compiled package in the directory can be found under drbd) </p><p> All commands and configuration files can be compiled in the source package directory to find success. </p><p> . / Scripts / drbd.conf is the original configuration file, when the / etc / drbd.conf is damaged, you can copy directly overwritten. </p><p> C, create a hardware device drbd </p><p> mknod / dev/drbd0 b 147 0 </p><p> mknod / dev/drbd1 b 147 1 </p><p> mknod / dev/drbd2 b 147 2 </p><p> Or use the shell to create multiple: </p><p> # For i in $ (seq 0 15); do mknod / dev / drbd $ ib 147 $ i; done </p><p> D, DRBD protocol specification </p><p> A data once written to disk and sent to the network to that the completion of the write operation. </p><p> B received a confirmation to that the completion of the write operation. </p><p> C receive a written confirmation to that the completion of the write operation. </p><p> You can also choose other parameters to the data to disk and network options. For more information, see drbdsetup man page. </p><p> Four: Configure drbd </p><p> Modify / etc / drbd.conf </p><p> The main changes: the machine name and device name ip address </p><p> ================================================== </p><p> on web1 { </p><p> device / dev/drbd0; </p><p> disk / dev/hdc3; </p><p> address 192.168.0.136:7788; </p><p> meta-disk internal; </p><p> # Meta-disk is either \'internal\' or \'/ dev / ice / name [idx]\' </p><p> # </p><p> # You can use a single block device to store meta-data </p><p> # Of multiple DRBD\'s. </p><p> # Eg use meta-disk / dev/hde6 [0]; and meta-disk / dev/hde6 [1]; </p><p> # For two different resources. In this case the meta-disk </p><p> # Would need to be at least 256 MB in size. </p><p> # </p><p> # \'Internal\' means, that the last 128 MB of the lower device </p><p> # Are used to store the meta-data. </p><p> # You must not give an index with \'internal\'. </p><p> } </p><p> on web2 { </p><p> device / dev/drbd0; </p><p> disk / dev/hdc2; </p><p> address 192.168.0.139:7788; </p><p> meta-disk internal; </p><p> } </p><p> ================================================== </p><p> Here is the drbd.conf profile: </p><p> Note: The configuration version is drbd-0.7.19.tar.gz, different versions are not compatible. The modifications to the above and comments in several places, as well as the outside in addition to resource r0 other configuration blocks, such as resource r1, and all removed. </p><p> That is </p><p> /**** </p><p> on root { </p><p> device / dev/drbd0; </p><p> disk / dev/hdc2; </p><p> address 192.168.0.139:7788; </p><p> meta-disk internal; </p><p> } </p><p> } </p><p> ****/ </p><p> Removed all the contents of all of the back, </p><p></p><p> The following is a complete configured drbd.conf </p><p> # </p><p> # Drbd.conf example </p><p> # </p><p> skip { </p><p> As you can see, you can also comment chunks of text </p><p> with a \'skip [optional nonsense] {skipped text}\' section. </p><p> This comes in handy, if you just want to comment out </p><p> some \'resource &lt;some name&gt; {...}\' section: </p><p> just precede it with \'skip\'. </p><p> The basic format of option assignment is </p><p> &lt;option name&gt; &lt;linear whitespace&gt; &lt;value&gt;; </p><p></p><p> It should be obvious from the examples below, </p><p> but if you really care to know the details: </p><p></p><p> &lt;option name&gt;: = </p><p> valid options in the respective scope </p><p> &lt;value&gt;: = &lt;num&gt; | &lt;string&gt; | &lt;choice&gt; | ... </p><p> depending on the set of allowed values </p><p> for the respective option. </p><p> &lt;num&gt;: = [0-9] +, sometimes with an optional suffix of K, M, G </p><p> &lt;string&gt;: = (&lt;name&gt; | \\ &quot;([^ \\&quot; <a>\\ \\ \\ n] * | \\ \\.) * \\</a> &quot;) + </p><p> &lt;name&gt;: = [/ _.A-Za-z0-9-] + </p><p> } </p><p> # Global { </p><p> # Use this if you want to define more resources later </p><p> # Without reloading the module. </p><p> # By default we load the module with exactly as many devices </p><p> # As configured mentioned in this file. </p><p> # </p><p> # Minor-count 5; </p><p> # The user dialog counts and displays the seconds it waited so </p><p> # Far. You might want to disable this if you have the con'),(220,'linux','en','/a/mz/2010/0711/318.html','Installing pcre-7.9 compile error [pcrecpp.lo] Error 1','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Download pcre-7.9 compile and install, make time error: </p><p> source = \'pcrecpp.cc\' object = \'pcrecpp.lo\' libtool = yes <br /> DEPDIR =. deps depmode = none / bin / sh. / Depcomp <br /> / Bin / sh. / Libtool - tag = CXX - mode = compile-DHAVE_CONFIG_H-I. -I/usr/kerberos/include-C-o pcrecpp.lo pcrecpp.cc <br /> libtool: ignoring unknown tag CXX <br /> libtool: unrecognized option `-DHAVE_CONFIG_H \' <br /> Try `libtool - help \'for more information. <br /> make [1]: *** [pcrecpp.lo] Error 1 <br /></p><p> This error, which can be concluded that the lack of system package created, but the lack of which packages are not clear, here recorded, this error is the lack of install gcc-c + +, just yum-y install gcc-c + +, re-configure, make &amp; &amp; make install approved. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(221,'linux','en','/a/mz/2010/0423/67.html','&quot;Unable to load dynamic library&quot; error solution','2010-04-23','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <strong>1. Description of the problem</strong> </p><p> Php-mysql is not good today, suddenly took. Has prompted the following <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/mz/\">error</a></u> message: </p><div class=\"quote_div\"> Libmysql.dll not found the application therefore failed to start apache php </div><div class=\"quote_div\"> startup: <font style=\"background-color: #ffff00\"><span class=\"hilite1\">Unable</span></font> <font style=\"background-color: #55ff55\"><span class=\"hilite2\">to</span></font> <font style=\"background-color: #aaffaa\"><span class=\"hilite3\">load</span></font> <font style=\"background-color: #00ffff\"><span class=\"hilite4\">dynamic</span></font> <span class=\"hilite5\">library:</span> C: / ApacheGroup/php5/ext \\ php_mysql.dll </div><p> Furthermore, when calling the mysql function to be wrong: </p><div class=\"quote_div\"> Fatal error: Call <font style=\"background-color: #55ff55\"><span class=\"hilite2\">to</span></font> undefined function: mysql_connect () </div><p> I looked under the production system, php.ini has the correct configuration inside the extension_dir: </p><p> extension_dir = &quot;C: / ApacheGroup/php5/ext&quot; </p><p> Extension_dir does exist but which also php_mysql.dll, can not get why he hung it happens. </p><p> <strong>2. Cause of the problem</strong> </p><p> google a bit found that: </p><p> To <font style=\"background-color: #aaffaa\"><span class=\"hilite3\">Load</span></font> &quot;php_mysql.dll&quot; this dll, must first <font style=\"background-color: #aaffaa\"><span class=\"hilite3\">Load</span></font> &quot;libmysql.dll&quot; the foundation dll, </p><p> While the former in the ext directory, can be found. </p><p> Then the latter is not in the ext directory (though even if he can get it working), a system can not find his place. </p><p> <strong>3. So there are two solutions:</strong> </p><p> 1. To copy the dll to the windows below them. </p><p> 2. Will be added to the path inside the php root directory. </p><p></p><p> <strong>4. Reference Links:</strong> </p><p> The nature of this type of error are the same, but there are some causes of variation, </p><p> Upgrading php, etc. For example, when more can refer to the following link: </p><p> http://www.javatang.com/archives/2007/07/04/1548182.html </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(222,'linux','en','/a/mz/2010/0422/61.html','PCI ROOT HID fail = 0x5 ACPI Linux general solution error','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> I have two servers in the dmesg in the following <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/mz/\">errors</a></u> , ask why? </p><p> os: rhel4.4 </p><p><br /> Server Model: hp dl380 g4, g5 </p><p><br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: \\ _SB_.PCI0 evaluate _BBN fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: get_device PCI ROOT HID fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: \\ _SB_.PCI0 evaluate _BBN fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: get_device PCI ROOT HID fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: \\ _SB_.PCI0 evaluate _BBN fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: get_device PCI ROOT HID fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: \\ _SB_.PCI0 evaluate _BBN fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: get_device PCI ROOT HID fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: \\ _SB_.PCI0 evaluate _BBN fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: get_device PCI ROOT HID fail = 0x5 <br /> hw_random hardware driver 1.0.0 loaded <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: \\ _SB_.PCI0 evaluate _BBN fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: get_device PCI ROOT HID fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: \\ _SB_.PCI0 evaluate _BBN fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: get_device PCI ROOT HID fail = 0x5 </p><p> Resolution: </p><p> Startup option to add parameters: <br /> Modify / boot / grub / menu.lst file, the line started the final with the core kernel <br /> acpi = off noapic or acpi = noapic or acpi = off </p><p><br /> 1) acpi = off against a number of advanced power management features, the application has no effect. <br /> 2) noapic change interrupt, the application would not be affected. </p><p><br /> If your linux system can send and receive data card, optical card can not access the disk array, disk, boot times and then stop errors such as ACPI, you can try the above method, there will be an unexpected effect! </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(223,'linux','en','/a/mz/2010/0422/43.html','java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: allocLargeArray of memory','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<html> <font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"lin