he 4.2.1 Linux Installation and Management <br /> 4.2.3 MySQL Installation and Management <br /> 4.2.4 PHP installation <br /> 4.2.5 integrated software (Apache + MySQL) installation and management <br /> Web 4.3 applications built on LAMP 4.3.1 content management system setup and management of information management systems 4.3.2 Setup and Management <br /> 4.3.3 Internet and Management in the education system 4.3.4 Establishment and management of e-commerce systems <br /> 4.3.5 Electronic Reporting System setup and management of real application of Chapter memcached <br /> About 5.1 memcached <br /> What is memcached 5.1.1 <br /> 5.1.2 memcached works <br /> 5.2 memcached 5.2.1 memcached installation and setup to install the setup process step 5.2.2 memcached <br /> 5.3 memcached how the management and application management memcached 5.3.1 <br /> 5.3.2 memcached common problems and solutions, data backup and recovery topics second Chapter Bacula open source network backup software <br /> 6.1 bacula 6.1.1 bacula general overview of what? <br /> 6.1.2 bacula for which the functional characteristics of the user 6.1.3 bacula 6.1.4 bacula works <br /> 6.2 Installing bacula <br /> 6.2.1 Download the 6.2.2 package compiled and installed bacula bacula <br /> 6.2.3 initialize the database, the operating authority authorized bacula <br /> 6.3 An example configuration of a backup system bacula 6.3.1 Introduction 6.3.2 Topological configuration of the Console Control configured bacula 6.3.2-side configuration of the director bacula bacula client 6.3.3 configured in SD (storage) end 6.3.4 configure bacula of FD ( client) side <br /> 6.4 Startup and Shutdown bacula <br /> 6.4.1 At the same time to enable or disable all services approach bacula 6.4.2 separately enable or disable the service method bacula <br'),(235,'linux','en','/a/db/oracle/2010/0521/111.html','oracle how to set the primary key','2010-05-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Primary key: <br /> 1. The primary key constraint: a table can have only one primary key constraint. Primary key can be a single field, there can be multiple fields. In either case, all of its fields are NOT NULL. <br /> 2.Unique constraint: A table can have multiple Unique constraint, Unique in the field can be NULL. <br /> 3. The primary key and Unique: The difference is a table can have only one primary key constraint, but can have multiple Unique Constraints; all primary key fields are not null, unique can be </p><p> null; the same point is guaranteed unique. <br /> 4. The primary key, Unique and Index: Unique constraints and primary key constraint will be indexed by default. Unique primary key and when there are multiple fields, there is an index prefix problem, that is, where language </p><p> Conditions of the sentence must have a primary key or unique in the first field, it would not use the index. <br /> 5. Foreign key and primary key, Unique: foreign key to one table to another (the parent table) the primary key or unique index. If you want to add a record, while the parent table is not the error. Conversely, if </p><p> If you want to delete the parent records in the table, and the child table has records, will be an error. However, if the foreign key constraint is created, if you use on delete cascade, then delete the parent table data </p><p> Does not directly handle error data associated with the table removed. <br /> If you want to delete the parent table, you need to add cascade constraints, then the child table\'s foreign key is removed, the table records remain unchanged. <br /> Foreign key: </p><p> Foreign key is the table is another table join between the foreign key field must be the primary key in another table is the use of foreign keys to ensure data integrity. It usually includes the following: <br /> Physical integrity, to ensure that each entity is unique (by primary key to the implementation). </p><p> Set the primary key oracle method 2: <br /> Since the growth of a primary key is set, and the other is to generate unique sequence; <br /> 1. Since the growth of the primary key </p><p> SQL&gt; create table Prim_key_Increase_Test ( <br /> 2 id number (10) primary key, <br /> 3 name varchar2 (30) <br /> 4); </p><p> Table has been created. </p><p> SQL&gt; create sequence Prim_key_Incre_Sequence <br /> 2 minvalue 1 <br /> 3 nomaxvalue <br /> 4 start with 1 <br /> 5 increase by 1 <br /> 6 nocycle <br /> 7 nocache; <br /> increase by 1 <br /> * <br /> Error Line 5: <br /> ORA-00933: SQL command not properly ended </p><p><br /> SQL&gt; 5 <br /> 5 * increase by 1 <br /> SQL&gt; c / increase / increment / <br /> 5 * increment by 1 <br /> SQL&gt; r <br /> 1 create sequence Prim_key_Incre_Sequence <br /> 2 minvalue 1 <br /> 3 nomaxvalue <br /> 4 start with 1 <br /> 5 increment by 1 <br /> 6 nocycle <br /> 7 * nocache </p><p> Sequence has been created. </p><p> SQL&gt; create trigger Prim_key_trigger before <br /> 2 insert on Prim_key_Increase_Test for each row <br /> 3 begin <br /> 4 select Prim_key_Incre_Sequence.nextval into: New.id from dual; <br /> 5 end; <br /> 6 / </p><p> Trigger has been created </p><p> SQL&gt; commit; </p><p> Submit completed. </p><p> SQL&gt; insert into Prim_key_Increase_Test (id) values (\'181 \'); </p><p> 1 row created. </p><p> SQL&gt; select * from Prim_key_Increase_Test; </p><p> ID NAME <br /> ---------- ------------------------------ <br /> 1 </p><p> SQL&gt; insert into Prim_key_Increase_Test (id) values (\'181 \'); </p><p> 1 row created. </p><p> SQL&gt; insert into Prim_key_Increase_Test (id) values (\'181 \'); </p><p> 1 row created. </p><p> SQL&gt; select * from Prim_key_Increase_Test; </p><p> ID NAME <br /> ---------- ------------------------------ <br /> 1 <br /> 2 <br /> 3 </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(236,'linux','en','/a/mz/2010/0421/14.html','su: / bin / bash: Permission denied confusion caused','2010-04-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><div> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Customers a <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/db/oracle/\">oracle</a></u> suddenly goes down, the business started, customers subconsciously to reboot the server, the system is up and ready to switch to the <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/db/oracle/\">oracle</a></u> user to start the database, how can not su to switch, really stoked Yeah, described as follows: <br /> Under the root user, su to a normal user oracle, get the following error: <br /><br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # su - oracle <br /> su: warning: cannot change directory to / home / oracle: Permission denied <br /> su: / bin / bash: Permission denied <br /><br /> The oracle user can not log in directly, made the same mistake. <br /><br /> This is a very strange question, in the end is what causes it? Ideas are as follows: <br /> 1, program execution permission problems <br /> 2, the program depends on shared library permissions problem <br /> 3, directory permission issues <br /> 4, the root space. <br /><br /> Check the / bin / bash, permissions correctly, check the / home / oracle permissions correctly, check / lib/ld- ***. so, permissions are correct. <br /><br /> Continue to debug, check the / etc / passwd, the oracle\'s home set to / tmp, the / tmp set to 777, this authority should be the most relaxed. <br /><br /> The same error su. <br /><br /> That is, 777 users can not access oracle permission / tmp. <br /><br /> Problem in the end there where? <br /><br /> Finally, star command, see the problem simply, <br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # stat / <br /> Output is as follows: Because you can not see ls. <br /> File: &quot;/&quot; <br /> Size: 1024 Blocks: 2 IO Block: 1024 directory <br /> Device: 803h/2051d Inode: 2 Links: 22 <br /> Access: (0666/drw-rw-rw-) Uid: (0 / root) Gid: (0 / root) <br /> Access: 2007-12-01 22:28:48.000000000 +0800 <br /> Modify: 2007-12-01 22:28:34.000000000 +0800 <br /> Change: 2007-12-01 23:17:35.000000000 +0800 <br /><br /> Problems arose, where permission is wrong, X caused the loss of privileges. <br /><br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # chmod 755 / <br /><br /><br /> Modifications, the problem disappeared. <br /><br /> Produce the problem: <br /> The first, chmod 666 /, can lead to. <br /><br /> Or, <br /> The second, chmod 700 / lib / ld-xxxx.so, can also lead to su to fail. <br /><br /> Are interested can try their own. <br /><br /> / Loss of privileges for various user runs on their own daemon also the same effect.</font> </div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(237,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0422/35.html','Talk shell of the &quot;&gt; / dev / null 2&gt; &amp; 1&quot;','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><div><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Today, a technology in their own group so they were asked a question, so he explained a bit popular, to be a record, we look to explain it clearly!</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">shell may often see:&gt; / dev / null 2&gt; &amp; 1</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">The results can command%&gt; to define the output in the form of</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Decomposition of this combination: &quot;&gt; / dev / null 2&gt; &amp; 1&quot; is in five parts.</font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff6600\" face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">1:&gt; redirected to where the representative, for example: echo &quot;123&quot;&gt; / home/123.txt <br /> 2: / dev / null device file on behalf of Air <br /> 3:2&gt; &quot;means standard error stderr <br /> 4: &amp; that is equivalent to the mean, 2 &quot;&amp; 1, 2, said redirect the output is equivalent to 1 <br /> 5:1 that stdout standard output, the system default value is 1, so &quot;&gt; / dev / null&quot; equivalent to &quot;1&gt; / dev / null&quot;</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Thus,&gt; / dev / null 2&gt; &amp; 1 can also be written as &quot;1&gt; / dev / null 2&gt; &amp; 1&quot;</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Then the execution of this statement in the title is: <br /> 1&gt; / dev / null: first that the standard output redirected to a null device file, which is not output any information to the terminal, it means do not display any information. <br /> 2 &quot;&amp; 1: Then, the standard error output redirected to standard output, because before the standard output has been redirected to a null device file, so the standard error output are redirected to a null device file.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">That clear to you, we understand, are you!</font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff6600\" face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Under such a contrast with the way the benefits of telling!</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">The most common methods are:</font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\" face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">command&gt; file 2&gt; file with the command&gt; file 2&gt; &amp; 1</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">What is different place?</font> </p><p><br /> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">First command&gt; file 2&gt; file means that the standards produced by the command output, and errors in the information to the file. Command&gt; file 2&gt; file that is written, stdout and stderr are sent directly to the file in, file will be opened twice, so stdout and stderr will overwrite each other so very used to write both FD1 and FD2 at the same time to seize the file in the pipeline. <br /> The command&gt; file 2&gt; &amp; 1 This command will be sent directly to the stdout file, stderr inherited FD1 pipe, and then was sent to file, time, file is opened only once, only use a pipe FD1, it includes the contents of stdout and stderr. <br /> From the IO efficiency, the efficiency of a command before the back of a command than less efficient, so when writing shell scripts, more time, we will command&gt; file 2&gt; &amp; 1 this writing.</font> </p></div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(238,'linux','en','/a/IT/2010/0430/90.html','Red Hat Enterprise Linux Introduction RHEL6 beta release','2010-04-30','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p class=\"newtext\"> Red Hat Enterprise <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\">Linux</a></u> has released the first version of the past 8 years. Since the release date, the product established as a leading enterprise-class open source operating <a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/\"><u>system,</u></a> one of the position. Installation of <a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/\"><u>the system</u></a> used in portable computer to the mainframe from a variety of machines to help establish the quality certification infrastructure, long-term stability, performance, and security models. From the main street to Wall Street, Red Hat Enterprise <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\">Linux</a></u> into almost all walks of life. </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Red Hat Enterprise Linux into the Beta testing, the currently supported versions: Red Hat Enterprise Linux 5, Red Hat is still the cornerstone of the portfolio of software products. Red Hat Enterprise Linux 5 in March 2007 was first released, self-released, through a number of regularly updated. Last month, we have just released the Red Hat Enterprise Linux 5 the 5th updated with new features and hardware support. In 2014, Red Hat Enterprise Linux 5 platform, Red Hat will continue to be, and its ISV and OEM partners for their support. </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Looking to the future, Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 blurred virtual, physical, and the boundaries between cloud computing to adapt to contemporary changes occurring in IT environments. Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 from the kernel to the application infrastructure to the development tool chain is used to upgrade the core technology to meet the future generations of hardware and software technology needs. </p><p class=\"newtext\"> New version of the theme, including the ubiquitous virtualization, better stability and high availability, higher energy efficiency and to provide more than the latest software technology. Beta version released today on the occasion, we will introduce several new and noteworthy improvements: </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Comprehensive power management capabilities </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Ã¢Â—Â‹ time kernel to improve the system there will be no more frequently active task processor becomes idle state. This will lead to a lower temperature than previous versions and higher CPU power saving. Powertop other new monitoring tools that can help identify energy problems can be solved, thus further reducing energy consumption. Like a &quot;tuned&quot; so that the new regulation tool (an adaptive system regulating daemon) service the system can adjust the energy usage pattern analysis. </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Performance Improvement </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Ã¢Â—Â‹ Red Hat engineers we plan to appear in Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 performance improvements in a variety of upstream development kernel play a key role in the process of completely rewriting the scheduler so that it can make the process a higher priority at the lowest limit lower priority treatment under the conditions of interference, a more equitable distribution among the processor computation time. In addition, for a variety of multi-processor lock synchronization improvements. For example, to eliminate unnecessary lock events, many of rotation instead of using the sleep lock (spin) lock and a more efficient locking primitives. Impact of these fundamental changes to many core subsystems. </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Improved scalability </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Ã¢Â—Â‹ The new hardware has led to major developments in commodity computing platforms. For example, now a 5U rack cabinet can hold 64 CPU and 2TB of memory. These systems and their subsequent products will be Red Hat Enterprise Linux 5 to achieve the scalability limits. Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 is one of the main features: it can provide scalability to adapt to future systems. The scalability of capacity from a large number of CPU and memory configuration for the optimization of the support to handle a larger number of systems the ability to interconnect bus and peripherals. With bare metal virtualization becomes ubiquitous, like the time of deployment, the ability of the environment suitable for bare metal and virtual environments. </p><p class=\"newtext\"> New security features </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Ã¢Â—Â‹ called security services daemon (SSSD) of the new service provides a centralized identity management. It also has a cache for offline use certificate capabilities. New SELinux sandbox feature allows untrusted content can not affect the system in an isolated environment for the rest of the run. This includes the isolation of any Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 running on a virtual client capabilities. </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Resource Management </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Ã¢Â—Â‹ called in a control group (ie cgroups) with the help of a new framework, the new system provides the hardware resources of fine-grained control, distribution and management. cgroups running in process group level, can be used for application management from the CPU, memory, network and disk I / O resources. The framework is also used to manage virtual clients. </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Virtualization </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Ã¢Â—Â‹ Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 extends the earlier versions of Red Hat Enterprise Linux integrated virtualization based on KVM technology. The new system has more than one performance, scheduler and hardware improvements, no matter what the deployment model to provide better flexibility and control. </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Storage </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Ã¢Â—Â‹ FCoE and iSCSI protocols through the network block storage support, so use LVM / DM to change the implementation of online and multi-path mirrored volume size possible. </p><p class=\"newtext\"> File System </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Ã¢Â—Â‹ new system includes the ext4 file system. Extended family of next-generation file system, which includes support for larger file sizes, more efficient disk space allocation, better and more robust file system check log. In addition to ext4, we also intend to provide XFS? File system. XFS? For large files and directories, including debris removal and the like when used in the file system the ability to change the file system size. Level has risen to NFS version 4, which includes IPv6 support. </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Reliability, availability and serviceability (RAS) </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Ã¢Â—Â‹ new version of the use of new hardware such as hot-add capability to provide equipment and hardware and equipment through the enhanced PCIe AER of error checking and other features. It will also include advanced data integrity features (DIF / DIX). Such characteristics of the hardware from the application of inspection and survey data. ABRT (automatic bug report tool) provides the introduction of the system to identify and report anomalies such as the core DD fault (kernel oops) and user space applications crash DD more consistent manner. </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Compilers and tools </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Ã¢Â—Â‹ GCC compiler has been upgraded to version 4.4. This version of the draft in accordance with C + + 0x standard compilation. It is also consistent with OpenMP 3.0, includes a number of debugging. SystemTap improvements include better user support for space exploration, more secure server and compile the script to make SystemTap non-root user can access the new non-privileged mode. In addition, there are many other new compiler has been upgraded to the latest version of the library and more languages and operating environment, including a complete LAMP stack and OpenJDK. </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Desktop </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Introduced a new version of the display type of testing and support for multiple monitors. We also added support for NVIDIA graphics device driver for the upgrade of the new. Of course, if GNOME and KDE desktop does not update the new version will be incomplete. </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 in a variety of technology hardware platform as the key to the expansion of support provided, we believe that these technologies will become a new platform to attract new customers an attractive choice. As always, the new version is part of the value of our enterprise certification. </p><p class=\"newtext\"> Currently, thousands of applications in Red Hat Enterprise Linux by running the certification, whether it runs on &quot;bare metal&quot; deployment, virtualization deployment, or cloud deployment. This makes Red Hat Enterprise Linux to become the first choice for customers and partners operating system. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(239,'linux','en','/a/db/oracle/2010/0422/21.html','Alibaba DBA interview questions, Cece own','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> A: SQL tuning category </p><p> 1: The table lists some connection </p><p> 2: without the help of third-party tools, how to view sql of the implementation plan </p><p> 3: How to use the CBO, CBO and the difference RULE </p><p> 4: how to locate the important (and consume more resources) of the SQL </p><p> 5: How to track a session of the SQL </p><p> 6: SQL adjust what is most concerned about </p><p> 7: Tell me about your understanding of the index (index of the structure, dml impact on the query of why improve query performance) </p><p> 8: Use the index lookup will be able to improve query performance? Why </p><p> 9: What is bind variables? What are the advantages and disadvantages bind variables? </p><p> 10: How stable (fixed) implementation plan </p><p> 11: and the sort of memory-related, respectively, in 8i and 9i how to adjust, temporary table space What is the role </p><p> 12: there is Table T (a, b, c, d), sorted according to the field c to take the first 21-30 records show, please give sql </p><p> II: basic concepts of database classes </p><p> 1: pctused and pctfree What is the meaning of what that role </p><p> 2: a brief description of table / segment / extent / block the relationship between </p><p> 3: Describe the relationship between the tablespace and datafile </p><p> 4: locally managed tablespaces and dictionary managed tablespaces feature, ASSM What are the characteristics </p><p> 5: What is the role rollback </p><p> 6: What is the role the log </p><p> 7: SGA are those that part, what is the role </p><p> 8racle What are the main system processes, what is the role </p><p> III: Backup and Recovery category </p><p> 1: Back to Categories </p><p> 2: What is the meaning of the archive </p><p> 3: If a table at 2004-08-04 10:30:00 by drop, in a sound archive and backup situation, how to restore </p><p> 4: rman is, What are the characteristics </p><p> 5: standby feature </p><p> 6: For a relatively short recovery time requirements of the system (database 50G, daily archiving 5G), how to design your backup strategy </p><p> IV: System Management </p><p> 1: For an existing system performance of the system, state your diagnosis and treatment ideas </p><p> 2: including several diagnostic IO, CPU, performance situation of the </p><p> 3: What knowledge of statspack </p><p> 4: If the system is a great need to create an index on the table, you will consider those factors, how to minimize the impact of the application </p><p> 5: What is awareness of raid10 and raid5 </p><p> V: Comprehensive free class </p><p> 1: you do best which part is the oracle? </p><p> 2: like the oracle it? Like forums? Or preferences which part of oracle? </p><p> 3: Do you think free to talk about the most interesting part of the oracle or the most difficult part of </p><p> 4: Why choose to be a DBA do? <br /></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(240,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0610/201.html','configuration and tuning tomcat cluster implementation plan','2010-06-10','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <font size=\"2\"><strong>First, the operating system tuning <br /></strong> Optimization of the operating system, it is possible the increase of memory capacity can be used to improve the CPU frequency, to ensure the file system read and write speed and so on. After pressure testing and certification, in the case of many concurrent connections, CPU processing power is stronger, the system runs faster. . <br /> SceneÃ£Â€Â‘ Ã£Â€Âapply to any project. <br /> <strong>Second, Java Virtual Machine tuning</strong> &lt;br /&gt; should choose SUN\'s JVM, the premise of meeting the needs of the project as far as selection of a higher version of JVM, generally high version of the product than the low speed and efficiency will be improved versions of . <br /> JDK1.4 JDK1.3 performance improvement than the nearly 10% -20%, JDK1.5 JDK1.4 than 25% -75% performance increase. <br /> Therefore, the situation on the high performance requirements recommended JDK1.6. <br /> SceneÃ£Â€Â‘ Ã£Â€Âapply to any project. <br /> <strong>Third, Apache Integration <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/web/tomcat/\">Tomcat</a></u></strong> <br /> HTTP Web server dedicated to handling requests, the application server is provided through a number of protocols for the application business logic. While the Tomcat web server can also be made, but the deal\'s not as fast as static html Apache, and web server functionality as far as Apache, so Apache and Tomcat to integrate, will feature some html and Jsp clear division of labor, Jsp Tomcat parts to deal only with the other by the Apache, IIS and other web servers to handle, thus greatly improving the operating efficiency of Tomcat. <br /> If a project makes extensive use of static pages, a large number of pictures and have a greater number of visits, integrated Apache Tomcat recommended way to improve overall system performance. <br /> The integration of Apache and Tomcat, there are three ways, namely, JK, http_proxy and ajp_proxy. Where JK is the most common way of approach, JK itself has two versions 1 and 2, respectively, present a new version is 1.2.8, and version 2 already obsolete. http_proxy is to use Apache\'s mod_proxy module is built using agent technology to connect to Tomcat. Ajp_proxy connection with the http_proxy the same way as a matter of fact, all the functions provided by the mod_proxy. Just need to configure the http:// into ajp: / /, while the connection is where Tomcat\'s AJP Connector port. <br /> JK\'s connections with respect to the latter two is relatively simple in configuration, flexibility, a little also favorably. But in terms of stability of not JK proven so, so JK\'s connection is recommended. <br /> Apache + JK + Tomcat configuration: <br /> The two configuration files used are: httpd.conf and mod_jk.conf. Which is the Apache server\'s httpd.conf configuration file to load the JK module, and specify the JK configuration file information. mod_jk.conf is connected to the Tomcat server definition file. <br /> Ã£Â€Â‘ Ã£Â€ÂDeployment steps <br /> 1. Installing Apache Server <br /> 2. Deployment Tomcat <br /> 3. Mod_jk.so copy the modules directory <br /> 4. Modify httpd.conf and mod_jk.conf <br /> Ã£Â€ÂÃ£Â€Â‘ Large number of scenarios for the applications use a static page. <br /> <strong>Fourth, Apache and Tomcat clustering</strong> &lt;br /&gt; demanding for concurrent systems, we need to take a balanced approach to share the load Tomcat server stress. Load balancing to achieve about four: the first is through DNS, but only the realization of a simple rotation distribution, can not deal with failure; the second is based on MS IIS, windows 2003 server itself with the load balancing services; the third is the hardware approach through the switch load balancing function or special equipment to achieve; the fourth is the software of the way through a load balancing server, install the software above. Done using Apache Httpd Server load balancer, Tomcat Tomcat cluster nodes can be done using the fourth approach, more flexible this way, the cost is relatively low, the other big advantage is that applications and servers according to the situation some flexibility in configuration. So it is Apache + Tomcat clustering for load balancing. <br /> Tomcat clusters can be used to play the greatest degree of performance of the server, the server can be configured to deploy a higher number of Tomcat, can also be deployed on multiple servers are Tomcat, Apache and Tomcat JK integrated way or manner. After verification, the system response to a large amount of users using the terms, Apache +3 Tomccat cluster&gt; Apache +2 Tomcat cluster&gt; Apache integrating Tomcat&gt; single Tomcat. And using Apache + Tomcat cluster deployment and more, if there a Tomcat is down, the system can continue to use, so the performance of the hardware system is superior enough to the case, you need to maximize the performance of the software can be used to increase the way Tomcat cluster. <br /> Apache + Tomcat to use the cluster configuration file must have httpd.conf, mod_jk.conf, workers.properties. JK mod_jk.conf which is the configuration information, including the path of JK, workers.properties Tomcat server configuration file is the connection definition file. <br /> Apache need to adjust the operating parameters, so as to build a network environment suitable for the corresponding web services. Which may be the optimal allocation is as follows: <br /> 1. Set MPM (Multi Processing Modules Multi-Processing Modules). ThreadPerChild, this parameter is used to set the number of threads per process in Windows environment, the default value is 64, maximum is 1920, the proposed set to 100-500 between the value of server performance, then a large number of high, whereas smaller. MaxRequestPerChild that each child process to handle the maximum number of requests. Greater the value of this parameter depends on the server\'s memory, if memory is relatively large, then the parameters can be set to large, or to set a smaller value, the proposed value is 3000. <br /> 2. Close DNS and name resolution</font> <wbr /><wbr /> <font size=\"2\">HostnameLookups off <br /> 3. Open UseCanonicalName module UseCanonicalName on <br /> 4. Close extra modules in general, need to load the module, mod_include.so, mod_autoindex.so, mod_access.so, mod_auth.so. <br /> 5. Open KeepAlive support <br /> KeepAlive on, KeepAliveTimeout 15 MaxKeepAliveRequests 1000 <br /></font> <wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> <font size=\"2\">Based on actual experience, by the way Apache and Tomcat clustering to improve system performance of the effect is very obvious, this approach can maximize the use of hardware resources, through multiple treatment to share a single Tomcat when Tomcat pressure. <br /> Ã£Â€Â‘ Ã£Â€ÂDeployment steps <br /> 1. Installing Apache Server <br /> 2. To deploy Tomcat cluster, that is more than the same Tomcat. <br /> 3. Mod_jk.so copy the modules directory <br /> 4. Modify httpd.conf, mod_jk.conf and workers.properties <br /> Ã£Â€ÂÃ£Â€Â‘ Concurrent users for the amount of the scene and the relatively high number of users online using the system. <br /> <strong>V., Tomcat itself Optimization</strong> <br /> <strong>1. JVM tuning parameters:-Xms</strong> &lt;size&gt; that initialize JVM heap size,-Xmx &lt;size&gt; that the maximum JVM heap. The size of these two values is generally based on the need for setting. When the application requires the maximum heap memory beyond the virtual machine will be prompted when the memory overflow and cause applications to crash. It is generally recommended the maximum heap is set to the maximum available memory to 80%. In catalina.bat, set JAVA_OPTS = \'-Xms256m-Xmx512m\', said initialization memory 256MB, you can use the maximum memory 512MB. <br /> <strong>2. Disable DNS query</strong> &lt;br /&gt; When the web application to client information to be recorded, it will record the client\'s IP address or domain name server looks through the machine names are converted to IP addresses. DNS queries need to occupy the network, and including the possibility of a lot of very far from the server or the server does not work up the process to obtain the corresponding IP, which will consume some time. In order to eliminate the performance impact of DNS queries that we can turn off DNS queries, way is to modify the server.xml file enableLookups parameter values: <br /> Tomcat4 <br /><br /> &lt;Connector className = &quot;org.apache.coyote.tomcat4.CoyoteConnector&quot; port = &quot;80&quot; minProcessors = &quot;5&quot; maxProcessors = &quot;75&quot; enableLookups = &quot;false&quot; redirectPort = &quot;8443&quot; acceptCount = &quot;100&quot; debug = &quot;0&quot; connectionTimeout = &quot;20000&quot; useURIValidationHack = &quot;false&quot; disableUploadTimeout = &quot;true&quot; /&gt; <br /><br /> Tomcat5 <br /><br /> &lt;Connector port = &quot;80&quot; maxThreads = &quot;150&quot; minSpareThreads = &quot;25&quot; maxSpareThreads = &quot;75&quot; enableLookups = &quot;false&quot; redirectPort = &quot;8443&quot; acceptCount = &quot;100&quot; debug = &quot;0&quot; connectionTimeout = &quot;20000&quot; disableUploadTimeout = &quot; true &quot;/&gt;</font> </p><p><br /> <strong>3.</strong> &lt;br /&gt; By <strong>adjusting the number of threads</strong> the application\'s connector (Connector) control the parameters of performance is to create a number of threads to process the request. Tomcat uses a thread pool to accelerate response time to process the request. In the Java runtime in the thread is the path in a program independent of the other threads of control that can operate independently of the code. They share the same address space. To help programmers write multi-threaded CPU maximum utilization of the efficient processes that maintain a minimum idle time to accept more requests. <br /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> Tomcat4 can modify minProcessors and maxProc'),(241,'linux','en','/a/db/oracle/2010/0421/13.html','TNS-12555: TNS: permission denied error solution','2010-04-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><div> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Oracle 10g + Redhat5, all the normal installation, install the user oracle. <br /><br /><br /><br /> Sqlplus oracle user to start today with the normal <br /> [Abc @ rhel4 admin] $ sqlplus / as sysdba <br /> SQL * Plus: Release 10.2.0.1.0 - Production on Thu Apr 23 12:11:25 2009 <br /> Copyright (c) 1982, 2005, Oracle. All rights reserved. <br /><br /> Connected to: <br /> Oracle Database 10g Enterprise Edition Release 10.2.0.1.0 - Production <br /> With the Partitioning, OLAP and Data Mining options <br /> SQL&gt; <br /><br /> However, the listener starts when the error was: <br /> [Abc @ rhel4 admin] $ lsnrctl <br /> LSNRCTL for Linux: Version 10.2.0.1.0 - Production on 23-APR-2009 12:13:06 <br /> Copyright (c) 1991, 2005, Oracle. All rights reserved. <br /> Welcome to LSNRCTL, type &quot;help&quot; for information. <br /><br /> <strong><font color=\"#ff0000\">LSNRCTL&gt; start</font></strong> <br /> Starting / u01/app/oracle/product/10.2.0/bin/tnslsnr: please wait ... <br /><br /> TNSLSNR for Linux: Version 10.2.0.1.0 - Production <br /> System parameter file is / u01/app/oracle/product/10.2.0/network/admin/listener.ora <br /> Log messages written to / u01/app/oracle/product/10.2.0/network/log/listener.log <br /> Listening on: (DESCRIPTION = (ADDRESS = (PROTOCOL = tcp) (HOST = localhost.localdomain) (PORT = 1521))) <br /> Error listening on: (DESCRIPTION = (ADDRESS = (PROTOCOL = IPC) (KEY = EXTPROC1))) <br /> <strong><font color=\"#ff0000\">TNS-12555: TNS: permission denied <br /> TNS-12560: TNS: protocol adapter error <br /> TNS-00525: Insufficient privilege for operation <br /> Linux Error: 1: Operation not permitted</font></strong> <br /><br /><br /><br /> Through the log <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/mz/\">the error</a></u> message shows, it should be related with the permissions, and finally found a hidden message <br /><br /> <font color=\"#ff6600\"><strong>/ Var / tmp / .oracle this directory is rather special, if the oracle no authority to operate this directory, then, oracle user can not access / var / tmp / .oracle folder.</strong></font> <br /><br /> Is simple, do: chmod 777 / var / tmp / .oracle <br /><br /> After ok.</font> </div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(242,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0422/33.html','PXE + TFTP + DHCP network automatically install the Linux boot','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">His earlier written an article to share with you the next! <br /><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\">Overview</font> <br /><br /> PXE (preboot execute environment), developed by Intel\'s latest technology, working in the Client / Server network model to support the station through the network from a remote server to download images, and thus support from the network operating system boot process, and its During startup, the terminal requires the server to assign IP addresses, then TFTP (trivial file transfer protocol) or MTFTP (multicast trivial file transfer protocol) protocol to download a boot package to a local memory and executed by the end of this startup software package basic software settings to guide the pre-installed in the server terminal operating system. PXE can boot multiple operating systems, such as: Windows 95/98/2000/xp/2003/vista/2008, linux and so on. <br /><br /> Most direct expression of PXE, the stations in the network environment can save hard drive, but not usually refer to the concept of diskless stations, since the use of the technology in the network mode PC running speed faster than the PC with disk 3 times. Of course, the PC using the PXE is not in the traditional sense TERMINAL terminal, because the PC using the PXE server is not consuming CPU, RAM and other resources, so the server hardware requirements low. <br /> Cloning PXE network is now the most widely used one is the cafe of the diskless technology. The field in a disk in the PXE network maintenance and installation can be the best system to use Internet cafes to install and maintain a unified guidance technology, PXE boot speed and stability are the best! <br /><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\">A: Installation Environment</font> <br /><br /> A Linux server, linux service, need to install the tftp + dhcp. As a remote installation of network servers. <br /> Client host, which is the need to install the Linux system, the host, the host motherboard must support boot from network. <br /><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\">II: Installation and Configuration Linux software on a network server to tftp and dhcp</font> <br /><br /> 1: Check for installed tftp <br /> [Root @ webserver html] # rpm-qa tftp * <br /> tftp-server-0.42-3.1.el5.centos <br /> tftp-0.42-3.1.el5.centos <br /> If not, that is not installed, if your system supports yum, direct execution <br /> [Root @ webserver html] # yum install * tftp * <br /> 2: Check whether the service in accordance with the dhcp <br /> [Root @ webserver html] # rpm-qa dhcp * <br /> dhcpv6-client-1.0.10-16.el5 <br /> dhcp-3.0.5-18.el5 <br /> If you do not dhcp, also perform yum install. <br /> [Root @ webserver html] # yum install dhcp * <br /> 3: Configuring tftp service dhcp service (1) configuration tftp service <br /> Tftp default is bound under the xinetd service, therefore, will want to modify the file to the tftp / etc / xinetd.d to complete, the modified tftp file as follows, where &quot;disable&quot; option from the &quot;yes&quot; is amended as &quot;no&quot;, an increase in the server_args option &quot;-u nobody&quot; parameter, so that any user can access. <br /> [Root @ webserver html] # more / etc / xinetd.d / tftp <br /> # Default: off <br /> # Description: The tftp server serves files using the trivial file transfer \\ <br /> # Protocol. The tftp protocol is often used to boot diskless \\ <br /> # Workstations, download configuration files to network-aware printers, \\ <br /> # And to start the installation process for some operating systems. <br /> service tftp <br /> { <br /> socket_type = dgram <br /> protocol = udp <br /> wait = yes <br /> user = root <br /> server = / usr / sbin / in.tftpd</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">server_args =-u nobody-s / tftpboot <br /> disable = no <br /> per_source = 11 <br /> cps = 100 2 <br /> flags = IPv4 <br /> } <br /> (2) the default configuration dhcp service dhcp configuration file in / etc / dhcpd.Conf, this file defaults to an empty file, so let\'s copy a dhcpd configuration file template file over, then you can modify. <br /> [Root @ webserverhtml] # cp / usr/share/doc/dhcp-3.0.5/dhcpd.conf.sample / etc / dhcpd.conf <br /> The default / etc / dhcpd.conf the following meanings: <br /> ddns-update-style interim; / / set the update mode dhcp Interactive <br /> ignore client-updates; / / ignore client updates <br /> subnet 192.168.12.0 netmask 255.255.255.0 { <br /> / / Set subnet state <br /> # --- Default gateway <br /> option routers 192.168.12.1; / / set the default gateway for clients <br /> option subnet-mask 255.255.255.0; / / Set the client subnet mask <br /> option nis-domain &quot;ixdba.net&quot;; / / set the NIS domain <br /> option domain-name &quot;ixdba.net&quot;; / / set the DNS domain <br /> option domain-name-servers 192.168.12.1; / / set the DNS server address <br /> option time-offset -18000; # Eastern Standard Time / / set the time offset <br /> # Option ntp-servers 192.168.12.1; <br /> # Option netbios-name-servers 192.168.12.1; <br /> # --- Selects point-to-point node (default is hybrid). Don\'t change this unless <br /> # - You understand Netbios very well <br /> # Option netbios-node-type 2; <br /> range dynamic-bootp 192.168.12.128 192.168.12.254; / / set the address pool <br /> default-lease-time 21600; / / set the default lease, in seconds <br /> max-lease-time 43200; / / set the client up to the lease, in seconds <br /> # We want the nameserver to appear at a fixed address <br /> host ns {/ / assign a static IP address of the following settings, can not give more explanation. <br /> next-server marvin.redhat.com; <br /> hardware ethernet 12:34:56:78: AB: CD; <br /> fixed-address 207.175.42.254; <br /> } <br /> } <br /> To use the default can work, but we can also we need to be changed. <br /> Other notes: <br /> range 192.168.12.2 192.168.12.125; can assign the IP address range limit. <br /> If you want to assign a fixed IP address of IP, change it to a host, the NIC\'s Mac address and IP to bind, is the last part, converted into the corresponding on it. <br /> Segments defined in the subnet of your network card with the same IP network segment in which, such as your network card that is 192.168.0.x, and dhcp services are to the subnet 10.1.1.0 is not enough to provide services, is can not start. <br /> In this experimental environment, my dhcpd.conf as follows: <br /> [Root @ webserver html] # more / etc / dhcpd.conf <br /> ddns-update-style interim; <br /> ignore client-updates; <br /><br /> subnet 192.168.12.0 netmask 255.255.255.0 { <br /><br /> option routers 192.168.12.1; <br /> option subnet-mask 255.255.255.0; <br /><br /> option nis-domain &quot;ixdba.net&quot;;</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">option domain-name &quot;ixdba.net</font>'),(243,'linux','en','/a/web/nginx/2010/0421/3.html','php-fpm to manage php FastCGI mode','2010-04-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Run php with FastCGI in time, if we change the php.ini settings, you must restart the fastcgi php daemon. If your system is relatively large load, then this process may restart your system will interrupt service for some time. php-fpm is born to solve this problem, it\'s in the php fastcgi process does not interrupt the circumstances had changed to reload your php.ini. <br /> Php-fpm and can no longer rely on other fastcgi initiator, such as lighttpd\'s spawn-fcgi, for me to finally get rid of the shadow of lighttpd. <br /> So what, go! <br /> My php version is 5.2.6, and the first official website to download the corresponding php version php-fpm patch: PHP-FPM <br /> Assumptions: php source directory in: / usr/local/src/php-5.2.6, php-fpm downloaded to the / usr / local / src <br /> cd / usr / local / src <br /> gzip-cd php-5.2.6-fpm-0.5.9.diff.gz | patch-d php-5.2.6-p1 </p><p></p><p> After the patch lay, when compiling php several parameters to increase the following: </p><p> -Enable-fpm fpm activated fastcgi mode support-with-fpm-conf php-fpm in the configuration file (default PREFIX / etc / php-fpm.conf) <br /> -With-fpm-log php-fpm log file (default PREFIX / logs / php-fpm.log) <br /> -With-fpm-pid php-fpm in the pid file (default PREFIX / logs / php-fpm.pid) </p><p> Compile time-enable-fpm, of course is necessary, several other conditions can adjust your own. <br /> Compilation parameters: <br /> cd / usr/local/src/php-5.2.6 <br /> . / Configure - enable-fastcgi - enable-fpm - prefix = / usr/local/php5 - with-config-file-path = / usr/local/php5/etc - THE-OTHERS <br /> make <br /> make install </p><p><br /> One-THE-OTHERS represent some other php build parameters, omitted here. <br /> After a while, so php built and installed, the following start configuring php-fpm. <br /> vi / usr/local/php5/etc/php-fpm.conf </p><p><br /> php-fpm.conf xml format is a plain text file, you can open it yourself to see the details, basically a look to understand. Here special attention to what these configuration fields: <br /> &lt;value name=&quot;listen_address&quot;&gt; 127.0.0.1:9000 &lt;/ value&gt; </p><p><br /> Php in fastcgi process of this that the ip address and port monitoring <br /> &lt;value name=&quot;user&quot;&gt; nobody &lt;/ value&gt; <br /> &lt;value name=&quot;group&quot;&gt; nobody &lt;/ value&gt; </p><p><br /> Php fastcgi process that\'s what users and user groups to run <br /> &lt;value name=&quot;display_errors&quot;&gt; 0 &lt;/ value&gt; </p><p><br /> Php error message is displayed <br /> &lt;value name=&quot;max_children&quot;&gt; 5 &lt;/ value&gt; </p><p><br /> Here the largest number of child processes to run php-fpm: <br /> / Usr/local/php5/bin/php-cgi - fpm </p><p><br /> Php-fastcgi process is already running in the background, and monitor port 9000 of 127.0.0.1. <br /> Can use ps and netstat to see the results: <br /> ps aux | grep php-cgi </p><p><br /> netstat-tpl | grep php-cgi </p><p><br /> Installed the php-fpm, then it is how to achieve our original objective of it? <br /> Fortunately, php-fpm we are prepared to give yourself a program to control the fastcgi process, the file in $ PREFIX / sbin / php-fpm <br /> Run it: <br /> / Usr/local/php5/sbin/php-fpm </p><p><br /> The program has the following parameters: </p><p> php-fastcgi start the process of starting <br /> php in fastcgi stop the process of forced termination <br /> php in fastcgi quit to terminate the process smooth <br /> php in fastcgi restart the process of restarting <br /> reload to reload the php.ini php <br /> re-enable the log files logrotate </p><p> In other words, to modify the php.ini, we can use <br /> / Usr/local/php5/sbin/php-fpm reload </p><p><br /> Thus, to maintain the fastcgi php process in continuous operation in the state, and reload the php.ini. <br /> After the words: This file can be slightly modified, making it the CentOS / Redhat services, reducing the number of management overhead. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(244,'linux','en','/a/lb/2010/0422/22.html','Equipment in the fence on the discussion RHCS','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\">