2 machines directly connected Ethernet port, and the other subnet port access switch, <br /> Test, unplug the machine then switches A network cable, B machine able to re-fence the signal from the A machine, return success, and will take over services and resources; A machine up, the same switch then unplug the machine B cable, A machine able to re-fence the signal from the B machine, return success, and will take over services and resources; <br /> However, if you unplug the power cord A, then there will be problems switching, B fence signal will be issued the same machine, but because the power has been broken A machine can not reboot, can not signal a successful return, the result will be prepared by machine has been shown fence failed, but not to take over the service, which is not a BUG RHCS it? Or IPMI device does not support the pulling power, the landlord, please advise. </p><p> hqonline </p><p> Cluster.conf attached file, there is no problem to help look, thank you Moderators </p><p> &lt;? Xml version = &quot;1.0&quot;?&gt; <br /> &lt;cluster alias=&quot;dbcluster&quot; config_version=&quot;2&quot; name=&quot;alpha_cluster&quot;&gt; <br /> &lt;fence_daemon post_fail_delay=&quot;0&quot; post_join_delay=&quot;3&quot;/&gt; <br /> &lt;clusternodes&gt; <br /> &lt;clusternode name=&quot;netview1&quot; votes=&quot;1&quot;&gt; <br /> &lt;fence&gt; <br /> &lt;method name=&quot;1&quot;&gt; <br /> &lt;device name=&quot;bmc&quot;/&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Method&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Fence&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Clusternode&gt; <br /> &lt;clusternode name=&quot;netview2&quot; votes=&quot;1&quot;&gt; <br /> &lt;fence&gt; <br /> &lt;method name=&quot;1&quot;&gt; <br /> &lt;device name=&quot;bmc&quot;/&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Method&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Fence&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Clusternode&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Clusternodes&gt; <br /> &lt;cman expected_votes=&quot;1&quot; two_node=&quot;1&quot;/&gt; <br /> &lt;fencedevices&gt; <br /> &lt;fencedevice agent=&quot;fence_ipmilan&quot; auth=&quot;none&quot; ipaddr=&quot;10.10.10.100&quot; login=&quot;USERID&quot; name=&quot;bmc&quot; passwd=&quot;PASSW0RD&quot;/&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Fencedevices&gt; <br /> &lt;rm&gt; <br /> &lt;failoverdomains&gt; <br /> &lt;failoverdomain name=&quot;sybase&quot; ordered=&quot;0&quot; restricted=&quot;1&quot;&gt; <br /> &lt;failoverdomainnode name=&quot;netview2&quot; priority=&quot;1&quot;/&gt; <br /> &lt;failoverdomainnode name=&quot;netview1&quot; priority=&quot;1&quot;/&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Failoverdomain&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Failoverdomains&gt; <br /> &lt;resources&gt; <br /> &lt;Fs device = &quot;/ dev/sdb1&quot; force_fsck = &quot;0&quot; force_unmount = &quot;1&quot; fsid = &quot;57438&quot; fstype = &quot;ext3&quot; mountpoint = &quot;/ sybasedata&quot; name = &quot;shdisk&quot; options = &quot;&quot; self_fence = &quot;0&quot; /&gt; <br /> &lt;ip address=&quot;192.168.10.91&quot; monitor_link=&quot;1&quot;/&gt; <br /> &lt;ip address=&quot;192.168.16.92&quot; monitor_link=&quot;1&quot;/&gt; <br /> &lt;ip address=&quot;192.168.16.93&quot; monitor_link=&quot;1&quot;/&gt; <br /> &lt;script file=&quot;/cluster/dbstart.sh&quot; name=&quot;dbscript&quot;/&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Resources&gt; <br /> &lt;service autostart=&quot;1&quot; domain=&quot;sybase&quot; name=&quot;sybase&quot;&gt; <br /> &lt;ip ref=&quot;192.168.16.93&quot;&gt; <br /> &lt;fs ref=&quot;shdisk&quot;/&gt; <br /> &lt;script ref=&quot;dbscript&quot;/&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Ip&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Service&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Rm&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Cluster&gt; </p><p><br /> hqonline </p><p> With the results of the </p><p> Afternoon to find a REDHAT 800, finally asked out of the results, <br /> REDHAT the fence device has two internal fence device (such as IBM RSAII cards, HP\'s iLO cards, as well as IPMI devices, etc.) and external fence devices (such as UPS, SAN SWITCH, NETWORK SWITCH, etc.). <br /> For the external fence devices, you can pull the power to do the test, because the machine can receive the fence device prepared to return the signal can be properly prepared to take over local services, <br /> For internal fence equipment'),(245,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0421/10.html','Individual works &quot;step by step Linux&quot; reprinted again, hot hair','2010-04-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<html> <font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â¾Â®Ã¨Â½Â¯Ã©Â›Â…Ã©Â»Â‘\"><font color=\"#f00000\"><strong><font size=\"4\">Comments on the Publication <br /><br /></font></strong></font> <font size=\"3\">Press received notification of today\'s editorial, linux book &lt;&lt;a gradual <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\">Linux</a></u> &gt;&gt; has begun publishing a large number of long-awaited moment finally arrived, ecstatic, which is sad and bitter and difficult to form words! <br /><br /> I remember the first contact with linux was in 2000, that time was in college, a student from the Netherlands came back, brought back a copy of a Linux version, remember that version or Redhat6.2. Have to install a <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E7%B3%BB%E7%BB%9F\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">system</span> allows us to forget fatigue, burning the midnight oil, enjoying themselves. At that time, little <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E5%AD%A6%E4%B9%A0\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">Linux-learning</span> materials, books are not able to learn more rarely online Linux <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E6%8A%80%E6%9C%AF\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">technical</span> community, it relied on Redhat6.2 few pages of instructions that comes with starting a career of learning linux. <br /><br /> In 2008, I received the invitation of Posts and Telecommunications Publishing House, began to prepare writing a book on linux technology plan, the completion of the book, writing, publishing and distribution basically took a year\'s time, originally planned to complete this within six months the preparation of the contents, but in the end it took nearly 8 months, it appears that the specific implementation plan and not the same thing, looks very simple matter, but it is extremely difficult to do it! <br /> Technology for a long time to do, the language has become stiff, it will be complicated by the technical details of the written language to express clearly, is not an easy thing, had discretion to sentence a morning time, as smooth, easy to understand language can make readers understand the short period of time the meaning of technical books, while not required vivid language <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E5%90%88%E7%90%86\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">and</span> rationality, but to understand the language is the reader\'s favorite, I have limited language skills, not technical issues of each life visualization, but sought in the phrase to express clearly the technical details of each issue. <br /><br /> Linux side of things, although a number of online resources, but quite a mixed bag, not only difficult to judge the accuracy of, and not the system, not a system. The correctness of the pursuit of technical articles, I see a lot of technical information, and technology has done in each of the correctness test, build a system as large and small to express the meaning of a <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E5%8F%82%E6%95%B0\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">parameter,</span> as each technical staff linux can not access all the <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E7%9F%A5%E8%AF%86\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">knowledge</span> areas and details, so a large part to the test time is wasted on this process. <br /><br /> The greatest feature of the book focus on practice, theory and time combination is completed in about a knowledge point, usually accompanied by many examples of the practice of knowledge as a supplement, and each <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E7%AB%A0%E8%8A%82\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">chapter</span> is an independent knowledge, the reader can choose to read from the middle, you can also order from the first chapter to read. Throughout the book, is a progressive approach, from the point and surface, gradual process. <br /> This book is divided into five articles, a total of 20 chapters, the basic <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E7%BB%93%E6%9E%84\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">structure is</span> as follows: <br /> ÃƒÂ˜ <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E5%9F%BA%E7%A1%80\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">basics</span> chapter (chapter to chapter V) <br /> ÃƒÂ˜ <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E6%9C%8D%E5%8A%A1%E5%99%A8\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">server</span> set up (Part VI to IX) <br /> ÃƒÂ˜ System <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E7%AE%A1%E7%90%86\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">Management</span> chapter (Chapter X to Chapter XIV) <br /> ÃƒÂ˜ <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E6%80%A7%E8%83%BD\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">performance</span> tuning article (from Chapter XV Chapter XVI) <br /> ÃƒÂ˜ clustering, high availability chapter (Chapter to Chapter XVII)</font> <br /><br /> <font size=\"3\">The object of a book for Linux enthusiasts, Linux beginners, Enterprise Linux system administrators, database administrators, <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E7%BD%91%E7%BB%9C\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">network</span> security management, system integration, system <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E6%9E%84%E6%9E%B6\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">architect</span> and so on.</font></font> <br /></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"><img alt=\"01.jpg\" file=\"attachments/month_1001/10012212548197f839ad2e1199.jpg\" id=\"aimg_11\" initialized=\"true\" outfunc=\"null\" src=\"/uploads/allimg/100421/193J42M9-0.jpg\" status=\"2\" unselectable=\"true\" width=\"600\" /></p><p></p><p><br /> <font face=\"Ã¥Â¾Â®Ã¨Â½Â¯Ã©Â›Â…Ã©Â»Â‘ \"><font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>&quot;Step by step Linux&quot; Introduction</strong></font> <br /></font> <font color=\"#ff0000\"><br /> <font color=\"#000000\"><font face=\"Ã¥Â¾Â®Ã¨Â½Â¯Ã©Â›Â…Ã©Â»Â‘ \">Study: High Junfeng Press: Posts &amp; Telecom Press</font></font></font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong><font face=\"Ã¥Â¾Â®Ã¨Â½Â¯Ã©Â›Â…Ã©Â»Â‘\"><font size=\"4\"><span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E5%BE%AA%E5%BA%8F%E6%B8%90%E8%BF%9B\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\"><span id=\"1271849777211S\" style=\"display: none\">Ã‚Â </span> Gradual</span> <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=Linux\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">Linux</span> &quot;in major online <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E5%8F%91%E5%94%AE\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">bookstores</span> address</font></font></strong></font> <table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"t_table\"><tbody><tr><td width=\"108\"></td><td> <font color=\"#000000\"><font color=\"#ff0000\"><font face=\"Ã¥Â¾Â®Ã¨Â½Â¯Ã©Â›Â…Ã©Â»Â‘\">Direct Link</font></font></font> </td><td> <font face=\"Ã¥Â¾Â®Ã¨Â½Â¯Ã©Â›Â…Ã©Â»Â‘\">Price (yuan)</font> </td><td> <font face=\"Ã¥Â¾Â®Ã¨Â½Â¯Ã©Â›Â…Ã©Â»Â‘\">Savings (yuan)</font> </td></tr><tr><td> <font face=\"Ã¥Â¾Â®Ã¨Â½Â¯Ã©Â›Â…Ã©Â»Â‘\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"/uploads/allimg/100421/193J431V-1.gif\" width=\"96\" /></font> </td><td> <font color=\"#336699\" face=\"Ã¥Â¾Â®Ã¨Â½Â¯Ã©Â›Â…Ã©Â»Â‘\"><a href=\"http://www.douban.com/link2?type=buy&subject=4166071&vendor=joyo&url=http%3A//p.yiqifa.com/c%3Fs%3D4f667baf%26w%3D55880%26c%3D245%26i%3D201%26l%3D0%26e%3D27390436_s4166071%26t%3Dhttp%3A//www.amazon.cn/mn/detailApp%3Fasin%3DB002YQ3WXU\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a></font> </td><td>'),(246,'linux','en','/a/web/nginx/2010/0421/4.html','Manager of nginx FastCGI tuning php-fpm','2010-04-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Nginx excellent performance of highly concurrent, it was equipped with a Nginx + php-fpm to run online agent, is assigned according to Zhang Yan article, just configured to run normally, but after running for some time, the site is slow to open, open website, enter in the input box to access the site, but also not slow. When the site opens slowly, in the SSH terminal, type the command is also slow, speed suspected room, but to enter the ssh <br /> w3m www.example.com <br /> The Open is also slow, which can rule out the engine room of the speed issue. <br /> When you open the site is slow, the server is restarted, it will be faster, but later found, with <br /> / Usr / local / webserver / php / sbin / php-fpm restart <br /> Will quickly put them under fastcgi restart, add it to plan the mission, the hourly restart, the basic guarantee for the site will not slow, but in the end not a solution. <br /> View the nginx.log and php-fpm.log, according to which the error, find the articles reproduced in the above, the problem is finally solved, the main change of the two places <br /> 1 <br /> Question: <br /> Find / usr / local / webserver / php / etc / php-fpm.conf file defines the number of open file descriptor limit is <br /> &lt;value name=&quot;rlimit_files&quot;&gt; 51200 &lt;/ value&gt; <br /> But with the command ulimit-n view, found that only 1024 <br /> I have in / etc / rc.local to add the <br /> ulimit-SHn 51200 <br /> Effect did not even address: <br /> vi / etc / security / limits.conf <br /> Document concludes with <br /> * Soft nofile 51200 <br /> * Hard nofile 51200 <br /> 2 <br /> Question: <br /> Command <br /> netstat-np | grep 127.0.0.1:9000 | wc-l <br /> Found that only 100 to solve: <br /> According to server memory situation, you can put the number of PHP FastCGI child transferred to 100 or more servers in the 200 4G of memory on the server memory can 8G, I put the number of PHP FastCGI child adjusted to 300 <br /> vi / usr / local / webserver / php / etc / php-fpm.conf <br /> Revised to 300 will be max_children <br /> &lt;value name=&quot;max_children&quot;&gt; 300 &lt;/ value&gt; <br /> Restart the server so the site opens fast and stable. </p><p> When you running a highload website with PHP-FPM via FastCGI, the following tips may be useful to you:) <br /> If you use high-load site management of PHP-FPM FastCGI, these techniques may be useful to you:) </p><p> 1. Compile PHP\'s modules as less as possible, the simple the best (fast); <br /> 1. As little as possible to install PHP modules, the simplest is the best (fast) </p><p> 2. Increas PHP FastCGI child number to 100 and even more. Sometime, 200 is OK! (On 4GB memory server); <br /> 2. Put your PHP FastCGI child processes transferred to 100 or more, in the 200 4G of memory on the server can Note: 1g of my test machine, opening 64 is the best stress test is recommended to obtain the best value </p><p> 3. Using SOCKET PHP FastCGI, and put into / dev / shm on Linux; <br /> 3. Using socket connection FastCGI, linux operating system on / dev / shm in Note: php-fpm.cnf in setting &lt;value name=&quot;listen_address&quot;&gt; / tmp / nginx.socket &lt;/ value&gt; to connect through socket FastCGI connections was, / dev / shm is a memory file system, will certainly be on the fast memory (this step to be confirmed) </p><p> 4. Increase Linux &quot;max open files&quot;, using the following command (must be root): <br /> # Echo \'ulimit-HSn 65536\'&gt;&gt; / etc / profile <br /> # Echo \'ulimit-HSn 65536&gt;&gt; / etc / rc.local <br /> # Source / etc / profile <br /> 4. To increase the number of open files linux kernel, you can use these commands (must be the root account) <br /> echo \'ulimit-HSn 65536\'&gt;&gt; / etc / profile <br /> echo \'ulimit-HSn 65536\'&gt;&gt; / etc / rc.local <br /> source / etc / profile <br /> Note: I modified / etc / rc.local, add the ulimit-SHn 51200 </p><p> 5. Increase PHP-FPM open file description rlimit: <br /> # Vi / path / to / php-fpm.conf <br /> Find &quot;&lt;value name=&quot;rlimit_files&quot;&gt; 1024 &lt;/ value&gt;&quot; <br /> Change 1024 to 4096 or higher number. <br /> Restart PHP-FPM. <br /> 5. Increase the PHP-FPM open file descriptor limit: <br /> # Vi / path / to / php-fpm.conf <br /> Find &quot;&lt;value name=&quot;rlimit_files&quot;&gt; 1024 &lt;/ value&gt;&quot; <br /> Change 4096 to 1024 or higher. <br /> Restart the PHP-FPM. </p><p><br /> 6. Using PHP code accelerator, eg eAccelerator, XCache. And set &quot;cache_dir&quot; to / dev / shm on Linux. <br /> 6. Using php code accelerators, such as eAccelerator, XCache. In the linux platform can `cache_dir` point to / dev / shm </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(247,'linux','en','/a/os/Solris/2010/0422/30.html','Solaris Performance Tuning Experience','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> In the maintenance of Solaris, is often <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/\"><span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E7%B3%BB%E7%BB%9F\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">the system</span></a></u> <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E6%80%A7%E8%83%BD\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">performance of</span> maintenance problems affecting the system performance by many factors, we will average the load on the system, <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E8%BF%9B%E7%A8%8B\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">process</span> monitoring, CPU, I / O and memory <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E7%AE%A1%E7%90%86\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">management,</span> <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E7%BD%91%E7%BB%9C\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">network</span> traffic diagnostics described aspects of the analysis presented in the performance of maintenance on some of the Solaris methods and experience. <br /> Performance of the system is done in the case of the system, its effectiveness, stability and response rate. System administrators often complain about poor performance, instability, slow system response, etc., all such issues are only some of the symptoms. The performance of the whole network system is good or bad network <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E7%BB%93%E6%9E%84\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">topology,</span> <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E6%9C%8D%E5%8A%A1%E5%99%A8\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">server</span> system, routing device, routing policy, access equipment, physical line, and other closely related, problems in any one part will affect the performance of the whole system . Before optimizing the performance of the entire system must be monitored every step of the audit <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E5%90%88%E7%90%86\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">the</span> reasonableness of the use of system resources and distribution. Server and workstation system performance depends on how it is good or bad the rational use and allocation of its resources, regularly monitoring the performance audit system is very important, and should know what resources to monitor the system. System resources include three aspects: <br /> ---- 1, CPU; <br /> ---- 2, the memory subsystem; <br /> ---- 3, I / O subsystem. <br /> This 3, whether the one hand, a problem that will impact on system performance, and auditing system performance is from 3 aspects. Performance audit of many <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E5%B7%A5%E5%85%B7\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">tools</span> in the Solaris <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E6%93%8D%E4%BD%9C%E7%B3%BB%E7%BB%9F\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">operating system</span> offers a variety of system resources for <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E8%BF%90%E8%A1%8C\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">the operation of</span> the audit tools, including: <br /> The uptime and sar commands, used to report the system load average; <br /> The ps command, the system is running the process to provide relevant information; <br /> The df command, provide disk usage information; <br /> The vmstat, iostat and sar commands, the activities of the reporting system to provide information about memory usage, I / O <br /> System information, CPU activity, etc.; <br /> The swap command, to the use of statistical systems in the swap; <br /> The netstat command, used to display information on network performance. <br /> It is noteworthy that, for the server / workstation system, due to the increasing volume of users, the system resource use and allocation may be more reasonable period of time, over time, system resources may be in a state of overload operation, so that the system performance management is a long term, should the system performance management as part of routine system administration tasks to maintain the system reliable, efficient operation. <br /> Optimize the performance of the system, you must know the system\'s hardware resources, software resources and the entire system configuration to use if there are problems. The discovery of these issues are often built on the system to people\'s impression. For example: the system slower response to the user, the process need to spend more time running and more. If you find these phenomena, it should be the main resource data acquisition systems and analysis, to find ways to improve system performance. <br /><br /> System <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E6%80%A7%E8%83%BD%E5%88%86%E6%9E%90\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">performance analysis</span> of standard tools: <br /> CPU: vmstat sar ps <br /> Memory: vmstat ps <br /> Disk: iostat vmstat <br /> Network: netstat nfsstat <br /> General performance tuning steps Note: the general standard should be: <br /> The main purpose of tuning the system to effectively use various resources, but to measure system resource utilization criteria for what is good or bad for different systems and <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E5%BA%94%E7%94%A8\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">applications</span> is no strict definition, a general reference to the following criteria to determine use of key resources Status: <br /><br /> Good bad bad <br /> CPU: user% + sys% &lt;70% user% + sys% = 85% user% + sys%&gt; = 90% <br /> Disk: iowait% &lt;30% iowait% = 40% iowait%&gt; = 50% <br /> Memory: No Page In &amp; Page Out Per CPU with 10 page / s More Page In &amp; Page Out <br /> Network: &lt;30% Bandwidth <br /> By following these steps, that affect the overall performance of key resources, performance optimization, if necessary, need to add or upgrade certain hardware devices. <br /> 1. Using iostat, sar detect whether the CPU causes <br /> 2. With vmstat, svmon detect the cause of the memory <br /> 3. With filemon, iostat detect the cause of the <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E7%A1%AC%E7%9B%98\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">hard disk</span> <br /> 4. With netstat, nfsstat detect whether the network causes <br /><br /> First, the system average load system at different times of the average load (Last mimute, Last 5 minutes, Last 15 minutes) was used to assess whether the system is overloaded more convenient, more commonly used methods. System under normal operation, the range of 3 values should be 0-2. For the Solaris operating system, you can use the following <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E5%91%BD%E4%BB%A4\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">command to</span> get a few average system load (for the host <br /> <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=solaris\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">solaris</span> EXP example): <br /><br /> ---- 1. Uptime <br /> solarisEXP% uptime <br /> 2:06 pm to run 1 day 5:27,7 users, load average: 0.00,0.01,0.01 <br /> ---- 2, sar (system activity reporter) command itself can be used to collect system activity data or from the daily activities of the establishment sadc extract <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E6%96%87%E4%BB%B6\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">the file</span> system activity data. <br /> solarisEXP% sar-q (taken from the file data) <br /> 00:00:01 runq-sz% runocc swpq-sz% swpocc <br /> 01:00:01 1.0 0 <br /> 02:00:01 1.8 0 <br /> 03:00:01 1.3 0 <br /> 04:00:01 1.8 0 <br /> 05:00:01 2.0 0 <br /> Average 1.6 0 <br /><br /> ---- Or use: &quot;sar-options tn&quot; starting from the current in t seconds (t&gt; = 5) time interval, the data acquisition system activity n times. <br /> ---- Runq-sz normal circumstances it should be less than 2. If this value is greater than 2 show that the system may be continuous in the CPU-bound state. <br /> If more than 90% runocc and runq-sz is greater than 2, indicating that the CPU is in overload, the system response rate of decline. <br /> Example: <br /> sar-u shows the meaning of item (check the CPU utilization) <br /> % Usr cpu time for the implementation of user process <br /> % Sys cpu time for the implementation of system processes <br /> % Wio cpu pending completion of the I / O time <br /> % Idel cpu idle time display the results of that under normal circumstances% usr and% sys is basically the same values in the general multi-user systems,% idel value is usually greater than 40% <br /> If'),(248,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0430/94.html','&quot;Step by step Linux&quot; book Errata (May 7, 2010','2010-04-30','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">In the &quot;step by step Linux&quot; published by the occasion of six months, thank you for your understanding and support, many readers gave us a lot of suggestions and comments, thank you for this, because I is limited, with some typesetting errors that cause some errors, please forgive me, here I will continue listing the omission of the book and some small mistakes, hope that they can bring some help in reading!</font> </p><p></p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\" face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">4.2.1 Section 78 of Chapter IV</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">In the &quot;ls options and their implications&quot; list</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">&quot;-R&quot; option to repeat</font> </p><p><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\" face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">80 pages in 4.2.4</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">date command parameter list</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">&quot;% C&quot; parameters of duplication and the first in this list% c option means due to typographical error, error code causing the error, the second &quot;% c&quot; parameter is the meaning of the right to the second basis.</font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\" face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">In Section 4.7, page 125, Table 4.47</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">&quot;: Wq&quot; the meaning, <font color=\"#ff6600\">&quot;: wq!&quot; Said they did not save, force quit,</font> it should be changed to <font color=\"#ff6600\">&quot;: wq!&quot; Save and exit, said mandatory</font></font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\" face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">6.1.1 Section 146 of Chapter VI</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">The first section, <br /> &quot;Software is superior to software based on&quot; should read &quot;software is based on superior hardware&quot;</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Page P58</span> <br /> Table 3.6 should be meminfo in meninfo</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Page P76</span> <br /> 4.shell the pipeline, &quot;the first a command input as the first two command output&quot; <br /> Should be &quot;the first one command\'s output as the first two command input&quot;</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Page P77</span> <br /> The section on the double quotes <br /> [Root @ LinuxTest ~] # str = &quot;This hotname is \'hostname\'&quot;</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Should be replaced</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">[Root @ LinuxTest ~] # str = &quot;This hotname is` hostname `&quot; <br /></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">P106 Page</span> <br /> 2. Example (3) in the <br /> tar-jtvf / opt / etc.tar.gz <br /> Should be <br /> tar-jtvf / opt/etc.tar.bz2</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">P141 Page</span> <br /> The last line <br /> tar-jxvf xxxxxx.tar.gz <br /> Should be <br /> tar-jxvf xxxxxx.tar.bz2</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">P160 Page <br /></span> 6.3.3 The title should be &quot;the concept of routing and configuration&quot;</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">P182 Table 7.1 on page <br /> Apmd should be &quot;apmd&quot; <br /> Kudzu should be a &quot;kudzu&quot; <br /><br /> <span style=\"color: #ff0000\">P227 <br /></span> 2. Vsftp configuration section in the &quot;where&quot; section of &quot;user.list is to allow the user list&quot; should be &quot;user_list is a list of users allowed&quot;</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Adjourned. .</font> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(249,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0817/485.html','[IMG]','2010-08-17','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Linux operating <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/\">system</a></u> is an open source product, but also a practice and application of open source software platform, this platform supports numerous open source software, our common apache, tomcat, mysql, php, etc., the largest open source software philosophy is free, open, then linux as an open source platform, and ultimately to be achieved is through these open-source software support to the most low cost, to achieve optimum application performance. Therefore, talking about performance issues, the main achievement is the linux operating <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/\">system</a></u> and applications the best combination.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Performance of the system is the operating system to complete the task effectiveness, stability and response speed. Linux system administrators may often encounter system instability, slow response and other issues, such as linux on a web service built, often can not open the page, and so slow to open, while experiencing these problems, some people will complain about linux system is not good, in fact, these are superficial. Operating system to complete a task, and the system itself settings, network topology, routing equipment, routing strategies, access equipment, and other aspects of the physical line is closely related to any aspect of a problem, it will affect the whole system performance. So when a problem occurs linux applications, it should be from the application, operating system, server hardware, network environment, comprehensive investigation, in which part of the positioning problems, and then concentrate on solving. <br /> In the application, operating system, server hardware, network environment, etc., affect the performance of most applications and operating systems are two aspects, because these two aspects of the problems difficult to detect, very subtle. The hardware, network problems as long as they are generally able to immediately locate. This chapter explains the main idea of the operating system\'s performance tuning, application specific problems need specific treatment. <br /><br /> Resolve system performance issues affect the general idea of the operating system from the performance of the following factors, performance optimization tools, system performance evaluation criteria introduced three Linux-optimized general ideas and methods. <br /><br /> <strong>Factors that affect the Linux performance</strong> <br /> <strong>1. CPU</strong> <br /> CPU is a fundamental and stable operation of the operating system, CPU speed and performance of a large part determines the overall system performance, therefore, cpu more the number the higher the frequency, the server also has a better performance. But that is not exactly true. <br /> Currently, most CPU can only run at the same time, a thread, Hyper-Threading processor can run multiple threads at the same time, therefore, can take advantage of Hyper-Threading processor features to improve system performance, in the linux system, only to run SMP kernel to support Hyper-Threading, but the greater the number of the installed CPU, Hyper-Threading obtained from the improved performance less. In addition, Linux kernel will multi-core processors as multiple separate CPU to identify, for example, two 4-core CPU, will be recognized in the linux system to eight CPU. But from a performance point of view, two 4-core CPU and eight single-core CPU is not completely equivalent, according to authorities test the conclusions drawn from the former than the latter to the overall performance of 25% -30%. <br /> The application may be a CPU bottleneck mail server, dynamic web servers, etc., for such applications should CPU configuration and performance on the main position. <br /> <strong>2. Memory <br /></strong> Linux memory size is also affected an important factor in performance, memory is too small, the system process will be blocked, the application will also become slow, or even loss of response, the memory is too large, resulting in waste of resources. Linux system uses the physical memory and virtual memory concepts, virtual memory, although you can ease the shortage of physical memory, but take up too much virtual memory, application performance will fall significantly, to ensure high-performance applications to run, physical memory must should be large enough, but too much physical memory will cause a waste of memory resources, such as 32-bit processor in a Linux operating system, more than 8G of physical memory will be wasted. Therefore, to use more memory, it is recommended to install 64-bit operating system, and open the linux kernel to support the large memory. <br /> Since the processor addressing range of restrictions, 32-bit linux operating system, applications can only use a single process the maximum 2G memory, so since, even if the system has more memory, the application can not &quot;enjoy&quot; using address approach is to use 64 as the processor, install the 64-bit operating system, the 64-bit operating system, all applications meet the demand for the use of memory [g1], almost no restrictions. <br /> Potential application performance bottlenecks of memory with print server, database server, static web servers, etc., for such applications on the main memory size should position. <br /> <strong>3. Disk I / O bandwidth</strong> &lt;br /&gt; disk I / O performance directly affects the performance of the application, read and write in the application of a frequent, if the disk I / O performance are not met, the application will lead to stagnation. Fortunately, today\'s disks are used a lot of ways to improve the I / O performance, such as the common disk RAID technology. <br /> Full name in English RAID: Redundant Array of Independent Disks. Translated into Chinese is the redundant array of independent disks, called disk arrays. Through the multi-block independent RAID disk (physical disk) in different combinations to form a disk group (logical drives), which provides more than a single disk I / O performance and data redundancy. <br /> RAID technology components through the disk group, the equivalent of a large hard drive, users can partition it format, a file system, etc, with the same single physical hard drive, the only difference is that RAID disk group, I / O performance than a single hard disk is much higher, while data security is also a great improvement. <br /> Different combinations according to the disk, RAID can be divided into RAID0, RAID1, RAID2, RAID3, RAID4, RAID5, RAID6, RAID7, RAID0 +1, RAID10 and other levels, commonly used RAID levels are RAID0, RAID1, RAID5, RAID0 +1, here briefly as follows: <br /> l RAID 0: By bonding multiple hard drives into a larger hard drive group, increased disk performance and throughput. This Fangshi low cost, requires at least two disks, but no fault tolerance and data recovery capabilities, which can only be used for less demanding data security environment. <br /> l RAID 1: disk mirroring is, by mirroring the data from one disk to another disk, disk to ensure maximum data reliability and recoverability, high data redundancy, but only the disk utilization 50%, and therefore, the highest cost, the use of the occasion in preserving important data. <br /> l RAID5: use of sub-additive odd parity disk technology to improve system reliability, RAID5 efficient read, write efficiency in general, at least three disks. Allow a disk failure, without affecting data availability. <br /> l RAID0 +1: the combination of RAID0 and RAID1 technology became RAID0 +1, at least 4 hard drives. In addition to the distribution of data in this way in a number of disc, each disc has its mirror disk, to provide full redundancy, while allowing a disk failure, without affecting data availability and fast read / write capability. <br /> Through the introduction of various RAID levels, we can apply the different characteristics of RAID to choose their own level, to ensure applications achieve optimal disk performance. <br /> <strong>4. Network I / O bandwidth</strong> <br /> Applications under Linux in general are based on the network, so network bandwidth is also an important factor affecting performance, slow and unstable network will result in blocking access to Web applications, and stable, high-speed bandwidth, can guarantee applications run unimpeded on the network. Fortunately, now generally Gigabit network bandwidth, or fiber-optic network, bandwidth issues on the impact of application performance are gradually reduced. <br /> <strong>5.</strong> &lt;br /&gt; <strong>Summarized</strong> by the above four aspects of the talk, not difficult to see, between each area are interdependent, can not be isolated in some ways to troubleshoot the problem, when one is experiencing performance problems, often cause problems in other areas. For example, is bound to consume a lot of CPU and disk read and write I / O resources, and memory deficiency can lead to frequent the memory pages written to disk, memory, disk write operations, resulting in disk I / O bottlenecks, while a large number of network traffic also cause CPU overload. Therefore, in dealing with performance issues, we should look at the overall situation into account in all its aspects.</span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(250,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0812/444.html','[IMG]','2010-08-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">concept and function of samba</span></span></strong> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Samba is a Linux system application allows Microsoft network communication protocol software, which is the Server Message Block SMB stands, is the Server Message Block, SMB mainly as Microsoft\'s network protocols, Samba the SMB protocol was applied to the Linux system on to the formation of the Samba software now. Microsoft SMB again later renamed CIFS (Common Internet File System), the public Internet File System, and added many new features, since this makes Samba with the more powerful. <br /> The biggest feature is the Samba Linux and windows systems can be used for direct file sharing and print sharing, Samba can be used for both windows and file sharing between Linux, Linux and Linux can also be used for resource sharing between, as NFS ( Network File System) can be well done between Linux and the Linux data sharing, and therefore more Samba Linux and windows used in the data sharing between the above. <br /> SMB is based on client / server type of agreement, and therefore, a Samba server can either act as a file sharing server, can also act as a Samba client, for example, in Linux, have a good Samba server set up, windows client SMB protocol to share through the resources on the Samba file server, while, Samba server can also access the network of other windows system or Linux system to share out files. <br /> Samba is used under the windows NetBIOS protocol, if you want to use Linux, to share out files, make sure your windows system is installed NetBIOS protocol. <br /></span></span> </p><p> <strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Samba installation and configuration</span></span></strong> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Our system environment is: <br /> Operating System: Red Hat Enterprise Linux Server release 5.1 <br /> Samba server IP address: 192.168.60.231 <br /> Samba version: samba-3.0.23c-2 <br /> <strong>1. Install samba</strong> <br /> Almost all Linux distributions by default comes in the package samba, landing systems, check whether the software is installed Samba, do the following: <br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # rpm-q samba <br /> samba-3.0.23c-2 <br /> If you have indicated that the system has been installed Samba, if there is no display, please go to the Samba system CD to find the corresponding package and install it. <br /> Samba installation is very simple, the installation process is as follows: <br /> [Root @ webserver ~] # rpm-ivh samba-3.0.23c-2.i386.rpm <br /> warning: samba-3.0.23c-2.i386.rpm: Header V3 DSA signature: NOKEY, key ID 37017186 <br /> Preparing ... ########################################### [100% ] <br /> 1: samba ########################################### [100%] <br /> Samba server is installed, will generate the configuration file directory / etc / samba samba executable commands and other tools, / etc / samba / smb.conf is the core of samba configuration file, / etc / init.d / smb start a samba / close the file. <br /> <strong>2. The composition and use of Samba services</strong> &lt;br /&gt; There are two components to run Samba services, one is SMB, the other is the NMB; SMB is the core of Samba to start the service, only the SMB service starts, the file sharing can be achieved, and NMB services is responsible for parsing the use, similar to DNS implementation feature, NMB Linux systems can share the name of the working group correspond to their IP, if the NMB service does not start, you can only access the shared files through the IP. <br /> For example, a platform for the Samba server IP address 192.168.60.231, the corresponding working group named ixdba, then in Windows, IE browser and type the following two commands can access shared files. In fact, this is Windows, see Linux Samba server to share documents. <br /> \\ \\ 192.168.60.231 \\ shared directory name <br /> \\ \\ Ixdba \\ shared directory name can be / etc / init.d / smb start / stop / restart to startup, shutdown, restart the Samba service, start the SMB service is as follows: <br /> [Root @ localhost Linuxdata] # / etc / init.d / smb start <br /> Starting SMB services: [OK] <br /> Starting NMB services: [OK] <br /> The output from the start, we can see, SMB\'s SMB and NMB start includes two services. <br /> Then Linux as a client, the view shared by other Linux Samba file server, how does it work, which use this tool to smbclient. The default comes with this command. Smbclient common use are described below. <br /> <u>(1) View Samba server to share information <br /></u> Smbclient-L / / Samba server ip address-U Samba user name &quot;-L&quot; list is the meaning of, &quot;-U&quot; is the user\'s meaning, if the Samba server is not password access, you can omit the &quot;-U Samba Users Name. &quot; <br /> For example: samba requires a password login, view shared as follows: <br /> [Root @ web ~] # smbclient-L / / 192.168.60.231/Linuxdata-U admin <br /> Password: Enter the admin password here. <br /> Samba no password access, execute the following command: <br /> [Root @ web ~] # smbclient-L / / 192.168.60.231/Linuxdata <br /> Password: Direct press Enter. <br /> <u>(2) landing Samba server</u> &lt;br /&gt; If you need to log in the Linux Samba server, the client, use the following: <br /> Smbclient / / Samba server ip address-U Samba user name see the following Action: <br /> [Root @ web samba] # smbclient / / 192.168.60.231/Linuxdata <br /> Password: <br /> Domain = [IXDBA.NET] OS = [Unix] Server = [Samba 3.0.23c-2] <br /> Server not using user level security and no password supplied. <br /> smb: \\&gt; ls <br /> . D 0 Thu Feb 19 23:49:33 2009 <br /> .. D 0 Thu Feb 19 19:05:24 2009 <br /> install.log 36563 Thu Feb 19 23:49:22 2009 <br /> install.log.syslog 4295 Thu Feb 19 23:49:22 2009 <br /><br /> 58113 blocks of size 262144. 44294 blocks available <br /> smb: \\&gt;? # enter here? to see the smb command line available to all commands. <br /> ? Altname archive blocksize cancel <br /> case_sensitive cd chmod chown close <br /> del dir du exit get <br /> getfacl hardlink help history lcd <br /> link lock lowercase ls mask <br /> md mget mkdir mor</span></span>'),(251,'linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0421/6.html','linux hosts.allow is set and the hosts.','2010-04-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> hosts.allow and hosts.deny <br /> Both <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E6%96%87%E4%BB%B6\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">files</span> are in / etc / <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E7%9B%AE%E5%BD%95\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">directory,</span> priority check hosts.deny, and then check hosts.allow, <br /> The latter over the former setting limits <br /><br /> For example: <br /> 1. Restrict all of the ssh, <br /> Except from 218.64.87.0 - 127 up. <br /> hosts.deny: <br /> in.sshd: ALL <br /> hosts.allow: <br /> in.sshd: 218.64.87.0/255.255.255.128 <br /><br /> 2. Sealing of 218.64.87.0 - 127 of telnet <br /> hosts.deny <br /> in.sshd: 218.64.87.0/255.255.255.128 <br /><br /> 3. Limit all TCP connections, unless from 218.64.87.0 - 127 visits <br /> hosts.deny <br /> ALL: ALL <br /> hosts.allow <br /> ALL: 218.64.87.0/255.255.255.128 <br /><br /> 4. Restrict 218.64.87.0 - 127 access to all services <br /> hosts.deny <br /> ALL: 218.64.87.0/255.255.255.128 <br /><br /> Colon in front of where the service is TCP daemon <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E8%BF%9B%E7%A8%8B\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">process</span> name, this is <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E7%B3%BB%E7%BB%9F\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">usually</span> <br /> Process in the / etc / inetd.conf to specify, for example in.ftpd, in.telnetd, in.sshd <br /><br /> IP address range in which the wording of several of the main three are: <br /> 1. <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E7%BD%91%E7%BB%9C\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">Network</span> Address - Subnet Mask Mode: <br /> 218.64.87.0/255.255.255.0 <br /> 2. Network address means (my own so called, huh, huh) <br /> 218.64. (That is, the IP address starts with 218.64) <br /> 3. Subnet mask abbreviated way, both in front of one of the best binary subnet mask number &quot;1&quot; for example: <br /> 218.64.87.0/255.255.255.0 &quot;====&quot; 218.64.87.0/24 </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(252,'linux','en','/a/db/mysql/2010/0521/110.html','[IMG]','2010-05-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> First, you have a table! <br /> CREATE TABLE example ( <br /> ID Number (4) NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY, <br /> NAME VARCHAR (25), <br /> PHONE VARCHAR (10), <br /> ADDRESS VARCHAR (50)); <br /> If you build the table for the above statement is also in doubt, we recommend that you do not continue it! Has those times you do not like to see Jin Qiong Yao read! <br /> Then, you need a custom sequence <br /> CREATE SEQUENCE emp_sequence <br /> INCREMENT BY 1 - plus a few each <br /> START WITH 1 - start counting from 1 <br /> NOMAXVALUE - do not set the maximum <br /> NOCYCLE - has been incremental, not cycle <br /> NOCACHE - do not build a buffer to complete the above code sequence (sequence) of the building process, the name emp_sequence, the range is from 1 to infinity (infinite extent is determined by your machine), nocycle the decision not to cycle If you set the maximum you can use the cycle to the largest circulation, would seq. For nocache By the way if you give a cache value of the system will automatically read the value of your cache size of a seq <br /> This will speed up the repeated operation speed, but if circumstances such as when an accident or the oracle of the dead machine, then the next value will be removed and the last seq incoherent. (It does not matter if even suggested incoherent cache, Because time is money it! beside the point!) <br /> Connected to the text book, you have only a table and the sequence is not enough, you also need a trigger to execute it! Code: <br /> CREATE TRIGGER &quot;trigger name&quot; BEFORE <br /> INSERT ON example FOR EACH ROW WHEN (new.id is null) <br /> begin <br /> select emp_sequence.nextval into: new.id from dual; <br /> end; <br /> Once on shore, call it a day! Here you try to insert data into it! <br /> INSERT INTO example (Name, phone, address) Values (\'\'Cao\'\',\'\' 56498543\'\',\'\' Heibei\'\'); <br /></p><p> ================================================== =========== <br /> ORACLE SEQUENCE brief introduction (from the growth of field) - - </p><p> In the oracle in the serial number sequence is called each time when it will be automatically taken to increase, generally required by the serial number used in the sort of place. <br /> 1, CreateSequence <br /> You must first have CREATESEQUENCE or CREATEANYSEQUENCE permissions <br /> CREATESEQUENCEemp_sequence <br /> INCREMENTBY1 - plus a few each <br /> STARTWITH1 - start counting from 1 <br /> NOMAXVALUE - do not set the maximum <br /> NOCYCLE - has been incremental, not cycle <br /> CACHE10; </p><p> Once you have defined emp_sequence, you can use CURRVAL, NEXTVAL <br /> CURRVAL = returns the current value of sequence <br /> NEXTVAL = the value added sequence, and then return sequence values such as: <br /> emp_sequence.CURRVAL <br /> emp_sequence.NEXTVAL </p><p> Can use the sequence of places: <br /> - Does not contain a sub-query, snapshot, VIEW of the SELECT statement <br /> -INSERT statement in a subquery <br /> -NSERT statement in the VALUES <br /> -UPDATE\'s SET in </p><p> Can see the following example: <br /> INSERTINTOempVALUES <br /> (Empseq.nextval,\'\'LEWIS\'\',\'\' CLERK\'\', 7902, SYSDATE, 1200, NULL, 20); </p><p> SELECTempseq.currvalFROMDUAL; </p><p> However, to note are: <br /> - The first returns the initial value NEXTVAL; subsequent NEXTVAL will automatically increase your INCREMENTBY defined value, then return to the increased value. SEQUENCE CURRVAL always returns the current value, but only after the first use initialization NEXTVAL CURRVAL, otherwise it will go wrong. NEXTVAL will increase once the value of a SEQUENCE, so if you are in the same statement, which use multiple NEXTVAL, its value is not the same. Understand? </p><p> - If you specify CACHE value, ORACLE memory which can be placed in a number of pre-sequence, so that faster access. After the cache inside the access, oracle and then take a group to automatically cache. No use of cache may jump, such as abnormal down suddenly off the database (shutdownabort), cache in the sequence will be lost. Therefore, when used in the createsequence nocache to prevent this situation. </p><p> 2, AlterSequence <br /> Is the sequence you or the owner, or have ALTERANYSEQUENCE permission to change sequence. You can start to alter than all the other sequence parameters. If you want to change the start value, you must dropsequence then re-create. <br /> Altersequence example <br /> ALTERSEQUENCEemp_sequence <br /> INCREMENTBY10 <br /> MAXVALUE10000 <br /> CYCLE - to 10,000 from scratch after <br /> NOCACHE; </p><p><br /> Sequence of the initialization parameters: <br /> SEQUENCE_CACHE_ENTRIES = cache settings can also be the sequence number. </p><p> Can be very simple DropSequence <br /> DROPSEQUENCEorder_seq; </p><p><br /> All right, here. </p><p><br /> -------------------------------------------------- ----------- <br /> Since the growth and triggers: </p><p> How to implement Oracle features like automatic increase ID? <br /> Finishing editor: ChinaASP </p><p> We often used in the design of the database when the ID is automatically assigned a system as our primary key, but there is no such ORACLE </p><p> Function, we can take the following functions automatically increase the ID of the function <br /> 1. First, create a sequence <br /> createsequenceseqmaxincrementby1 <br /> 2. Use <br /> selectseqmax.nextvalIDfromdual <br /> To get a ID <br /> If this statement is on the trigger, you can achieve the automatic increase in ID and mssql the same functionality! </p><p><br /> -------------------------------------------------- ----------------------- </p><p> Create table # # # # # # </p><p> CREATETABLE &quot;SPORTS&quot;. &quot;LINEUP&quot; (&quot;ID&quot; NUMBERNOTNULL, &quot;TYPE&quot; <br /> NUMBER (3) NOTNULL, &quot;BODY&quot; VARCHAR2 (100) NOTNULL, &quot;HITS&quot; NUMBER ( <br /> 10) DEFAULT0NOTNULL, PRIMARYKEY (&quot;ID&quot;)) <br /> TABLESPACE &quot;TS_SPORTS&quot; </p><p> Construction sequence # # # # # # </p><p> CREATESEQUENCE &quot;SPORTS&quot;. &quot;SPORTS_LINEUP_ID_SEQ&quot; INCREMENTBY1 <br /> STARTWITH1MAXVALUE1.0E28MINVALUE1NOCYCLE <br /> CACHE50NOORDER </p><p> # # # Build triggers automatic update # # # </p><p> CREATEORREPLACETRIGGER &quot;SPORTS&quot;. &quot;SPORTS_LINEUP_ID_TRIGGER&quot; <br /> BEFOREINSERT <br /> ON &quot;SPORTS&quot;. &quot;LINEUP&quot; <br /> FOREACHROW <br /> DECLARE <br /> next_idNUMBER; <br /> BEGIN <br /> - Getthenextidnumberfromthesequence <br /> SELECTsports_lineup_id_seq.NEXTVAL <br /> INTOnext_id <br /> FROMdual; </p><p> - Usethesequencenumberastheprimarykey <br /> - Fortherecordbeinginserted. <br /> : New.id: = next_id; <br /> END; </p><p> # # # Build protection PRIMARYKEY trigger # # # </p><p> CREATEORREPLACETRIGGER &quot;SPORTS&quot;. &quot;LINEUP_ID_UPDATE_TRIGGER&quot; <br /> BEFOREUPDATEOF &quot;ID&quot; ON &quot;SPORTS&quot;. &quot;LINEUP&quot; <br /> FOREACHROW <br /> BEGIN <br /> RAISE_APPLICATION_ERROR (-20000, <br /> \'\'Sports_lineup_id_update_trigger: UpdatesoftheIDfield\'\' <br /> | |\'\'Arenotallowed .\'\'); <br /> END; </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(253,'linux','en','/a/db/oracle/2010/0422/20.html','Used to solve data dblink oracle snapshot','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> This example has been fully tested, one-way, two-way synchronization can be used. </p><p> - Terms Description: Source - are synchronized <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/db/\">database</a></u> <br /> Objective - To synchronize to the database </p><p> Step 6 must be performed before, 6 after some auxiliary information. </p><p> - 1, the destination database, create a dblink <br /> drop public database link dblink_orc92_182; <br /> Create public DATABASE LINK dblink_orc92_182 CONNECT TO bst114 IDENTIFIED BY password USING\'\'orc92_192.168.254.111\'\'; <br /> - Dblink_orc92_182 is dblink_name <br /> - Bst114 is the username <br /> - Password is the password <br /> -\'\'Orc92_192.168.254.111\'\'is the name of the remote database </p><p><br /> - 2, in the source and destination to be synchronized to create a database table (preferably with a primary key constraint, the snapshot can quickly refresh) <br /> drop table test_user; <br /> create table test_user (id number (10) primary key, name varchar2 (12), age number (3)); </p><p> - 3, in the destination database, test dblink <br /> Select * from <a href=\"mailto:test_user@dblink_orc92_182\">test_user @ dblink_orc92_182</a> ; / / query the source database table <br /> select * from test_user; </p><p> - 4, in the source database, create a snapshot log table to be synchronized <br /> Create snapshot log on test_user; </p><p> - 5 to create a snapshot, the snapshot is created on the destination database <br /> Create as Select * from Snapshot sn_test_user <a href=\"mailto:test_user@dblink_orc92_182\">test_user @ dblink_orc92_182</a> ; </p><p> - 6, set the refresh time snapshot (can choose only one way to refresh, fast refresh is recommended, so that it can trigger two-way synchronization) <br /> Fast refresh <br /> Alter snapshot sn_test_user refresh fast Start with sysdate next sysdate with primary key; <br /> - Oracle automatic fast refresh immediately, after constantly refreshed, only in test use. Real project to properly weigh the refresh time. </p><p> Complete refresh <br /> Alter snapshot sn_test_user refresh complete Start with sysdate +30 / 24 * 60 * 60 next sysdate +30 / 24 * 60 * 60; <br /> - Oracle automatically after 30 seconds, the first complete refresh, after a full refresh every 30 seconds </p><p> - 7, manually refresh the snapshot, in the case does not automatically refresh, you can manually refresh the snapshot. <br /> Manual refresh mode 1 <br /> begin <br /> dbms_refresh.refresh (\'\'sn_test_user\'\'); <br /> end; </p><p> Manual refresh mode 2 <br /> EXEC DBMS_SNAPSHOT.REFRESH (\'\'sn_test_user\'\',\'\' F\'\'); / / The first parameter is the snapshot name, the second parameter is a fast refresh F C is completely refreshed. </p><p> - 8. To modify the session time format <br /> ALTER SESSION SET NLS_DATE_FORMAT =\'\'YYYY-MM-DD HH24: MI: SS\'\'; </p><p> - 9. See the last refresh time snapshot <br /> SELECT NAME, LAST_REFRESH FROM ALL_SNAPSHOT_REFRESH_TIMES; </p><p> - 10. See a snapshot of the next execution time <br /> select last_date, next_date, what from user_jobs order by next_date; </p><p> - 11. Print debugging information <br /> dbms_output.put_line (\'\'use\'\'||\'\' plsql\'\'); </p><p> - 12. If you want one-way synchronization, then the destination database, create the following trigger (when the source database table changes, the purpose of the database table along with change, but the purpose of the database table changes, the source database table does not change). <br /> create or replace trigger TRI_test_user_AFR <br /> after insert or update or delete on sn_test_user <br /> for each row <br /> begin <br /> if deleting then <br /> delete from test_user where id =: old.id; <br /> end if; <br /> if inserting then <br /> insert into test_user (id, name) <br /> values (: new.id,: new.name); <br /> end if; <br /> if updating then <br /> update test_user set name =: new.name where id =: old.id; <br /> end if; <br /> end TRI_test_user_AFR; </p><p> - 13. If you want two-way synchronization, the implementation in the source database before step 6, and both create the following trigger (when the source database table changes, the purpose of the database table changes with the purpose of the database table changes, the source database Table has changed) <br /> CREATE OR REPLACE TRIGGER BST114.TRI_TEST_USER_AFR <br /> AFTER DELETE OR INSERT OR UPDATE <br /> ON BST114.SN_TEST_USER <br /> REFERENCING NEW AS NEW OLD AS OLD <br /> FOR EACH ROW <br /> declare <br /> tmp_id number (10): =- 1; <br /> begin </p><p> dbms_output.put_line (\'\'begin\'\'); <br /> if inserting then <br /> - Select id into tmp_id from test_user where id =: new.id; <br /> for p in (select id from test_user where id =: new.id) <br /> loop <br /> tmp_id: = p.id; <br /> end loop; <br /><br /> dbms_output.put_line (tmp_id ||\'\'===------------\'\'); <br /> if (tmp_id =- 1) then <br /> insert into test_user (id, name, age) <br /> values (: new.id,: new.name,: new.age); <br /> end if; <br /> end if; <br /><br /> if updating then <br /> dbms_output.put_line (\'\'updated\'\'); <br /> for p in (select name, age from test_user where id =: old.id) <br /> loop <br /> if (p.name! =: new.name) or (p.age! =: new.age) then <br /> update test_user set name =: new.name, age =: new.age where id =: old.id; <br /> end if; <br /> end loop; <br /> end if; <br /><br /> if deleting then <br /> dbms_output.put_line (\'\'deleted\'\'); <br /> delete from test_user where id =: old.id; <br /> end if; <br /> dbms_output.put_line (\'\'end\'\'); <br /> end TRI_test_user_AFR; <br /> - To prevent two-way synchronization trigger an infinite loop, so to increase the number of judgments in the trigger to stop the endless loop. </p><p> - The above synchronization principle <br /> 1. First create a dblink, can access the remote database <br /> 2. To create a snapshot of local, remote data mapping table, when the remote table has changed, it will respond to the snapshot. <br /> 3. As a snapshot view of the table is similar, so create a local trigger for the snapshot, the snapshot when there are changes, it will trigger the corresponding event. <br /> 4. To write a trigger to synchronize data in the code. </p><p> - Attachment: Snapshot refresh time parameter that day, the number of seconds = 24 hours * 60 minutes * 60 note so in order to refresh after 30 seconds, the parameter should be written like sysdate +30 / (24 * 60 * 60) <br /> 1 minute == sysdate +60 / (24 * 60 * 60) </p><p> The number of minutes a day = 24 hours * 60 minutes, one minute can write sysdate +1 / (24 * 60) <br /> == Sysdate + 30 minutes'),(254,'linux','en','/a/db/mysql/2010/0422/49.html','How to set MySQL Sync (mysql dual hot','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> MySQL provides <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/db/\">database</a></u> synchronization features, which we implemented <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/db/\">the database</a></u> of redundant disaster, backup, restore, load balancing, etc. are of great help. This paper describes a common method of synchronization settings. </p><p> Synchronization in two forms: </p><p> &quot;Master - slave&quot;, and &quot;Lord - Lord.&quot; </p><p> A: &quot;Lord - from the&quot; way </p><p> 1, for the server </p><p> Between the different versions of MySQL (the binary log) binlog format may be different, so the best combinations is the Master of the MySQL version and the version of the same or lower Slave, Master\'s version will definitely not be higher than Slave version. </p><p> In this paper, we assume that the primary server (hereinafter referred to as Master) and from the server (hereinafter referred to as the Slave) version is 4.1.24, the operating system is Redhat Linux AS4.0 </p><p> Suppose </p><p> Sync Master is the host ip: 192.168.60.219, Slave host ip is: 192.168.60.132,2 a MySQL the basedir directory is / usr / local / mysql, datadir is: / usr / local / mysql / data (is the mysql database default data directory). </p><p> 2, set the synchronization server </p><p> (1), set the Sync Master </p><p> Each synchronization server must be set to a unique number, or can not properly run simultaneously. Then sync profile configuration database, mysql database, the default configuration file called my.cnf, start the database when the data directory from the default my.cnf read the information, if not the next data file, you can create a, my . cnf Default template generally mysql / support-files directory, this directory has a variety of situations cnf files, such as my-huge.cnf, my-large.cnf, my-medium.cnf, my-small . cnf, etc., under the circumstances, to choose my-medium.cnf can then copy it to data, the renamed my.cnf. began to modify the my.cnf, add the following lines: </p><p> log-bin </p><p> server-id = 1 (identified as the master database) </p><p> sql-bin-update-same </p><p> binlog-ignore-db = mysql </p><p> set-variable = binlog-ignore-db = mysql # specify the database log </p><p> Then add an account in the Master devoted to synchronization, as follows: </p><p> MySQL&gt; GRANT REPLICATION SLAVE ON *.* TO <a href=\"mailto:backup@192.168.60.132\">backup@192.168.60.132</a> IDENTIFIED BY \'1234 \'; </p><p> If you want to have permission to do Slave &quot;LOAD TABLE FROM MASTER&quot; or &quot;LOAD DATA FROM MASTER&quot; statement, it must grant the global FILE and SELECT permissions: </p><p> MySQL&gt; GRANT FILE, SELECT, REPLICATION SLAVE ON *.* TO <a href=\"mailto:backup@192.168.60.132\">backup@192.168.60.132</a> IDENTIFIED BY \'1234 \'; </p><p> Above the fourth line in the my.cnf file that does not record the mysql database update log, which avoids the permissions settings on the Master are synchronized to the Slave, if there is no restriction in this regard, can not set this parameter. </p><p> The last set to complete my.cnf, setting is completed, first check the mysql / data directory if mysql start off at values similar to *. info, localhost *, ib * and the like on the value of information. If you have deleted, then the master server, start the mysql. You can view the data files under the localhost.localdomain.err, test the connectivity of the master in the Slave. At the same time with the show slave status to see synchronous configuration. </p><p> Then back up the data on the Master, the first execute the following SQL statement: </p><p> mysql&gt; FLUSH TABLES WITH READ LOCK; </p><p> Do not exit the terminal, otherwise the lock is not in force; and then export the data, compressed data files can be packaged directly, or you can use the mysqldump tool to do, recommend the former approach, so much more quick and easy. </p><p> root $ cd / usr / local / mysql </p><p> root $ tar zcf data.tar.gz. / data (where it may be &quot;var&quot;, and other practical storage of data files, according to the truth may be) </p><p> Then copy the data to the Slave server, unlock, set the correct permissions and owner, etc., start the Slave database, then &quot;UNLOCK TABLES&quot; statement to release the lock. Then close the database. </p><p> (2), set the Slave </p><p> As with the primary database to find the my.cnf template, repair to as my.cnf, add the following lines: </p><p> server-id = 2 (Slave server ID) </p><p> master-host = 192.168.60.219 # master server name </p><p> master-user = backup # sync account name, the default is to test </p><p> master-password = 1234 # sync account password, default is empty </p><p> master-port = 3306 # master server TCP / IP port number, default is 3306 </p><p> set-variable = replicate-ignore-db = mysql # skip the synchronization of the database name, if there are multiple, set times </p><p> set-variable = replicate-do-db = cicro # want to synchronize the database name, if you have more than one, set many times. </p><p> master-connect-retry = 10 default retry interval of 60 seconds </p><p> After setting, first check the mysql / data directory if mysql start off at values similar to *. info, localhost *, ib * and the like on the value of information. If you have deleted, then the Slave server, start mysql, then test it on the Slave whether connected to the Master on the right, and have the appropriate permissions. </p><p> You can view the data under the localhost.localdomain.err file, test the connectivity of Slave and master. </p><p> root $ mysql-h192.168.60.219-ubackup-p 1234 </p><p> mysql&gt; SHOW GRANTS; </p><p> +------------------------------------------------- -------------------------------------------------- -----------------------------------+ </p><p> | Grants for <a href=\"mailto:backup@192.168.60.132\">backup@192.168.60.132</a> | </p><p> +------------------------------------------------- -------------------------------------------------- -----------------------------------+ </p><p> | GRANT SELECT, FILE, REPLICATION SLAVE ON *.* TO <a href=\"mailto:\'backup\'@\'192.168.60.132\'\">\'Backup\' @ \'192 .168.60.132 \'</a> IDENTIFIED BY PASSWORD \'* 9FF2C222F44C7BBA5CC7E3BE8573AA4E1776278C\' | </p><p> +------------------------------------------------- -------------------------------------------------- -----------------------------------+ </p><p> Now, restart the Slave. After the successful launch, log Slave, check synchronization status: </p><p> mysql-hlocalhost-uroot </p><p> mysql&gt; SHOW SLAVE STATUS \\ G </p><p> *************************** 1. Row ******************** ******* </p><p> Slave_IO_State: Waiting for master to send event </p><p> Master_Host: 192.168.60.132 </p><p> Master_User: backup </p><p> Master_Port: 3306 </p><p> Connect_Retry: 10 </p><p> Master_Log_File: localhost-bin.000002 </p><p> Read_Master_Log_Pos: 1556 </p><p> Relay_Log_File: localhost-relay-bin.000004 </p><p> Relay_Log_Pos: 51 </p><p> Relay_Master_Log_File: localhost-bin.000002 </p><p> Slave_IO_Running: Yes </p><p> Slave_SQL_Running: Yes </p><p> Replicate_Do_DB: cicro, cicro </p><p> Replicate_Ignore_DB:'),(255,'linux','en','/a/db/oracle/2010/0423/63.html','Oracle database to write TO_DATE format','2010-04-23','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> TO_DATE format (time :2007 -11-02 13:45:25 example) <br /><br /> Year: <br /> yy two digits show the value of two years: 07 <br /> yyy three digits show the value of three years: 007 <br /> yyyy four digits show the value of four years: 2007 <br /><br /> Month: <br /> mm number two on display: 11 <br /> mon abbreviated character set display: 11 months, if the English version, showing nov <br /> month spelled out character set display: 11 months, if the English version, show november <br /><br /> Day: <br /> dd number the first few days show the value of the month: 02 <br /> ddd number then display the first few days: 02 <br /> dy abbreviated days of the week the first short display: Friday, if the English version, show fri <br /> day spelled out the first days of the week in full display: Friday, if the English version, show friday <br /> ddspth spelled out, ordinal twelfth <br /><br /> Hour: <br /> hh two digits 12 Ã¥Â°ÂÃ¦Â—Â¶ hex display: 01 <br /> hh24 two digits 24 Ã¥Â°ÂÃ¦Â—Â¶ hexadecimal display: 13 <br /><br /> Minute: <br /> mi two digits 60 hexadecimal display: 45 <br /><br /> Second: <br /> ss two digits 60 hexadecimal display: 25 <br /><br /> Other Q digit quarter showed the value: 4 <br /> WW digit year display the first few weeks: 44 <br /> W digit month of the first few weeks, the displayed value: 1 <br /><br /> Under 24-hour format time range: 0:00:00 - 23:59:59 .... <br /> 12-hour format time range: 1:00:00 - 12:59:59 .... <br /><br /> 1. Date and character conversion function usage (to_date, to_char) <br /><br /> select to_char (sysdate, \'yyyy-mm-dd hh24: mi: ss\') as nowTime from dual; / / date into a string <br /> select to_char (sysdate, \'yyyy\') as nowYear from dual; / / get the time of <br /> select to_char (sysdate, \'mm\') as nowMonth from dual; / / get the monthly time <br /> select to_char (sysdate, \'dd\') as nowDay from dual; / / Get the daily time <br /> select to_char (sysdate, \'hh24\') as nowHour from dual; / / obtain the time when <br /> select to_char (sysdate, \'mi\') as nowMinute from dual; / / Get the sub-time <br /> select to_char (sysdate, \'ss\') as nowSecond from dual; / / Get time in seconds <br /> select to_date (\'2004-05-07 13:23:44 \',\' yyyy-mm-dd hh24: mi: ss\') from dual / / </p><p> 2. <br /> select to_char (to_date (222, \'J\'), \'Jsp\') from dual <br /><br /> Display Two Hundred Twenty-Two </p><p> 3. Seeking one day of the week <br /> select to_char (to_date (\'2002-08-26 \',\' yyyy-mm-dd \'),\' day \') from dual; <br /> Monday <br /> select to_char (to_date (\'2002-08-26 \',\' yyyy-mm-dd \'),\' day \',\' NLS_DATE_LANGUAGE = American \') from dual; <br /> monday <br /> Set the date language <br /> ALTER SESSION SET NLS_DATE_LANGUAGE = \'AMERICAN\'; <br /> The same can be <br /> TO_DATE (\'2002-08-26 \',\' YYYY-mm-dd \',\' NLS_DATE_LANGUAGE = American \') </p><p> 4. The number of days between two dates <br /> select floor (sysdate - to_date (\'20020405 \',\' yyyymmdd \')) from dual; </p><p> 5. Time for the use of null <br /> select id, active_date from table1 <br /> UNION <br /> select 1, TO_DATE (null) from dual; <br /><br /> Note that to use TO_DATE (null) </p><p> 6. Months difference <br /> a_date between to_date (\'20011201 \',\' yyyymmdd \') and to_date (\'20011231\', \'yyyymmdd\') <br /> So at 12:00 on December 31 and December 1 after a 12-point is not included in the prior within this range. <br /> So, when the time requires precise, I felt to_char still necessary <br /> 7. Date format conflict <br /> Enter the format depends on your character set installed on the type of ORACLE, such as: US7ASCII, date format, type is: \'01-Jan-01 \' <br /> alter system set NLS_DATE_LANGUAGE = American <br /> alter session set NLS_DATE_LANGUAGE = American <br /> Or write in to_date <br /> select to_char (to_date (\'2002-08-26 \',\' yyyy-mm-dd \'),\' day \',\' NLS_DATE_LANGUAGE = American \') from dual; <br /> Note me to cite only NLS_DATE_LANGUAGE, of course, there are many, <br /> To see <br /> select * from nls_session_parameters <br /> select * from V $ NLS_PARAMETERS </p><p> 8. <br /> select count (*) <br /> from (select rownum-1 rnum <br /> from all_objects <br /> where rownum &lt;= to_date (\'2002-02-28 \',\' yyyy-mm-dd \') - to_date (\'2002- <br /> 02-01 \',\' yyyy-mm-dd \') +1 <br /> ) <br /> where to_char (to_date (\'2002-02-01 \',\' yyyy-mm-dd \') + rnum-1,\' D \') <br /> not in ('),(256,'linux','en','/a/db/oracle/2010/0422/17.html','Oracle DB Link get two steps using two','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> 1, the target to create Oracle DB Link: <br /> A, in the network / admin / tnsname.ora file to add the source database connection information, such as: <br /> AAA = <br /> (DESCRIPTION = <br /> (ADDRESS = (PROTOCOL = TCP) (HOST = 10.5.1.3) (PORT = 1521)) <br /> (CONNECT_DATA = <br /> (SERVER = DEDICATED) <br /> (SERVICE_NAME = AAA) <br /> ) <br /> ) <br /> B, the target machine using sqlplus user / pwd login. <br /> C, with the following command to create DB Link: <br /> create public database link AAA_LINK connect to user identified by pwd using \'AAA\'; <br /> Command Description: <br /> CREATE PUBLIC DATABASE LINK <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/db/\">database</a></u> link name CONNECT TO username IDENTIFIED BY password USING \'local configuration data instance name\'; <br /> If successfully established, it will prompt: Database link created. </p><p> 2, use the following script, you can synchronize data table: <br /> #! / Bin / sh <br /> # To sync table A to BBB database from AAA database <br /> sqlplus <a href=\"mailto:user/pwd@BBB\">User / pwd @ BBB</a> &lt;&lt;EOF # Here is the BBB\'s database instance name and password there, follow the practical situation <br /> truncate table A; <br /> insert into A <br /> Select * from <a href=\"mailto:b_schema.A@AAA_LINK\">b_schema.A @ AAA_LINK</a> ; # This is the point source to synchronize the table, the table name must be &lt;table owner&gt;. &lt;table name&gt; @ &lt;dblink name&gt; <br /> commit; </p><p> PS: need DB support for Advanced replication capabilities, whether to support, available as SQL view: <br /> select * from v $ option where PARAMETER = \'Advanced replication\'; returns True if it is to support. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(257,'linux','en','/a/web/2010/0422/44.html','[IMG]','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> A: Unison Introduction </p><p><br /> Unison is a windows and unix platforms can use file synchronization tool that can make two folders (local or network) to keep the content consistent. unison with other file system synchronization tools or the same characteristics, but also has its own characteristics: </p><p> Cross-platform; </p><p> Kernel and user rights for no special requirements; </p><p> unison is a two-way, two points can automatically copy the update processing is not part of the conflict, some conflict will be displayed to the user to select update strategy; </p><p> IXDBA.NET Technical Community </p><p> Can be connected as long as two hosts, you can run unison, can use secure socket connection or ssh connection, less demanding on the bandwidth, the use of the compression protocol similar to rsync. </p><p> Unison with text and graphical interface, here only how to use the text interface. </p><p><br /> Second: Install unison </p><p><br /> Download various versions of unison: </p><p> <a href=\"http://www.seas.upenn.edu/~bcpierce/unison//download.html\">http://www.seas.upenn.edu/ ~ bcpierce / unison / / download.html</a> </p><p> unison compiler Download: </p><p> <a href=\"http://caml.inria.fr/pub/distrib/ocaml-3.10\">http://caml.inria.fr/pub/distrib/ocaml-3.10</a> </p><p> Other useful links; </p><p> <a href=\"http://worldhello.net/doc/bcp/unison.html\">http://worldhello.net/doc/bcp/unison.html</a> </p><p> <a href=\"http://www.seas.upenn.edu/~bcpierce/unison//contrib.html\">http://www.seas.upenn.edu/ ~ bcpierce / unison / / contrib.html</a> </p><p> <a href=\"http://www.cis.upenn.edu/~bcpierce/unison/download/releases/stable/unison-manual.html#rshmeth\">http://www.cis.upenn.edu/ ~ bcpierce / unison / download / releases / stable / unison-manual.html # rshmeth</a> </p><p> <a href=\"http://linux.chinaunix.net/bbs/viewthread.php?tid=888250&extra=page%3D1%26amp%3Bfilter%3Dreward\">http://linux.chinaunix.net/bbs/viewthread.php?tid=888250&amp;extra=page% 3D1% 26amp% 3Bfilter% 3Dreward</a> </p><p> Can be downloaded from the above address a variety of platforms, various versions of unison, are based on source code installed, there are binary, I downloaded the binary can be used directly. Here are source code installation: </p><p> Source install unison </p><p> Linux, compile and install packages from source, you need a tool called the Objective Caml compiler, version 3.0.7 at least, you can download from here: <a href=\"http://caml.inria.fr/\">http://caml.inria.fr/</a> </p><p> Ocaml installation script as follows: </p><p> # Tar-zxf ocaml-3.09.3.tar.gz </p><p> # Cd ocaml-3.09.3 </p><p> #. / Configure </p><p> # Make world opt </p><p> # Make install </p><p> Demanding on the version of Unison to synchronize the two hosts need the same version of unison, so the same is used here and the windows version 2.13.16, unison-2.13.16.tar.gz </p><p> The installation script as follows: </p><p> # Tar-zxf unison-2.13.16.tar.gz </p><p> # Cd unison-2.13.16 </p><p> # Make UISTYLE = text </p><p> # Make install </p><p> Executable file will be generated after the unison, to the system PATH will be to their cp. </p><p> # Cp. / Unison / usr / local / bin </p><p><br /> Three: Configure ssh double trust </p><p><br /> As unison to synchronize folders in the remote login a remote server, so you want to configure the two machines trust each other </p><p> This example assumes the local machine is: 10.178.1.132 (linux) </p><p> Remote machine: 10.178.1.110 (solaris) </p><p> 1. In the two machines to create RSA keys </p><p> The following actions to the local machine and remote machine is executed again </p><p> (1) to root user login </p><p> (2) in the root user\'s home directory to create. Ssh directory and set the correct permissions </p><p> [Root @ gsgatzhapp1 ~] # mkdir ~ /. Ssh </p><p> [Root @ gsgatzhapp1 ~] # chmod 700 ~ /. Ssh </p><p> (3) the use of ssh-keygen command to generate the first version of the SSH protocol 2 RSA key </p><p> [Root @ gsgatzhapp1 ~] # ssh-keygen-t rsa </p><p> Generating public / private rsa key pair. </p><p> Enter file in which to save the key (/ root / .ssh / id_rsa): </p><p> Enter passphrase (empty for no passphrase): </p><p> Enter same passphrase again: </p><p> Your identification has been saved in / root / .ssh / id_rsa. </p><p> Your public key has been saved in / root / .ssh / id_rsa.pub. </p><p> The key fingerprint is: </p><p> 17: E4: 7C: 79:8 d: A0: 00:3 b: D9: F7: 7A: 56: F3: AC: 54:4 d <a href=\"mailto:oracle@gsgatzhapp1\">@ gsgatzhapp1 Oracle</a> </p><p> In prompted to save the private key (key) and public key (public key) of the location, use the default values. If the private key password (passphrase), then enter a private key password (if using the private key password when using ssh to execute remote commands to enter the private key password, so, in this case the private key password is not used), therefore, directly back to cars can be. </p><p> 2. Add the key to the authorized key file (authorized key file) in the </p><p> (1) to root user login </p><p> (2) the implementation of the local machine </p><p> [Root @ gsgatzhapp1 ~] # cd ~ /. Ssh </p><p> [Root@gsgatzhapp1.ssh] # ssh 10.178.1.132 cat / root / .ssh / id_rsa.pub&gt;&gt; authorized_keys </p><p> [Oracle@gsgatzhapp1.ssh] # ssh 10.178.1.110 cat / root / .ssh / id_rsa.pub&gt;&gt; authorized_keys </p><p> [Oracle@gsgatzhapp1.ssh] # scp authorized_keys 10.178.1.110: / root / .ssh / </p><p> [Oracle @ gsgatzhapp1. Ssh] # chmod 600 / root / .ssh / authorized_keys </p><p> (3) on the remote machine 10.178.1.110: </p><p> bash-2.05 # chmod 600 / root / .ssh / authorized_keys </p><p> (4) Test </p><p> After running in the gsgatzhapp1: </p><p> [Root @ gsgatzhapp1 ~] # ssh 10.178.1.132 date </p><p> [Root @ gsgatzhapp1 ~] # ssh 10.178.1.110 date </p><p> If you do not need to enter a password to a system date, indicating that SSH configuration is successful. </p><p><br /> IV: unison use </p><p><br /> Unison can be used in a host, synchronize two folders, can also be used on the network. </p><p> 1: for local use </p><p> Usage: </p><p> # Unison 111 222 # 111 and 222 synchronize the local folder </p><p> Contacting server ... </p><p> Looking for changes </p><p> Warning: No archive files were found for these roots. This can happen either </p><p> because this is the first time you have synchronized these roots, </p><p> or because you have upgraded Unison to a new version with a different </p><p> archive format. </p><p> Update detection may take a while on this run if the replicas are </p><p> large. </p><p> Unison will assume that the \'last synchronized state\' of both replicas </p><p> was completely empty. This means that any files that are different </p><p> will be reported as conflict'),(258,'linux','en','/a/web/apache/2010/0422/42.html','[IMG]','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Download module: </p><p> To the official website: <a href=\"http://www.nowhere-land.org/programs/mod_vhost_limit/\">http://www.nowhere-land.org/programs/mod_vhost_limit/</a> download module </p><p> <a href=\"http://www.nowhere-land.org/prog\">http://www.nowhere-land.org/prog</a> ... st_limit-0.4.tar.gz </p><p> Installation: <br /> apxs-c mod_vhost_limit.c-o / path / to / libexec / mod_vhost_limit.so </p><p> In httpd.conf add: <br /> LoadModule vhost_limit_module libexec / mod_vhost_limit.so <br /> AddModule mod_vhost_limit.c </p><p> Configuration: </p><p> MaxClients 150 <br /> ExtendedStatus On </p><p> NameVirtualHost * </p><p> &lt;VIRTUALHOST * /&gt; <br /> ServerName server1 <br /> DocumentRoot / some/where/1 <br /> MaxVhostClients 100 </p><p><br /> &lt;VIRTUALHOST * /&gt; <br /> ServerName server2 <br /> DocumentRoot / some/where/2 <br /> MaxVhostClients 30 </p><p><br /> &lt;VIRTUALHOST * /&gt; <br /> ServerName server3 <br /> DocumentRoot / some/where/3 </p><p><br /> Where: server1 is limited to 100 concurrent threads. server2 is limited to 30 concurrent threads. server3 is not limited. </p><p> Note: the need to support mod_status the ExtendedStatus On! ! </p><p> Exceed the limit as the number of concurrent client will appear in the error 503 </p><p> -------------------------------------------------- ----------------------------------------- </p><p> Limit the number of IP connections </p><p> Here to download the module <a href=\"http://dominia.org/djao/limit/mod_limitipconn-0.04.tar.gz\">http://dominia.org/djao/limit/mod_limitipconn-0.04.tar.gz</a> </p><p> Installation: <br /> tar zxvf mod_limitipconn-0.04.tar.gz <br /> cd mod_limitipconn-0.04 <br /> make APXS = / usr / local / apache / bin / apxs ÃƒÂŸ ----- Here the path is set according to your own <br /> make install APXS = / usr / local / apache / bin / apxs ÃƒÂŸ ----- Here the path is set according to your own </p><p> Editing httpd.conf <br /> Add a global variable: <br /> &lt;IfModule mod_limitipconn.c&gt; <br /> &lt;Location /&gt; # of all virtual hosts / directory MaxConnPerIP 3 # 3 for each IP only allows concurrent connections NoIPLimit image / * # IP restrictions on the pictures do not do &lt;/ Location&gt; </p><p> &lt;Location / mp3&gt; # all the hosts of the / mp3 directory MaxConnPerIP 1 # IP allows only one connection per request <br /> OnlyIPLimit audio / mpeg video # The limit is only for video and audio format file &lt;/ Location&gt; <br /> &lt;/ IfModule&gt; </p><p></p><p> Or virtual host: <br /> &lt;VirtualHost xx.xxx.xx.xx&gt; # # ip address <a href=\"mailto:ServerAdmineasy@phpv.net\">ServerAdmineasy@phpv.net</a> <br /> DocumentRoot / home / easy <br /> ServerNamewww.phpv.net <br /> &lt;IfModule mod_limitipconn.c&gt; <br /> &lt;Location /&gt; </p><p></p><p> MaxConnPerIP 5 <br /> NoIPLimit image / * <br /> &lt;/ Location&gt; <br /> &lt;Location / mp3&gt; # all the hosts of the / mp3 directory MaxConnPerIP 2 # IP allows only one connection per request <br /> OnlyIPLimit audio / mpeg video # The limit is only for video and audio format file &lt;/ Location&gt; <br /> &lt;/ IfModule&gt; <br /> &lt;/ VirtualHost&gt; </p><p><br /> -------------------------------------------------- -------------------------------------------- </p><p> Bandwidth restrictions: </p><p> Download module <a href=\"ftp://ftp.cohprog.com/pub/apache/module/1.3.0/mod_bandwidth.c\">ftp://ftp.cohprog.com/pub/apache/module/1.3.0/mod_bandwidth.c</a> <br /> Installation: <br /> / Usr / local / apache / bin / apxs-c. / Mod_bandwidth.c-o / usr / local / apache / libexec / mod_bandwidth.so </p><p><br /> &lt;------- More / usr / local / apache set the path for you </p><p> Editing httpd.conf <br /> Add: <br /> LoadModule bandwidth_module libexec / mod_bandwidth.so <br /> AddModule mod_bandwidth.c </p><p> Restart your apache </p><p> Related documents: </p><p> Global configuration directives: </p><p> * BandWidthDataDir <br /> Syntax: BandWidthDataDir &lt;directory&gt; <br /> Default: &quot;/ tmp / apachebw&quot; <br /> Context: server config </p><p> Sets the name of the root directory usedby mod_bandwidth to store its internal temporary information. Don\'t forget to create the needed directories: &lt;directory&gt; / master and &lt;directory&gt; / link </p><p> * BandWidthModule <br /> Syntax: BandWidthModule &lt;On|Off&gt; <br /> Default: Off <br /> Context: per server config </p><p> Enable or disable totaly the whole module. By default, the module is disable so it is safe to compile it in the server anyway. </p><p> PLEASE, NOTE THAT IF YOU SET A BANDWIDTH LIMIT INSIDE A VIRTUALHOST BLOCK, YOU ALSO __NEED__ TO PUT THE &quot;BandWidthModule On&quot; DIRECTIVE INSIDE THAT VIRTUALHOST BLOCK! </p><p> IF YOU SET BANDWIDTH LIMITS INSIDE DIRECTORY BLOCKS (OUTSIDE OF ANY VIRTUALHOST BLOCK), YOU ONLY NEED TO PUT THE &quot;BandWidthModule On&quot; DIRECTIVE ONCE, OUTSIDE OF ANY VIRTUALHOST OR DIRECTORY BLOCK. </p><p> * BandWidthPulse <br /> Syntax: BandWidthPulse &lt;microseconds&gt; <br /> Default: <br /> Context: per server config </p><p> Change the algorithm used to calculate bandwidth and transmit data. In norma'),(259,'linux','en','/a/web/nginx/2010/0422/41.html','Under the original Linux build environment to build Nginx','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> A,) to install Nginx <br /> 1.) Installation <br /> Pronounced Nginx [engine x], is established by the Russian Igor Sysoev project, based on the BSD license. F5 said that he is a member of the original, the English home page: <a href=\"http://nginx.net\">http://nginx.net</a> . Some large sites in Russia have been using it for more than two years, and has been doing a great job. </p><p></p><p> Need to be installed before installing nginx and zlib pcre package to support the override, and web compression, and so regular. </p><p></p><p> Installing pcre </p><p> Download: <a href=\"http://www.pcre.org/\">http://www.pcre.org/</a> </p><p> Download for their own version, and then install: </p><p> tar zxvf pcre-7.7.tar.gz </p><p> cd pcre-7.7 </p><p> make </p><p> make install </p><p></p><p> Installing zlib </p><p> Download: <a href=\"http://www.zlib.net/\">http://www.zlib.net/</a> </p><p> Download for their own version, and then install: </p><p> tar zxvf zlib-1.2.3.tar.gz </p><p> cd zlib-1.2.3 </p><p> make </p><p> make install </p><p> Download: <a href=\"http://www.nginx.net/\">http://www.nginx.net/</a> </p><p></p><p> Wait pcre and zlib installed, start the installation nginx </p><p></p><p> Download for their own version, and then compile and install: </p><p></p><p> Nginx compile parameters are as follows: </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 /] # tar zxvf nginx-0.6.31 </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # cd nginx-0.6.31 </p><p></p><p> Special Note: Nginx requires PCRE module support, but in the next RHEL, even if the PCRE module has been installed, Nginx compile time still can not find the correct library files, so need to do the following modifications. </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # mkdir / usr / include / pcre </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # cp / usr / local / lib / libpcre.a / usr / include / pcre / libpcre.a </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # cp / usr / local / lib / libpcre.a / usr / include / pcre / libpcre.la </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # cp / oracle/pcre-7.7/pcre.h / usr / include / pcre / pcre.h </p><p></p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # mkdir / usr / include / pcre / .libs </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # cp / usr / local / lib / libpcre.a / usr / include / pcre / .libs / libpcre.a </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # cp / usr / local / lib / libpcre.a / usr / include / pcre / .libs / libpcre.la </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # cp / oracle/pcre-7.7/pcre.h / usr / include / pcre / .libs / pcre.h </p><p></p><p> The above modifications are finished, then began to compile the installation. </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] #. / Configure - with-pcre = / usr / include / pcre - with-http_stub_status_module </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # vi. / Objs / Makefile (Note: 1006 OK to delete this file &quot;. / Configure - disable-shared&quot;) </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # make </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # make install </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # </p><p> Installed, the default nginx installed in / usr / local /, enter nginx folder, open the configuration file! </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 conf] # pwd </p><p> / Usr / local / nginx / conf </p><p></p><p> 2) nginx Detailed profile </p><p></p><p> [Root @ oracle132 conf] # vi nginx.conf </p><p> user nobody nobody; # run the user </p><p> worker_processes 1; # start the process </p><p></p><p> # Global error log and PID file </p><p> # Error_log logs / error.log; </p><p> error_log logs / error.log notice; </p><p> # Error_log logs / error.log info; </p><p></p><p> pid logs / nginx.pid; </p><p></p><p> # Maximum number of working patterns and connections </p><p> events { </p><p> use epoll; </p><p> worker_connections 1024; </p><p> } </p><p></p><p> # Set http server using its capabilities to provide load balancing reverse proxy support </p><p> http { </p><p></p><p> # Set mime type </p><p> include mime.types; </p><p> default_type application / octet-stream; </p><p></p><p> # Set the log format </p><p> # Log_format main \'$ remote_addr - $ remote_user [$ time_local] $ request\' </p><p> # \'&quot;$ Status&quot; $ body_bytes_sent &quot;$ http_referer&quot;\' </p><p> # \'&quot;$ Http_user_agent&quot; &quot;$ http_x_forwarded_for&quot;\'; <br /><br /> # Access_log logs / access.log main; <br /><br /> # Set the request buffer <br /> client_header_buffer_size 1k; <br /> large_client_header_buffers 4 4k; <br /><br /> # Set the access log <br /> sendfile on; </p><p> tcp_nopush on; <br /> keepalive_timeout 65; <br /><br /> # Enable Web compression gzip on; <br /> gzip_http_version 1.0; <br /> gzip_comp_level 2; <br /> gzip_proxied any; <br /> gzip_types text / plain text / html text / css application / x-javascript text / xml application / xml application / xml + rss text / javascript; <br /> gzip_min_length 1100; <br /> gzip_buffers 4 8k; <br /> # Set the list of servers load balancing <br /> upstream ixdba { <br /> # Weigth parameter that weights are assigned to the higher weight the greater the chances <br /> # Squid on the machine open port 3128 <br /> server 192.168.8.1:3128 weight = 5; <br /> server 192.168.8.2:80 weight = 1; <br /> server 192.168.8.3:80 weight = 6; <br /> } <br /> # The following is to configure virtual hosts include / usr / local / nginx / conf / proxy.conf; <br /> include / usr / local / nginx / conf / vhosts / www.test.com.conf; <br /><br /> 3) Detailed virtual host configuration file <br /> Because each virtual host to specify a file, the following example, a virtual host configuration is as follows: <br /> [Root @ oracle132 vhosts] # <br /> vi / usr / local / nginx / conf / vhosts / www.test.com.conf; <br /><br /> server { <br /> listen 80; # virtual host using port server_name <a href=\"http://www.test.com\">www.test.com</a> ; # virtual host access to domain name charset UTF-8; # set the default character encoding nginx # access_log logs / host.access.log main; <br /> # All the jpg format pictures have nginx to handle the location ~ \\. Jpg $ { <br /> root / cicro/cws3/vhosts/www.test.com/ROOT; <br />'),(260,'linux','en','/a/mz/2010/0422/32.html','[IMG]','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Customer\'s server in the New Year, was burned out, the customer to find out data recovery company to recover the data, but applications still can not access, it is best here to apache, apache2 fails to start, said libsasl2.so.2 find, apache can not start. <br /><br /><br /> Solution: <br /> # Whereis httpd <br /> Find your absolute path to the installation of httpd. If / usr / sbin / httpd <br /><br /> # Ldd / usr / sbin / httpd <br /> libpcre.so.0 =&gt; / lib/libpcre.so.0 (0xf6f8a000) <br /> libpcreposix.so.0 =&gt; / usr/lib/libpcreposix.so.0 (0xf6f86000) <br /> libaprutil-0.so.0 =&gt; / usr/lib/libaprutil-0.so.0 (0xf6f72000) <br /> libldap-2.2.so.7 =&gt; / usr/lib/libldap-2.2.so.7 (0xf6f41000) <br /> liblber-2.2.so.7 =&gt; / usr/lib/liblber-2.2.so.7 (0xf6f35000) <br /> libdb-4.2.so =&gt; / lib/tls/i686/libdb-4.2.so (0xf6e67000) <br /> libexpat.so.0 =&gt; / usr/lib/libexpat.so.0 (0xf6e48000) <br /> libapr-0.so.0 =&gt; / usr/lib/libapr-0.so.0 (0xf6e25000) <br /> librt.so.1 =&gt; / lib/tls/librt.so.1 (0xf6e11000) <br /> libm.so.6 =&gt; / lib/tls/libm.so.6 (0xf6dee000) <br /> libcrypt.so.1 =&gt; / lib/libcrypt.so.1 (0xf6dc0000) <br /> libpthread.so.0 =&gt; / lib/tls/libpthread.so.0 (0xf6dae000) <br /> libdl.so.2 =&gt; / lib/libdl.so.2 (0xf6daa000) <br /> libc.so.6 =&gt; / lib/tls/libc.so.6 (0xf6c82000) <br /> libresolv.so.2 =&gt; / lib/libresolv.so.2 (0xf6c6e000) <br /> libsasl2.so.2 =&gt; not found <br /> libssl.so.4 =&gt; / lib/libssl.so.4 (0xf6c26000) <br /> libcrypto.so.4 =&gt; / lib/libcrypto.so.4 (0xf6b3e000) <br /> / Lib/ld-linux.so.2 (0xf6fab000) <br /> libgssapi_krb5.so.2 =&gt; / usr/lib/libgssapi_krb5.so.2 (0xf6b29000) <br /> libkrb5.so.3 =&gt; / usr/lib/libkrb5.so.3 (0xf6ac4000) <br /> libcom_err.so.2 =&gt; / lib/libcom_err.so.2 (0xf6ac1000) <br /> libk5crypto.so.3 =&gt; / usr/lib/libk5crypto.so.3 (0xf6aa0000) <br /> libz.so.1 =&gt; / usr/lib/libz.so.1 (0xf6a90000) <br /><br /><br /> # Whereis libsasl2.so.2 <br /> / Usr/local/lib/libsasl2.so.2 <br /><br /> / Usr/local/lib/libsasl2.so.2.0.21 <br /><br /> ls-l / usr/local/lib/libsasl2.so.2 <br /> Find / usr/local/lib/libsasl2.so.2 ==&gt; / usr/local/lib/libsasl2.so.2.0.21 <br /><br /> So ln-s / usr/local/lib/libsasl2.so.2.0.21 / lib/libsasl2.so.2 <br /><br /> Then check again: # ldd / usr / sbin / httpd <br /><br /> libpcre.so.0 =&gt; / lib/libpcre.so.0 (0xf6f8a000) <br /> libpcreposix.so.0 =&gt; / usr/lib/libpcreposix.so.0 (0xf6f86000) <br /> libaprutil-0.so.0 =&gt; / usr/lib/libaprutil-0.so.0 (0xf6f72000) <br /> libldap-2.2.so.7 =&gt; / usr/lib/libldap-2.2.so.7 (0xf6f41000) <br /> liblber-2.2.so.7 =&gt; / usr/lib/liblber-2.2.so.7 (0xf6f35000) <br /> libdb-4.2.so =&gt; / lib/tls/i686/libdb-4.2.so (0xf6e67000) <br /> libexpat.so.0 =&gt; / usr/lib/libexpat.so.0 (0xf6e48000) <br /> libapr-0.so.0 =&gt; / usr/lib/libapr-0.so.0 (0xf6e25000) <br /> librt.so.1 =&gt; / lib/tls/librt.so.1 (0xf6e11000) <br /> libm.so.6 =&gt; / lib/tls/libm.so.6 (0xf6dee000) <br /> libcrypt.so.1 =&gt; / lib/libcrypt.so.1 (0xf6dc0000) <br /> libpthread.so.0 =&gt; / lib/tls/libpthread.so.0 (0xf6dae000) <br /> libdl.so.2 =&gt; / lib/libdl.so.2 (0xf6daa000) <br /> libc.so.6 =&gt; / lib/tls/libc.so.6 (0xf6c82000) <br /> libresolv.so.2 =&gt; / lib/libresolv.so.2 (0xf6c6e000) <br /> libsasl2.so.2 =&gt; / lib/libsasl2.so.2 (0xf6c5a000) <br /> libssl.so.4 =&gt; / lib/libssl.so.4 (0xf6c26000) <br /> libcrypto.so.4 =&gt; / lib/libcrypto.so.4 (0xf6b3e000) <br /> / Lib/ld-linux.so.2 (0xf6fab000) <br /> libgssapi_krb5.so.2 =&gt; / usr/lib/libgssapi_krb5.so.2 (0xf6b29000)</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">libkrb5.so.3 =&gt; / usr/lib/libkrb5.so.3 (0xf6ac4000) <br /> libcom_err.so.2 =&gt; / lib/libcom_err.so.2 (0xf6ac1000) <br /> libk5crypto.so.3 =&gt; / usr/lib/libk5crypto.so.3 (0xf6aa0000) <br /> libz.so.1 =&gt; / usr/lib/libz.so.1 (0xf6a90000) <br /><br /><br /><br /> Restart httpd, OK the.</font> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(261,'linux','en','/a/mz/2010/0421/15.html','[IMG]','2010-04-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><div> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">vsftpd 500 OOPS: cannot change directory <br /><br /> Today in the ftp configuration, all configuration is completed, start the vsftpd, user login through ftp, actually an error: <br /> C: \\&gt; ftp 10.10.1.239</font> </div><div> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Connected to 10.10.1.239 <br /> 220 (vsFTPd 2.0.5) <br /> User (10.10.1.239: (none)): xaftp <br /> 331 Please specify the password. <br /> Password: <br /></font> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Tahoma\"><strong>500 OOPS: cannot change directory: / home / xaftp <br /></strong> Login failed. <br /> ftp&gt; ls <br /> 500 OOPS: child died <br /> Connection closed by remote host. <br /><br /> Find this very strange problem, configuration, certainly no problem, always prompt <strong>500 OOPS: cannot change directory: / home / xaftp</strong> <br /><br /> Solution: <br /> In the terminal enter the command: <br /> setsebool ftpd_disable_trans 1 <br /> service vsftpd restart <br /> To OK! <br /><br /> In fact, this is set SELinux commands. <br /> In fact, the man knows what setsebool: <br /> NAME <br /> setsebool - set SELinux boolean value <br /><br /> In unfamiliar SELnux before they can turn off the SELinux. Have time to study under SELinux. <br /> But do not want to use SELinux in familiar circumstances can the SELinux set to Permissive, SELinux rules that start, but only to irregularities in the record to the log.</font></font> </div><p></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(262,'linux','en','/a/mz/2010/0421/11.html','Argument list too long &quot;error solution','2010-04-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><div><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">This article is a response a few days ago a friend of the forum questions, free today, order a bit, post it, for your reference! <br /></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">When Linux, try to pass too many arguments to a <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/\">system</a></u> command (ls *; cp *; rm *; cat *; etc ...), they will appear &quot;Argument list too long&quot; <a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/mz/\"><u>error</u></a> . This article will provide 4 solution, the degree of complexity from low to high order.</font> </p><p> <strong><font color=\"#ff0000\" face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Method # 1: command line parameters manually into smaller pieces</font></strong> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Example 1</font> </p><p><br /> mv [al] * ../directory2 </p><p> mv [mz] * ../directory2 </p><p> This is the 4 methods in the most simple, but far from ideal. You must have the means to the average split files, but for very many cases the number of documents, you need to enter the command N times. </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>Method # 2: Use the find command</strong></font> </p><p> Example 2 <br /><br /><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.ixdba.net/hbcms/upload/image/big/54/544e77b81bf490ee5d212961a59c067c.jpg\" /></p><p> Method 2 files via find command to filter the list of documents to meet the requirements passed to the series of commands. </p><p> Find command has the advantage of a very powerful filtering capabilities, and, perhaps most important, this method requires only one line of command. </p><p> The only drawback is that Method 2 need to traverse the file, so time-consuming. </p><p><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>Method # 3: Create a function</strong></font> </p><p> Example 3 </p><p> #! / Bin / bash </p><p> # Set the folder to delete <br /> RM_DIR = \'/ data / files\' </p><p> cd $ RM_DIR <br /> for I in `ls` <br /> do <br /> rm-f $ I <br /> done </p><p><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>Method # 4: Re-compile the Linux kernel</strong></font> </p><p> The last method requires two words: caution, this method is very high, so there is no linux user experience is best not to try. In addition, permanent use, be sure to thoroughly test the system environment. </p><p> Method 4 only need to manually add the kernel command line parameters assigned to the number of pages. Open include / linux / binfmts.h file, near the beginning of the file location in the following lines: </p><p> / * </p><p> * MAX_ARG_PAGES defines the number of pages allocated for arguments </p><p> * And envelope for the new program. 32 should suffice, this gives </p><p> * A maximum env + arg of 128kB w/4KB pages! </p><p> * / </p><p> # Define MAX_ARG_PAGES 32 </p><p> In order to increase the allocation of the memory cell command line parameters, just assign a larger value MAX_ARG_PAGES, save, recompile, install, restart, get </p><p> In my system, I MAX_ARG_PAGES value to 64 to solve all the problems. After changing this value, I have not encountered any problems. This is understandable, when MAX_ARG_PAGES was changed to 64, the longest line of argument only with 256KB of system memory - the hardware standards for nothing now. </p><p> Obviously the advantages of Method 4, and now you just run the command as usual. Shortcomings are obvious, if the memory allocated to the command line is greater than the available system memory, the system itself may lead to denial of service attack (DoS attack), cause the system to crash. Especially for multi-user system, even a small increase in memory allocation will have a significant impact, because each user is assigned to the extra memory. Therefore, we must fully tested to determine whether your system can use 4. </p></div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(263,'linux','en','/a/lb/2010/0421/1.html','[IMG]','2010-04-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Learning linux, you may encounter problems linux cluster here will introduce the method of <font style=\"background-color: #ffffff\">load balancing</font> linux cluster, after careful finishing, out here and share with you, I hope this will teach you more. </p><p> <strong>Cluster theory</strong> <br /> linux cluster nodes and cluster system consists of two parts, the cluster manager. Sometimes referred to as node cluster nodes, servers, or server node is to provide the processing resources of the system, which carried out the actual work of the cluster. In general, it must be configured in order to become part of the cluster, the cluster must run the application software. Applications can be dedicated to the cluster software can also be designed for distributed systems with standard software. node linux cluster manager sucked bundled together to form the logical structure of the appearance of a single system, which is used to break down tasks to all nodes. </p><p> Cluster due to a variety of reasons have different types of linux cluster to establish the most direct reason is to share CPU resources, balance the load between multiple machines, more reliability, or failure to provide the host backup system (switch). </p><p> Through the analysis of related software, to achieve the function of the cluster load is achieved through traffic management, specifically the following approaches: direct routing (Direct Forwarding), Network Address Translation (NAT) and tunneling (Tunneling). </p><p> Direct routing (Direct Forwarding) is that when participating in the cluster control and management computer and the computer as a segment in the same time make this method. Control and management of the computer receives the request packet, directly to the participating cluster nodes. The advantage is that the flow is not returned to the client through the control unit, speed, cost less. </p><p> Perhaps we are all familiar with Network Address Translation (NAT) this approach. Address converter has access to the outside world can be a legitimate IP address, it changes the outflow from the private network address of the package, the outside world looks from the address converter package itself. When the external packet to the converter, it should determine which packets to the internal network nodes. Its advantage is to save IP addresses can be disguised within; disadvantage is low efficiency, because the flow is returned to the requesting party to go through a converter. </p><p> Tunneling (Tunneling) linux cluster in this way the nodes are not in the same segment of the forwarding mechanism used, the IP packet is encapsulated in the other network traffic. From a security point of view, technology should be used in the tunnel VPN, leased lines can also be used. </p><p> linux cluster can provide the service is based on TCP / IP, Web Services, Mail Services, News Services, DNS Services and Proxy servers. Here I will take a specific product TurboLinux Cluster Server to implement a load balancing linux cluster system, used to provide Web and FTP services. </p><p> <strong>Planning <br /></strong> 1. Providing services: Web, FTP. <br /> 2. Do a better load balancing system to which more features can be used to. <br /> 3. With 4 servers, 3 sets to install TurboLinux Cluster Server, 1 station to install Windows 2000 Sever. </p><p> <strong>Installation</strong> <br /> 1. In the 3 servers installed Turbo Linux, also need to install Apache and wu-ftpd, because the linux cluster to provide this service. After installation is complete, restart the machine, mount CD-ROM in the directory / mnt / cdrom, execute. / TLCS-install, then follow the prompts to complete installation. <br /> 2. In a single server installation of Windows 2000 Server, also install Internet Information Server 5.0. </p><p> <strong>Linux cluster manager configuration <br /></strong> 1. To set the server\'s IP address, subnet mask, routing, etc., transferred through the network, and a table set TurboLinux Server DNS server to be able to resolve forward and reverse resolution. In this case the server is named pc1, domain test.com. <br /> 2. Configure Cluster Server. Executive Turbolinuxclusteradmin, set as follows (hyphen connected to the lower menu or menu option, set the case after the colon): <br /> (1) ClusterServer Configuration-Cluster Services-Application Stability Agents: <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† http as the default service, do not set. <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† ftp:/usr/lib/ftpAgent. <br /> (2) ClusterServer Configuration - Cluster Services - Service Settings: <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† http, 80: TCP, sticky. <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† ftp, 21: TCP, ftp. <br /> (3) ClusterServer Configuration - Servers Configuration: <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† pc1 (pc1.test.com), direct, ping. <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† pc2 (pc2.test.com), direct, ping. <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† pc3 (pc3.test.com), direct, ping. <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† pc4 (pc4.test.com), direct, ping. <br /> (4) ClusterServer Configuration - Advance Traffic Managers: <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† Advance Traffic Manager System: pc1.test.com. <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† Advance Traffic Manager Setting: The default value. <br /> (5) ClusterServer ConfigurationÃƒÂ Virtual Severs: <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† host: pc1.test.com. <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† sendmail: master @ pc1. Test.com. <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† Server pool name: Server Group1. <br /> (6) ClusterServer ConfigurationÃƒÂ Globle Settings: <br /> Network settings: netmask 255.255.255.0. </p><p> <strong>Each node in the cluster configuration <br /></strong> 1. Configuring Windows 2000 Server node as TurboLinux Cluster Server tool itself can be automatically synchronized, so long as you can configure Windows 2000 Server. <br /> (1) Start Ã¢Â†Â’ Settings Ã¢Â†Â’ Control Panel Ã¢Â†Â’ Add New Hardware Ã¢Â†Â’ Next Ã¢Â†Â’ Add / Troubleshoot a device to add new equipment Ã¢Â†Â’ Ã¢Â†Â’ not, then select from a list of other equipment, hardware Ã¢Â†Â’ Ã¢Â†Â’ Microsoft: Microsoft Loopback Adapter Ã¢Â†Â’ completed. <br /> (2) Right-click the desktop select My Network Places Ã¢Â†Â’ Properties Ã¢Â†Â’ TCP / IP, set the IP address, default gateway, subnet mask (the first set to 255.255.255.0). <br /> (3) Start Ã¢Â†Â’ Run Ã¢Â†Â’ regedit Ã¢Â†Â’ find the registry with the Microsoft Loopback Adapter-related items, change the subnet mask 255.255.255.255. <br /> (4) configure the system to run the appropriate services, and configuration management for the cluster manager configuration so that we can use the Control Manager. </p><p> 2. Configuration TurboLinux Cluster Server Node (1) in the management of the implementation of the contents of the menu select tlcs_content _sync synchronization, enter the password to configure the node, the cluster manager will copy the content to the service node. <br /> (2) in the Management menu, select tlcs_ config _sync execution settings synchronization, the input node will be configured password, copy the settings in the cluster manager Neirong to the node. <br /> At this point we can already see that the cluster manager running on PC1, the client can access servers connected to the switch, the client can request Web and FTP services. If you want to see the operation can also be used from the Cluster Manager console https: / / pc1.test.com: 910 to manage. </p><p> In computer technology, cluster load balancing is a hot technology, but also a high-end applications. Internet / Intranet solutions using a wide range of load-balancing cluster, especially in medium to large sites is immune from this technology. Direct routing, Network Address Translation, tunneling technology will be used according to application needs. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(264,'linux','en','/a/sp/2010/0422/57.html','[IMG]','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><div><p align=\"center\"> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">Many users learn linux, are complaining that there is no environment, so entry is difficult, very slow, so now have a simulation software, vmware, this software can simulate a variety of operating systems, common windows, linux, solaris is not a problem With this software, system installation, software installation and configuration can operate in a simulated environment, not much to say, take a look at how to use this software tutorials now!</span> </p><p align=\"center\"> <a href=\"http://blog.ixdba.net/ixdba/ixdba003\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"4\">Online Play</font></strong></a> </p></div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(265,'linux','en','/a/sp/2010/0422/56.html','[IMG]','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><div><p align=\"center\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Strongly recommended: Oracle 11g SQL Basics series of <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/sp/\">video</a></u> (1-5 sets), one after another update!</font> </p><p align=\"center\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Oracle 11g SQL Basics video series episode:</font> <a href=\"http://blog.ixdba.net/ixdba/ixdba038/\" target=\"_blank\"><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Play</font></a> </p><p align=\"center\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Oracle 11g SQL Basics video series II:</font> <a href=\"http://blog.ixdba.net/ixdba/ixdba039/\" target=\"_blank\"><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Play</font></a> </p><p align=\"center\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Oracle 11g SQL Basics video series III:</font> <a href=\"http://blog.ixdba.net/ixdba/ixdba040/\" target=\"_blank\"><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Play</font></a> </p><p align=\"center\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Oracle 11g SQL Basics video series Episode IV:</font> <a href=\"http://blog.ixdba.net/ixdba/ixdba041/\" target=\"_blank\"><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Play</font></a> </p><p align=\"center\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Oracle 11g SQL Basics series of video Trek V: The</font> <a href=\"http://blog.ixdba.net/ixdba/ixdba042/\" target=\"_blank\"><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Play</font></a> </p></div><p></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(266,'linux','en','/a/IT/2010/0430/88.html','Looking for open source enterprise: the enterprise open source company Red Hat','2010-04-30','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> As the world\'s leading open source and Linux provider, Red Hat Software\'s corporate culture and the &quot;open, free, collaboration,&quot; has a natural kinship, HR is the most expected this concept to the limits. </p><p> Red Hat Beijing office lounge in the pool table, Zheng Yan dubbed by the Office of the busiest table. In addition to writing the code in the gap for those who break the engineers responsible for Greater China and Australia, Zheng Yan, senior recruiting manager will own or even after lunch marked the two Councils. Today, free and open corporate culture more and more present in the enterprise, but Red Hat\'s culture is more prominent. As the most revolutionary technology of the company, Red Hat software product itself for such a unique corporate culture of dedication. </p><p> &quot;At first I did not understand Red Hat\'s open source is, but the search was digging I came very professional, and he told me that the future must be open source world, the world\'s best engineers so much doing in this product contribution, and our code is free to use for the community. &quot;joining the company, Zheng Yan more convinced their judgments. As the financial crisis, many companies have reduced revenue, and Red Hat in the world all achieve a contrarian uplink. </p><p> In China, the report also reflected the beautiful changes in the organization, from the beginning of this year, Red Hat to Beijing looking for new office, because this year the company\'s development plans and last year just as quickly. In fact, in that room with pool tables in the lounge, the walls continued with new recruits Post self-introduction, and this one, many people are attracted to Red Hat\'s campus presentation. </p><p> <strong>Flexible Culture</strong> </p><p> End of last year\'s campus recruitment propaganda, Zheng Yan\'s style and very different from other HR companies. Traditionally, such propaganda in the strict sense should be wearing suits, and Zheng Yan was wearing boots and denim shorts, and her cool short hair style, it is added to this alternative points. </p><p> &quot;HR on behalf of the company\'s corporate culture, is a candidate to understand the company\'s bridge, the day I am also very active on stage, I move around, jump, and students interaction, joking. And we preach the process, to take a very variety of forms, including a video, is the company\'s own making, the topic is the performance of our daily working conditions, this casual and very attractive short positive students. &quot; </p><p> Now more and more young people with personality, how to meet them? Zheng Yanxi hope this message is Red Hat\'s free and open spirit. Many of my colleagues as the company needs to report directly to the United States, so sometimes you will work, meetings late into the night, and many colleagues hope to have the time to write code more quiet work space, the company respect the work habits of employees, staff believed arranged for independent work time, so Red Hat is not used flexible working time system. </p><p> Zheng Yan themselves are the direct beneficiaries of this work system. As a child is just 1 year old new mother, at first, her friends around to the Red Hat development rather puzzled. For a career woman, in order to balance work and life, such moments are usually more suitable for Enron in the original live enterprise Moreover, Zheng Yan, she has worked for a company in the last 4 years and outstanding performance. </p><p> After the Red Hat, Zheng Yan of the great pressure of work, but she still can arrange your own pace, and working hours. &quot;Red Hat is a user-friendly and encourage personal development company, our culture is the most important freedom, because open source is free, this freedom is based on trust, which also reflects the company\'s employees respect. My house from the company very far, but I can choose to stagger the rush hour, so that flexible working for me to win a higher efficiency, but also can arrange a good family life. &quot; </p><p> Open and free culture is reflected in many ways, the flexible working time management is a human performance. In addition, the company will arrange special staff for everyone to buy their favorite snacks, beverages, for staff to provide quality meals. This culture is indeed a truly effective the favorite to win the staff, although the average age of Red Hat employees only 26 years old, but the rate of turnover of enterprises remain a low level of below 5%, which is rare in the IT industry, Moreover, Red Hat is not completely rely on the kind of salaries to keep people in the management system. </p><p> <strong>Within the recommended optimal</strong> </p><p> And corporate values to keep the same people, the source of recruitment is the choice of candidates. For July 2009 to join Red Hat software just Yan Cheng, the company initially invited her rather puzzled. Because that time period, we more or talking about the financial crisis, most companies have a hiring freeze, and she has to do a recruitment focus for the HR person in charge of the work. </p><p> And the recent past, Red Hat\'s efforts to recruit and completely different. Zheng Yan in the year before the company, Red Hat not only recruited 20 people, and she came after six months, has reached 40 people. To attract more outstanding personnel, in addition to the number of jobs, even before the problem difficult to solve the graduate account, Zheng Yan fundamental for the company through the multi-mediation resolved. </p><p> In addition to graduates, the company now more than ever, attention to the recommendation of internal talent. In Zhengyan Gang joined the company when the internal referral system has been started, and the company also provides a high for this budget. Now from the company headquarters to China, we hope to dig more deeply this project, for which Red Hat in the global selection of some wonderful HR to join the project, Zheng Yan is one of the member. </p><p> Optimized internal referral system is more rigorous than ever before, and humane. The key is, the company hopes will be in the previous Red Hat Enterprise culture to candidates, in order to improve the success rate of this project. As employees of Red Hat in the past often only published in a number of industry forums employment needs of their company, and most of the resume is given the staff and Red Hat is not met, so the past success of Red Hat\'s recommended rate of zero. Today, the project carried out soon, already have three colleagues through the way of success within the recommended joining Red Hat. </p><p> &quot;In the past only screening employees, and now we ask to interview each other, thus improving the success rate, but also allow a better understanding of the new employees joining the likes of Red Hat\'s culture, so although the recent time, we increased the number of recruitment Many, but not dilute our culture. &quot; </p><p> Within the recommended approach has been the HR technology companies favored by natural cost advantage is one of the reasons this project to deepen, but the traditional recruitment channels, Red Hat still has not given up. Zheng Yan to the company, will be invited each of the company\'s service provider negotiations and the formation of competition between them to quickly improve the service level of service. When the search firm candidates fail to provide Red Hat requirements, Zheng Yan, and their detailed analysis will be the reason, once again clarify the job requirements, to understand the business as much as possible the intention of the other party to continue to promote their service. </p><p> Zheng Yan\'s efforts to get the company\'s identity, his boss, the boss of the region are working for her efficiency and performance that surprises. Zheng Yan to feel proud of their business also includes the recognition of her head, because the rapid expansion of business, R &amp; D centers in China, general manager of one of the things that most worried the rapid establishment of the team, and Zheng Yan just help to him. </p><p> &quot;I believe the next 5 to 10 years, China\'s HR recruitment is still dominated, as the business managers, HR to help them the most, and most obvious is the recruitment, finding the right person to build a good team, which only after we talk about talent management and business development. &quot; </p><p> <strong>Of boss</strong> </p><p> However, Yan Zheng clearer that, as HR, is not to find the right employees to the company even if successful, it is important also to obtain the trust of leaders of HR, trust comes from the professionalism and good communication, has been for 12 years Yan Zheng recruiting experience, she\'s a very deep understanding of this trust. </p><p> &quot;At this point, I am very grateful to the original company, because where I need to handle larger volumes of recruitment, personnel need to be more diversified, which I accumulated a lot of experience.&quot; Which is a very important one and owner communication. </p><p> Professional competence required of employers in Red Hat, Zheng Yan received the greatest support for his boss. This is one of the most obvious is the boss of her trust. As the boss\'s office office in the United States, so far, Zheng Yan, and the boss has no chance to really meet up. &quot;But my boss is very good character, and she do things cleanly, my personality is also very direct, so the communication between us is very smooth. I soon after taking office, we exchanged pictures. When I select local Chinese excellent service, looking for her approval of some projects, she is very fast to me feedback, as long as I made clear reason, she would say, \'I think you must be the best choice.\' &quot; </p><p> In addition to the support of the work, there are quite a lot of things to Zheng Yan moved. Due to time differences, in the past, Zheng Yan needs about 3 times a week, and headquarters in the evening to meet the various project departments, because the more the project leader in the United States or Europe, Zheng Yan to adapt to most of their working time. And once in a meeting and his boss, the other heard the sound of crying children Zheng Yan, the boss immediately said after the meeting, be sure to Zheng Yan of the day, but their choice in the evening. &quot;I believe it is the management of human, so I have a driving force even more. In fact, this is where Red Hat\'s culture.&quot; </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(267,'linux','en','/a/IT/2010/0711/316.html','Domestic open source software company Red Flag 2000, CEOs were','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <strong>Red Flag 2000 out of office software</strong> </p><p> Insider sources, early May, &quot;Nuclear high base&quot; project-based software testing has been completed. In the office area, Kingsoft office software products ranked first, Evermore Office subordination, both of which were obtained 50 million ~ 60 million of central government funding. The Red Flag 2000 office software product is definitely out, because of its so-called China-made products are not really open source office software with independent intellectual property rights of domestic products. </p><p> Yuan Meng introduced red RedOffice office 2000 software products owned by over 90% of software code to copy the open source OpenOffice. Red flag on the surface of 2000 added a shell, which claimed 100% of the independent intellectual property rights, and changed its name from the OpenOffice RedOffice, traces directly to the elimination of open source products. </p><p> OpenOffice open source office software was first developed for a German company, later acquired by the U.S. Sun. Sun has now merged with Oracle, its intellectual property rights belonging to Oracle. </p><p> In the &quot;nuclear high base&quot; project-based software testing, the Red Flag 2000 RedOffice winning software and office software products because the &quot;non-domestic&quot; and is blocked at the door, dragged a red flag in 2000 the company directly. </p><p> The insider said the better things in the open source software, &quot;fifth&quot; period, the CAS software investment 30% owned by Red Flag Software, a Hong Kong investment company called the Chinese 70% in 2000, the Chinese joint venture company in 2000, before Hu Yong president. Yong Hu was later combined in a joint venture enterprise set up a red 2000 power, power is the controlling shareholder in the enterprise. Red Flag 2000, the goal is to RedOffice office software applications for state financial support. </p><p> It is understood the company\'s working capital difficult to sustain the funding to other countries. Funding can not come now, the shareholders of the investment will boondoggle. </p><p> Alleged, when the red flag will be invested in power prices in 2000, is made of the value of their products will be supported by the State, but now found that &quot;domestic&quot; is a farce, so the recent Red Flag 2000, a major shareholder in power eliminates the red flag 2000 rate Yong Hu, general manager duties only. </p><p> When this reporter interviewed the red flag in 2000, the company\'s brand in this part of the Department of a dedicated staff of content distribution does not deny this, saying only that &quot;there is no clear message in this regard can be made public.&quot; </p><p> <strong>Universal South is also false?</strong> </p><p> Yuan Meng said the Chinese IT circles nowadays from a local copy or other open source products and packaging to 100% independent intellectual property products, and then apply for grants to state examples of particularly high. </p><p> Insider sources, the South is another common example. </p><p> GM recently held in the South of product release, the company\'s main database product GBase8g product development background in the phrase: &quot;Universal Data Technology Co., Ltd. Tianjin, Nanjing University and a research institute cooperation, joint research and data technology, Nankai University, Jilin University Department of scientific research database ... .... &quot; But the reporters call the Nankai University and Jilin University, all told, these two institutions did not exist. </p><p> For the company claims its database products with independent intellectual property rights GBase8g, Yuan Meng pointed out that the product claims to support Windows platform, which is obvious flaws. According to him, nowadays the major database products are built on open architecture, based on only a small database will support Windows platforms, GBase8g database is a large database of products, said, &quot;support the Windows platform&quot;, it is certainly false. </p><p> &quot;Daily Economic News&quot; interviewed GM CEO Liu Bo South. Data on the company and the Nankai Institute of Technology, Jilin University, Department of Technical Cooperation of the things the database, Liu Bo said he was half-way into this company, and therefore it is not clear. &quot;South Common database products developed technical architecture is the new architecture, and Oracle and other database technology architecture is completely different.&quot; Liu Bo said some people raised objections to the company\'s product technology, this is not a bad thing, you can sit down communication. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(268,'linux','en','/a/IT/2010/0722/341.html','Oracle Mysql and java development after the acquisition will be better','2010-07-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> A few days ago to see a lot of people buy SUN oracle all the talk after, everyone was very worried about mysql and java will be taken for granted that the MySQL and Java is about to face this experience. <br /> However, according to Jaspersoft survey of developers, after the Oracle acquisition of SUN, MySQL, Java has not been much impact, in fact, the development of both better than before. <br /> The following are the survey of some interesting conclusions: </p><p><br /> Ã¢Â€Â¢ More than 75% of people think that under the impetus of MySQL in Oracle will maintain the status quo or better <br /> Ã¢Â€Â¢ More than 75% of people think that the development of MySQL will remain the same pace or faster <br /> Ã¢Â€Â¢ Almost all developers participating in the survey said they would continue to use the Java <br /><br /> Ã¢Â€Â¢ Nearly 80% of people think that Java Community Process (JCP) will remain the same or better development </p><p><br /> The findings on the Java not a surprise, because otherwise no better choice. And although there are many other open source database, but most developers still prefer to use MySQL, they also believe that Oracle will maintain the sustainable development of MySQL. <br /> In any case, the future of MySQL and Java compare with OpenSolaris is not appropriate, because both use the very broad, to give them to give up most of the users. <br /></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(269,'linux','en','/a/IT/2010/0719/326.html','OpenSolaris is facing the disintegration of the Commission?','2010-07-19','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> SUN OpenSolaris is a company (now acquired by Oracle) initiated by the open source operating system project to build the Solaris operating system-based developer community for the project was mainly targeted at developers (that is, software design , computer programmer), system administrator (Information Management Division, Information Management Division, Information Management staff) and the user (users), who expect to make Solaris through the further development and enhancement. <br /> Recently, foreign media reports, the Commission is currently faced with the dissolution of OpenSolaris crisis. After the Oracle acquisition of Sun, OpenSolaris is easy to face the problem of the main transition. Currently OpenSolaris Commission (OGB) has issued an ultimatum to the Oracle, Oracle hopes before the Aug. 16 to appoint a contact person to participate in decision-making OpenSolaris. Otherwise OpenSolaris Management Committee will be dissolved or transferred to Oracle to manage themselves. <br /> The provisions of Articles in the OpenSolaris OGB must be composed of three administrators, one of whom must be a member of their company as, and now the situation is less than 3 members, which will also lead to the disintegration of OGB. From the beginning of this year in February, OpenSolaris community and the relationship between Oracle is very tense, which also led to neglect and communities Oracle of the community. <br /> Former Oracle vice president and chief officer Jeb Dabsteel said users will attend OGB held in the July 11 meeting, but reports said he did not attend that day and did not make any explanation. OGB can do is now resigned to refuse cooperation with Oracle. <br /> It is said that, Sun Open Source Advocacy Officer Simon Phipps before the 11th General Assembly on OGB said, OpenSolaris can not be established between the community and Oracle working together. In his view, there is now the community has lost the value of target. <br /> Oracle in the end, how would the relationship between treatment and OGB, OGB Do you really want to face the disintegration? <br /></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(270,'linux','en','/a/IT/2010/0711/313.html','50 most intelligent global technology executives: Ma list','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> According to foreign media reports, the &quot;Fortune&quot; magazine online edition of the global technology markets on Friday named its 50 top executives the most intelligent, Apple CEO Steve Jobs (Steve Jobs) and Alibaba CEO Jack Ma, etc. the list. </p><div class=\"NewsContent TextContent\" id=\"OSChina_News_10419\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/uploads/allimg/100711/1RRRH6-0.png\" style=\"float: right; margin: 0px 0px 10px 10px\" /></div><p> &quot;Fortune&quot; magazine list of the 50 top executives were subdivided, respectively, the smartest named its CEO, the most intelligent designer, the most intelligent analyst, founder of the most intelligent, most intelligent engineers, the most intelligent scientists, inventor of the most intelligent, most intelligent and most intelligent scientists and other senior management personnel. </p><p> <strong>The following is the &quot;wealth&quot; area of the Top 50 global technology smartest executives:</strong> </p><p> <strong>The smartest CEO Champion:</strong> </p><p> 1. Steve Jobs (Steve Jo