 in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(272,'linux','en','/a/web/nginx/2010/0422/40.html','nginx configuration anti-hotlinking','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">I, for different file types <br /> location ~ .* \\. (wma | wmv | asf | mp3 | mmf | zip | rar | jpg | gif | png | swf | flv) $ { <br /> valid_referers none blocked *. admin99.net admin99.net; <br /> if ($ invalid_referer) { <br /> # Rewrite ^ / http://www.admin99.net/403.html; <br /> return 403; <br /> } <br /> } <br /><br /> Second, for a different directory <br /> location / img / { <br /> root / data / img /; <br /> valid_referers none blocked *. admin99.net admin99.net; <br /> if ($ invalid_referer) { <br /> rewrite ^ / http://www.admin99.net/images/error.gif <br /> # Return 403; <br /> } <br /> } <br /><br /> Third, these are anti-hotlinking features built nginx, nginx also can be used to achieve third-party modules ngx_http_accesskey_module download anti-hotlinking not discussed.</font> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(273,'linux','en','/a/web/nginx/2010/0422/39.html','Nginx error page redirection method','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><div><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">In the nginx configuration file, you can place <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/mz/\">the error</a></u> page redirection is configured, the nginx.conf file has the following configuration information:</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">error_page 404 / 404.html;</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">This 404.html ensure html nginx home directory to the directory, if necessary, after 404 in the event of a direct jump to another address, you can directly set as follows:</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /> error_page 404 http://www.ixdba.net;</font> </p><p><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Can be defined the same way as the 403,500 other common errors.</font> </p><p><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Special attention is paid 404.html file page size to more than 512k, otherwise the browser will be replaced ie ie default error page. I have had in the past this problem.</font> </p></div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(274,'linux','en','/a/web/nginx/2010/0421/5.html','Compile the linux install nginx + php (fastcgi)','2010-04-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> connected with nginx fastcgi php, install the linux compile the following support to compile php fastcgi mode, some other things, according to the way the original installed on it. <br /> Divided into the following steps: <br /> 1, install the fastcgi version of php <br /> 2, the use of spawn-fcgi php-fastcgi start engine <br /> 3, configure php to fastcgi engine connection nginx <br /> 1, install the fastcgi version of php <br /> mkdir / usr / local / modules <br /> # Jpeg directory <br /> mkdir / usr/local/modules/jpeg6 <br /> mkdir / usr/local/modules/jpeg6/bin <br /> mkdir / usr/local/modules/jpeg6/lib <br /> mkdir / usr/local/modules/jpeg6/include <br /> mkdir / usr/local/modules/jpeg6/man <br /> mkdir / usr/local/modules/jpeg6/man/man1 <br /> A1, install zlib <br /> tar xzvf zlib-1.2.1.tar.gz <br /> cd zlib-1.2.1 <br /> # Do not use - prefix custom installation directory, the installation of gd <br /> . / Configure <br /> make <br /> make install <br /> A2, install freetype <br /> tar xzvf freetype-2.1.5.tar.gz <br /> cd freetype-2.1.5 <br /> . / Configure - prefix = / usr / local / modules / freetype <br /> make <br /> make install <br /> A3, install libpng <br /> tar xzvf libpng-1.2.5.tar.gz <br /> # Do not use - prefix custom installation directory, the installation of gd <br /> cd libpng-1.2.5 <br /> cp scripts / makefile.std makefile <br /> make test <br /> make install <br /> A3, install jpeg <br /> tar xzvf jpegsrc.v6b.tar.gz <br /> cd jpeg-6b <br /> . / Configure - prefix = / usr/local/modules/jpeg6 - enable-shared - enable-static <br /> make <br /> make install <br /> A4, install GD <br /> tar xzvf gd-2.0.28.tar.gz <br /> . / Configure - prefix = / usr / local / modules / gd - with-jpeg = / usr/local/modules/jpeg6 - with-png - with-zlib - with-freetype = / usr / local / modules / freetype <br /> make <br /> make install <br /> Then compile and install php, note with - enable-fastcgi parameters and - enable-force-cgi-redirect parameter <br /> . / Configure - prefix = / usr / local / php - with-gd = / usr / local / modules / gd - with-jpeg-dir = / usr/local/modules/jpeg6 - with-zlib - with-png - with-freetype-dir = / usr / local / modules / freetype - enable-magic-quotes - enable-fastcgi - with-mysql = / usr / local / mysql - enable-track-vars - enable-ftp - with-config-file-path = / usr / local / php / etc - with-zip - enable-force-cgi-redirect <br /> make-j10 <br /> make install <br /> 2, the use of spawn-fcgi php-fastcgi start after engine build in / usr / local / php / bin / php-cgi will have following the executable program, the use of spawn-fcgi php-fastcgi start the engine: <br /> / Data / nginx / sbin / spawn-fcgi-a 127.0.0.1-p 9000-u nobody-f / usr / bin / php-cgi-C 20 <br /> Means fastcgi ip and port to use the machine 9000 to provide services, permissions nobody, start 20 process. The main attention-C this parameter, the general process of 20, sufficient, and that not enough can turn up on my machine every php-cgi process will take 7-8 megabytes of memory, opening 100 is 700-800 MB . </p><p> spawn-fcgi nginx in this program does not provide, you can <br /> <a href=\"http://www.sudone.com/download/spawn-fcgi\">http://www.sudone.com/download/spawn-fcgi</a> <br /> Downloaded to the general on the nginx the sbin directory, and then added to give it executable permissions: <br /> chmod + x / data / nginx / sbin / spawn-fcgi <br /> 3, configure php to fastcgi engine connection nginx get a fastcgi-params first configuration, in the conf directory of nginx build a text file, reads: <br /> # Fastcgi-params <br /> fastcgi_param QUERY_STRING $ query_string; <br /> fastcgi_param REQUEST_METHOD $ request_method; <br /> fastcgi_param CONTENT_TYPE $ content_type; <br /> fastcgi_param CONTENT_LENGTH $ content_length; <br /> fastcgi_param SCRIPT_NAME $ fastcgi_script_name; <br /> fastcgi_param REQUEST_URI $ request_uri; <br /> fastcgi_param DOCUMENT_URI $ document_uri; <br /> fastcgi_param DOCUMENT_ROOT $ document_root; <br /> fastcgi_param SERVER_PROTOCOL $ server_protocol; <br /> fastcgi_param GATEWAY_INTERFACE CGI/1.1; <br /> fastcgi_param SERVER_SOFTWARE nginx; <br /> fastcgi_param REMOTE_ADDR $ remote_addr; <br /> fastcgi_param REMOTE_PORT $ remote_port; <br /> fastcgi_param SERVER_ADDR $ server_addr; <br /> fastcgi_param SERVER_PORT $ server_port; <br /> fastcgi_param SERVER_NAME $ server_name; <br /> # PHP only, required if PHP was built with - enable-force-cgi-redirect <br /> fastcgi_param REDIRECT_STATUS 200; <br /> # End <br /> This is the most primitive fastcgi-params, the Internet may have a more optimized version, you can access accordingly. <br /> Then configure nginx.conf, such as <a href=\"http://www.sudone.com\">www.sudone.com</a> , this configuration can be used by: <br /> server { <br /> include port.conf; <br /> server_name <a href=\"http://www.sudone.com\">www.sudone.com</a> sudone.com; <br /> location / { <br /> index index.html index.php; <br /> root / data / sudone / php /; <br /> } <br /> location ~. php $ { <br /> fastcgi_pass 127.0.0.1:9000; <br /> fastcgi_index index.php; <br /> fastcgi_param SCRIPT_FILENAME / data / sudone / php $ fastcgi_script_name; <br /> include fastcgi_params; <br /> } <br /> } <br /> Brought down after a few need to change the place: <br /> 1, server_name <br /> 2, location / inside the root <br /> 3, location ~. Php $ inside fastcgi_param SCRIPT_FILENAME <br /> The parameters of which fastcgi_param SCRIPT_FILENAME, $ fastcgi_script_name php file path in front of the general and the same root, and finally do not have to write /, seemingly would be a problem, not superfluous. <br /> Note: <br /> The administrator may have always forget to start nginx start after the spawn-fcgi, so it is best to write a script to start, and then to cultivate the habit of testing services available. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(275,'linux','en','/a/web/apache/2010/0422/38.html','[IMG]','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><div><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Now the so-called search engine Web crawler, also known as the spider is too much like some of the search engine algorithms is poor, to climb the serious consumption of server resources, but also may cause memory overflow. Can set the robots.txt to ban reptiles to climb the server. Online search for the next data, the default web root directory is not placed under the robots.txt file, to allow all web crawlers search all documents. Khan! ! <br /><br /> Put a file in the root directory robots.txt, but if not immediately. <br /> To prohibit sogou reptiles, set in the robots.txt so that User-agent: Sogou web spider <br /> Disallow: /</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">There is a stupid way to view the log, observation of the browser features, such as sogou is characterized by &quot;Sogou web spider&quot;, which can be set in the apache setenvif User-Agent &quot;Sogou web spider *&quot; den <br /> Order deny, allow <br /> deny from env = den <br /> Look at the apache log information, are reported to 403</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">The most practical way to view apache log to see the source IP, confirmation, letters, the most effective</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">These operations are a temporary solution, but now the search engine too much, sometimes affect the normal operation of the server, it is necessary, you can make some restrictions on their operation.</font> </p></div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(276,'linux','en','/a/db/oracle/2010/0422/18.html','oracle of some basic knowledge but easily confused','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> 1. A table space belongs to only one database. </p><p> 2. Each database at least one control file (recommendation 3, on separate disk). </p><p> 3. Each database at least one tablespace (SYSTEM tablespace). </p><p> 4. To establish the purpose of SYSTEM table space is the same as the destination table stored together in order to improve efficiency, only the data dictionary should be kept. </p><p> 5. Each database at least two online log groups, each with at least one online log file. </p><p> 6. A data file can only belong to a table space. </p><p> 7. Once a data file is added to a table space, you can not remove from the table space, could no longer be added to other table space. </p><p> 8. To create a new table space needs to create a new data file. </p><p> 9. Data files are formatted as ORACLE ORACLE block, Oracle9i previous versions, ORACLE block size is in the first set when creating a database. </p><p> 10. And can not be changed later, to change, can only rebuild the database. </p><p> 11. A segment belongs to only one section of the table space, but can belong to multiple data files. </p><p> 12. A zone data file belongs to only one extent, the range (extent) can not span data files. </p><p> 13.PCTFREE and PCTUSED sum not greater than or equal 100. </p><p> 14. A single transaction can span multiple rollback segments. </p><p> 15. Index table without ROWID value. </p><p> 16. Rollback segments with different sizes without any benefit. </p><p> 17.COMMIT, the data do not immediately write disk (data files). </p><p> 18. Even if a transaction is not submitted, will be written to the redo log. </p><p> 19.Oracle 8.0.4, in the initial installation of the default created when the database instance named ORCL. </p><p> 20. A block of the maximum length of 16KB (with 2K, 4K, 8K, 16K). </p><p> Maximum number of files per database (by block size) </p><p> 20000 block of 2K files </p><p> 4K block of 40,000 files </p><p> 8K or more blocks of 65,536 files </p><p> 21.oracle server can start multiple databases. </p><p> 22. A set of operating system you can install multiple versions of the ORACLE database system (UNIX can, NT can not.) </p><p> 23. An ORACLE database system can have multiple ORACLE database and its corresponding instance. </p><p> 24. Every ORACLE database has a database instance (INSTANCE) (OPS excluded). </p><p> 25. Therefore, an operating system at the same time can have multiple oracle database instance start. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(277,'linux','en','/a/db/oracle/2010/0422/19.html','[IMG]','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> This article discusses the parameters involved are: <br /> log_archive_dest <br /> log_archive_dest_n <br /> log_archive_start <br /> db_recovery_file_dest <br /> Oracle version: <br /> SQL&gt; select * from v $ version; </p><p> BANNER </p><p> -------------------------------------------------- ------------------------------ </p><p> Oracle Database 10g Enterprise Edition Release 10.2.0.2.0 - Prod <br /> PL / SQL Release 10.2.0.2.0 - Production <br /> CORE 10.2.0.2.0 Production <br /> TNS for Solaris: Version 10.2.0.2.0 - Production <br /> NLSRTL Version 10.2.0.2.0 - Production </p><p> Oracle 10g Enterprise Edition to </p><p> SQL&gt; show parameter spfile <br /> NAME TYPE VALUE <br /> ----------------------------------- --------------- ------- ------------------------------ </p><p> spfile string / export / home / oracledb / oracle / p roduct/10.2.0/dbs/spfileorcl.ora </p><p> Using a spfile parameters. </p><p><br /> SQL&gt; alter system set log_archive_dest_1 = \'location = / export / home / arch\'; </p><p> System altered. </p><p></p><p> SQL&gt; alter system set log_archive_dest_1 =\'\'; # set to empty, no location message. </p><p> System altered. </p><p></p><p> SQL&gt; alter system set log_archive_dest = \'/ export / home / arch\'; </p><p> alter system set log_archive_dest = \'/ export / home / arch\' </p><p> * </p><p> ERROR at line 1: <br /> ORA-02097: parameter cannot be modified because specified value is invalid ORA-16018: cannot use LOG_ARCHIVE_DEST with LOG_ARCHIVE_DEST_n orDB_RECOVERY_FILE_DEST </p><p> Error, the error message is LOG_ARCHIVE_DEST_n LOG_ARCHIVE_DEST and can not be used, but now log_archive_dest_N already empty, why not use log_archive_dest it, check the following settings: </p><p></p><p> SQL&gt; show parameter LOG_ARCHIVE_DEST <br /> NAME TYPE VALUE </p><p> ------------------------------------ -------------- -------- ------------------------------ <br /> log_archive_dest string <br /> log_archive_dest_1 string <br /> log_archive_dest_10 string <br /> log_archive_dest_2 string <br /> log_archive_dest_3 string <br /> log_archive_dest_4 string <br /> log_archive_dest_5 string <br /> log_archive_dest_6 string <br /> log_archive_dest_7 string <br /> log_archive_dest_8 string <br /> log_archive_dest_9 string </p><p></p><p> NAME TYPE VALUE </p><p> ------------------------------------ -------------- -------- ------------------------------ </p><p> log_archive_dest_state_1 string enable <br /> log_archive_dest_state_10 string enable <br /> log_archive_dest_state_2 string enable <br /> log_archive_dest_state_3 string enable <br /> log_archive_dest_state_4 string enable <br /> log_archive_dest_state_5 string enable <br /> log_archive_dest_state_6 string enable <br /> log_archive_dest_state_7 string enable <br /> log_archive_dest_state_8 string enable <br /> log_archive_dest_state_9 string enable </p><p> SQL&gt; </p><p></p><p> log_archive_dest and log_archive_dest_1 are empty, but DB_RECOVERY_FILE_DEST value is not empty: </p><p><br /> SQL&gt; show parameter DB_RECOVERY_FILE_DEST </p><p></p><p> NAME TYPE VALUE </p><p> -------------------------------------------------- - ------------------------------ <br /> db_recovery_file_dest string / export / home / oracledb / oracle / flash_recovery_area <br /> db_recovery_file_dest_size big integer 2G </p><p></p><p> The reason here, blank DB_RECOVERY_FILE_DEST </p><p></p><p> SQL&gt; alter system set db_recovery_file_dest =\'\'; </p><p> System altered. </p><p></p><p> SQL&gt; show parameter DB_RECOVERY_FILE_DEST </p><p> NAME TYPE VALUE </p><p> ------------------------------------ -------------- -------- ------------------------------ <br /> db_recovery_file_dest string <br /> db_recovery_file_dest_size big integer 2G </p><p> Re-run log_archive_dest set </p><p></p><p> SQL&gt; alter system set log_archive_dest = \'/ export / home / arch\'; <br /> System altered. </p><p></p><p> Can be smoothly implemented </p><p></p><p> Another parameter, log_archive_start in oracle10g been abandoned, but the oracle did not abandon this argument, or can be found: </p><p> SQL&gt; show parameter log_archive_start </p><p></p><p> NAME TYPE VALUE </p><p> ------------------------------------ ---'),(278,'linux','en','/a/db/mysql/2010/0521/109.html','[IMG]','2010-05-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"color: black; font-size: 12pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><span>Hibernate</span> does not use a long time and I wanted to do a little hands-on example of <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/db/\">the database</a></u> using <span>Oracle. Oracle</span> intends to use the sequence as the primary key, but do not know how to use <span>Hibernate</span> associated together. Ask colleagues, was told to use a query such as <span>select</span> statement <span>&quot;select</span></span> <span>sequence.nextval from <span style=\"color: black; font-size: 12pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">dual&quot;,</span></span> </p><p> <span><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 12pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">As follows:</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"color: black; font-size: 12pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><span>1,</span> first create a <span>sequence</span> in <span>oracle <br /></span></span> <span style=\"font-size: 12pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">2. <span>Hbm.xml</span> in the configuration of your <span><br /></span> This data, when re-inserted, <span>Hibernate</span> automatically returns the following statement: <span><br /></span></span> <span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span> <span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">Automatically generate the next sequence value, then insert an object into the table. <br /> Solutions to this problem was! <br /> <span><br /> <span style=\"color: black; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt\">sequence is provided by the database mechanism for generating the primary key sequence. If the Sequence oralce <br /> native is based on the hibernate database Dialect, automatic use of identity, hilo, sequence one of the primary key generation methods as</span></span></span> </p><div style=\"border-bottom: #cccccc 1px solid; border-left: #cccccc 1px solid; padding-bottom: 4px; background-color: #eeeeee; padding-left: 4px; width: 98%; padding-right: 5px; font-size: 13px; word-break: break-all; border-top: #cccccc 1px solid; border-right: #cccccc 1px solid; padding-top: 4px\"><img align=\"top\" alt=\"\" src=\"/uploads/allimg/100521/161H910C-0.gif\" /><span style=\"color: #000000\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span> <span style=\"color: #0000ff\">create</span> <span style=\"color: #000000\">sequence seq_id <br /><img align=\"top\" alt=\"\" src=\"/uploads/allimg/100521/161H910C-0.gif\" /> minvalue</span> <span style=\"color: #800000; font-weight: bold\">1</span> <span style=\"color: #000000\"><br /><img align=\"top\" alt=\"\" src=\"/uploads/allimg/100521/161H910C-0.gif\" /> start</span> <span style=\"color: #0000ff\">with</span> <span style=\"color: #000000\"> </span> <span style=\"color: #800000; font-weight: bold\">1</span> <span style=\"color: #000000\"><br /><img align=\"top\" alt=\"\" src=\"/uploads/allimg/100521/161H910C-0.gif\" /> increment</span> <span style=\"color: #0000ff\">by</span> <span style=\"color: #000000\"> </span> <span style=\"color: #800000; font-weight: bold\">1</span> <span style=\"color: #000000\"><br /><img align=\"top\" alt=\"\" src=\"/uploads/allimg/100521/161H910C-0.gif\" /> cache <span style=\"color: #800000; font-weight: bold\">20;</span> <br /><img align=\"top\" alt=\"\" src=\"/uploads/allimg/100521/161H910C-0.gif\" /></span> </div><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 21pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"></p><div style=\"border-bottom: #cccccc 1px solid; border-left: #cccccc 1px solid; padding-bottom: 4px; background-color: #eeeeee; padding-left: 4px; width: 98%; padding-right: 5px; font-size: 13px; word-break: break-all; border-top: #cccccc 1px solid; border-right: #cccccc 1px solid; padding-top: 4px\"><img align=\"top\" alt=\"\" src=\"/uploads/allimg/100521/161H910C-0.gif\" /><span style=\"color: #000000\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span> <span style=\"color: #800000\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff\">&lt;Id</span></span> <span style=\"color: #ff0000\">column</span> </span'),(279,'linux','en','/a/db/mysql/2010/0423/65.html','[IMG]','2010-04-23','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span>solution is very simple mysqldump import, export, when the character set specified on the line. <br /> mysqldump-u root-p-c - default-character-set = utf-8 wapad site&gt; dd.sql</span> </p><p> <span>mysql-uroot-p - default-character-set = utf8 wapad &lt;dd.sql <br /><br /> mysqldump-u root-p-c - default-character-set = latin1 wap_resdb downlog_bak&gt; downlog_bak.sql <br /> mysqldump-u root-p-c - default-character-set = latin1 wap_resdb downlog_month&gt; downlog_month.sql <br /> mysqldump-u root-p-c - default-character-set = latin1 wap_resdb haoduan&gt; haoduan.sql</span> </p><p></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>'),(280,'linux','en','/a/db/mysql/2010/0422/52.html','[IMG]','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font color=\"red\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Ã£Â€ÂReproduced in the form of a hyperlink when you identify the source and author information in the article and the statementÃ£Â€Â‘ <br /> Original Link:</span></span></font> <script> \r\nfunction selecturl(){ \r\nz=document.body.createTextRange(); \r\nz.moveToElementText(selecturlDiv); \r\nz.select(); \r\n} \r\n</script><script>document.write(location.href)</script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Today, R &amp; D personnel in the debug java program, found the mysql quoted the following problems: </p><p> java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Packet is larger than max_allowed_packet from server configuration of 1048576 bytes </p><p> at org.gjt.mm.mysql.Buffer.ensureCapacity (Buffer.java: 398) </p><p> at org.gjt.mm.mysql.Buffer.writeBytesNoNull (Buffer.java: 386) </p><p> at org.gjt.mm.mysql.PreparedStatement.executeUpdate (PreparedStatement.java: 352) </p><p> at com.cicro.cws.database.DBManager.execute (DBManager.java: 450) </p><p> at com.cicro.cws.publish.PreparePublish.saveSiteInstanceXmlIntoDB (PreparePublish.java: 827) </p><p> at com.cicro.cws.publish.PreparePublish.generatePublishFiles (PreparePublish.java: 181) </p><p> at com.cicro.cws.publish.PublishManager.publish (PublishManager.java: 180) </p><p> at com.cicro.cws.synchronize.InstanceSynchronize.publishSite (InstanceSynchronize.java: 954) </p><p> at com.cicro.cws.site.Site.publish (Site.java: 365) </p><p> at com.cicro.cws.site.Site.run (Site.java: 338) </p><p> at java.lang.Thread.run (Thread.java: 536) </p><p></p><p> Resolve as follows: </p><p> This problem is due to import sql file is larger than the system default value of max_allowed_packet, the solution: for example, modify the increase in the my.cnf: max_allowed_packet = 32M # or higher, of course, can also join the mysqld startup parameters, but This variable must restart mysqld effect when it is loaded, it must restart mysqld! </p><p> I loaded the max_allowed_packet parameter to mysqld in the mysql startup file, mysqld file some settings are as follows: </p><p> $ {MYSQL} / bin / mysqld - user = mysql - datadir = $ {MYSQL} / data &quot;$ @&quot; \\ </p><p> - Language = $ {MYSQL} / share / mysql / english-O max_connections = 500-O wait_timeout = 600 \\ </p><p> -O key_buffer = 32M - max_allowed_packet = 32M - port = $ {port} - socket = / tmp / mysql.sock &amp; </p><p></p><p> One - max_allowed_packet = 32M must sign in front of DD. </p><p></p><p> Some information about the max_allowed_packet: </p><p> Many MySQL programs have some internal variables can be set at run time. Process variable settings and other long option with the same value. </p><p> For example, mysql has a max_allowed_packet variable, you can control the maximum length of its communication buffer. Mysql will want to set the value of max_allowed_packet variable 16MB, use any of the following command: </p><p> shell&gt; mysql - max_allowed_packet = 16777216 </p><p> shell&gt; mysql - max_allowed_packet = 16M </p><p> 1 byte command to the specified value. 2 command specify a value in megabytes. Variable values can have a suffix of K, M or G (for uppercase or lowercase) to indicate kilobytes, megabytes or gigabytes of units. </p><p> In the options file, the variable setting does not guide the dash: </p><p> [Mysql] </p><p> max_allowed_packet = 16777216 </p><p> Or: </p><p> [Mysql] </p><p> max_allowed_packet = 16M </p><p> If you like the underscore variable name can be a dash. </p><p> Note: max_allowed_packet parameter is only after the mysql4, in mysql4 previous versions, this parameter has not </p><p> In addition, you can also be / etc / my.cnf file to increase in the my.cnf to set max_allowed_packet = 16M, then restart mysql also. As for the acquisition of my.cnf, mysql home directory from the support-files through the change template by. <br /></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>');
